    ('<span class="comment">// Creating the buffer **after** the `await` prevents it from\n            // being stored in the async task.\n            </span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 在 `await` **之后**创建缓冲区可以防止其\n            // 被存储在异步任务中。\n            </span>'),
    # Reserve capacity
    ('<span class="comment">// Reserve capacity\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 预留容量\n</span>'),
    # The value sent on the permit is received
    ('<span class="comment">// The value sent on the permit is received\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 接收在 permit 上发送的值\n</span>'),
    # Sending on the permit succeeds
    ('<span class="comment">// Sending on the permit succeeds\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 在 permit 上发送成功\n</span>'),
    # Upgrading will succeed
    ('<span class="comment">// Upgrading will succeed because `tx` still exists.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 升级会成功，因为 `tx` 仍然存在。\n</span>'),
    ('<span class="comment">// If we drop `tx`, then it will fail.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 如果 drop 掉 `tx`，则升级会失败。\n</span>'),
    # Try to reserve an additional slot
    ('<span class="comment">// Trying to reserve an additional slot on the `tx` will\n            // fail because there is no capacity.\n            </span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 尝试在 `tx` 上再预留一个位置会\n            // 失败，因为没有可用容量。\n            </span>'),
    ('<span class="comment">// Trying to send directly on the `tx` will fail due to no\n            // available capacity.\n            </span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 直接在 `tx` 上发送会失败，因为\n            // 没有可用容量。\n            </span>'),
    # Wait for the pipe
    ('<span class="comment">// Wait for the pipe to be readable\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 等待管道变为可读\n</span>'),
    ('<span class="comment">// Wait for the pipe to be writable\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 等待管道变为可写\n</span>'),
    # Assert uncontended
    ('<span class="comment">// Assert uncontended.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 断言无争用。\n</span>'),
    # Get a handle
    ('<span class="comment">// Get a handle from this runtime\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 从此运行时获取一个句柄\n</span>'),
    # Run the local task set
    ('<span class="comment">// Run the local task set.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 运行本地任务集。\n</span>'),
    # Execute the future
    ('<span class="comment">// Execute the future, blocking the current thread until completion\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 执行 future，阻塞当前线程直到完成\n</span>'),
    # Await the completion of the blocking task
    ('<span class="comment">// Await the completion of the blocking task.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 等待阻塞任务完成。\n</span>'),
    # Bind socket
    ('<span class="comment">// Bind socket\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 绑定套接字\n</span>'),
    # Peek at the data / Read the data
    ('<span class="comment">// Peek at the data\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 窥视数据\n</span>'),
    ('<span class="comment">// Read the data\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 读取数据\n</span>'),
    # async logic here
    ('<span class="comment">// async logic here\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 这里是异步逻辑\n</span>'),
    # Returns the value of
    ('<p>Returns the value of the <code>SO_ERROR</code> option.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>SO_ERROR</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    # Returns the local/remote address
    ('<p>Returns the local address that this stream is bound to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此流绑定的本地地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the remote address that this stream is connected to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此流连接到的远程地址。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of Sender/WeakSender handles
    ('<p>Returns the number of <code>Sender</code> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>Sender</code> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <code>WeakSender</code> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>WeakSender</code> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    # common "Returns true if senders belong to..."
    ('<p>Returns true if senders belong to the same channel.</p>',
     '<p>如果这些 sender 属于同一个通道，则返回 true。</p>'),
    # "Returns a view that lets you get information..."
    ('<p>Returns a view that lets you get information about how the runtime is performing.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个视图，可用于获取运行时性能的相关信息。</p>'),
    # "Returns a reference to the original Arc<RwLock>."
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the original <code>Arc&lt;RwLock&gt;</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回对原始 <code>Arc&lt;RwLock&gt;</code> 的引用。</p>'),
    # "This function is intended for cases where..."
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future via <code>readable</code> is not feasible. Where possible, using <code>readable</code> is preferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <code>readable</code> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <code>readable</code>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future via <code>writable</code> is not feasible. Where possible, using <code>writable</code> is preferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <code>writable</code> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <code>writable</code>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    # The closure should only return a WouldBlock error
    ('<p>The closure should only return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error if it has performed an IO operation on the socket that failed due to the socket not being ready. Returning a <code>WouldBlock</code> error in any other situation will result in unexpected behavior.</p>',
     '<p>闭包仅在已对套接字执行了 I/O 操作且因套接字未就绪而失败时，才应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在其他任何情况下返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误都会导致意外行为。</p>'),
    ('<p>The closure should only return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error if it has performed an IO operation on the pipe that failed due to the pipe not being ready. Returning a <code>WouldBlock</code> error in any other situation will result in unexpected behavior.</p>',
     '<p>闭包仅在已对管道执行了 I/O 操作且因管道未就绪而失败时，才应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在其他任何情况下返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误都会导致意外行为。</p>'),
    # MacOS / Windows specific
    ('<p>On Windows, if the data is larger than the buffer specified, the buffer is filled with the first part of the data, and <code>peek</code> returns the error <code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>. The excess data is lost. Make sure to use a sufficiently large buffer to avoid this error.</p>',
     '<p>在 Windows 上，如果数据大于指定的缓冲区，则缓冲区会被填满数据的开头部分，<code>peek</code> 返回错误 <code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>。多余的数据将丢失。请使用足够大的缓冲区以避免此错误。</p>'),
    # private fields
    ('<span class="comment">/* private fields */</span>',
     '<span class="comment">/* 私有字段 */</span>'),
    # "While main has an active read lock..."
    ('<span class="comment">// While main has an active read lock, we acquire one too.\n</span>',
     '<span class="comment">// 当 main 持有一个活动的读锁时，我们也获取一个。\n</span>'),
    # "The function will attempt to write the entire contents of buf..."
    ('<p>The function will attempt to write the entire contents of <code>buf</code>, but only part of the buffer may be written.</p>',
     '<p>该函数将尝试写入 <code>buf</code> 的全部内容，但缓冲区可能只有部分被写入。</p>'),
    # "Data is copied to fill each buffer in order..."
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer written to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves equivalently to a single call to <code>try_read()</code> with concatenated buffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序复制以填充每个缓冲区，最后一个被写入的缓冲区可能仅被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用连接后的缓冲区对 <code>try_read()</code> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    # "Data is written from each buffer in order..."
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read from possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves equivalently to a single call to <code>try_write()</code> with concatenated buffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序从每个缓冲区写入，最后一个从中读取的缓冲区可能仅被部分消费。此方法的行为等效于使用连接后的缓冲区对 <code>try_write()</code> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    # "If the pipe is not ready to write data..."
    ('<p>If the pipe is not ready to write data, <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道未准备好写入数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # Tries to read data from the stream
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the stream into the provided buffer, returning how many bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从流中读取数据到提供的缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the stream into the provided buffers, returning how many bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从流中读取数据到提供的多个缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    # Tries to write several buffers
    ('<p>Tries to write several buffers to the stream, returning how many bytes were written.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将多个缓冲区写入流，返回写入的字节数。</p>'),
    # "The function may complete without the socket being ready..."
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being ready. This is a false-positive and attempting an operation will return with <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>. The function can also return with an empty <code>Ready</code> value, so the user should always check the returned value.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未就绪时完成。这是一种误报，尝试进行操作将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。该函数也可能返回一个空的 <code>Ready</code> 值，因此用户应始终检查返回值。</p>'),
    # "Receives data on the socket from the remote address..."
    ('<p>Receives data on the socket from the remote address to which it is connected, without removing that data from the queue. On success, returns the number of bytes peeked.</p>',
     '<p>在套接字上从其连接的远程地址接收数据，但不会从队列中移除该数据。成功时返回窥视到的字节数。</p>'),
    # "The read method is defined on the AsyncReadExt trait."
    ('<p>The <code>read</code> method is defined on the <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p><code>read</code> 方法定义在 <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上。</p>'),
    # "The connect method will connect this socket to a remote address."
    ('<p>The <code>connect</code> method will connect this socket to a remote address. This method will fail if the socket is not connected.</p>',
     '<p><code>connect</code> 方法会将此套接字连接到远程地址。如果套接字未连接，此方法将失败。</p>'),
    # "Note that on multiple calls to a poll_* method..."
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a poll_* method in the recv direction, only the Waker from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call will be scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 recv 方向多次调用 poll_* 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 Waker 会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_write_ready</code> or <code>poll_write</code>, only the Waker from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup. (However, <code>poll_read_ready</code> retains a second, separate wakeup slot.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_write_ready</code> 或 <code>poll_write</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 Waker 会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_read_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒槽。）</p>'),
    # "The runtime is usually set implicitly..."
    ('<p>The runtime is usually set implicitly when this function is called from a future driven by a tokio runtime, otherwise runtime can be set explicitly with <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>当从由 tokio 运行时驱动的 future 中调用此函数时，运行时通常是隐式设置的；否则可以通过 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> 函数显式设置运行时。</p>'),
    # "worker is the index of the worker..."
    ('<p><code>worker</code> is the index of the worker being queried. The given value must be between 0 and <a href="struct.RuntimeMetrics.html#method.num_workers" title="method tokio::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::num_workers"><code>num_workers()</code></a>. The index uniquely identifies a single worker and will continue to identify the worker throughout the lifetime of the runtime instance.</p>',
     '<p><code>worker</code> 是被查询的工作线程的索引。给定值必须介于 0 和 <a href="struct.RuntimeMetrics.html#method.num_workers" title="method tokio::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::num_workers"><code>num_workers()</code></a> 之间。该索引唯一标识一个工作线程，并将在运行时实例的整个生命周期内持续标识该工作线程。</p>'),
    # "The method panics when worker represents an invalid worker..."
    ('<p>The method panics when <code>worker</code> represents an invalid worker, i.e. is greater than or equal to <a href="struct.RuntimeMetrics.html#method.num_workers" title="method tokio::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::num_workers"><code>num_workers()</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>worker</code> 表示无效的工作线程时（即大于或等于 <a href="struct.RuntimeMetrics.html#method.num_workers" title="method tokio::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::num_workers"><code>num_workers()</code></a>），该方法会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # "Passing a listener in blocking mode is always erroneous..."
    ('<p>Passing a listener in blocking mode is always erroneous, and the behavior in that case may change in the future. For example, it could panic.</p>',
     '<p>在阻塞模式下传入监听器始终是错误的，这种情况下行为将来可能会发生变化。例如，可能会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # "Gets the value of the IP_TTL option..."
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IP_TTL</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IP_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value for the <code>IP_TTL</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IP_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This value sets the time-to-live field that is used in every packet sent from this socket.</p>',
     '<p>此值设置从此套接字发送的每个数据包中使用的生存时间字段。</p>'),
    # "When the method returns Poll::Pending..."
    ('<p>When the method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>, the <code>Waker</code> in the provided <code>Context</code> is scheduled to receive a wakeup when a message is sent on any receiver, or when the channel is closed. Note that on multiple calls to <code>recv</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>当该方法返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code> 时，所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会在任意接收器上发送消息或通道被关闭时被调度以接收唤醒。请注意，在多次调用 <code>recv</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # "Outstanding borrows hold a read lock on the inner value..."
    ('<p>Outstanding borrows hold a read lock on the inner value. This means that long-lived borrows could cause the producer half to block. It is recommended to keep the borrow as short-lived as possible. Additionally, splitting and then trying to send the new half will also cause the producer half to block.</p>',
     '<p>未释放的借用会对内部值保持一个读锁。这意味着长时间存活的借用可能会导致生产者一半被阻塞。建议尽量缩短借用的生命周期。此外，拆分后尝试发送新的一半也会导致生产者一半被阻塞。</p>'),
    # "Blocking receive to call outside of asynchronous contexts."
    ('<p>Blocking receive to call outside of asynchronous contexts.</p>',
     '<p>阻塞接收，可在异步上下文之外调用。</p>'),
    # "Instances are created by the channel function."
    ('<p>Instances are created by the <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>实例由 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数创建。</p>'),

    # ============ Top untranslated <p> patterns (count >= 3) ============
    ('<p>The function returns:</p>',
     '<p>函数返回：</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns:</p>',
     '<p>此方法返回：</p>'),
    ('<p>This function returns:</p>',
     '<p>此函数返回：</p>'),
    ('<p>This looks something like this:</p>',
     '<p>大致如下：</p>'),
    # Note that the socket address cannot be implicitly trusted
    ('<p>Note that the socket address <strong>cannot</strong> be implicitly trusted, because it is relatively\ntrivial to send a UDP datagram with a spoofed origin in a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Packet_injection">packet injection attack</a>.\nBecause UDP is stateless and does not validate the origin of a packet,\nthe attacker does not need to be able to intercept traffic in order to interfere.\nIt is important to be aware of this when designing your application-level protocol.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，套接字地址<strong>不能</strong>被隐式信任，因为相对容易以伪造的源地址发送 UDP 数据报以实施<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Packet_injection">数据包注入攻击</a>。由于 UDP 是无状态的，并且不验证数据包的来源，攻击者无需拦截流量即可实施干扰。在设计应用层协议时，请务必了解这一点。</p>'),
    # "This method is not intended to be used with combined interests"
    ('<p>This method is not intended to be used with combined interests.\nThe closure should perform only one type of IO operation, so it should not\nrequire more than one ready state. This method may panic or sleep forever\nif it is called with a combined interest.</p>',
     '<p>此方法不应用于组合的就绪事件。闭包应当只执行一种 I/O 操作，因此不应需要多于一个的就绪状态。如果以组合的就绪事件调用，此方法可能会发生 panic 或永久休眠。</p>'),
    # "This method is cancel safe. Once a readiness event occurs, the method\nwill continue to return immediately until the readiness event is\nconsumed by an attempt to read or write..."
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. Once a readiness event occurs, the method\nwill continue to return immediately until the readiness event is\nconsumed by an attempt to read or write that fails with <code>WouldBlock</code> or\n<code>Poll::Pending</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。一旦就绪事件发生，该方法将继续立即返回，直到通过尝试读取或写入而消费该就绪事件（失败时返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 或 <code>Poll::Pending</code>）。</p>'),
    # If data is successfully written (stream)
    ('<p>If data is successfully written, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the\nnumber of bytes written. If the stream is not ready to write data,\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果成功写入数据，则返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是写入的字节数。如果流未准备好写入数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # If data is successfully read (stream)
    ('<p>If data is successfully read, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the\nnumber of bytes read. If <code>n</code> is <code>0</code>, then it can indicate one of two scenarios:</p>',
     '<p>如果成功读取数据，则返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是读取的字节数。如果 <code>n</code> 为 <code>0</code>，则可能表示以下两种情况之一：</p>'),
    # Equivalent to ready(READABLE) / WRITABLE
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to <code>ready(Interest::READABLE)</code> and is usually\npaired with <code>try_read()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于 <code>ready(Interest::READABLE)</code>，通常与 <code>try_read()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to <code>ready(Interest::WRITABLE)</code> and is usually\npaired with <code>try_write()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于 <code>ready(Interest::WRITABLE)</code>，通常与 <code>try_write()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    # "The function will attempt to write the entire contents of buf..."
    ('<p>The function will attempt to write the entire contents of <code>buf</code>, but\nonly part of the buffer may be written.</p>',
     '<p>该函数将尝试写入 <code>buf</code> 的全部内容，但缓冲区可能只有部分被写入。</p>'),
    # "When there is no pending data, Err(...)"
    ('<p>When there is no pending data, <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is\nreturned. This function is usually paired with <code>readable()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当没有待处理数据时，返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。此函数通常与 <code>readable()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    # Windows UDP
    ('<p>On Windows, if the data is larger than the buffer specified, the buffer\nis filled with the first part of the data, and peek returns the error\n<code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>. The excess data is lost.\nMake sure to always use a sufficiently large buffer to hold the\nmaximum UDP packet size, which can be up to 65536 bytes in size.</p>',
     '<p>在 Windows 上，如果数据大于指定的缓冲区，则缓冲区会被填满数据的开头部分，peek 返回错误 <code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>。多余的数据将丢失。请务必使用足够大的缓冲区以容纳最大 UDP 数据包（可达 65536 字节）。</p>'),
    # I/O errors
    ('<p>This errors if called outside of a <a href="../../../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">Tokio Runtime</a>, or in a runtime that\nhas not <a href="../../../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_io" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_io">enabled I/O</a>, or if any OS-specific I/O errors occur.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <a href="../../../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">Tokio 运行时</a> 之外调用、在未<a href="../../../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_io" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_io">启用 I/O</a> 的运行时中调用，或发生任何操作系统特定的 I/O 错误，则返回错误。</p>'),
    # panics if called within an asynchronous execution context
    ('<p>This function panics if called within an asynchronous execution\ncontext.</p>',
     '<p>如果在异步执行上下文中调用，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # cancel safe - read only
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. Once a readiness event occurs, the method\nwill continue to return immediately until the readiness event is\nconsumed by an attempt to read that fails with <code>WouldBlock</code> or\n<code>Poll::Pending</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。一旦就绪事件发生，该方法将继续立即返回，直到通过尝试读取而消费该就绪事件（失败时返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 或 <code>Poll::Pending</code>）。</p>'),
    # cancel safe - write only
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. Once a readiness event occurs, the method\nwill continue to return immediately until the readiness event is\nconsumed by an attempt to write that fails with <code>WouldBlock</code> or\n<code>Poll::Pending</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。一旦就绪事件发生，该方法将继续立即返回，直到通过尝试写入而消费该就绪事件（失败时返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 或 <code>Poll::Pending</code>）。</p>'),
    # socket closure WouldBlock
    ('<p>The closure should only return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error if it has performed\nan IO operation on the socket that failed due to the socket not being\nready. Returning a <code>WouldBlock</code> error in any other situation will\nincorrectly clear the readiness flag, which can cause the socket to\nbehave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包仅在已对套接字执行了 I/O 操作且因套接字未就绪而失败时，才应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在其他任何情况下返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误都会错误地清除就绪标志，可能导致套接字行为异常。</p>'),
    # pipe closure WouldBlock
    ('<p>The closure should only return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error if it has performed\nan IO operation on the pipe that failed due to the pipe not being\nready. Returning a <code>WouldBlock</code> error in any other situation will\nincorrectly clear the readiness flag, which can cause the pipe to\nbehave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包仅在已对管道执行了 I/O 操作且因管道未就绪而失败时，才应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在其他任何情况下返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误都会错误地清除就绪标志，可能导致管道行为异常。</p>'),
    # "function may complete without the socket being ready"
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being ready. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting an operation will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>. The function can also return with an empty\n<a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> set, so you should always check the returned value and possibly\nwait again if the requested states are not set.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未就绪时完成。这是一种误报，尝试进行操作将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。该函数也可能返回空的 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> 集合，因此应始终检查返回值，如果请求的状态未设置，可能需要再次等待。</p>'),
    # Equivalent to TcpStream::ready
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>TcpStream::ready</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>TcpStream::ready</code></a>。</p>'),
    # If data is successfully written (pipe)
    ('<p>If data is successfully written, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the\nnumber of bytes written. If the pipe is not ready to write data,\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果成功写入数据，则返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是写入的字节数。如果管道未准备好写入数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # Inside of f, you retain exclusive access (with embedded <code>)
    ('<p>Inside of <code>f</code>, you retain exclusive access to the data, despite only being given a <code>&amp;T</code>. Handing out a\n<code>&amp;mut T</code> would result in unsoundness, as you could use interior mutability.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>f</code> 内部，即使只获得了 <code>&amp;T</code>，你仍然保留对数据的独占访问权。交出 <code>&amp;mut T</code> 将导致内存不安全，因为你可以使用内部可变性。</p>'),
    # Returns an RAII guard (RwLock read)
    ('<p>Returns an RAII guard which will drop this read access of the <code>RwLock</code>\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 RAII 守卫，当它被 drop 时会释放此 <code>RwLock</code> 的读访问权。</p>'),
    # RwLockWriteGuard cannot fail
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> passed in already\nlocked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    # Returns true if senders belong to the same channel
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if senders belong to the same channel.</p>',
     '<p>如果这些 sender 属于同一个通道，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    # When method returns Poll::Pending, the Waker ...
    ('<p>When the method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>, the <code>Waker</code> in the provided\n<code>Context</code> is scheduled to receive a wakeup when a message is sent on any\nreceiver, or when the channel is closed.  Note that on multiple calls to\n<code>poll_recv</code> or <code>poll_recv_many</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code>\npassed to the most recent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>当该方法返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code> 时，所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会在任意接收器上发送消息或通道被关闭时被调度以接收唤醒。请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_recv</code> 或 <code>poll_recv_many</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # Outstanding borrows
    ('<p>Outstanding borrows hold a read lock on the inner value. This means that\nlong-lived borrows could cause the producer half to block. It is recommended\nto keep the borrow as short-lived as possible. Additionally, if you are\nrunning in an environment that allows <code>!Send</code> futures, you must ensure that\nthe returned <code>Ref</code> type is never held alive across an <code>.await</code> point,\notherwise, it can lead to a deadlock.</p>',
     '<p>未释放的借用会对内部值保持一个读锁。这意味着长时间存活的借用可能会导致生产者一半被阻塞。建议尽量缩短借用的生命周期。此外，如果运行在允许 <code>!Send</code> future 的环境中，必须确保返回的 <code>Ref</code> 类型不会跨越 <code>.await</code> 点存活，否则可能会导致死锁。</p>'),
    # "It can be triggered when Builder::enable_time..."
    ('<p>It can be triggered when <a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_time" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_time"><code>Builder::enable_time</code></a> or\n<a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_all" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_all"><code>Builder::enable_all</code></a> are not included in the builder.</p>',
     '<p>当 <a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_time" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_time"><code>Builder::enable_time</code></a> 或 <a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_all" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_all"><code>Builder::enable_all</code></a> 未包含在 builder 中时，可能会触发 panic。</p>'),
    # Sleep panic (long version with backticks)
    ('<p>It can also panic whenever a timer is created outside of a\nTokio runtime. That is why <code>rt.block_on(sleep(...))</code> will panic,\nsince the function is executed outside of the runtime.\nWhereas <code>rt.block_on(async {sleep(...).await})</code> doesn’t panic.\nAnd this is because wrapping the function on an async makes it lazy,\nand so gets executed inside the runtime successfully without\npanicking.</p>',
     '<p>每当在 Tokio 运行时之外创建定时器时，它也可能会发生 panic。这就是 <code>rt.block_on(sleep(...))</code> 会发生 panic 的原因，因为该函数在运行时之外执行。而 <code>rt.block_on(async {sleep(...).await})</code> 不会 panic，这是因为将函数包装在 async 中使其变为惰性的，从而可以在运行时内成功执行而不会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Passing a listener in blocking mode is always erroneous
    ('<p>Passing a listener in blocking mode is always erroneous,\nand the behavior in that case may change in the future.\nFor example, it could panic.</p>',
     '<p>在阻塞模式下传入监听器始终是错误的，这种情况下行为将来可能会发生变化。例如，可能会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # "The runtime is usually set implicitly..."
    ('<p>The runtime is usually set implicitly when this function is called\nfrom a future driven by a tokio runtime, otherwise runtime can be set\nexplicitly with <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>当从由 tokio 运行时驱动的 future 中调用此函数时，运行时通常是隐式设置的；否则可以通过 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> 函数显式设置运行时。</p>'),
    # TTL
    ('<p>This value sets the time-to-live field that is used in every packet sent\nfrom this socket.</p>',
     '<p>此值设置从此套接字发送的每个数据包中使用的生存时间字段。</p>'),
    # Polls for read/write readiness
    ('<p>Polls for read readiness.</p>',
     '<p>轮询读就绪状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polls for write readiness.</p>',
     '<p>轮询写就绪状态。</p>'),
    # Tries to read data from the stream (try_read, try_read_vectored)
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the stream into the provided buffer, returning how\nmany bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从流中读取数据到提供的缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the stream into the provided buffers, returning\nhow many bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从流中读取数据到提供的多个缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the stream is not ready to read data,\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果流未准备好读取数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # Receives any pending data from the socket (try_read and try_read_vectored)
    ('<p>Receives any pending data from the socket but does not wait for new data\nto arrive. On success, returns the number of bytes read. Because\n<code>try_read()</code> is non-blocking, the buffer does not have to be stored by\nthe async task and can exist entirely on the stack.</p>',
     '<p>接收套接字上任何待处理的数据，但不会等待新数据到达。成功时返回读取的字节数。由于 <code>try_read()</code> 是非阻塞的，缓冲区不必由异步任务存储，可以完全存在于栈上。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives any pending data from the socket but does not wait for new data\nto arrive. On success, returns the number of bytes read. Because\n<code>try_read_vectored()</code> is non-blocking, the buffer does not have to be\nstored by the async task and can exist entirely on the stack.</p>',
     '<p>接收套接字上任何待处理的数据，但不会等待新数据到达。成功时返回读取的字节数。由于 <code>try_read_vectored()</code> 是非阻塞的，缓冲区不必由异步任务存储，可以完全存在于栈上。</p>'),
    # If data is successfully read (vectored)
    ('<p>If data is successfully read, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the\nnumber of bytes read. <code>Ok(0)</code> indicates the stream’s read half is closed\nand will no longer yield data. If the stream is not ready to read data\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果成功读取数据，则返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是读取的字节数。<code>Ok(0)</code> 表示流的读半部分已关闭，将不再产生数据。如果流未准备好读取数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # Receives data on socket from remote (peek)
    ('<p>Receives data on the socket from the remote address to which it is\nconnected, without removing that data from the queue. On success,\nreturns the number of bytes read.</p>',
     '<p>在套接字上从其连接的远程地址接收数据，但不会从队列中移除该数据。成功时返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    # Tries to write several buffers to the stream
    ('<p>Tries to write several buffers to the stream, returning how many bytes\nwere written.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将多个缓冲区写入流，返回写入的字节数。</p>'),
    # Basic usage header
    ('<p>Basic usage</p>', '<p>基本用法</p>'),
    # Returns the number of Sender/WeakSender (with link)
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the the number of <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of Sender handles (no link)
    ('<p>Returns the number of <code>Sender</code> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>Sender</code> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <code>WeakSender</code> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>WeakSender</code> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    # Checks if a channel is closed/empty
    ('<p>Checks if a channel is closed.</p>', '<p>检查通道是否已关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if a channel is empty.</p>', '<p>检查通道是否为空。</p>'),
    # This includes the filled portion
    ('<p>This includes the filled portion.</p>', '<p>这包括已填充的部分。</p>'),
    # The number of initialized bytes is not changed
    ('<p>The number of initialized bytes is not changed.</p>',
     '<p>已初始化的字节数不会改变。</p>'),
    # Panics if filled region would become larger than initialized
    ('<p>Panics if the filled region of the buffer would become larger than the initialized region.</p>',
     '<p>如果缓冲区的填充区域变得大于初始化区域，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Tokio runtime
    ('<p>The Tokio runtime.</p>', '<p>Tokio 运行时。</p>'),
    # Spawns a future onto the Tokio runtime
    ('<p>Spawns a future onto the Tokio runtime.</p>',
     '<p>将 future 派生到 Tokio 运行时。</p>'),
    # This spawns the given future onto the runtime
    ('<p>This spawns the given future onto the runtime’s executor, usually a\nthread pool. The thread pool is then responsible for polling the future\nuntil it completes.</p>',
     '<p>这会将给定的 future 派生到运行时的执行器上，通常是线程池。然后由该线程池负责轮询该 future 直到其完成。</p>'),
    # Returns a handle to the runtime
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> handle to the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>返回运行时的 <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a handle to the runtime’s spawner.</p>',
     '<p>返回运行时 spawner 的句柄。</p>'),
    # Runs a future to completion
    ('<p>Runs a future to completion on the Tokio runtime. This is the\nruntime’s entry point.</p>',
     '<p>在 Tokio 运行时上运行 future 直到完成。这是运行时的入口点。</p>'),
    # Enters the runtime context
    ('<p>Enters the runtime context.</p>', '<p>进入运行时上下文。</p>'),
    # Shuts down the runtime
    ('<p>Shuts down the runtime, without waiting for any spawned work to stop.</p>',
     '<p>关闭运行时，但不等待任何已派生的工作停止。</p>'),
    ('<p>Shuts down the runtime, waiting for at most <code>timeout</code> for all spawned\nwork to stop.</p>',
     '<p>关闭运行时，并最多等待 <code>timeout</code> 时间让所有已派生的工作停止。</p>'),
    # Returns a Handle view over the currently running Runtime
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> view over the currently running <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前正在运行的 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 的 <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> 视图。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of worker threads
    ('<p>Returns the number of worker threads used by the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>返回运行时使用的工作线程数。</p>'),
    # Returns the current number of alive tasks
    ('<p>Returns the current number of alive tasks in the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>返回运行时中当前存活的任务数。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of tasks currently scheduled in the runtime
    ('<p>Returns the number of tasks currently scheduled in the runtime’s\nglobal queue.</p>',
     '<p>返回运行时全局队列中当前调度的任务数。</p>'),
    # Returns the total capacity of the buffer
    ('<p>Returns the total capacity of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>返回缓冲区的总容量。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of bytes at the end of the slice that have not yet been filled
    ('<p>Returns the number of bytes at the end of the slice that have not yet been filled.</p>',
     '<p>返回切片末尾尚未填充的字节数。</p>'),
    # Returns a shared reference / mutable reference to the filled portion
    ('<p>Returns a shared reference to the filled portion of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区已填充部分的共享引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the filled portion of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区已填充部分的可变引用。</p>'),
    # Returns a shared reference / mutable reference to the initialized portion
    ('<p>Returns a shared reference to the initialized portion of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区已初始化部分的共享引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the initialized portion of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区已初始化部分的可变引用。</p>'),
    # Returns the local/remote address that this listener/socket is bound to / connected to
    ('<p>Returns the local address that this listener is bound to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此监听器绑定的本地地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the local address that this socket is bound to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此套接字绑定的本地地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the socket address of the remote peer this socket was connected to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此套接字所连接到的远程对等方的套接字地址。</p>'),
    # Tries to read or write from the socket using a user-provided IO operation
    ('<p>Tries to read or write from the socket using a user-provided IO operation.</p>',
     '<p>尝试使用用户提供的 I/O 操作从套接字读取或写入数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reads or writes from the socket using a user-provided IO operation.</p>',
     '<p>使用用户提供的 I/O 操作从套接字读取或写入数据。</p>'),
    # This function panics if it is not called from within a runtime with IO enabled
    ('<p>This function panics if it is not called from within a runtime with\nIO enabled.</p>',
     '<p>如果不在已启用 I/O 的运行时中调用，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # TCP send/receive buffer sizes
    ('<p>Returns the size of the TCP send buffer for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>返回此套接字的 TCP 发送缓冲区大小。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the size of the TCP receive buffer for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>返回此套接字的 TCP 接收缓冲区大小。</p>'),
    # Tries to write a buffer to the stream / pipe
    ('<p>Tries to write a buffer to the stream, returning how many bytes were\nwritten.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将缓冲区写入流，返回写入的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to write a buffer to the pipe, returning how many bytes were\nwritten.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将缓冲区写入管道，返回写入的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to write several buffers to the pipe, returning how many bytes\nwere written.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将多个缓冲区写入管道，返回写入的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to read or write from the pipe using a user-provided IO operation.</p>',
     '<p>尝试使用用户提供的 I/O 操作从管道读取或写入数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reads or writes from the pipe using a user-provided IO operation.</p>',
     '<p>使用用户提供的 I/O 操作从管道读取或写入数据。</p>'),
    # Waits for the pipe to become readable/writable
    ('<p>Waits for the pipe to become readable.</p>',
     '<p>等待管道变为可读。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for the pipe to become writable.</p>',
     '<p>等待管道变为可写。</p>'),
    # Tries to read data from the pipe
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the pipe into the provided buffer, returning how\nmany bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从管道读取数据到提供的缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to read data from the pipe into the provided buffers, returning\nhow many bytes were read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从管道读取数据到提供的多个缓冲区，返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    # Indicates the end of a named pipe / Pipe mode
    ('<p>Indicates the end of a named pipe.</p>',
     '<p>表示命名管道的结束。</p>'),
    ('<p>The pipe mode of a named pipe.</p>',
     '<p>命名管道的管道模式。</p>'),
    # Creates a new named pipe builder with the default settings
    ('<p>Creates a new named pipe builder with the default settings.</p>',
     '<p>使用默认设置创建一个新的命名管道 builder。</p>'),
    # "This function will consume ownership of the handle..."
    ('<p>This function will consume ownership of the handle given, passing\nresponsibility for closing the handle to the returned object.</p>',
     '<p>此函数将取得所提供句柄的所有权，将关闭句柄的责任移交给返回的对象。</p>'),
    # Concurrently read and write to the pipe
    ('<p>Concurrently read and write to the pipe on the same task without\nsplitting.</p>',
     '<p>在同一任务上并发地对管道进行读写，而无需拆分。</p>'),
    # The number of bytes to reserve for the output/input buffer
    ('<p>The number of bytes to reserve for the output buffer.</p>',
     '<p>为输出缓冲区预留的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>The number of bytes to reserve for the input buffer.</p>',
     '<p>为输入缓冲区预留的字节数。</p>'),
    # A sender that does not prevent the channel from being closed
    ('<p>A sender that does not prevent the channel from being closed.</p>',
     '<p>不会阻止通道被关闭的 sender。</p>'),
    # The counter is monotonically increasing
    ('<p>The counter is monotonically increasing. It is never decremented or\nreset to zero.</p>',
     '<p>计数器单调递增。它永不会递减或重置为零。</p>'),
    # This can be used to hold a subfield of the protected data
    ('<p>This can be used to hold a subfield of the protected data.</p>',
     '<p>这可用于保存受保护数据的子字段。</p>'),
    # Creates a new lock in an unlocked state
    ('<p>Creates a new lock in an unlocked state ready for use.</p>',
     '<p>以未锁定状态创建一个新锁，可直接使用。</p>'),
    # If the mutex is available to be acquired immediately
    ('<p>If the mutex is available to be acquired immediately, then this call\nwill typically not yield to the runtime. However, if the mutex is\ncontended, then the future will yield, allowing the runtime to schedule\nother tasks.</p>',
     '<p>如果互斥锁可以立即获取，那么此调用通常不会让出执行权给运行时。但是，如果互斥锁存在争用，那么 future 将会让出执行权，允许运行时调度其他任务。</p>'),
    # Returns a mutable reference to the underlying data
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the underlying data.</p>',
     '<p>返回对底层数据的可变引用。</p>'),
    # Returns the number of messages in the channel
    ('<p>Returns the number of messages in the channel.</p>',
     '<p>返回通道中的消息数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the current capacity of the channel.</p>',
     '<p>返回通道的当前容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the maximum buffer capacity of the channel.</p>',
     '<p>返回通道的最大缓冲区容量。</p>'),
    # Unbound mpmc channel
    ('<p>Unbound multi-producer multi-consumer (mpmc) channel.</p>',
     '<p>无界多生产者多消费者 (mpmc) 通道。</p>'),
    # A thread-safe cell that can be written to only once
    ('<p>A thread-safe cell that can be written to only once.</p>',
     '<p>只能写入一次的线程安全单元。</p>'),
    # Atomically downgrades a write lock into a read lock
    ('<p>Atomically downgrades a write lock into a read lock without allowing\nany writers to take exclusive access of the lock in the meantime.</p>',
     '<p>原子地将写锁降级为读锁，期间不允许任何写入者获取锁的独占访问权。</p>'),
    # The calling task will yield until there are no writers
    ('<p>The calling task will yield until there are no writers which hold the\nlock. There may be other readers inside the lock when the read lock is\nacquired.</p>',
     '<p>调用任务将让出执行权，直到没有任何持有锁的写入者。在获取读锁时，锁内可能还有其他读取者。</p>'),
    # This method is intended for use cases where you need to use this rwlock
    ('<p>This method is intended for cases where you\nneed to use this rwlock in asynchronous code as well as in synchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>此方法适用于需要在异步代码和同步代码中都使用此 rwlock 的场景。</p>'),
    # The calling task will yield while other writers or readers
    ('<p>The calling task will yield while other writers or readers currently\nhave access to the lock.</p>',
     '<p>当其他写入者或读取者持有锁时，调用任务将让出执行权。</p>'),
    # RAII guards
    ('<p>Owned RAII structure used to release the exclusive write access of a lock when\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>用于在 drop 时释放锁的独占写访问权的 owned RAII 结构。</p>'),
    ('<p>RAII structure used to release the exclusive write access of a lock when\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>用于在 drop 时释放锁的独占写访问权的 RAII 结构。</p>'),
    # Creates a new semaphore
    ('<p>Creates a new semaphore with the initial number of permits.</p>',
     '<p>使用初始许可数创建一个新的信号量。</p>'),
    # Acquires a permit / Tries to acquire a permit
    ('<p>Acquires a permit from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>从信号量获取一个许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to acquire a permit from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从信号量获取一个许可。</p>'),
    # This method is cancel safe
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。</p>'),
    # There are no more active senders
    ('<p>There are no more active senders implying no further messages will ever\nbe sent.</p>',
     '<p>没有更多活动的 sender，这意味着不会再发送任何消息。</p>'),
    # Includes the number of skipped messages
    ('<p>Includes the number of skipped messages.</p>',
     '<p>包含已跳过消息的数量。</p>'),
    # Sends a value using the reserved capacity
    ('<p>Sends a value using the reserved capacity.</p>',
     '<p>使用预留的容量发送一个值。</p>'),
    # worker is the index of the worker being queried
    ('<p><code>worker</code> is the index of the worker being queried. The given value must\nbe between 0 and <code>num_workers()</code>. The index uniquely identifies a\nsingle worker and will continue to identify the worker throughout the\nlifetime of the runtime instance.</p>',
     '<p><code>worker</code> 是被查询的工作线程的索引。给定值必须介于 0 和 <code>num_workers()</code> 之间。该索引唯一标识一个工作线程，并将在运行时实例的整个生命周期内持续标识该工作线程。</p>'),
    # The method panics when worker represents an invalid worker
    ('<p>The method panics when <code>worker</code> represents an invalid worker, i.e. is\ngreater than or equal to <code>num_workers()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>worker</code> 表示无效的工作线程时（即大于或等于 <code>num_workers()</code>），该方法会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Although this method is deprecated
    ('<p>Although this method is deprecated, it will not be removed from Tokio.</p>',
     '<p>尽管此方法已弃用，但它不会从 Tokio 中移除。</p>'),
    # This value sets the type-of-service field
    ('<p>This value sets the type-of-service field that is used in every packet\nsent from this socket.</p>',
     '<p>此值设置从此套接字发送的每个数据包中使用的服务类型字段。</p>'),
    # Attempts to receive data on the socket without removing
    ('<p>Attempts to receive data on the socket, without removing that data from\nthe queue, registering the current task for wakeup if data is not yet\navailable.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在套接字上接收数据，但不会从队列中移除该数据。如果数据尚未可用，则注册当前任务以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # This may not have any effect on IPv6 sockets
    ('<p>This may not have any effect on IPv6 sockets.</p>',
     '<p>这可能对 IPv6 套接字没有任何效果。</p>'),
    # See module level documentation for more details
    ('<p>See <a href="index.html">module level</a> documentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="index.html">模块级</a> 文档。</p>'),
    # "Returns the value of the SO_ERROR option"
    ('<p>Returns the value of the <code>SO_ERROR</code> option.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>SO_ERROR</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    # "Returns the local address that this stream is bound to"
    ('<p>Returns the local address that this stream is bound to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此流绑定的本地地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the remote address that this stream is connected to.</p>',
     '<p>返回此流连接到的远程地址。</p>'),
    # "Returns a view that lets you get information..."
    ('<p>Returns a view that lets you get information about how the runtime is\nperforming.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个视图，可用于获取运行时性能的相关信息。</p>'),
    # "Returns a reference to the original Arc<RwLock>"
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the original <code>Arc&lt;RwLock&gt;</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回对原始 <code>Arc&lt;RwLock&gt;</code> 的引用。</p>'),
    # "This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future..."
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future via <code>readable</code> is not feasible. Where possible, using <code>readable</code> is preferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <code>readable</code> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <code>readable</code>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future via <code>writable</code> is not feasible. Where possible, using <code>writable</code> is preferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <code>writable</code> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <code>writable</code>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    # "Reads bytes from a source" / "Writes bytes to a destination" / similar
    ('<p>Reads bytes from a source.</p>', '<p>从源读取字节。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reads bytes asynchronously.</p>', '<p>异步读取字节。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writes bytes asynchronously.</p>', '<p>异步写入字节。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writes bytes to a destination.</p>', '<p>向目标写入字节。</p>'),
    ('<p>Seek bytes asynchronously.</p>', '<p>异步定位字节。</p>'),
    # Interest
    ('<p>Readiness event interest.</p>', '<p>就绪事件兴趣。</p>'),
    # Wrapper around a byte buffer
    ('<p>A wrapper around a byte buffer that is incrementally filled and initialized.</p>',
     '<p>一个字节缓冲区的包装器，可增量填充和初始化。</p>'),
    # Readiness state of an I/O resource
    ('<p>Describes the readiness state of an I/O resources.</p>',
     '<p>描述 I/O 资源的就绪状态。</p>'),
    # "Note that on multiple calls to a poll_* method..."
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a <code>poll_*</code> method in the <code>recv</code> direction, only the\n<code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 <code>recv</code> 方向多次调用 <code>poll_*</code> 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # "Note that on multiple calls to poll_write_ready or poll_write..."
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_write_ready</code> or <code>poll_write</code>, only\nthe <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup. (However, <code>poll_read_ready</code> retains a\nsecond, separate wakeup slot.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_write_ready</code> 或 <code>poll_write</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_read_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒槽。）</p>'),
    # "Data is copied to fill each buffer in order..."
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <code>try_read()</code> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序复制以填充每个缓冲区，最后一个被写入的缓冲区可能仅被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用连接后的缓冲区对 <code>try_read()</code> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    # "Data is written from each buffer in order..."
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <code>try_write()</code> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序从每个缓冲区写入，最后一个从中读取的缓冲区可能仅被部分消费。此方法的行为等效于使用连接后的缓冲区对 <code>try_write()</code> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    # "The function may complete without the socket being ready" (simpler version)
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being ready. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting an operation will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>. The function can also return with an empty\n<code>Ready</code> value, so the user should always check the returned value.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未就绪时完成。这是一种误报，尝试进行操作将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。该函数也可能返回一个空的 <code>Ready</code> 值，因此用户应始终检查返回值。</p>'),
    # "The <code>read</code> method is defined on the AsyncReadExt trait"
    ('<p>The <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>read</code></a> method is defined on the <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p><a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>read</code></a> 方法定义在 <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>read</code> method is defined on the <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p><code>read</code> 方法定义在 <a href="trait.AsyncReadExt.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上。</p>'),
    # "The connect method will connect this socket to a remote address"
    ('<p>The <code>connect</code> method will connect this socket to a remote address. This\nmethod will fail if the socket is not connected.</p>',
     '<p><code>connect</code> 方法会将此套接字连接到远程地址。如果套接字未连接，此方法将失败。</p>'),
    # Sets the value for IP_TTL
    ('<p>Sets the value for the <code>IP_TTL</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IP_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IP_TTL</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IP_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>。</p>'),
    # The semaphore must be wrapped in an Arc
    ('<p>The semaphore must be wrapped in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> to be able to share it with other tasks.</p>',
     '<p>信号量必须包装在 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 中，以便与其他任务共享。</p>'),
    # If the access couldn't be acquired immediately, returns TryLockError
    ('<p>If the access couldn’t be acquired immediately, returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果无法立即获取访问权限，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Returns the total / current capacity
    ('<p>Returns the total capacity of the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>返回信号量的总容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the current capacity of the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>返回信号量的当前可用容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of available permits in this semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>返回此信号量中的可用许可数。</p>'),
    # Returns the next value
    ('<p>Returns the next value in the channel.</p>',
     '<p>返回通道中的下一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Closes the channel by preventing further messages.</p>',
     '<p>通过阻止后续消息来关闭通道。</p>'),
    # Returns true if there are no values
    ('<p>Returns true if there are no values in the channel.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道中没有值，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if there are no senders.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有 sender，则返回 true。</p>'),
    # Receives the next value
    ('<p>Receives the next value for this receiver.</p>',
     '<p>接收此接收器的下一个值。</p>'),
    # Sends values / Receives values
    ('<p>Sends values to the associated <code>Receiver</code>.</p>',
     '<p>向关联的 <code>Receiver</code> 发送值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives values from the associated <code>Sender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从关联的 <code>Sender</code> 接收值。</p>'),
    # Returns true if this task is finished
    ('<p>Returns true if this task is finished.</p>',
     '<p>如果此任务已完成，则返回 true。</p>'),
    # Spawns a blocking task
    ('<p>Spawns a blocking task on the blocking threadpool.</p>',
     '<p>在阻塞线程池上派生一个阻塞任务。</p>'),
    # Returns a handle
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> for the spawned task.</p>',
     '<p>返回已派生任务的 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Consumes the stream
    ('<p>Consumes stream, returning the tokio I/O object.</p>',
     '<p>消耗流，返回 Tokio 的 I/O 对象。</p>'),
    # Converts a TcpStream
    ('<p>Converts a <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> into an <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html" title="struct tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf"><code>OwnedReadHalf</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html" title="struct tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf"><code>OwnedWriteHalf</code></a> which can be used to read and write independently of\neach other.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 转换为 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html" title="struct tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf"><code>OwnedReadHalf</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html" title="struct tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf"><code>OwnedWriteHalf</code></a>，可分别用于独立的读写操作。</p>'),
    # Splits a TcpStream
    ('<p>Splits a <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> into a borrowed read half and a borrowed write half,\nwhich can be used to read and write independently of each other.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 拆分为借用的读半部分和借用的写半部分，可用于独立的读写操作。</p>'),
    # Reunites the two halves
    ('<p>Reunites the two halves back into a <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将两个半部分重新合并回 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。</p>'),
    # "Attaches the cancellation token"
    ('<p>Attaches the cancellation token to the future, returning a future that\nwill be cancelled when the token is cancelled.</p>',
     '<p>将取消令牌附加到 future，返回一个在令牌被取消时将被取消的 future。</p>'),
    # Blocks the current thread
    ('<p>Blocks the current thread on the future until the future is complete.</p>',
     '<p>阻塞当前线程，直到 future 完成。</p>'),
    # Blocks on a single future
    ('<p>Blocks on a single future on the current thread.</p>',
     '<p>在当前线程上阻塞单个 future。</p>'),
    # Returns the wrapped TcpStream
    ('<p>Returns the wrapped <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>返回包装的 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Builds Tokio Runtime with custom configuration
    ('<p>Builds Tokio Runtime with custom configuration values.</p>',
     '<p>使用自定义配置值构建 Tokio 运行时。</p>'),
    # Handle to the runtime
    ('<p>Handle to the runtime.</p>', '<p>运行时句柄。</p>'),
    # Runtime context guard
    ('<p>Runtime context guard.</p>', '<p>运行时上下文守卫。</p>'),
    # An opaque ID that uniquely identifies a runtime
    ('<p>An opaque ID that uniquely identifies a runtime relative to all other currently\nrunning runtimes.</p>',
     '<p>唯一标识一个运行时（相对于所有其他当前正在运行的运行时）的不透明 ID。</p>'),
    # A local Tokio runtime
    ('<p>A local Tokio runtime.</p>', '<p>本地 Tokio 运行时。</p>'),
    # Handle to the runtime's metrics
    ('<p>Handle to the runtime’s metrics.</p>', '<p>运行时指标的句柄。</p>'),
    # Checks whether the given error was emitted by Tokio when shutting down
    ('<p>Checks whether the given error was emitted by Tokio when shutting down its runtime.</p>',
     '<p>检查给定的错误是否由 Tokio 在关闭其运行时时发出。</p>'),
    # A multi-producer, multi-consumer broadcast queue
    ('<p>A multi-producer, multi-consumer broadcast queue. Each sent value is seen by\nall consumers.</p>',
     '<p>多生产者、多消费者的广播队列。每个发送的值会被所有消费者看到。</p>'),
    # A multi-producer, single-consumer queue
    ('<p>A multi-producer, single-consumer queue for sending values between\nasynchronous tasks.</p>',
     '<p>用于在异步任务之间发送值的多生产者、单消费者队列。</p>'),
    # A TCP socket server, listening for connections
    ('<p>A TCP socket server, listening for connections.</p>',
     '<p>监听连接的 TCP 套接字服务器。</p>'),
    # A TCP stream between a local and a remote socket
    ('<p>A TCP stream between a local and a remote socket.</p>',
     '<p>本地套接字和远程套接字之间的 TCP 流。</p>'),
    # Performs a DNS resolution
    ('<p>Performs a DNS resolution.</p>', '<p>执行 DNS 解析。</p>'),
    # Windows specific network types
    ('<p>Windows specific network types.</p>', '<p>Windows 特定的网络类型。</p>'),
    # Error indicating that two halves were not from the same socket
    ('<p>Error indicating that two halves were not from the same socket, and thus could\nnot be reunited.</p>',
     '<p>指示两个半部分不是来自同一个套接字，因此无法重新合并的错误。</p>'),
    # A builder suitable for building and interacting with named pipes
    ('<p>A builder suitable for building and interacting with named pipes from the\nclient side.</p>',
     '<p>适用于从客户端构建和与命名管道交互的 builder。</p>'),
    # Information about a named pipe
    ('<p>Information about a named pipe.</p>', '<p>关于命名管道的信息。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 2: more untranslated patterns ============
    # Returns view over currently running Runtime
    ('<p>Returns a view that lets you get information about how the runtime\nis performing.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个视图，可用于获取运行时性能的相关信息。</p>'),
    # worker index
    ('<p><code>worker</code> is the index of the worker being queried. The given value must\nbe between 0 and <code>num_workers()</code>. The index uniquely identifies a single\nworker and will continue to identify the worker throughout the lifetime\nof the runtime instance.</p>',
     '<p><code>worker</code> 是被查询的工作线程的索引。给定值必须介于 0 和 <code>num_workers()</code> 之间。该索引唯一标识一个工作线程，并将在运行时实例的整个生命周期内持续标识该工作线程。</p>'),
    # OwnedMutexGuard cannot fail
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a> passed in already locked the mutex.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a> 已经锁定了互斥锁。</p>'),
    # Returns number of handles (with link)
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a> handles.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a> 句柄的数量。</p>'),
    # cancel safe - select!
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>recv</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, it is guaranteed that no messages were received on this\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>recv</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证此通道没有接收到任何消息。</p>'),
    # This method returns true if the channel has no messages
    ('<p>This method returns <code>true</code> if the channel has no messages.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道中没有消息，此方法返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    # recv with error
    ('<p>If the sender is dropped without sending, the receiver will fail with\n<a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::error::RecvError"><code>error::RecvError</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>如果 sender 在未发送的情况下被 drop，则 receiver 将失败并返回 <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::error::RecvError"><code>error::RecvError</code></a>：</p>'),
    # priority policy of the lock
    ('<p>The priority policy of the lock is dependent on the underlying lock\nimplementation, and this type does not guarantee that any particular policy\nwill be used. In particular, a producer which is waiting to acquire the lock\nin <code>send</code> might or might not block concurrent calls to <code>borrow</code>, e.g.:</p>',
     '<p>锁的优先级策略取决于底层锁实现，本类型不保证使用任何特定策略。特别是，正在等待通过 <code>send</code> 获取锁的生产者可能会阻塞对 <code>borrow</code> 的并发调用，也可能不会，例如：</p>'),
    # spawn_blocking warning
    ('<p>Be aware that tasks spawned using <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> cannot be aborted\nbecause they are not async. If you call <code>abort</code> on a <code>spawn_blocking</code>\ntask, then this <em>will not have any effect</em>, and the task will continue\nrunning normally. The exception is if the task has not started running\nyet; in that case, calling <code>abort</code> may prevent the task from starting.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，使用 <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> 派生的任务无法被中止，因为它们不是异步的。如果对 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务调用 <code>abort</code>，<em>则不会产生任何效果</em>，任务将继续正常运行。例外情况是任务尚未开始运行；此时调用 <code>abort</code> 可能会阻止任务启动。</p>'),
    # provided future will start running immediately
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen this method is called, even if you don’t await anything on this\n<code>JoinSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当调用此方法时，提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你未在 <code>JoinSet</code> 上 await 任何东西也是如此。</p>'),
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen this method is called, even if you don\'t await anything on this\n<code>JoinSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当调用此方法时，提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你未在 <code>JoinSet</code> 上 await 任何东西也是如此。</p>'),
    # "In code:"
    ('<p>In code:</p>', '<p>代码：</p>'),
    # MissedTickBehavior
    ('<p>This method ignores <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> strategy.</p>',
     '<p>此方法忽略 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 策略。</p>'),
    # Poll::Ready(Err(e)) for other errors
    ('<p><code>Poll::Ready(Err(e))</code> for other errors are standard I/O errors coming from the\nunderlying object.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Ready(Err(e))</code> 表示其他错误，这些是来自底层对象的标准 I/O 错误。</p>'),
    # If the object is not ready for writing
    ('<p>If the object is not ready for writing, the method returns\n<code>Poll::Pending</code> and arranges for the current task (via\n<code>cx.waker()</code>) to receive a notification when the object becomes\nwritable or is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果对象未准备好写入数据，则方法返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排当前任务（通过 <code>cx.waker()</code>）在对象变为可写或被关闭时接收通知。</p>'),
    # Binding with port 0
    ('<p>Binding with a port number of 0 will request that the OS assigns a port\nto this listener. The port allocated can be queried via the <code>local_addr</code>\nmethod.</p>',
     '<p>使用端口号 0 绑定将请求操作系统为此监听器分配一个端口。所分配的端口可以通过 <code>local_addr</code> 方法查询。</p>'),
    # On success, newly created TcpSocket is returned
    ('<p>On success, the newly created <code>TcpSocket</code> is returned. If an error is\nencountered, it is returned instead.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回新创建的 <code>TcpSocket</code>。如果遇到错误，则改为返回该错误。</p>'),
    # Sets or gets the maximum socket send buffer
    ('<p>Sets or gets the maximum socket send buffer in bytes. The\nkernel doubles this value (to allow space for bookkeeping\noverhead) when it is set using <code>setsockopt(2)</code>, and this doubled\nvalue is returned by <code>getsockopt(2)</code>.</p>',
     '<p>设置或获取套接字最大发送缓冲区（以字节为单位）。使用 <code>setsockopt(2)</code> 设置时，内核会将该值加倍（以容纳簿记开销），而 <code>getsockopt(2)</code> 返回的是加倍后的值。</p>'),
    # Sets the linger duration
    ('<p>Sets the linger duration of this socket by setting the <code>SO_LINGER</code> option.</p>',
     '<p>通过设置 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 选项来设置此套接字的 linger 时长。</p>'),
    # This option controls the action taken when a stream has unsent messages
    ('<p>This option controls the action taken when a stream has unsent messages and the stream is\nclosed. If <code>SO_LINGER</code> is set, the system shall block the process until it can transmit the\ndata or until the time expires.</p>',
     '<p>此选项控制当流存在未发送消息且流已关闭时所采取的动作。如果设置了 <code>SO_LINGER</code>，系统将阻塞进程，直到能够传输数据或时间到期。</p>'),
    # From ultimate SO_LINGER page
    ('<p>From <a href="https://blog.netherlabs.nl/articles/2009/01/18/the-ultimate-so_linger-page-or-why-is-my-tcp-not-reliable">The ultimate <code>SO_LINGER</code> page, or: why is my tcp not reliable</a></p>',
     '<p>来自 <a href="https://blog.netherlabs.nl/articles/2009/01/18/the-ultimate-so_linger-page-or-why-is-my-tcp-not-reliable">终极 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 页面，或者说：为什么我的 TCP 不可靠</a></p>'),
    # Linger duration zero / Reads linger duration
    ('<p>Sets a linger duration of zero on this socket by setting the <code>SO_LINGER</code> option.</p>',
     '<p>通过设置 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 选项将此套接字的 linger 时长设置为零。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reads the linger duration for this socket by getting the <code>SO_LINGER</code>\noption.</p>',
     '<p>通过获取 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 选项来读取此套接字的 linger 时长。</p>'),
    # TCP_NODELAY
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>TCP_NODELAY</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>TCP_NODELAY</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>TCP_NODELAY</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字上 <code>TCP_NODELAY</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    # IP_TOS
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IP_TOS</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IP_TOS</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value for the <code>IP_TOS</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IP_TOS</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    # write_all method defined on AsyncWriteExt
    ('<p>The <a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::write_all"><code>write_all</code></a> method is defined on the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::write_all"><code>write_all</code></a> 方法定义在 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait 上。</p>'),
    # The function may complete without socket being ready (variant)
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being ready. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting an operation will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>. The function can also return with an empty\n<a href="../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> set, so you should always check the returned value and possibly\nwait again if the requested states are not set.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未就绪时完成。这是一种误报，尝试进行操作将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。该函数也可能返回空的 <a href="../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> 集合，因此应始终检查返回值，如果请求的状态未设置，可能需要再次等待。</p>'),
    # "Usually, readable() or ready() is used with this function" (link version)
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    # If the socket is ready, the provided closure is called
    ('<p>If the socket is ready, the provided closure is called. The closure\nshould attempt to perform IO operation on the socket by manually\ncalling the appropriate syscall. If the operation fails because the\nsocket is not actually ready, then the closure should return a\n<code>WouldBlock</code> error and the readiness flag is cleared. The return value\nof the closure is then returned by <code>try_io</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果套接字已就绪，则调用提供的闭包。闭包应通过手动调用适当的系统调用来尝试在套接字上执行 I/O 操作。如果操作失败的原因是套接字实际上尚未就绪，则闭包应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误，同时会清除就绪标志。闭包的返回值随后由 <code>try_io</code> 返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the socket is not ready, then the closure is not called\nand a <code>WouldBlock</code> error is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果套接字未就绪，则不会调用闭包，并返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。</p>'),
    # "The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the methods defined on the Tokio TcpStream"
    ('<p>The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the methods\ndefined on the Tokio <code>TcpStream</code> type, as this will mess with the\nreadiness flag and can cause the socket to behave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包不应使用 Tokio <code>TcpStream</code> 类型上定义的任何方法来执行 I/O 操作，因为这会干扰就绪标志，并可能导致套接字行为异常。</p>'),
    # Readiness loop
    ('<p>The readiness of the socket is awaited and when the socket is ready,\nthe provided closure is called. The closure should attempt to perform\nIO operation on the socket by manually calling the appropriate syscall.\nIf the operation fails because the socket is not actually ready,\nthen the closure should return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error. In such case the\nreadiness flag is cleared and the socket readiness is awaited again.\nThis loop is repeated until the closure returns an <code>Ok</code> or an error\nother than <code>WouldBlock</code>.</p>',
     '<p>会等待套接字的就绪状态，当套接字就绪时，会调用提供的闭包。闭包应通过手动调用适当的系统调用来尝试在套接字上执行 I/O 操作。如果操作失败的原因是套接字实际上尚未就绪，则闭包应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在这种情况下，会清除就绪标志并重新等待套接字就绪。该循环将一直重复，直到闭包返回 <code>Ok</code> 或除 <code>WouldBlock</code> 之外的错误。</p>'),
    # "Splits a TcpStream into a read half and a write half"
    ('<p>Splits a <code>TcpStream</code> into a read half and a write half, which can be used\nto read and write the stream concurrently.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>TcpStream</code> 拆分为读半部分和写半部分，可用于并发地读写流。</p>'),
    # "The function must be called with valid byte array buf"
    ('<p>The function must be called with valid byte array <code>buf</code> of sufficient\nsize to hold the message bytes. If a message is too long to fit in the\nsupplied buffer, excess bytes may be discarded.</p>',
     '<p>调用此函数时必须传入足够大小的有效字节数组 <code>buf</code> 以容纳消息字节。如果消息太长而无法装入提供的缓冲区，则多余字节可能会被丢弃。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method must be called with valid byte array <code>buf</code> of sufficient size\nto hold the message bytes. If a message is too long to fit in the\nsupplied buffer, excess bytes may be discarded.</p>',
     '<p>调用此方法时必须传入足够大小的有效字节数组 <code>buf</code> 以容纳消息字节。如果消息太长而无法装入提供的缓冲区，则多余字节可能会被丢弃。</p>'),
    # UdpSocket try_io closure
    ('<p>The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the methods\ndefined on the Tokio <code>UdpSocket</code> type, as this will mess with the\nreadiness flag and can cause the socket to behave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包不应使用 Tokio <code>UdpSocket</code> 类型上定义的任何方法来执行 I/O 操作，因为这会干扰就绪标志，并可能导致套接字行为异常。</p>'),
    # peek_sender variants
    ('<p>If you’re merely interested in learning the sender of the data at the head of the queue,\ntry <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::peek_sender"><code>peek_sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果你只想了解队列头部数据的发送方，请尝试 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::peek_sender"><code>peek_sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you’re merely interested in learning the sender of the data at the head of the queue,\ntry <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.poll_peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::poll_peek_sender"><code>poll_peek_sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果你只想了解队列头部数据的发送方，请尝试 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.poll_peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::poll_peek_sender"><code>poll_peek_sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you’re merely interested in learning the sender of the data at the head of the queue,\ntry <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.try_peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::try_peek_sender"><code>try_peek_sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果你只想了解队列头部数据的发送方，请尝试 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.try_peek_sender" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::try_peek_sender"><code>try_peek_sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Attempts to put two halves back together
    ('<p>Attempts to put the two halves of a <code>TcpStream</code> back together and\nrecover the original socket. Succeeds only if the two halves\noriginated from the same call to <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将 <code>TcpStream</code> 的两个半部分重新合并并恢复原始套接字。仅当两个半部分源自同一调用 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a> 时才会成功。</p>'),
    # "Note that on multiple calls to poll_peek or poll_read"
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_peek</code> or <code>poll_read</code>, only the\n<code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is scheduled\nto receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_peek</code> 或 <code>poll_read</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # "See the ... level documentation"
    ('<p>See the <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.poll_peek" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::poll_peek"><code>TcpStream::poll_peek</code></a> level documentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.poll_peek" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::poll_peek"><code>TcpStream::poll_peek</code></a> 的方法级文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.peek" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::peek"><code>TcpStream::peek</code></a> level documentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.peek" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::peek"><code>TcpStream::peek</code></a> 的方法级文档。</p>'),
    # "This function is also equivalent to TcpStream::ready"
    ('<p>This function is also equivalent to <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>TcpStream::ready</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数同样等价于 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>TcpStream::ready</code></a>。</p>'),
    # The pipe mode
    ('<p>The pipe mode.</p>', '<p>管道模式。</p>'),
    # Note that on multiple calls to poll_write_ready or poll_write
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_write_ready</code> or <code>poll_write</code>, only\nthe <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup. (However, <code>poll_read_ready</code> retains a\nsecond, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_write_ready</code> 或 <code>poll_write</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_read_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒器。）</p>'),
    # Receives data on socket from remote (peek, returns bytes peeked)
    ('<p>Receives data on the socket from the remote address to which it is\nconnected, without removing that data from the queue. On success,\nreturns the number of bytes peeked.</p>',
     '<p>在套接字上从其连接的远程地址接收数据，但不会从队列中移除该数据。成功时返回窥视到的字节数。</p>'),
    # The read method is defined on AsyncReadExt (fn@crate::io format)
    ('<p>The <a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncReadExt::read"><code>read</code></a> method is defined on the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncReadExt::read"><code>read</code></a> 方法定义在 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上。</p>'),
    # UdpSocket connect
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::connect"><code>connect</code></a> method will connect this socket to a remote address.\nThis method will fail if the socket is not connected.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::connect"><code>connect</code></a> 方法会将此套接字连接到远程地址。如果套接字未连接，此方法将失败。</p>'),
    # Note on multiple calls in recv direction
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a <code>poll_*</code> method in the <code>recv</code> direction, only the\n<code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call will be scheduled to\nreceive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 <code>recv</code> 方向多次调用 <code>poll_*</code> 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a <code>poll_*</code> method in the <code>recv</code> direction, only the\n<code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call will be scheduled to\nreceive a wakeup</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 <code>recv</code> 方向多次调用 <code>poll_*</code> 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # OwnedReadHalf/ReadHalf readable() variants
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    # Caller must not de-initialize
    ('<p>The caller must not de-initialize portions of the buffer that have already been initialized.\nThis includes any bytes in the region marked as uninitialized by <code>ReadBuf</code>.</p>',
     '<p>调用者不得反初始化缓冲区中已经初始化的部分。这包括 <code>ReadBuf</code> 标记为未初始化的区域中的任何字节。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 3: more patterns ============
    # Default pipe mode
    ('<p>The default pipe mode is <a href="enum.PipeMode.html#variant.Byte" title="variant tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::PipeMode::Byte"><code>PipeMode::Byte</code></a>. See <a href="enum.PipeMode.html" title="enum tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::PipeMode"><code>PipeMode</code></a> for\ndocumentation of what each mode means.</p>',
     '<p>默认管道模式为 <a href="enum.PipeMode.html#variant.Byte" title="variant tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::PipeMode::Byte"><code>PipeMode::Byte</code></a>。关于每种模式的含义，请参阅 <a href="enum.PipeMode.html" title="enum tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::PipeMode"><code>PipeMode</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    # Opens / Creates named pipe
    ('<p>Opens the named pipe identified by <code>addr</code>.</p>',
     '<p>打开由 <code>addr</code> 标识的命名管道。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates the named pipe identified by <code>addr</code> for use as a server.</p>',
     '<p>创建由 <code>addr</code> 标识的命名管道以用作服务器。</p>'),
    # This function is also unsafe as the primitives
    ('<p>This function is also unsafe as the primitives currently returned have\nthe contract that they are the sole owner of the file descriptor they\nare wrapping. Usage of this function could accidentally allow violating\nthis contract which can cause memory unsafety in code that relies on it\nbeing true.</p>',
     '<p>此函数同样是不安全的，因为当前返回的原语带有以下约定：它们是其包装的文件描述符的唯一所有者。使用此函数可能会意外违反该约定，从而在依赖该约定的代码中导致内存不安全。</p>'),
    # This function is usually paired with try_read() or try_write()
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <code>try_read()</code> or <code>try_write()</code>. It\ncan be used to concurrently read / write to the same pipe on a single\ntask without splitting the pipe.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <code>try_read()</code> 或 <code>try_write()</code> 配对使用。它可用于在单个任务上同时对同一管道进行读/写，而无需拆分管道。</p>'),
    # The function may complete without the pipe being ready
    ('<p>The function may complete without the pipe being ready. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting an operation will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>. The function can also return with an empty\n<a href="../../../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> set, so you should always check the returned value and possibly\nwait again if the requested states are not set.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在管道尚未就绪时完成。这是一种误报，尝试进行操作将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。该函数也可能返回空的 <a href="../../../io/struct.Ready.html" title="struct tokio::io::Ready"><code>Ready</code></a> 集合，因此应始终检查返回值，如果请求的状态未设置，可能需要再次等待。</p>'),
    # If pipe is not currently ready for reading/writing
    ('<p>If the pipe is not currently ready for reading, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the pipe\nbecomes ready for reading, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the waker.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道当前未准备好读取数据，此方法将存储来自所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 的克隆。当管道变为可读时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the pipe is not currently ready for writing, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the pipe\nbecomes ready for writing, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the waker.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道当前未准备好写入数据，此方法将存储来自所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 的克隆。当管道变为可写时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    # Note on multiple calls to poll_read_ready or poll_read
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_read_ready</code> or <code>poll_read</code>, only\nthe <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup. (However, <code>poll_write_ready</code> retains a\nsecond, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_read_ready</code> 或 <code>poll_read</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_write_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒器。）</p>'),
    # Receives any pending data from pipe (try_read and try_read_vectored)
    ('<p>Receives any pending data from the pipe but does not wait for new data\nto arrive. On success, returns the number of bytes read. Because\n<code>try_read()</code> is non-blocking, the buffer does not have to be stored by\nthe async task and can exist entirely on the stack.</p>',
     '<p>接收管道上任何待处理的数据，但不会等待新数据到达。成功时返回读取的字节数。由于 <code>try_read()</code> 是非阻塞的，缓冲区不必由异步任务存储，可以完全存在于栈上。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives any pending data from the pipe but does not wait for new data\nto arrive. On success, returns the number of bytes read. Because\n<code>try_read_vectored()</code> is non-blocking, the buffer does not have to be\nstored by the async task and can exist entirely on the stack.</p>',
     '<p>接收管道上任何待处理的数据，但不会等待新数据到达。成功时返回读取的字节数。由于 <code>try_read_vectored()</code> 是非阻塞的，缓冲区不必由异步任务存储，可以完全存在于栈上。</p>'),
    # Usually readable() or ready() for NamedPipeClient/Server
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    # If pipe is not ready to read data
    ('<p>If the pipe is not ready to read data,\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道未准备好读取数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # If data is successfully read (pipe - vectored variant)
    ('<p>If data is successfully read, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the\nnumber of bytes read. <code>Ok(0)</code> indicates the pipe’s read half is closed\nand will no longer yield data. If the pipe is not ready to read data\n<code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果成功读取数据，则返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是读取的字节数。<code>Ok(0)</code> 表示管道的读半部分已关闭，将不再产生数据。如果管道未准备好读取数据，则返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    # If pipe is ready, the provided closure is called
    ('<p>If the pipe is ready, the provided closure is called. The closure\nshould attempt to perform IO operation from the pipe by manually\ncalling the appropriate syscall. If the operation fails because the\npipe is not actually ready, then the closure should return a\n<code>WouldBlock</code> error and the readiness flag is cleared. The return value\nof the closure is then returned by <code>try_io</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道已就绪，则调用提供的闭包。闭包应通过手动调用适当的系统调用来尝试在管道上执行 I/O 操作。如果操作失败的原因是管道实际上尚未就绪，则闭包应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误，同时会清除就绪标志。闭包的返回值随后由 <code>try_io</code> 返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the pipe is not ready, then the closure is not called\nand a <code>WouldBlock</code> error is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果管道未就绪，则不会调用闭包，并返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。</p>'),
    # The closure should not perform IO using NamedPipeClient methods
    ('<p>The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the methods\ndefined on the Tokio <code>NamedPipeClient</code> type, as this will mess with the\nreadiness flag and can cause the pipe to behave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包不应使用 Tokio <code>NamedPipeClient</code> 类型上定义的任何方法来执行 I/O 操作，因为这会干扰就绪标志，并可能导致管道行为异常。</p>'),
    # Pipe readiness loop
    ('<p>The readiness of the pipe is awaited and when the pipe is ready,\nthe provided closure is called. The closure should attempt to perform\nIO operation on the pipe by manually calling the appropriate syscall.\nIf the operation fails because the pipe is not actually ready,\nthen the closure should return a <code>WouldBlock</code> error. In such case the\nreadiness flag is cleared and the pipe readiness is awaited again.\nThis loop is repeated until the closure returns an <code>Ok</code> or an error\nother than <code>WouldBlock</code>.</p>',
     '<p>会等待管道的就绪状态，当管道就绪时，会调用提供的闭包。闭包应通过手动调用适当的系统调用来尝试在管道上执行 I/O 操作。如果操作失败的原因是管道实际上尚未就绪，则闭包应返回 <code>WouldBlock</code> 错误。在这种情况下，会清除就绪标志并重新等待管道就绪。该循环将一直重复，直到闭包返回 <code>Ok</code> 或除 <code>WouldBlock</code> 之外的错误。</p>'),
    # Event interval
    ('<p>The runtime will check for new IO or timer events whenever there are no\ntasks ready to be scheduled, or when it has scheduled 61 tasks in a row. The\nnumber 61 may be changed using the <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.event_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::event_interval"><code>event_interval</code></a> setting.</p>',
     '<p>每当没有任务可以被调度时，或者已经连续调度了 61 个任务时，运行时将检查新的 I/O 或定时器事件。数字 61 可以使用 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.event_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::event_interval"><code>event_interval</code></a> 设置进行更改。</p>'),
    # Spawn future runs in background
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen <code>spawn</code> is called, even if you don’t await the returned\n<code>JoinHandle</code> (assuming that the runtime <a href="index.html#driving-the-runtime">is running</a>).</p>',
     '<p>当调用 <code>spawn</code> 时，提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你未 await 返回的 <code>JoinHandle</code> 也是如此（假设运行时<a href="index.html#driving-the-runtime">正在运行</a>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen <code>spawn</code> is called, even if you don\'t await the returned\n<code>JoinHandle</code> (assuming that the runtime <a href="index.html#driving-the-runtime">is running</a>).</p>',
     '<p>当调用 <code>spawn</code> 时，提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你未 await 返回的 <code>JoinHandle</code> 也是如此（假设运行时<a href="index.html#driving-the-runtime">正在运行</a>）。</p>'),
    # Handle can be cloned
    ('<p>The returned handle can be used to spawn tasks that run on this runtime, and can\nbe cloned to allow moving the <code>Handle</code> to other threads.</p>',
     '<p>返回的句柄可用于派生在此运行时上运行的任务，并且可以克隆以便将 <code>Handle</code> 移到其他线程。</p>'),
    # Allows you to construct types that must have an executor
    ('<p>This allows you to construct types that must have an executor\navailable on creation such as <a href="../time/struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> or <a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>. It will\nalso allow you to call methods such as <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这允许你构造在创建时必须有执行器可用的类型，例如 <a href="../time/struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> 或 <a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。它还允许你调用诸如 <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> 之类的方法。</p>'),
    # Shuts down runtime, waiting for at most duration
    ('<p>Shuts down the runtime, waiting for at most <code>duration</code> for all spawned\nwork to stop.</p>',
     '<p>关闭运行时，并最多等待 <code>duration</code> 时间让所有已派生的工作停止。</p>'),
    # See struct level documentation
    ('<p>See the <a href="struct.LocalRuntime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime">struct level documentation</a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.LocalRuntime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime">结构体级文档</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">struct level documentation</a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">结构体级文档</a>。</p>'),
    # shutdown_background
    ('<p>This can be useful if you want to drop a runtime from within another runtime.\nNormally, dropping a runtime will block indefinitely for spawned blocking tasks\nto complete, which would normally not be permitted within an asynchronous context.\nBy calling <code>shutdown_background()</code>, you can drop the runtime from such a context.</p>',
     '<p>如果你想从另一个运行时中 drop 一个运行时，这会很有用。通常情况下，drop 一个运行时会无限期阻塞以等待已派生的阻塞任务完成，而异步上下文通常不允许这样做。通过调用 <code>shutdown_background()</code>，你可以从此类上下文中 drop 该运行时。</p>'),
    # shutdown_timeout equivalent
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to calling <code>shutdown_timeout(Duration::from_nanos(0))</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于调用 <code>shutdown_timeout(Duration::from_nanos(0))</code>。</p>'),
    # _timeout methods not runtime agnostic
    ('<p>As an exception, methods ending in <code>_timeout</code> are not runtime agnostic\nbecause they require access to the Tokio timer. See the documentation of\neach <code>*_timeout</code> method for more information on its use.</p>',
     '<p>作为例外，以 <code>_timeout</code> 结尾的方法不是与运行时无关的，因为它们需要访问 Tokio 定时器。有关其使用的更多信息，请参阅各个 <code>*_timeout</code> 方法的文档。</p>'),
    # Makes a new MappedMutexGuard
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为已锁定数据的某个组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    # This operation cannot fail MappedMutexGuard
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a> passed in already locked the mutex.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a> 已经锁定了互斥锁。</p>'),
    # Attempts to make a new MappedMutexGuard
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data. The\noriginal guard is returned if the closure returns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为已锁定数据的某个组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始守卫。</p>'),
    # mutex available, not guaranteed
    ('<p>If the mutex is available to be acquired immediately, then this call\nwill typically not yield to the runtime. However, this is not guaranteed\nunder all circumstances.</p>',
     '<p>如果互斥锁可以立即获取，那么此调用通常不会让出执行权给运行时。但是，并非在所有情况下都能保证这一点。</p>'),
    # lock released when guard dropped
    ('<p>The lock is automatically released whenever the guard is dropped, at which\npoint <code>lock</code> will succeed yet again.</p>',
     '<p>每当守卫被 drop 时，锁会自动释放，此时 <code>lock</code> 将再次成功。</p>'),
    # MutexGuard cannot fail
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a> passed in already locked the mutex.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a> 已经锁定了互斥锁。</p>'),
    # Notify explanation
    ('<p>By adding the <code>Notified</code> futures to the list by calling <code>enable</code> before\n<code>try_recv</code>, the <code>notify_one</code> calls in step three would remove the\nfutures from the list and mark them notified instead of adding a permit\nto the <code>Notify</code>. This ensures that both futures are woken.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <code>try_recv</code> 之前通过调用 <code>enable</code> 将 <code>Notified</code> future 添加到列表中，则第三步中的 <code>notify_one</code> 调用会从列表中移除这些 future 并将它们标记为已通知，而不是向 <code>Notify</code> 添加许可。这确保了两个 future 都会被唤醒。</p>'),
    # New Notify
    ('<p>Create a new <code>Notify</code>, initialized without a permit.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <code>Notify</code>，初始化时没有许可。</p>'),
    # New OnceCell
    ('<p>Creates a new empty <code>OnceCell</code> instance.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的空 <code>OnceCell</code> 实例。</p>'),
    # Gets value from OnceCell
    ('<p>Gets the value currently in the <code>OnceCell</code>, or initialize it with the\ngiven asynchronous operation.</p>',
     '<p>获取 <code>OnceCell</code> 中当前的值，或使用给定的异步操作进行初始化。</p>'),
    # Some other task is currently working
    ('<p>If some other task is currently working on initializing the <code>OnceCell</code>,\nthis call will wait for that other task to finish, then return the value\nthat the other task produced.</p>',
     '<p>如果其他任务当前正在初始化 <code>OnceCell</code>，此调用将等待该其他任务完成，然后返回该其他任务产生的值。</p>'),
    # Will deadlock if f tries to initialize recursively
    ('<p>This will deadlock if <code>f</code> tries to initialize the cell recursively.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>f</code> 尝试递归初始化单元，则会发生死锁。</p>'),
    # Takes value from cell
    ('<p>Takes the value from the cell, destroying the cell in the process.\nReturns <code>None</code> if the cell is empty.</p>',
     '<p>从单元中取出值，此过程会销毁单元。如果单元为空，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    # OwnedMappedMutexGuard variants
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为已锁定数据的某个组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data. The\noriginal guard is returned if the closure returns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为已锁定数据的某个组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始守卫。</p>'),
    # associated function notes
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as <code>OwnedMutexGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A\nmethod would interfere with methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要以 <code>OwnedMutexGuard::try_map(...)</code> 的方式使用。如果使用方法，将与已锁定数据内容上同名的方法产生冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods\nof the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要以 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map(..)</code> 的方式使用。如果使用方法，将与已锁定数据内容上同名的方法产生冲突。</p>'),
    # OwnedRwLock variants
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> passed\nin already locked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> passed in\nalready locked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> passed in already\nlocked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    # If this function returns Err(...)
    ('<p>If this function returns <code>Err(...)</code>, the lock is never unlocked nor downgraded.</p>',
     '<p>如果此函数返回 <code>Err(...)</code>，则锁既不会被解锁，也不会被降级。</p>'),
    # Won't necessarily allow additional readers
    ('<p><strong>Note:</strong> This won’t <em>necessarily</em> allow any additional readers to acquire\nlocks, since <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> is fair and it is possible that a writer is next\nin line.</p>',
     '<p><strong>注意：</strong>这<em>不一定</em>会允许任何额外的读取者获取锁，因为 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 是公平的，并且可能有写入者排在下一位。</p>'),
    # Forgets the permit
    ('<p>Forgets the permit <strong>without</strong> releasing it back to the semaphore.\nThis can be used to reduce the amount of permits available from a\nsemaphore.</p>',
     '<p><strong>不</strong>将许可释放回信号量就将其遗忘。这可用于减少信号量中可用的许可数量。</p>'),
    # Permits held by both
    ('<p>Permits held by both <code>self</code> and <code>other</code> are released when <code>self</code> drops.</p>',
     '<p>由 <code>self</code> 和 <code>other</code> 持有的许将在 <code>self</code> 被 drop 时一起释放。</p>'),
    # This function panics if permits merged
    ('<p>This function panics if permits from different <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> instances\nare merged.</p>',
     '<p>如果合并来自不同 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> 实例的许可，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # If there are insufficient permits
    ('<p>If there are insufficient permits and it’s not possible to reduce by <code>n</code>, returns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有足够的许可且无法减少 <code>n</code>，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are insufficient permits and it\'s not possible to reduce by <code>n</code>, returns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有足够的许可且无法减少 <code>n</code>，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    # Returns number of permits held
    ('<p>Returns the number of permits held by <code>self</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>self</code> 持有的许可数。</p>'),
    # Creates a new RwLock<T>
    ('<p>Creates a new instance of an <code>RwLock&lt;T&gt;</code> which is unlocked.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个未锁定的 <code>RwLock&lt;T&gt;</code> 新实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new instance of an <code>RwLock&lt;T&gt;</code> which is unlocked\nand allows a maximum of <code>max_reads</code> concurrent readers.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个未锁定的 <code>RwLock&lt;T&gt;</code> 新实例，允许最多 <code>max_reads</code> 个并发读取者。</p>'),
    # Panics if max_reads is 0 or too big
    ('<p>Panics if <code>max_reads</code> is <code>0</code> or is bigger than <code>u32::MAX &gt;&gt; 3</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>max_reads</code> 为 <code>0</code> 或大于 <code>u32::MAX &gt;&gt; 3</code>，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Locks RwLock with shared read access
    ('<p>Locks this <code>RwLock</code> with shared read access, causing the current task\nto yield until the lock has been acquired.</p>',
     '<p>使用共享读访问锁定此 <code>RwLock</code>，导致当前任务让出执行权，直到锁被获取。</p>'),
    ('<p>The calling task will yield until there are no writers which hold the\nlock. There may be other readers inside the lock when the task resumes.</p>',
     '<p>调用任务将让出执行权，直到没有任何持有锁的写入者。当任务恢复时，锁内可能还有其他读取者。</p>'),
    # Note priority policy
    ('<p>Note that under the priority policy of <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a>, read locks are not\ngranted until prior write locks, to prevent starvation. Therefore\ndeadlock may occur if a read lock is held by the current task, a write\nlock attempt is made, and then a subsequent read lock attempt is made\nby the current task.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，根据 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 的优先级策略，为防止饥饿，在先前的写锁释放之前不会授予读锁。因此，如果当前任务持有读锁，然后尝试获取写锁，再尝试获取读锁，则可能发生死锁。</p>'),
    # Attempts to acquire RwLock with shared read access
    ('<p>Attempts to acquire this <code>RwLock</code> with shared read access.</p>',
     '<p>尝试使用共享读访问获取此 <code>RwLock</code>。</p>'),
    # If access couldn't be acquired
    ('<p>If the access couldn’t be acquired immediately, returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, an RAII guard is returned which will release read access\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果无法立即获取访问权限，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。否则返回一个 RAII 守卫，当它被 drop 时会释放读访问权。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the access couldn\'t be acquired immediately, returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, an RAII guard is returned which will release read access\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果无法立即获取访问权限，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。否则返回一个 RAII 守卫，当它被 drop 时会释放读访问权。</p>'),
    # Locks RwLock with exclusive write access
    ('<p>Locks this <code>RwLock</code> with exclusive write access, causing the current\ntask to yield until the lock has been acquired.</p>',
     '<p>使用独占写访问锁定此 <code>RwLock</code>，导致当前任务让出执行权，直到锁被获取。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 4 ============
    # RwLock synchronous/async use cases
    ('<p>This method is intended for use cases where you\nneed to use this rwlock in asynchronous code as well as in synchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>此方法适用于需要在异步代码和同步代码中都使用此 rwlock 的场景。</p>'),
    # RwLock write access RAII guard
    ('<p>Returns an RAII guard which will drop the write access of this <code>RwLock</code>\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 RAII 守卫，当它被 drop 时会释放此 <code>RwLock</code> 的写访问权。</p>'),
    # Attempts to acquire this RwLock with exclusive write access
    ('<p>Attempts to acquire this <code>RwLock</code> with exclusive write access.</p>',
     '<p>尝试使用独占写访问获取此 <code>RwLock</code>。</p>'),
    # RwLockMappedWriteGuard cannot fail
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> passed in already\nlocked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    # Async version of RwLockWriteGuard::map
    ('<p>This is an asynchronous version of <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::map</code></a> from the\n<a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是来自 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 的 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::map</code></a> 的异步版本。</p>'),
    # RwLockMappedWriteGuard::try_map async
    ('<p>This is an asynchronous version of <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.try_map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map</code></a> from\nthe <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是来自 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 的 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.try_map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map</code></a> 的异步版本。</p>'),
    # Attempts to make a new RwLockMappedWriteGuard
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component of\nthe locked data. The original guard is returned if the closure returns\n<code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为已锁定数据的某个组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始守卫。</p>'),
    # RwLockReadGuard cannot fail
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>RwLockReadGuard</code> passed in already\nlocked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>RwLockReadGuard</code> 已经锁定了数据。</p>'),
    # Acquires n permits / Tries to acquire n permits
    ('<p>Acquires <code>n</code> permits from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>从信号量获取 <code>n</code> 个许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to acquire <code>n</code> permits from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从信号量获取 <code>n</code> 个许可。</p>'),
    # Semaphore acquire error
    ('<p>The semaphore must be wrapped in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> to call this method.\nIf the semaphore has been closed, this returns an <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, this returns a <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the\nacquired permit.</p>',
     '<p>调用此方法时，信号量必须包装在 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 中。如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>。否则返回表示已获取许可的 <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The semaphore must be wrapped in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> to call this method. If\nthe semaphore has been closed, this returns a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>\nand a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a> if there are no permits left.\nOtherwise, this returns a <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the\nacquired permit.</p>',
     '<p>调用此方法时，信号量必须包装在 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 中。如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>；如果没有任何许可，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a>。否则返回表示已获取许可的 <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a>。</p>'),
    # SetOnce / Handling lag
    ('<p>Creates a new empty <code>SetOnce</code> instance.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的空 <code>SetOnce</code> 实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>Handling lag</p>', '<p>处理延迟</p>'),
    # Returns true if receivers belong
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if receivers belong to the same channel.</p>',
     '<p>如果这些 receiver 属于同一个通道，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    # This future is fused
    ('<p>This future is fused, so once it has completed, any future calls to poll\nwill immediately return <code>Poll::Ready</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此 future 是 fused 的，因此一旦它完成，后续任何对 poll 的调用都会立即返回 <code>Poll::Ready</code>。</p>'),
    # Adds this future to the list
    ('<p>Adds this future to the list of futures that are ready to receive\nwakeups from calls to <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将此 future 添加到已准备好通过调用 <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one</code></a> 接收唤醒的 future 列表中。</p>'),
    # Capacity for the message has already been reserved
    ('<p>Capacity for the message has already been reserved. The message is sent\nto the receiver and the permit is consumed. The operation will succeed\neven if the receiver half has been closed. See <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a> for\nmore details on performing a clean shutdown.</p>',
     '<p>消息的容量已被预留。消息被发送到 receiver，并且许可被消费。即使 receiver 半部分已关闭，此操作也会成功。有关执行干净关闭的更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Returns None if channel closed
    ('<p>This method returns <code>None</code> if the channel has been closed and there are\nno remaining messages in the channel’s buffer. This indicates that no\nfurther values can ever be received from this <code>Receiver</code>. The channel is\nclosed when all senders have been dropped, or when <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已关闭且通道缓冲区中没有剩余消息，则此方法返回 <code>None</code>。这表明从此 <code>Receiver</code> 不再可能接收到任何值。当所有 sender 都被 drop 或调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 时，通道会被关闭。</p>'),
    # Values are buffered
    ('<p>Values are buffered:</p>', '<p>值被缓冲：</p>'),
    # Receives the next values / capacity
    ('<p>Receives the next values for this receiver and extends <code>buffer</code>.</p>',
     '<p>为此 receiver 接收下一个值并扩展 <code>buffer</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The capacity of <code>buffer</code> is increased as needed.</p>',
     '<p><code>buffer</code> 的容量会按需增加。</p>'),
    # recv_many cancel safe
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>recv_many</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, it is guaranteed that no messages were received on this\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>recv_many</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证此通道没有接收到任何消息。</p>'),
    # Tries to receive the next value
    ('<p>Tries to receive the next value for this receiver.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为该 receiver 接收下一个值。</p>'),
    # TryRecvError Empty/Disconnected
    ('<p>This method returns the <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> error if the channel is currently\nempty, but there are still outstanding <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender">senders</a> or <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit">permits</a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道当前为空，但仍存在未释放的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender">sender</a> 或 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit">permit</a>，则此方法返回 <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns the <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Disconnected" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Disconnected"><code>Disconnected</code></a> error if the channel is\ncurrently empty, and there are no outstanding <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender">senders</a> or <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit">permits</a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道当前为空，且没有未释放的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender">sender</a> 或 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit">permit</a>，则此方法返回 <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Disconnected" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Disconnected"><code>Disconnected</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    # Polls to receive
    ('<p>Polls to receive the next message on this channel.</p>',
     '<p>轮询以接收此通道上的下一条消息。</p>'),
    # If Poll::Pending due to spurious failure
    ('<p>If this method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code> due to a spurious failure, then\nthe <code>Waker</code> will be notified when the situation causing the spurious\nfailure has been resolved. Note that receiving such a wakeup does not\nguarantee that the next call will succeed — it could fail with another\nspurious failure.</p>',
     '<p>如果此方法由于虚假失败而返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，那么在导致虚假失败的情况得到解决后，会收到 <code>Waker</code> 通知。请注意，收到这样的唤醒并不能保证下一次调用一定会成功——它可能会因另一个虚假失败而失败。</p>'),
    # Polls to receive multiple messages
    ('<p>Polls to receive multiple messages on this channel, extending the provided buffer.</p>',
     '<p>轮询以接收此通道上的多条消息，并扩展所提供的缓冲区。</p>'),
    # Note that this method does not guarantee exactly limit
    ('<p>Note that this method does not guarantee that exactly <code>limit</code> messages\nare received. Rather, if at least one message is available, it returns\nas many messages as it can up to the given limit. This method returns\nzero only if the channel is closed (or if <code>limit</code> is zero).</p>',
     '<p>请注意，此方法不保证一定接收到恰好 <code>limit</code> 条消息。而是如果至少有一条消息可用，它会尽可能多地返回消息，直到达到给定的上限。仅当通道已关闭（或 <code>limit</code> 为 0）时，此方法才返回零。</p>'),
    # If receive half closed
    ('<p>If the receive half of the channel is closed, either due to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>\nbeing called or the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle dropping, the function returns\nan error. The error includes the value passed to <code>send</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道的接收半部分已关闭（无论是由于调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>，还是由于 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄被 drop），则函数返回错误。错误中包含传递给 <code>send</code> 的值。</p>'),
    # Completes when receiver dropped
    ('<p>Completes when the receiver has dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当 receiver 被 drop 时完成。</p>'),
    # Allows producers to get notified
    ('<p>This allows the producers to get notified when interest in the produced\nvalues is canceled and immediately stop doing work.</p>',
     '<p>这允许生产者在对所产生值的兴趣被取消时收到通知，并立即停止工作。</p>'),
    # Cancel safe - channel closed stays closed
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. Once the channel is closed, it stays closed\nforever and all future calls to <code>closed</code> will return immediately.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。一旦通道关闭，它将永远保持关闭状态，并且所有对 <code>closed</code> 的未来调用都将立即返回。</p>'),
    # Dropping Permit / PermitIterator
    ('<p>Dropping <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> without sending a message releases the capacity back\nto the channel.</p>',
     '<p>在不发送消息的情况下 drop <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 会将容量释放回通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>Dropping <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> without consuming it entirely releases the remaining\npermits back to the channel.</p>',
     '<p>在不完整消费的情况下 drop <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> 会将剩余的许可释放回通道。</p>'),
    # Instances are created by unbounded_channel
    ('<p>Instances are created by the <a href="fn.unbounded_channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::unbounded_channel"><code>unbounded_channel</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>实例由 <a href="fn.unbounded_channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::unbounded_channel"><code>unbounded_channel</code></a> 函数创建。</p>'),
    # Receive half closed
    ('<p>The receive half of the channel was explicitly closed or has been\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>通道的接收半部分已被显式关闭或已被 drop。</p>'),
    # Each handle can be used on separate tasks
    ('<p>Each handle can be used on separate tasks.</p>',
     '<p>每个句柄可以用于不同的任务。</p>'),
    # Sender from destructor
    ('<p>To use a <code>Sender</code> from a destructor, put it in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option"><code>Option</code></a> and call\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/option/enum.Option.html#method.take" title="method core::option::Option::take"><code>Option::take</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>要在析构函数中使用 <code>Sender</code>，请将其放入 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option"><code>Option</code></a> 中并调用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/option/enum.Option.html#method.take" title="method core::option::Option::take"><code>Option::take</code></a>。</p>'),
    # One-shot channel
    ('<p>A pair of both a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and a <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>  are created by the\n<a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>一对 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 由 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数创建。</p>'),
    # Dropping the sender
    ('<p>Dropping the sender.</p>', '<p>Dropping sender。</p>'),
    # Receiver is closed
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is closed by either calling <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> explicitly or the\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> value is dropped.</p>',
     '<p>通过显式调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 或 drop <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 值来关闭 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。</p>'),
    # The following example prints hello world
    ('<p>The following example prints <code>hello! world! </code>.</p>',
     '<p>以下示例会打印 <code>hello! world! </code>。</p>'),
    # watch::channel
    ('<p>Instances are created by the <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::watch::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>实例由 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::watch::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数创建。</p>'),
    # watch modify
    ('<p>This can be useful for modifying the watched value, without\nhaving to allocate a new instance. Additionally, this\nmethod permits sending values even when there are no receivers.</p>',
     '<p>这对于修改被监视的值很有用，而无需分配新实例。此外，即使没有 receiver，此方法也允许发送值。</p>'),
    # watch modify closure panics
    ('<p>This function panics when the invocation of the <code>modify</code> closure panics.\nNo receivers are notified when panicking. All changes of the watched\nvalue applied by the closure before panicking will be visible in\nsubsequent calls to <code>borrow</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>modify</code> 闭包被调用时发生 panic，此函数也会 panic。panic 时不会通知任何 receiver。在 panic 之前闭包对被监视的值所做的所有更改，都将在后续的 <code>borrow</code> 调用中可见。</p>'),
    # Abort task
    ('<p>Abort the task associated with the handle.</p>', '<p>中止与该句柄关联的任务。</p>'),
    # Awaiting cancelled task
    ('<p>Awaiting a cancelled task might complete as usual if the task was\nalready completed at the time it was cancelled, but most likely it\nwill fail with a <a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">cancelled</a> <code>JoinError</code>.</p>',
     '<p>await 一个已取消的任务可能会像往常一样完成（如果任务在被取消时已经完成），但最有可能的是失败并返回<a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">已取消</a>的 <code>JoinError</code>。</p>'),
    # See also module level docs
    ('<p>See also <a href="index.html#cancellation" title="mod tokio::task">the module level docs</a> for more information on cancellation.</p>',
     '<p>有关取消的更多信息，另请参阅 <a href="index.html#cancellation" title="mod tokio::task">模块级文档</a>。</p>'),
    # Returns task ID
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a> that uniquely identifies this task relative to other\ncurrently spawned tasks.</p>',
     '<p>返回相对于其他当前已派生任务能唯一标识此任务的 <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">任务 ID</a>。</p>'),
    # Method panics outside runtime
    ('<p>This method panics if called outside of a Tokio runtime.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 Tokio 运行时之外调用，此方法会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Returns None if set is empty
    ('<p>Returns <code>None</code> if the set is empty.</p>',
     '<p>如果集合为空，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    # When method returns error, id accessible
    ('<p>When this method returns an error, then the id of the task that failed can be accessed\nusing the <a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.id" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::id"><code>JoinError::id</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>当此方法返回错误时，失败任务的 ID 可以通过 <a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.id" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::id"><code>JoinError::id</code></a> 方法访问。</p>'),
    # Returns None if no completed tasks
    ('<p>Returns <code>None</code> if there are no completed tasks, or if the set is empty.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有已完成的任务，或集合为空，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    # Polls for one of the tasks to complete
    ('<p>Polls for one of the tasks in the set to complete.</p>',
     '<p>轮询集合中是否有任务完成。</p>'),
    # If this returns Ready(Some(_))
    ('<p>If this returns <code>Poll::Ready(Some(_))</code>, then the task that completed is removed from the set.</p>',
     '<p>如果返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Some(_))</code>，则已完成的任务会从集合中移除。</p>'),
    # When Poll::Pending, Waker scheduled
    ('<p>When the method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>, the <code>Waker</code> in the provided <code>Context</code> is scheduled\nto receive a wakeup when a task in the <code>JoinSet</code> completes. Note that on multiple calls to\n<code>poll_join_next</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>当方法返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code> 时，所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会在 <code>JoinSet</code> 中有任务完成时被调度以接收唤醒。请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_join_next</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    # Note that this method may return Poll::Pending
    ('<p>Note that this method may return <code>Poll::Pending</code> even if one of the tasks has completed.\nThis can happen if the <a href="coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">coop budget</a> is reached.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，即使其中一个任务已完成，此方法也可能返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>。这可能发生在达到了<a href="coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">协作预算</a>上限时。</p>'),
    # Equivalent to JoinSet::spawn
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::spawn"><code>JoinSet::spawn</code></a> on each element of the iterator.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于对迭代器的每个元素调用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::spawn"><code>JoinSet::spawn</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Accesses current task-local
    ('<p>Accesses the current task-local and runs the provided closure.</p>',
     '<p>访问当前 task-local 并运行所提供的闭包。</p>'),
    # Task local panics
    ('<p>This function will panic if the task local doesn’t have a value set.</p>',
     '<p>如果 task local 没有设置值，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will panic if the task local doesn\'t have a value set.</p>',
     '<p>如果 task local 没有设置值，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # Returns copy of task-local
    ('<p>Returns a copy of the task-local value\nif the task-local value implements <code>Clone</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 task-local 值实现了 <code>Clone</code>，则返回该值的一份副本。</p>'),
    # Interval cancels
    ('<p>An interval will tick indefinitely. At any time, the <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> value can\nbe dropped. This cancels the interval.</p>',
     '<p>interval 将无限期地 tick。在任何时候都可以 drop 该 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 值。这将取消该 interval。</p>'),
    # period zero panics
    ('<p>This function panics if <code>period</code> is zero.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>period</code> 为零，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    # If tick replaced with sleep
    ('<p>If the tick in the example below was replaced with <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a>, the task\nwould only be executed once every three seconds, and not every two\nseconds.</p>',
     '<p>如果将下面示例中的 tick 替换为 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a>，那么该任务将每 3 秒才执行一次，而不是每 2 秒执行一次。</p>'),
    # To run something regularly see interval
    ('<p>To run something regularly on a schedule, see <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>若要按计划定期运行某些任务，请参阅 <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a>。</p>'),
    # Canceling sleep
    ('<p>Canceling a sleep instance is done by dropping the returned future. No additional\ncleanup work is required.</p>',
     '<p>取消 sleep 实例的方法是 drop 返回的 future。无需进行额外的清理工作。</p>'),
    # See Sleep type for more
    ('<p>See the documentation for the <a href="struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> type for more examples.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多示例，请参阅 <a href="struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> 类型的文档。</p>'),
    # Timeout return type
    ('<p>This function returns a future whose return type is <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/result/enum.Result.html" title="enum core::result::Result"><code>Result</code></a><code>&lt;T,</code><a href="error/struct.Elapsed.html" title="struct tokio::time::error::Elapsed"><code>Elapsed</code></a><code>&gt;</code>, where <code>T</code> is the\nreturn type of the provided future.</p>',
     '<p>此函数返回一个 future，其返回类型为 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/result/enum.Result.html" title="enum core::result::Result"><code>Result</code></a><code>&lt;T,</code><a href="error/struct.Elapsed.html" title="struct tokio::time::error::Elapsed"><code>Elapsed</code></a><code>&gt;</code>，其中 <code>T</code> 是所提供 future 的返回类型。</p>'),
    # Cancelling timeout
    ('<p>Cancelling a timeout is done by dropping the future. No additional cleanup\nor other work is required.</p>',
     '<p>取消 timeout 的方法是 drop 该 future。无需进行额外的清理或其他工作。</p>'),
    # Original future via Timeout::into_inner
    ('<p>The original future may be obtained by calling <a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.into_inner" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::into_inner"><code>Timeout::into_inner</code></a>. This\nconsumes the <code>Timeout</code>.</p>',
     '<p>可以通过调用 <a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.into_inner" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::into_inner"><code>Timeout::into_inner</code></a> 来获取原始 future。这会消费 <code>Timeout</code>。</p>'),
    # Create new Timeout 10 ms
    ('<p>Create a new <code>Timeout</code> set to expire in 10 milliseconds.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个设置为在 10 毫秒后到期的新 <code>Timeout</code>。</p>'),
    # Returns elapsed time
    ('<p>Returns the amount of time elapsed from another instant to this one, or\nzero duration if that instant is later than this one.</p>',
     '<p>返回从另一时刻到此刻所经过的时间量，如果该时刻晚于此刻，则返回零时长。</p>'),
    # Curly quote variants
    ('<p>Wait 100ms and print “100 ms have elapsed”.</p>',
     '<p>等待 100 毫秒并打印 “已过 100 毫秒”。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the access couldn’t be acquired immediately, returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, an RAII guard is returned which will release write access\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果无法立即获取访问权限，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。否则返回一个 RAII 守卫，当它被 drop 时会释放写访问权。</p>'),
    ('<p>Dropping sender…</p>', '<p>Dropping sender……</p>'),

    # ============ Round 5: UdpSocket (99 items) ============
    ('<p>A UDP socket.</p>', '<p>一个 UDP 套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>UDP is “connectionless”, unlike TCP. Meaning, regardless of what address you’ve bound to, a <code>UdpSocket</code>\nis free to communicate with many different remotes. In tokio there are basically two main ways to use <code>UdpSocket</code>:</p>',
     '<p>UDP 与 TCP 不同，是“无连接”的。这意味着，无论你绑定到什么地址，<code>UdpSocket</code> 都可以自由地与许多不同的远程端通信。在 Tokio 中，基本上有两种主要的使用 <code>UdpSocket</code> 的方式：</p>'),
    ('<p>This type does not provide a <code>split</code> method, because this functionality\ncan be achieved by instead wrapping the socket in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a>. Note that\nyou do not need a <code>Mutex</code> to share the <code>UdpSocket</code> — an <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code>\nis enough. This is because all of the methods take <code>&amp;self</code> instead of\n<code>&amp;mut self</code>. Once you have wrapped it in an <code>Arc</code>, you can call\n<code>.clone()</code> on the <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code> to get multiple shared handles to the\nsame socket. An example of such usage can be found further down.</p>',
     '<p>本类型不提供 <code>split</code> 方法，因为可以通过将套接字包装在 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 中来实现此功能。请注意，你不需要 <code>Mutex</code> 来共享 <code>UdpSocket</code>——一个 <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code> 就足够了。这是因为所有方法都接受 <code>&amp;self</code> 而非 <code>&amp;mut self</code>。一旦将其包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中，你就可以对 <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code> 调用 <code>.clone()</code> 来获得多个共享句柄以访问同一套接字。此类用法的示例可在下方找到。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you need to listen over UDP and produce a <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a>, you can look\nat <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/udp/struct.UdpFramed.html"><code>UdpFramed</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果你需要通过 UDP 进行监听并产生一个 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a>，可以参考 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/udp/struct.UdpFramed.html"><code>UdpFramed</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Using <code>bind</code> we can create a simple echo server that sends and recv’s with many different clients:</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code>bind</code>，我们可以创建一个简单的 echo 服务器，它与许多不同的客户端之间相互收发数据：</p>'),
    ('<p>Or using <code>connect</code> we can echo with a single remote address using <code>send</code> and <code>recv</code>:</p>',
     '<p>或者使用 <code>connect</code>，我们可以使用 <code>send</code> 和 <code>recv</code> 与单个远程地址进行 echo：</p>'),
    ('<p>Because <code>send_to</code> and <code>recv_from</code> take <code>&amp;self</code>. It’s perfectly alright\nto use an <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code> and share the references to multiple tasks.\nHere is a similar “echo” example that supports concurrent\nsending/receiving:</p>',
     '<p>由于 <code>send_to</code> 和 <code>recv_from</code> 接受 <code>&amp;self</code>，因此完全可以使用 <code>Arc&lt;UdpSocket&gt;</code> 并将其引用共享给多个任务。下面是一个类似的 “echo” 示例，它支持并发的发送/接收：</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will create a new UDP socket and attempt to bind it to\nthe <code>addr</code> provided.</p>',
     '<p>此函数将创建一个新的 UDP 套接字，并尝试将其绑定到所提供的 <code>addr</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates new <code>UdpSocket</code> from a previously bound <code>std::net::UdpSocket</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从先前已绑定的 <code>std::net::UdpSocket</code> 创建一个新的 <code>UdpSocket</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended to be used to wrap a UDP socket from the\nstandard library in the Tokio equivalent.</p>',
     '<p>此函数旨在将标准库的 UDP 套接字包装为其 Tokio 等价物。</p>'),
    ('<p>This can be used in conjunction with <code>socket2</code>’s <code>Socket</code> interface to\nconfigure a socket before it’s handed off, such as setting options like\n<code>reuse_address</code> or binding to multiple addresses.</p>',
     '<p>这可与 <code>socket2</code> 的 <code>Socket</code> 接口配合使用，以便在套接字被移交之前对其进行配置，例如设置 <code>reuse_address</code> 等选项或绑定到多个地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller is responsible for ensuring that the socket is in\nnon-blocking mode. Otherwise all I/O operations on the socket\nwill block the thread, which will cause unexpected behavior.\nNon-blocking mode can be set using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::udp::UdpSocket::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>调用者负责确保套接字处于非阻塞模式。否则，对套接字的所有 I/O 操作都会阻塞线程，从而导致意外行为。可以使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::udp::UdpSocket::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 设置非阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function panics if thread-local runtime is not set.</p>',
     '<p>如果未设置线程本地运行时，此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Turns a <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::UdpSocket"><code>tokio::net::UdpSocket</code></a> into a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct std::net::udp::UdpSocket"><code>std::net::UdpSocket</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将一个 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::UdpSocket"><code>tokio::net::UdpSocket</code></a> 转换为 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct std::net::udp::UdpSocket"><code>std::net::UdpSocket</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The returned <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct std::net::udp::UdpSocket"><code>std::net::UdpSocket</code></a> will have nonblocking mode set as\n<code>true</code>.  Use <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::udp::UdpSocket::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> to change the blocking mode if needed.</p>',
     '<p>返回的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html" title="struct std::net::udp::UdpSocket"><code>std::net::UdpSocket</code></a> 将 nonblocking 模式设置为 <code>true</code>。如需更改阻塞模式，请使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/udp/struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::udp::UdpSocket::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Connects the UDP socket setting the default destination for send() and\nlimiting packets that are read via <code>recv</code> from the address specified in\n<code>addr</code>.</p>',
     '<p>连接此 UDP 套接字，为 send() 设置默认目标地址，并限制通过 <code>recv</code> 只能从 <code>addr</code> 指定的地址读取数据包。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <code>try_recv()</code> or <code>try_send()</code>. It\ncan be used to concurrently <code>recv</code> / <code>send</code> to the same socket on a single\ntask without splitting the socket.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <code>try_recv()</code> 或 <code>try_send()</code> 配对使用。它可用于在单个任务上同时对同一套接字进行 <code>recv</code> / <code>send</code>，而无需拆分套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Concurrently receive from and send to the socket on the same task\nwithout splitting.</p>',
     '<p>在同一任务上同时对套接字进行接收和发送，而无需拆分。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to <code>ready(Interest::WRITABLE)</code> and is\nusually paired with <code>try_send()</code> or <code>try_send_to()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于 <code>ready(Interest::WRITABLE)</code>，通常与 <code>try_send()</code> 或 <code>try_send_to()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being writable. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting a <code>try_send()</code> will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未可写时完成。这是一种误报，尝试调用 <code>try_send()</code> 将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polls for write/send readiness.</p>',
     '<p>轮询写/发送就绪状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the udp stream is not currently ready for sending, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the udp\nstream becomes ready for sending, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the\nwaker.</p>',
     '<p>如果 UDP 流当前未准备好发送数据，此方法将存储来自所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 的克隆。当 UDP 流变为可发送时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_send_ready</code> or <code>poll_send</code>, only\nthe <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call is\nscheduled to receive a wakeup. (However, <code>poll_recv_ready</code> retains a\nsecond, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_send_ready</code> 或 <code>poll_send</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_recv_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒器。）</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable</code></a> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends data on the socket to the remote address that the socket is\nconnected to.</p>',
     '<p>将数据发送到套接字所连接的远程地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method may fail with a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.ConnectionRefused" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::ConnectionRefused"><code>ConnectionRefused</code></a> error if the remote\naddress has replied with ICMP Unreachable to a previously sent packet.\nHowever, this behavior depends on the OS.</p>',
     '<p>如果远程地址对先前发送的数据包回复了 ICMP Unreachable，则此方法可能会失败并返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.ConnectionRefused" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::ConnectionRefused"><code>ConnectionRefused</code></a> 错误。但是，此行为取决于操作系统。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, the number of bytes sent is returned, otherwise, the\nencountered error is returned.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回已发送的字节数，否则返回遇到的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>send</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that the message was not sent.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>send</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证该消息未被发送。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to send data on the socket to the remote address to which it\nwas previously <code>connect</code>ed.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将数据发送到套接字先前已 <code>connect</code> 的远程地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a <code>poll_*</code> method in the send direction,\nonly the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call will\nbe scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 send 方向多次调用 <code>poll_*</code> 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to send data on the socket to the remote address to which it is\nconnected.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将数据发送到套接字所连接的远程地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the socket buffer is full, <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is\nreturned. This function is usually paired with <code>writable()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当套接字缓冲区已满时，返回 <code>Err(io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。此函数通常与 <code>writable()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>If successful, <code>Ok(n)</code> is returned, where <code>n</code> is the number of bytes\nsent. If the socket is not ready to send data,\n<code>Err(ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回 <code>Ok(n)</code>，其中 <code>n</code> 是已发送的字节数。如果套接字未准备好发送数据，则返回 <code>Err(ErrorKind::WouldBlock)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to <code>ready(Interest::READABLE)</code> and is usually\npaired with <code>try_recv()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等价于 <code>ready(Interest::READABLE)</code>，通常与 <code>try_recv()</code> 配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The function may complete without the socket being readable. This is a\nfalse-positive and attempting a <code>try_recv()</code> will return with\n<code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>.</p>',
     '<p>该函数可能在套接字尚未可读时完成。这是一种误报，尝试调用 <code>try_recv()</code> 将返回 <code>io::ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polls for read/receive readiness.</p>',
     '<p>轮询读/接收就绪状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the udp stream is not currently ready for receiving, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the udp\nsocket becomes ready for reading, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the\nwaker.</p>',
     '<p>如果 UDP 流当前未准备好接收数据，此方法将存储来自所提供 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 的克隆。当 UDP 套接字变为可读时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_recv_ready</code>, <code>poll_recv</code> or\n<code>poll_peek</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most\nrecent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup. (However,\n<code>poll_send_ready</code> retains a second, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_recv_ready</code>、<code>poll_recv</code> 或 <code>poll_peek</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_send_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个唤醒器。）</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数适用于无法通过 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建并固定 future 的情况。在可能的情况下，优先使用 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives a single datagram message on the socket from the remote address\nto which it is connected. On success, returns the number of bytes read.</p>',
     '<p>从套接字所连接的远程地址接收单个数据报消息。成功时返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>recv</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, it is guaranteed that no messages were received on this\nsocket.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>recv</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证此套接字没有接收到任何消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to receive a single datagram message on the socket from the remote\naddress to which it is <code>connect</code>ed.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从套接字所 <code>connect</code> 的远程地址接收单个数据报消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::connect"><code>connect</code></a> method will connect this socket to a remote address. This method\nresolves to an error if the socket is not connected.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::connect"><code>connect</code></a> 方法会将此套接字连接到远程地址。如果套接字未连接，此方法解析为错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to receive a single datagram message on the socket from the remote\naddress to which it is connected. On success, returns the number of\nbytes read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从套接字所连接的远程地址接收单个数据报消息。成功时返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends data on the socket to the given address. On success, returns the\nnumber of bytes written.</p>',
     '<p>将数据发送到套接字上的给定地址。成功时返回已写入的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Address type can be any implementor of <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait. See its\ndocumentation for concrete examples.</p>',
     '<p>地址类型可以是任何实现了 <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait 的类型。有关具体示例，请参阅其文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is possible for <code>addr</code> to yield multiple addresses, but <code>send_to</code>\nwill only send data to the first address yielded by <code>addr</code>.</p>',
     '<p><code>addr</code> 可能会产生多个地址，但 <code>send_to</code> 只会将数据发送到 <code>addr</code> 产生的第一个地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>This will return an error when the IP version of the local socket does\nnot match that returned from <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>当本地套接字的 IP 版本与 <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> 返回的不匹配时，将返回错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>send_to</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that the message was not sent.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>send_to</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证该消息未被发送。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to send data on the socket to a given address.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将数据发送到套接字上的给定地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to a <code>poll_*</code> method in the send direction, only the\n<code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most recent call will be scheduled to\nreceive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在 send 方向多次调用 <code>poll_*</code> 方法时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度以接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to send data on the socket to the given address, but if the send is\nblocked this will return right away.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将数据发送到套接字上的给定地址，但如果发送被阻塞，此调用将立即返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>If successful, returns the number of bytes sent</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回已发送的字节数</p>'),
    ('<p>Users should ensure that when the remote cannot receive, the\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.WouldBlock" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::WouldBlock"><code>ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code></a> is properly handled. An error can also occur\nif the IP version of the socket does not match that of <code>target</code>.</p>',
     '<p>用户应确保在远程端无法接收时，<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.WouldBlock" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::WouldBlock"><code>ErrorKind::WouldBlock</code></a> 得到正确处理。如果套接字的 IP 版本与 <code>target</code> 的 IP 版本不匹配，也会发生错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives a single datagram message on the socket. On success, returns\nthe number of bytes read and the origin.</p>',
     '<p>在套接字上接收单个数据报消息。成功时返回读取的字节数和来源地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>recv_from</code> is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, it is guaranteed that no messages were received on this\nsocket.</p>',
     '<p>此方法可安全取消。如果 <code>recv_from</code> 在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中作为事件使用，并且其他分支先完成，则可以保证此套接字没有接收到任何消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to receive a single datagram on the socket.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在套接字上接收单个数据报。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to receive a single datagram message on the socket. On success,\nreturns the number of bytes read and the origin.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在套接字上接收单个数据报消息。成功时返回读取的字节数和来源地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>, <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>、<a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数配对使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives a single datagram from the connected address without removing it from the queue.\nOn success, returns the number of bytes read from whence the data came.</p>',
     '<p>从已连接的地址接收单个数据报，但不会将其从队列中移除。成功时返回读取的字节数以及数据的来源地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives data from the connected address, without removing it from the input queue.</p>',
     '<p>从已连接的地址接收数据，但不会将其从输入队列中移除。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to receive data on the connected address without removing it from the input queue.\nOn success, returns the number of bytes read.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从已连接的地址接收数据，但不会将其从输入队列中移除。成功时返回读取的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives data from the socket, without removing it from the input queue.\nOn success, returns the number of bytes read and the address from whence\nthe data came.</p>',
     '<p>从套接字接收数据，但不会将其从输入队列中移除。成功时返回读取的字节数以及数据来源的地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>On Windows, if the data is larger than the buffer specified, the buffer\nis filled with the first part of the data, and <code>peek_from</code> returns the error\n<code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>. The excess data is lost.\nMake sure to always use a sufficiently large buffer to hold the\nmaximum UDP packet size, which can be up to 65536 bytes in size.</p>',
     '<p>在 Windows 上，如果数据大于指定的缓冲区，则缓冲区会被填满数据的开头部分，<code>peek_from</code> 返回错误 <code>WSAEMSGSIZE(10040)</code>。多余的数据将丢失。请务必使用足够大的缓冲区以容纳最大 UDP 数据包（可达 65536 字节）。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receives data from the socket, without removing it from the input queue.\nOn success, returns the sending address of the datagram.</p>',
     '<p>从套接字接收数据，但不会将其从输入队列中移除。成功时返回数据报的发送地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to receive data on the socket without removing it from the input queue.\nOn success, returns the number of bytes read and the sending address of the\ndatagram.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从套接字接收数据，但不会将其从输入队列中移除。成功时返回读取的字节数和数据报的发送地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Retrieve the sender of the data at the head of the input queue, waiting if empty.</p>',
     '<p>检索输入队列头部数据的发送方，如果队列为空则等待。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.peek_from" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::peek_from"><code>peek_from</code></a> with a zero-sized buffer,\nbut suppresses the <code>WSAEMSGSIZE</code> error on Windows and the “invalid argument” error on macOS.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于使用零大小的缓冲区调用 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.peek_from" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::peek_from"><code>peek_from</code></a>，但会抑制 Windows 上的 <code>WSAEMSGSIZE</code> 错误和 macOS 上的 “invalid argument” 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Retrieve the sender of the data at the head of the input queue,\nscheduling a wakeup if empty.</p>',
     '<p>检索输入队列头部数据的发送方，如果队列为空则调度唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.poll_peek_from" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::poll_peek_from"><code>poll_peek_from</code></a> with a zero-sized buffer,\nbut suppresses the <code>WSAEMSGSIZE</code> error on Windows and the “invalid argument” error on macOS.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于使用零大小的缓冲区调用 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.poll_peek_from" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::poll_peek_from"><code>poll_peek_from</code></a>，但会抑制 Windows 上的 <code>WSAEMSGSIZE</code> 错误和 macOS 上的 “invalid argument” 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Try to retrieve the sender of the data at the head of the input queue.</p>',
     '<p>尝试检索输入队列头部数据的发送方。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>SO_BROADCAST</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>SO_BROADCAST</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_broadcast" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_broadcast"><code>set_broadcast</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_broadcast" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_broadcast"><code>set_broadcast</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>SO_BROADCAST</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>SO_BROADCAST</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>When enabled, this socket is allowed to send packets to a broadcast\naddress.</p>',
     '<p>启用后，此套接字将允许向广播地址发送数据包。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IP_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IP_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_loop_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_loop_v4"><code>set_multicast_loop_v4</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_loop_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_loop_v4"><code>set_multicast_loop_v4</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>IP_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IP_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If enabled, multicast packets will be looped back to the local socket.</p>',
     '<p>如果启用，多播数据包将被环回到本地套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IP_MULTICAST_TTL</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IP_MULTICAST_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_ttl_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_ttl_v4"><code>set_multicast_ttl_v4</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_ttl_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_ttl_v4"><code>set_multicast_ttl_v4</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>IP_MULTICAST_TTL</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IP_MULTICAST_TTL</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Indicates the time-to-live value of outgoing multicast packets for\nthis socket. The default value is 1 which means that multicast packets\ndon’t leave the local network unless explicitly requested.</p>',
     '<p>指示此套接字对外发送的多播数据包的生存时间值。默认值为 1，这意味着多播数据包除非明确要求，否则不会离开本地网络。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>IPV6_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的 <code>IPV6_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_loop_v6" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_loop_v6"><code>set_multicast_loop_v6</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_multicast_loop_v6" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_multicast_loop_v6"><code>set_multicast_loop_v6</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>IPV6_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> option for this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>IPV6_MULTICAST_LOOP</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Controls whether this socket sees the multicast packets it sends itself.</p>',
     '<p>控制此套接字是否能看见它自己发送的多播数据包。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_tos_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_tos_v4"><code>set_tos_v4</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.set_tos_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::set_tos_v4"><code>set_tos_v4</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Executes an operation of the <code>IP_ADD_MEMBERSHIP</code> type.</p>',
     '<p>执行 <code>IP_ADD_MEMBERSHIP</code> 类型的操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function specifies a new multicast group for this socket to join.\nThe address must be a valid multicast address, and <code>interface</code> is the\naddress of the local interface with which the system should join the\nmulticast group. If it’s equal to <code>INADDR_ANY</code> then an appropriate\ninterface is chosen by the system.</p>',
     '<p>此函数为此套接字要加入的多播组指定一个新地址。地址必须是有效的多播地址，<code>interface</code> 是系统应使用其加入多播组的本地接口的地址。如果它等于 <code>INADDR_ANY</code>，则系统会选择一个合适的接口。</p>'),
    ('<p>Executes an operation of the <code>IPV6_ADD_MEMBERSHIP</code> type.</p>',
     '<p>执行 <code>IPV6_ADD_MEMBERSHIP</code> 类型的操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function specifies a new multicast group for this socket to join.\nThe address must be a valid multicast address, and <code>interface</code> is the\nindex of the interface to join/leave (or 0 to indicate any interface).</p>',
     '<p>此函数为此套接字要加入的多播组指定一个新地址。地址必须是有效的多播地址，<code>interface</code> 是要加入/离开的接口的索引（或 0 表示任意接口）。</p>'),
    ('<p>Executes an operation of the <code>IP_DROP_MEMBERSHIP</code> type.</p>',
     '<p>执行 <code>IP_DROP_MEMBERSHIP</code> 类型的操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.join_multicast_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::join_multicast_v4"><code>join_multicast_v4</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.join_multicast_v4" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::join_multicast_v4"><code>join_multicast_v4</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Executes an operation of the <code>IPV6_DROP_MEMBERSHIP</code> type.</p>',
     '<p>执行 <code>IPV6_DROP_MEMBERSHIP</code> 类型的操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.join_multicast_v6" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::join_multicast_v6"><code>join_multicast_v6</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.join_multicast_v6" title="method tokio::net::UdpSocket::join_multicast_v6"><code>join_multicast_v6</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to\n<a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::UdpSocket::from_std"><code>UdpSocket::from_std(stream)</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于 <a href="struct.UdpSocket.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::UdpSocket::from_std"><code>UdpSocket::from_std(stream)</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 6: TcpSocket (54 items) ============
    ('<p>A TCP socket that has not yet been converted to a <code>TcpStream</code> or\n<code>TcpListener</code>.</p>',
     '<p>一个尚未转换为 <code>TcpStream</code> 或 <code>TcpListener</code> 的 TCP 套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>TcpSocket</code> wraps an operating system socket and enables the caller to\nconfigure the socket before establishing a TCP connection or accepting\ninbound connections. The caller is able to set socket option and explicitly\nbind the socket with a socket address.</p>',
     '<p><code>TcpSocket</code> 包装一个操作系统套接字，使调用者能够在建立 TCP 连接或接受入站连接之前配置套接字。调用者可以设置套接字选项并使用套接字地址显式绑定套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>The underlying socket is closed when the <code>TcpSocket</code> value is dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>TcpSocket</code> 值被 drop 时，底层套接字将被关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>TcpSocket</code> should only be used directly if the default configuration used\nby <code>TcpStream::connect</code> and <code>TcpListener::bind</code> does not meet the required\nuse case.</p>',
     '<p>只有当 <code>TcpStream::connect</code> 和 <code>TcpListener::bind</code> 使用的默认配置不满足所需的使用场景时，才应直接使用 <code>TcpSocket</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling <code>TcpStream::connect("127.0.0.1:8080")</code> is equivalent to:</p>',
     '<p>调用 <code>TcpStream::connect("127.0.0.1:8080")</code> 等价于：</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling <code>TcpListener::bind("127.0.0.1:8080")</code> is equivalent to:</p>',
     '<p>调用 <code>TcpListener::bind("127.0.0.1:8080")</code> 等价于：</p>'),
    ('<p>Setting socket options not explicitly provided by <code>TcpSocket</code> may be done by\naccessing the <code>RawFd</code>/<code>RawSocket</code> using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/os/fd/trait.AsRawFd.html"><code>AsRawFd</code></a>/<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/os/windows/io/trait.AsRawSocket.html"><code>AsRawSocket</code></a> and\nsetting the option with a crate like <a href="https://docs.rs/socket2/"><code>socket2</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>要设置 <code>TcpSocket</code> 尚未明确提供的套接字选项，可以通过使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/os/fd/trait.AsRawFd.html"><code>AsRawFd</code></a>/<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/os/windows/io/trait.AsRawSocket.html"><code>AsRawSocket</code></a> 访问 <code>RawFd</code>/<code>RawSocket</code>，并使用诸如 <a href="https://docs.rs/socket2/"><code>socket2</code></a> 的 crate 来设置选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new socket configured for IPv4.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个配置为 IPv4 的新套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calls <code>socket(2)</code> with <code>AF_INET</code> and <code>SOCK_STREAM</code>.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code>AF_INET</code> 和 <code>SOCK_STREAM</code> 调用 <code>socket(2)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Create a new IPv4 socket and start listening.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 IPv4 套接字并开始监听。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new socket configured for IPv6.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个配置为 IPv6 的新套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calls <code>socket(2)</code> with <code>AF_INET6</code> and <code>SOCK_STREAM</code>.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code>AF_INET6</code> 和 <code>SOCK_STREAM</code> 调用 <code>socket(2)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Create a new IPv6 socket and start listening.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 IPv6 套接字并开始监听。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets value for the <code>SO_KEEPALIVE</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 <code>SO_KEEPALIVE</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the value of the <code>SO_KEEPALIVE</code> option on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字上 <code>SO_KEEPALIVE</code> 选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Allows the socket to bind to an in-use address.</p>',
     '<p>允许套接字绑定到正在使用的地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Behavior is platform specific. Refer to the target platform’s\ndocumentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>行为因平台而异。有关更多详细信息，请参阅目标平台的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Retrieves the value set for <code>SO_REUSEADDR</code> on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>检索此套接字上 <code>SO_REUSEADDR</code> 的设置值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the size of the TCP send buffer on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 TCP 发送缓冲区的大小。</p>'),
    ('<p>On most operating systems, this sets the <code>SO_SNDBUF</code> socket option.</p>',
     '<p>在大多数操作系统上，这会设置 <code>SO_SNDBUF</code> 套接字选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>On most operating systems, this is the value of the <code>SO_SNDBUF</code> socket\noption.</p>',
     '<p>在大多数操作系统上，这是 <code>SO_SNDBUF</code> 套接字选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that if <a href="#method.set_send_buffer_size"><code>set_send_buffer_size</code></a> has been called on this socket\npreviously, the value returned by this function may not be the same as\nthe argument provided to <code>set_send_buffer_size</code>. This is for the\nfollowing reasons:</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果先前已在此套接字上调用了 <a href="#method.set_send_buffer_size"><code>set_send_buffer_size</code></a>，则此函数返回的值可能与传递给 <code>set_send_buffer_size</code> 的参数不同。原因如下：</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the size of the TCP receive buffer on this socket.</p>',
     '<p>设置此套接字上 TCP 接收缓冲区的大小。</p>'),
    ('<p>On most operating systems, this sets the <code>SO_RCVBUF</code> socket option.</p>',
     '<p>在大多数操作系统上，这会设置 <code>SO_RCVBUF</code> 套接字选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>On most operating systems, this is the value of the <code>SO_RCVBUF</code> socket\noption.</p>',
     '<p>在大多数操作系统上，这是 <code>SO_RCVBUF</code> 套接字选项的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that if <a href="#method.set_recv_buffer_size"><code>set_recv_buffer_size</code></a> has been called on this socket\npreviously, the value returned by this function may not be the same as\nthe argument provided to <code>set_recv_buffer_size</code>. This is for the\nfollowing reasons:</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果先前已在此套接字上调用了 <a href="#method.set_recv_buffer_size"><code>set_recv_buffer_size</code></a>，则此函数返回的值可能与传递给 <code>set_recv_buffer_size</code> 的参数不同。原因如下：</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>SO_LINGER</code> is not specified, and the socket is closed, the system handles the call in a\nway that allows the process to continue as quickly as possible.</p>',
     '<p>如果未指定 <code>SO_LINGER</code>，并且套接字已关闭，系统会以允许进程尽快继续的方式处理此调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This option is deprecated because setting <code>SO_LINGER</code> on a socket used with Tokio is always\nincorrect as it leads to blocking the thread when the socket is closed. For more details,\nplease see:</p>',
     '<p>此选项已被弃用，因为在 Tokio 中使用的套接字上设置 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 始终是错误的，这会导致在套接字关闭时阻塞线程。有关更多详细信息，请参阅：</p>'),
    ('<p>Volumes of communications have been devoted to the intricacies of <code>SO_LINGER</code> versus\nnon-blocking (<code>O_NONBLOCK</code>) sockets. From what I can tell, the final word is: don’t do\nit. Rely on the <code>shutdown()</code>-followed-by-<code>read()</code>-eof technique instead.</p>',
     '<p>关于 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 与非阻塞 (<code>O_NONBLOCK</code>) 套接字之间的复杂性，已有大量通信文献加以讨论。据我所知，最终结论是：不要这样做。而是依赖于 <code>shutdown()</code> 后接 <code>read()</code> 获得 EOF 的技术。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that the special case of setting <code>SO_LINGER</code> to zero does not lead to blocking. Tokio\nprovides <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> for this purpose.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，将 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 设为零的特殊情况不会导致阻塞。Tokio 为此提供了 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This causes the connection to be forcefully aborted (“abortive close”) when the socket is\ndropped or closed. Instead of the normal TCP shutdown handshake (<code>FIN</code>/<code>ACK</code>), a TCP <code>RST</code>\n(reset) segment is sent to the peer, and the socket immediately discards any unsent data\nresiding in the socket send buffer. This prevents the socket from entering the <code>TIME_WAIT</code>\nstate after closing it.</p>',
     '<p>这将导致在套接字被 drop 或关闭时强制中止连接（“abortive close”）。正常的 TCP 关闭握手（<code>FIN</code>/<code>ACK</code>）将不再发生，而是会向对等方发送一个 TCP <code>RST</code>（重置）段，并且套接字会立即丢弃驻留在套接字发送缓冲区中的任何未发送数据。这可以防止套接字在关闭后进入 <code>TIME_WAIT</code> 状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is a destructive action. Any data currently buffered by the OS but not yet transmitted\nwill be lost. The peer will likely receive a “Connection Reset” error rather than a clean\nend-of-stream.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个破坏性操作。操作系统当前已缓冲但尚未传输的任何数据都将丢失。对等方很可能会收到一个 “Connection Reset” 错误，而不是干净的流结束。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the documentation for <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a> for additional details on how\n<code>SO_LINGER</code> works.</p>',
     '<p>有关 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 工作原理的更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> and <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If set, this option disables the Nagle algorithm. This means that segments are always\nsent as soon as possible, even if there is only a small amount of data. When not set,\ndata is buffered until there is a sufficient amount to send out, thereby avoiding\nthe frequent sending of small packets.</p>',
     '<p>如果设置，则此选项禁用 Nagle 算法。这意味着段会尽快发送，即使只有少量数据。当未设置时，数据会被缓冲，直到有足够的数据量再发送，从而避免频繁发送小数据包。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_nodelay" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_nodelay"><code>set_nodelay</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_nodelay" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_nodelay"><code>set_nodelay</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_tos_v4" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_tos_v4"><code>set_tos_v4</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html#method.set_tos_v4" title="method tokio::net::TcpSocket::set_tos_v4"><code>set_tos_v4</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets the local address of this socket.</p>',
     '<p>获取此套接字的本地地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>Will fail on windows if called before <code>bind</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <code>bind</code> 之前调用，在 Windows 上将会失败。</p>'),
    ('<p>Binds the socket to the given address.</p>',
     '<p>将套接字绑定到给定地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>This calls the <code>bind(2)</code> operating-system function. Behavior is\nplatform specific. Refer to the target platform’s documentation for more\ndetails.</p>',
     '<p>此函数调用操作系统的 <code>bind(2)</code> 函数。行为因平台而异。有关更多详细信息，请参阅目标平台的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Bind a socket before listening.</p>',
     '<p>在监听之前绑定套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Establishes a TCP connection with a peer at the specified socket address.</p>',
     '<p>与指定套接字地址处的对等方建立 TCP 连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>TcpSocket</code> is consumed. Once the connection is established, a\nconnected <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> is returned. If the connection fails, the\nencountered error is returned.</p>',
     '<p><code>TcpSocket</code> 会被消费。一旦连接建立，就会返回一个已连接的 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。如果连接失败，则返回遇到的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This calls the <code>connect(2)</code> operating-system function. Behavior is\nplatform specific. Refer to the target platform’s documentation for more\ndetails.</p>',
     '<p>此函数调用操作系统的 <code>connect(2)</code> 函数。行为因平台而异。有关更多详细信息，请参阅目标平台的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Connecting to a peer.</p>', '<p>连接到对等方。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts the socket into a <code>TcpListener</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将套接字转换为 <code>TcpListener</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>backlog</code> defines the maximum number of pending connections are queued\nby the operating system at any given time. Connection are removed from\nthe queue with <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept"><code>TcpListener::accept</code></a>. When the queue is full, the\noperating-system will start rejecting connections.</p>',
     '<p><code>backlog</code> 定义了操作系统在任意时刻允许排队的待处理连接的最大数量。连接通过 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept"><code>TcpListener::accept</code></a> 从队列中移除。当队列已满时，操作系统将开始拒绝连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>This calls the <code>listen(2)</code> operating-system function, marking the socket\nas a passive socket. Behavior is platform specific. Refer to the target\nplatform’s documentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>此函数调用操作系统的 <code>listen(2)</code> 函数，将套接字标记为被动套接字。行为因平台而异。有关更多详细信息，请参阅目标平台的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Create a <code>TcpListener</code>.</p>', '<p>创建一个 <code>TcpListener</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a> into a <code>TcpSocket</code>. The provided\nsocket must not have been connected prior to calling this function. This\nfunction is typically used together with crates such as <a href="https://docs.rs/socket2/"><code>socket2</code></a> to\nconfigure socket options that are not available on <code>TcpSocket</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a> 转换为 <code>TcpSocket</code>。在调用此函数之前，所提供的套接字必须尚未连接。此函数通常与诸如 <a href="https://docs.rs/socket2/"><code>socket2</code></a> 的 crate 一起使用，以配置 <code>TcpSocket</code> 上不可用的套接字选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller is responsible for ensuring that the socket is in\nnon-blocking mode. Otherwise all I/O operations on the socket\nwill block the thread, which will cause unexpected behavior.\nNon-blocking mode can be set using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>调用者负责确保套接字处于非阻塞模式。否则，对套接字的所有 I/O 操作都会阻塞线程，从而导致意外行为。可以使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 设置非阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts a <code>RawSocket</code> to a <code>TcpStream</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>RawSocket</code> 转换为 <code>TcpStream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller is responsible for ensuring that the socket is in\nnon-blocking mode.</p>',
     '<p>调用者负责确保套接字处于非阻塞模式。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 7: Sender (45 items) ============
    ('<p>To convert the <code>Sender</code> into a <code>Sink</code> or use it in a poll function, you can\nuse the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/sync/struct.PollSender.html"><code>PollSender</code></a> utility.</p>',
     '<p>若要将 <code>Sender</code> 转换为 <code>Sink</code> 或在 poll 函数中使用它，可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/sync/struct.PollSender.html"><code>PollSender</code></a> 工具。</p>'),
    ('<p>A successful send occurs when it is determined that the other end of the\nchannel has not hung up already. An unsuccessful send would be one where\nthe corresponding receiver has already been closed. Note that a return\nvalue of <code>Err</code> means that the data will never be received, but a return\nvalue of <code>Ok</code> does not mean that the data will be received. It is\npossible for the corresponding receiver to hang up immediately after\nthis function returns <code>Ok</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当确定通道的另一端尚未挂起时，发送成功。不成功的发送指的是相应的接收端已被关闭的情况。请注意，返回 <code>Err</code> 意味着数据将永远不会被接收，但返回 <code>Ok</code> 并不意味着数据一定会被接收。完全有可能在此函数返回 <code>Ok</code> 后，相应的接收端立即挂起。</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>send</code> is used as the event in a <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a>\nstatement and some other branch completes first, then it is guaranteed\nthat the message was not sent. <strong>However, in that case, the message\nis dropped and will be lost.</strong></p>',
     '<p>如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将 <code>send</code> 用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，那么可以保证该消息未被发送。<strong>但是，在这种情况下，消息会被丢弃并丢失。</strong></p>'),
    ('<p>To avoid losing messages, use <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a> to reserve\ncapacity, then use the returned <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> to send the message.</p>',
     '<p>为避免消息丢失，请使用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a> 预留容量，然后使用返回的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 发送消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel uses a queue to ensure that calls to <code>send</code> and <code>reserve</code>\ncomplete in the order they were requested.  Cancelling a call to\n<code>send</code> makes you lose your place in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此通道使用一个队列来确保对 <code>send</code> 和 <code>reserve</code> 的调用按其请求顺序完成。取消对 <code>send</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method differs from <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> by returning immediately if the channel’s\nbuffer is full or no receiver is waiting to acquire some data. Compared\nwith <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a>, this function has two failure cases instead of one (one for\ndisconnection, one for a full buffer).</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 的区别在于：如果通道的缓冲区已满或没有接收者等待获取数据，则会立即返回。与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 相比，此函数有两种失败情况而不是一种（一种表示断开连接，一种表示缓冲区已满）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel capacity has been reached, i.e., the channel has <code>n</code>\nbuffered values where <code>n</code> is the argument passed to <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a>, then an\nerror is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果已达到通道容量，即通道有 <code>n</code> 个已缓冲的值，其中 <code>n</code> 是传递给 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 的参数，则会返回一个错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Shares the same success and error conditions as <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a>, adding one more\ncondition for an unsuccessful send, which is when the provided timeout has\nelapsed, and there is no capacity available.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 共享相同的成功和错误条件，并增加了一个不成功发送的条件：当所提供的超时已过且没有可用容量时。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the receive half of the channel is closed, either due to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>\nbeing called or the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> having been dropped,\nthe function returns an error. The error includes the value passed to <code>send</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道的接收端已关闭——无论是由于调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 还是 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 被 drop——函数都会返回一个错误。该错误包含传递给 <code>send</code> 的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function panics if it is called outside the context of a Tokio\nruntime <a href="../../runtime/struct.Builder.html#method.enable_time" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_time">with time enabled</a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在没有启用时间功能的 Tokio 运行时上下文之外调用此函数，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is intended for use cases where you are sending from\nsynchronous code to asynchronous code, and will work even if the\nreceiver is not using <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>blocking_recv</code></a> to receive the message.</p>',
     '<p>此方法适用于从同步代码向异步代码发送数据的用例，即使接收端未使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>blocking_recv</code></a> 来接收消息也能正常工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if the channel has been closed. This happens when the\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is dropped, or when the <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a> method is\ncalled.</p>',
     '<p>检查通道是否已关闭。当 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 被 drop 时，或调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a> 方法时，会发生这种情况。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for channel capacity. Once capacity to send one message is\navailable, it is reserved for the caller.</p>',
     '<p>等待通道容量。一旦有一个消息的发送容量可用，就会为调用者预留。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is full, the function waits for the number of unreceived\nmessages to become less than the channel capacity. Capacity to send one\nmessage is reserved for the caller. A <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> is returned to track\nthe reserved capacity. The <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>send</code></a> function on <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> consumes the\nreserved capacity.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已满，此函数会等待未接收消息的数量小于通道容量。发送一个消息的容量将为调用者预留。返回一个 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 来跟踪已预留的容量。<a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>send</code></a> 函数会消费预留的容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel uses a queue to ensure that calls to <code>send</code> and <code>reserve</code>\ncomplete in the order they were requested.  Cancelling a call to\n<code>reserve</code> makes you lose your place in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此通道使用一个队列来确保对 <code>send</code> 和 <code>reserve</code> 的调用按其请求顺序完成。取消对 <code>reserve</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for channel capacity. Once capacity to send <code>n</code> messages is\navailable, it is reserved for the caller.</p>',
     '<p>等待通道容量。一旦有发送 <code>n</code> 条消息的容量可用，就会为调用者预留。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is full or if there are fewer than <code>n</code> permits available, the function waits\nfor the number of unreceived messages to become <code>n</code> less than the channel capacity.\nCapacity to send <code>n</code> message is then reserved for the caller.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已满或可用许可少于 <code>n</code> 个，函数会等待未接收消息的数量小于通道容量 <code>n</code> 个。发送 <code>n</code> 条消息的容量随后将为调用者预留。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> is returned to track the reserved capacity.\nYou can call this <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html" title="trait core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator"><code>Iterator</code></a> until it is exhausted to\nget a <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> and then call <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a>. This function is similar to\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve_many"><code>try_reserve_many</code></a> except it waits for the slots to become available.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> 来跟踪已预留的容量。你可以调用此 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html" title="trait core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator"><code>Iterator</code></a> 直到它耗尽，以获取一个 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a>，然后调用 <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a>。此函数类似于 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve_many"><code>try_reserve_many</code></a>，不同之处在于它会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel uses a queue to ensure that calls to <code>send</code> and <code>reserve_many</code>\ncomplete in the order they were requested. Cancelling a call to\n<code>reserve_many</code> makes you lose your place in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此通道使用一个队列来确保对 <code>send</code> 和 <code>reserve_many</code> 的调用按其请求顺序完成。取消对 <code>reserve_many</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for channel capacity, moving the <code>Sender</code> and returning an owned\npermit. Once capacity to send one message is available, it is reserved\nfor the caller.</p>',
     '<p>等待通道容量，移动 <code>Sender</code> 并返回一个拥有的 permit。一旦有一个消息的发送容量可用，就会为调用者预留。</p>'),
    ('<p>This moves the sender <em>by value</em>, and returns an owned permit that can\nbe used to send a message into the channel. Unlike <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>Sender::reserve</code></a>,\nthis method may be used in cases where the permit must be valid for the\n<code>\'static</code> lifetime. <code>Sender</code>s may be cloned cheaply (<code>Sender::clone</code> is\nessentially a reference count increment, comparable to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.clone" title="method alloc::sync::Arc::clone"><code>Arc::clone</code></a>),\nso when multiple <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>s are needed or the <code>Sender</code> cannot be\nmoved, it can be cloned prior to calling <code>reserve_owned</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法按值移动 sender，并返回一个可用于向通道发送消息的拥有的 permit。与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>Sender::reserve</code></a> 不同，此方法可用于 permit 必须对 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期有效的场景。<code>Sender</code> 可以廉价地克隆（<code>Sender::clone</code> 本质上是一个引用计数增加，可与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.clone" title="method alloc::sync::Arc::clone"><code>Arc::clone</code></a> 媲美），因此在需要多个 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 或无法移动 <code>Sender</code> 时，可以在调用 <code>reserve_owned</code> 之前对其进行克隆。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is full, the function waits for the number of unreceived\nmessages to become less than the channel capacity. Capacity to send one\nmessage is reserved for the caller. An <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> is returned to\ntrack the reserved capacity. The <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit::send"><code>send</code></a> function on <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>\nconsumes the reserved capacity.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已满，此函数会等待未接收消息的数量小于通道容量。发送一个消息的容量将为调用者预留。返回一个 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 来跟踪已预留的容量。<a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit::send"><code>send</code></a> 函数会消费预留的容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Dropping the <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> without sending a message releases the\ncapacity back to the channel.</p>',
     '<p>在不发送消息的情况下 drop <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 会将容量释放回通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel uses a queue to ensure that calls to <code>send</code> and <code>reserve</code>\ncomplete in the order they were requested.  Cancelling a call to\n<code>reserve_owned</code> makes you lose your place in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此通道使用一个队列来确保对 <code>send</code> 和 <code>reserve</code> 的调用按其请求顺序完成。取消对 <code>reserve_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sending a message using an <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>使用 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 发送消息：</p>'),
    ('<p>When multiple <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>s are needed, or the sender cannot be moved\nby value, it can be inexpensively cloned before calling <code>reserve_owned</code>:</p>',
     '<p>当需要多个 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>，或者 sender 无法按值移动时，可以在调用 <code>reserve_owned</code> 之前廉价地克隆它：</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to acquire a slot in the channel without waiting for the slot to become\navailable.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在通道中获取一个槽位，而不会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is full this function will return <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError"><code>TrySendError</code></a>, otherwise\nif there is a slot available it will return a <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> that will then allow you\nto <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>send</code></a> on the channel with a guaranteed slot. This function is similar to\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a> except it does not await for the slot to become available.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已满，此函数将返回 <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError"><code>TrySendError</code></a>；否则，如果有可用槽位，它将返回一个 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a>，从而允许你在保证有槽位的情况下在通道上 <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>send</code></a>。此函数类似于 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a>，不同之处在于它不会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to acquire <code>n</code> slots in the channel without waiting for the slot to become\navailable.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在通道中获取 <code>n</code> 个槽位，而不会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> is returned to track the reserved capacity.\nYou can call this <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html" title="trait core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator"><code>Iterator</code></a> until it is exhausted to\nget a <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> and then call <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a>. This function is similar to\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_many"><code>reserve_many</code></a> except it does not await for the slots to become available.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 <a href="struct.PermitIterator.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::PermitIterator"><code>PermitIterator</code></a> 来跟踪已预留的容量。你可以调用此 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html" title="trait core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator"><code>Iterator</code></a> 直到它耗尽，以获取一个 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a>，然后调用 <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a>。此函数类似于 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_many"><code>reserve_many</code></a>，不同之处在于它不会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are fewer than <code>n</code> permits available on the channel, then\nthis function will return a <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html#variant.Full" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError::Full"><code>TrySendError::Full</code></a>. If the channel is closed\nthis function will return a <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError::Closed"><code>TrySendError::Closed</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道上可用许可少于 <code>n</code> 个，则此函数将返回 <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html#variant.Full" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError::Full"><code>TrySendError::Full</code></a>。如果通道已关闭，此函数将返回 <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError::Closed"><code>TrySendError::Closed</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to acquire a slot in the channel without waiting for the slot to become\navailable, returning an owned permit.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在通道中获取一个槽位，而不会等待槽位变为可用，并返回一个拥有的 permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>This moves the sender <em>by value</em>, and returns an owned permit that can\nbe used to send a message into the channel. Unlike <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve"><code>Sender::try_reserve</code></a>,\nthis method may be used in cases where the permit must be valid for the\n<code>\'static</code> lifetime.  <code>Sender</code>s may be cloned cheaply (<code>Sender::clone</code> is\nessentially a reference count increment, comparable to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.clone" title="method alloc::sync::Arc::clone"><code>Arc::clone</code></a>),\nso when multiple <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>s are needed or the <code>Sender</code> cannot be\nmoved, it can be cloned prior to calling <code>try_reserve_owned</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法按值移动 sender，并返回一个可用于向通道发送消息的拥有的 permit。与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve"><code>Sender::try_reserve</code></a> 不同，此方法可用于 permit 必须对 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期有效的场景。<code>Sender</code> 可以廉价地克隆（<code>Sender::clone</code> 本质上是一个引用计数增加，可与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.clone" title="method alloc::sync::Arc::clone"><code>Arc::clone</code></a> 媲美），因此在需要多个 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 或无法移动 <code>Sender</code> 时，可以在调用 <code>try_reserve_owned</code> 之前对其进行克隆。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is full this function will return a <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError"><code>TrySendError</code></a>.\nSince the sender is taken by value, the <code>TrySendError</code> returned in this\ncase contains the sender, so that it may be used again. Otherwise, if\nthere is a slot available, this method will return an <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>\nthat can then be used to <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit::send"><code>send</code></a> on the channel with a guaranteed slot.\nThis function is similar to  <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_owned"><code>reserve_owned</code></a> except it does not await\nfor the slot to become available.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已满，此函数将返回 <a href="error/enum.TrySendError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TrySendError"><code>TrySendError</code></a>。由于 sender 是按值获取的，因此在这种情况下返回的 <code>TrySendError</code> 包含 sender，以便可以再次使用。否则，如果有可用槽位，此方法将返回一个 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a>，然后可用于在保证有槽位的情况下在通道上 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit::send"><code>send</code></a>。此函数类似于 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_owned"><code>reserve_owned</code></a>，不同之处在于它不会等待槽位变为可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Dropping the <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> without sending a message releases the capacity back\nto the channel.</p>',
     '<p>在不发送消息的情况下 drop <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 会将容量释放回通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>The capacity goes down when sending a value by calling <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> or by reserving capacity\nwith <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a>. The capacity goes up when values are received by the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>.\nThis is distinct from <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a>, which always returns buffer capacity initially\nspecified when calling <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a></p>',
     '<p>容量在通过调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 发送值或通过 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>reserve</code></a> 预留容量时减少。容量在 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 接收值时增加。这与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> 不同，后者始终返回最初调用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 时指定的缓冲区容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts the <code>Sender</code> to a <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> that does not count\ntowards RAII semantics, i.e. if all <code>Sender</code> instances of the\nchannel were dropped and only <code>WeakSender</code> instances remain,\nthe channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>Sender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a>，该 <code>WeakSender</code> 不计入 RAII 语义，即如果通道的所有 <code>Sender</code> 实例都已 drop，仅剩 <code>WeakSender</code> 实例，则通道将关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>The maximum capacity is the buffer capacity initially specified when calling\n<a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a>. This is distinct from <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a>, which returns the <em>current</em>\navailable buffer capacity: as messages are sent and received, the\nvalue returned by <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> will go up or down, whereas the value\nreturned by <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> will remain constant.</p>',
     '<p>最大容量是最初调用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 时指定的缓冲区容量。这与 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> 不同，后者返回<em>当前</em>可用的缓冲区容量：随着消息的发送和接收，<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> 返回的值会上下波动，而 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> 返回的值则保持不变。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is closed, the function returns a <a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已关闭，此函数将返回 <a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends a value, waiting until there is capacity.</p>', '<p>发送一个值，一直等待直到有可用容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>In the following example, each call to <code>send</code> will block until the\npreviously sent value was received.</p>',
     '<p>在以下示例中，每次调用 <code>send</code> 都会阻塞，直到先前发送的值被接收。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to immediately send a message on this <code>Sender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在此 <code>Sender</code> 上立即发送一条消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends a value, waiting until there is capacity, but only for a limited time.</p>',
     '<p>发送一个值，一直等待直到有可用容量，但仅限于有限的时间。</p>'),
    ('<p>In the following example, each call to <code>send_timeout</code> will block until the\npreviously sent value was received, unless the timeout has elapsed.</p>',
     '<p>在以下示例中，每次调用 <code>send_timeout</code> 都会阻塞，直到先前发送的值被接收，除非超时已过。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blocking send to call outside of asynchronous contexts.</p>',
     '<p>用于在异步上下文之外调用的阻塞发送。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 8: Semaphore (41 items) ============
    ('<p>Counting semaphore performing asynchronous permit acquisition.</p>',
     '<p>执行异步许可获取的计数信号量。</p>'),
    ('<p>A semaphore maintains a set of permits. Permits are used to synchronize\naccess to a shared resource. A semaphore differs from a mutex in that it\ncan allow more than one concurrent caller to access the shared resource at a\ntime.</p>',
     '<p>信号量维护一组许可。许可用于同步对共享资源的访问。信号量与互斥锁的区别在于，它允许一个以上的并发调用者同时访问共享资源。</p>'),
    ('<p>When <code>acquire</code> is called and the semaphore has remaining permits, the\nfunction immediately returns a permit. However, if no remaining permits are\navailable, <code>acquire</code> (asynchronously) waits until an outstanding permit is\ndropped. At this point, the freed permit is assigned to the caller.</p>',
     '<p>当调用 <code>acquire</code> 并且信号量有剩余许可时，函数会立即返回一个许可。但是，如果没有剩余许可可用，<code>acquire</code> 会（异步地）等待，直到某个未完成的许可被 drop。此时，释放的许可将分配给调用者。</p>'),
    ('<p>This <code>Semaphore</code> is fair, which means that permits are given out in the order\nthey were requested. This fairness is also applied when <code>acquire_many</code> gets\ninvolved, so if a call to <code>acquire_many</code> at the front of the queue requests\nmore permits than currently available, this can prevent a call to <code>acquire</code>\nfrom completing, even if the semaphore has enough permits complete the call\nto <code>acquire</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此 <code>Semaphore</code> 是公平的，这意味着许可按请求顺序发放。这种公平性也适用于涉及 <code>acquire_many</code> 的情况，因此如果队列前端的 <code>acquire_many</code> 调用请求的许可数超过当前可用的数量，即使信号量有足够的许可完成该 <code>acquire</code> 调用，也会阻止其完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>To use the <code>Semaphore</code> in a poll function, you can use the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/sync/struct.PollSemaphore.html"><code>PollSemaphore</code></a>\nutility.</p>',
     '<p>要在 poll 函数中使用 <code>Semaphore</code>，可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/sync/struct.PollSemaphore.html"><code>PollSemaphore</code></a> 工具。</p>'),
    ('<p>Most operating systems have limits on the number of open file\nhandles. Even in systems without explicit limits, resource constraints\nimplicitly set an upper bound on the number of open files. If your\nprogram attempts to open a large number of files and exceeds this\nlimit, it will result in an error.</p>',
     '<p>大多数操作系统对打开的文件句柄数量有限制。即使在没有显式限制的系统中，资源约束也会隐式设置打开文件数量的上限。如果你的程序尝试打开大量文件并超出此限制，则会导致错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example uses a Semaphore with 100 permits. By acquiring a permit from\nthe Semaphore before accessing a file, you ensure that your program opens\nno more than 100 files at a time. When trying to open the 101st\nfile, the program will wait until a permit becomes available before\nproceeding to open another file.</p>',
     '<p>此示例使用具有 100 个许可的 Semaphore。通过在访问文件之前从 Semaphore 获取许可，你可以确保程序一次最多打开 100 个文件。当尝试打开第 101 个文件时，程序将等待直到有许可可用，然后再继续打开另一个文件。</p>'),
    ('<p>In some scenarios, it might be required to limit the number of outgoing\nrequests being sent in parallel. This could be due to limits of a consumed\nAPI or the network resources of the system the application is running on.</p>',
     '<p>在某些情况下，可能需要限制并行发送的传出请求的数量。这可能是由于所使用 API 的限制或应用程序所运行系统的网络资源限制。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example uses an <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code> with 10 permits. Each task spawned is\ngiven a reference to the semaphore by cloning the <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code>. Before\na task sends a request, it must acquire a permit from the semaphore by\ncalling <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire"><code>Semaphore::acquire</code></a>. This ensures that at most 10 requests are\nsent in parallel at any given time. After a task has sent a request, it\ndrops the permit to allow other tasks to send requests.</p>',
     '<p>此示例使用具有 10 个许可的 <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code>。通过克隆 <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code>，每个生成的任务都会获得对信号量的引用。在任务发送请求之前，它必须通过调用 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire"><code>Semaphore::acquire</code></a> 从信号量获取许可。这确保了在任何给定时间最多并行发送 10 个请求。任务发送请求后，它会 drop 该许可以允许其他任务发送请求。</p>'),
    ('<p>Similar to limiting the number of simultaneously opened files, network handles\nare a limited resource. Allowing an unbounded amount of requests to be processed\ncould result in a denial-of-service, among many other issues.</p>',
     '<p>与限制同时打开的文件数量类似，网络句柄也是一种有限的资源。允许无限制地处理请求可能会导致拒绝服务，以及许多其他问题。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example uses an <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code> instead of a global variable.\nTo limit the number of requests that can be processed at the time,\nwe acquire a permit for each task before spawning it. Once acquired,\na new task is spawned; and once finished, the permit is dropped inside\nof the task to allow others to spawn. Permits must be acquired via\n<a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire_owned"><code>Semaphore::acquire_owned</code></a> to be movable across the task boundary.\n(Since our semaphore is not a global variable — if it was, then <code>acquire</code> would be enough.)</p>',
     '<p>此示例使用 <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code> 而不是全局变量。为了限制可以同时处理的请求数，我们在生成每个任务之前为其获取一个许可。一旦获取，就会生成一个新任务；任务完成后，许可会在任务内部被 drop，以允许其他任务生成。许可必须通过 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire_owned"><code>Semaphore::acquire_owned</code></a> 获取，才能跨任务边界移动。（因为我们的信号量不是全局变量——如果是的话，那么 <code>acquire</code> 就足够了。）</p>'),
    ('<p>By default, Rust runs tests in the same file in parallel. However, in some\ncases, running two tests in parallel may lead to problems. For example, this\ncan happen when tests use the same database.</p>',
     '<p>默认情况下，Rust 在同一文件中并行运行测试。但是，在某些情况下，并行运行两个测试可能会导致问题。例如，当测试使用同一数据库时，可能会发生这种情况。</p>'),
    ('<p>In this example, <code>test_insert</code> and <code>test_update</code> need to run in sequence to\nwork, but it doesn’t matter which test runs first. We can leverage a\nsemaphore with a single permit to address this challenge.</p>',
     '<p>在此示例中，<code>test_insert</code> 和 <code>test_update</code> 需要按顺序运行才能工作，但哪个测试先运行并不重要。我们可以利用具有单个许可的信号量来解决此挑战。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example showcases the <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.add_permits" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::add_permits"><code>add_permits</code></a> and <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html#method.forget" title="method tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit::forget"><code>SemaphorePermit::forget</code></a> methods.</p>',
     '<p>此示例展示了 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.add_permits" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::add_permits"><code>add_permits</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html#method.forget" title="method tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit::forget"><code>SemaphorePermit::forget</code></a> 方法。</p>'),
    ('<p>Many applications and systems have constraints on the rate at which certain\noperations should occur. Exceeding this rate can result in suboptimal\nperformance or even errors.</p>',
     '<p>许多应用程序和系统对某些操作的执行速率有限制。超过此速率可能导致性能不佳甚至出错。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example implements rate limiting using a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Token_bucket">token bucket</a>. A token bucket is a form of rate\nlimiting that doesn’t kick in immediately, to allow for short bursts of incoming requests that\narrive at the same time.</p>',
     '<p>此示例使用<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Token_bucket">令牌桶</a>实现速率限制。令牌桶是一种速率限制形式，它不会立即生效，以允许同时到达的请求出现短时突发。</p>'),
    ('<p>With a token bucket, each incoming request consumes a token, and the tokens are refilled at a\ncertain rate that defines the rate limit. When a burst of requests arrives, tokens are\nimmediately given out until the bucket is empty. Once the bucket is empty, requests will have to\nwait for new tokens to be added.</p>',
     '<p>使用令牌桶时，每个传入的请求都会消耗一个令牌，并且令牌以定义速率限制的特定速率进行补充。当请求突发到达时，令牌会立即发放，直到桶空为止。一旦桶为空，请求将不得不等待新令牌的添加。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike the example that limits how many requests can be handled at the same time, we do not add\ntokens back when we finish handling a request. Instead, tokens are added only by a timer task.</p>',
     '<p>与限制可以同时处理的请求数量的示例不同，我们在处理完一个请求后不会将令牌添加回去。相反，令牌仅由计时器任务添加。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that this implementation is suboptimal when the duration is small, because it consumes a\nlot of cpu constantly looping and sleeping.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，当持续时间很短时，此实现并非最优，因为它会不断循环和休眠，从而消耗大量 CPU。</p>'),
    ('<p>The maximum number of permits which a semaphore can hold. It is <code>usize::MAX &gt;&gt; 3</code>.</p>',
     '<p>信号量可以持有的最大许可数。它是 <code>usize::MAX &gt;&gt; 3</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>Semaphore</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Semaphore::new"><code>Semaphore::new</code></a> should be used to\ncreate an instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定特性</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>Semaphore</code> 将不会被检测。因此，它将不会出现在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Semaphore::new"><code>Semaphore::new</code></a> 创建一个已检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>The maximum number of permits is <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>, and this function will panic if the limit is exceeded.</p>',
     '<p>最大许可数为 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>，如果超出此限制，此函数将 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Decrease a semaphore’s permits by a maximum of <code>n</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将信号量的许可最多减少 <code>n</code> 个。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are insufficient permits and it’s not possible to reduce by <code>n</code>,\nreturn the number of permits that were actually reduced.</p>',
     '<p>如果许可不足且无法减少 <code>n</code> 个，则返回实际减少的许可数。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the semaphore has been closed, this returns an <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, this returns a <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the\nacquired permit.</p>',
     '<p>如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>。否则，返回一个 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a>，表示已获取的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute permits in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>acquire</code> makes you lose your place\nin the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发许可。取消对 <code>acquire</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the semaphore has been closed, this returns an <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>.\nOtherwise, this returns a <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the\nacquired permits.</p>',
     '<p>如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="struct.AcquireError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::AcquireError"><code>AcquireError</code></a>。否则，返回一个 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a>，表示已获取的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute permits in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>acquire_many</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发许可。取消对 <code>acquire_many</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the semaphore has been closed, this returns a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>\nand a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a> if there are no permits left. Otherwise,\nthis returns a <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the acquired permits.</p>',
     '<p>如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>；如果没有剩余许可，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a>。否则，返回一个 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a>，表示已获取的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the semaphore has been closed, this returns a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>\nand a <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a> if there are not enough permits left.\nOtherwise, this returns a <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> representing the acquired permits.</p>',
     '<p>如果信号量已关闭，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::Closed"><code>TryAcquireError::Closed</code></a>；如果没有足够的剩余许可，则返回 <a href="enum.TryAcquireError.html#variant.NoPermits" title="variant tokio::sync::TryAcquireError::NoPermits"><code>TryAcquireError::NoPermits</code></a>。否则，返回一个 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a>，表示已获取的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute permits in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>acquire_owned</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发许可。取消对 <code>acquire_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute permits in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>acquire_many_owned</code> makes you lose\nyour place in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发许可。取消对 <code>acquire_many_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This prevents the semaphore from issuing new permits and notifies all pending waiters.</p>',
     '<p>这会阻止信号量发放新的许可，并通知所有挂起的等待者。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the current number of available permits.</p>', '<p>返回当前可用的许可数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Adds <code>n</code> new permits to the semaphore.</p>', '<p>向信号量添加 <code>n</code> 个新许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>Basic usage:</p>', '<p>基本用法：</p>'),
    ('<p>Closes the semaphore.</p>', '<p>关闭信号量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the semaphore is closed</p>', '<p>如果信号量已关闭，则返回 true</p>'),
    ('<p>Panics if <code>permits</code> exceeds <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>permits</code> 超过 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consider the following scenario:</p>', '<p>考虑以下场景：</p>'),
    ('<p>Exceeding this limit typically results in a panic.</p>', '<p>超出此限制通常会导致 panic。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 9: TcpStream (40 items) ============
    ('<p>A TCP stream can either be created by connecting to an endpoint, via the\n<a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.connect" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpStream::connect"><code>connect</code></a> method, or by <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept">accepting</a> a connection from a <a href="struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpListener">listener</a>. A\nTCP stream can also be created via the <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a> type.</p>',
     '<p>TCP 流可以通过 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.connect" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpStream::connect"><code>connect</code></a> 方法连接到端点来创建，也可以通过 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept">接受</a>来自 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpListener">监听器</a> 的连接来创建。也可以通过 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a> 类型创建 TCP 流。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reading and writing to a <code>TcpStream</code> is usually done using the\nconvenience methods found on the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> and <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a>\ntraits.</p>',
     '<p>对 <code>TcpStream</code> 的读写通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> 和 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait 上的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>To shut down the stream in the write direction, you can call the\n<a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::shutdown"><code>shutdown()</code></a> method. This will cause the other peer to receive a read of\nlength 0, indicating that no more data will be sent. This only closes\nthe stream in one direction.</p>',
     '<p>要在写入方向关闭流，可以调用 <a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::shutdown"><code>shutdown()</code></a> 方法。这将导致对等方收到长度为 0 的读取，表示不会再发送更多数据。这只会单向关闭流。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>addr</code> is an address of the remote host. Anything which implements the\n<a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait can be supplied as the address.  If <code>addr</code>\nyields multiple addresses, connect will be attempted with each of the\naddresses until a connection is successful. If none of the addresses\nresult in a successful connection, the error returned from the last\nconnection attempt (the last address) is returned.</p>',
     '<p><code>addr</code> 是远程主机的地址。任何实现了 <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait 的类型都可以作为地址提供。如果 <code>addr</code> 产生多个地址，则会依次尝试与每个地址进行连接，直到连接成功。如果没有任何地址导致成功连接，则返回最后一次连接尝试（最后一个地址）的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>To configure the socket before connecting, you can use the <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a>\ntype.</p>',
     '<p>要在连接之前配置套接字，可以使用 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a> 类型。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates new <code>TcpStream</code> from a <code>std::net::TcpStream</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>std::net::TcpStream</code> 创建一个新的 <code>TcpStream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended to be used to wrap a TCP stream from the\nstandard library in the Tokio equivalent.</p>',
     '<p>此函数旨在用于将标准库的 TCP 流包装为 Tokio 等价物。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller is responsible for ensuring that the stream is in\nnon-blocking mode. Otherwise all I/O operations on the stream\nwill block the thread, which will cause unexpected behavior.\nNon-blocking mode can be set using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>调用者负责确保流处于非阻塞模式。否则，对流的所有 I/O 操作都会阻塞线程，从而导致意外行为。可以使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 设置非阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Turns a <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>tokio::net::TcpStream</code></a> into a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>tokio::net::TcpStream</code></a> 转换为 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The returned <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a> will have nonblocking mode set as <code>true</code>.\nUse <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> to change the blocking mode if needed.</p>',
     '<p>返回的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpStream"><code>std::net::TcpStream</code></a> 将 nonblocking 模式设置为 <code>true</code>。如果需要，使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpStream::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 更改阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_peek</code>, <code>poll_read</code> or\n<code>poll_read_ready</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the\nmost recent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup. (However,\n<code>poll_write</code> retains a second, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_peek</code>、<code>poll_read</code> 或 <code>poll_read_ready</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_write</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个 waker。）</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <code>try_read()</code> or <code>try_write()</code>. It\ncan be used to concurrently read / write to the same socket on a single\ntask without splitting the socket.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <code>try_read()</code> 或 <code>try_write()</code> 配对使用。它可用于在单个任务上同时对同一套接字进行读/写，而无需拆分套接字。</p>'),
    ('<p>Concurrently read and write to the stream on the same task without\nsplitting.</p>',
     '<p>在单个任务上同时对流进行读写，而无需拆分。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the tcp stream is not currently ready for reading, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the tcp\nstream becomes ready for reading, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the\nwaker.</p>',
     '<p>如果 tcp 流当前尚未准备好读取，此方法将存储从所提供 <code>Context</code> 克隆的 <code>Waker</code>。当 tcp 流准备好读取时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to <code>poll_read_ready</code>, <code>poll_read</code> or\n<code>poll_peek</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most\nrecent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup. (However,\n<code>poll_write_ready</code> retains a second, independent waker.)</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_read_ready</code>、<code>poll_read</code> 或 <code>poll_peek</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度接收唤醒。（但是，<code>poll_write_ready</code> 保留了一个独立的第二个 waker。）</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建并固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持一次从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序被复制以填充每个缓冲区，最后一个写入的缓冲区可能仅部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用连接缓冲区对 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the tcp stream is not currently ready for writing, this method will\nstore a clone of the <code>Waker</code> from the provided <code>Context</code>. When the tcp\nstream becomes ready for writing, <code>Waker::wake</code> will be called on the\nwaker.</p>',
     '<p>如果 tcp 流当前尚未准备好写入，此方法将存储从所提供 <code>Context</code> 克隆的 <code>Waker</code>。当 tcp 流准备好写入时，将在该 waker 上调用 <code>Waker::wake</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable</code></a> 创建并固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable</code></a>，因为它支持一次从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Try to write a buffer to the stream, returning how many bytes were\nwritten.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将缓冲区写入流，返回已写入的字节数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possibly being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序从每个缓冲区写入，最后读取的缓冲区可能仅被部分消费。此方法的行为等效于使用连接缓冲区对 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>, <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>、<a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数一起使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Successive calls return the same data. This is accomplished by passing\n<code>MSG_PEEK</code> as a flag to the underlying <code>recv</code> system call.</p>',
     '<p>连续调用将返回相同的数据。这是通过将 <code>MSG_PEEK</code> 作为标志传递给底层 <code>recv</code> 系统调用来实现的。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If the method is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that no peek was performed, and\nthat <code>buf</code> has not been modified.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将此方法用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，那么可以保证未执行任何 peek 操作，并且 <code>buf</code> 未经修改。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nodelay" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_nodelay"><code>set_nodelay</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_nodelay" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_nodelay"><code>set_nodelay</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If set, this option disables the Nagle algorithm. This means that\nsegments are always sent as soon as possible, even if there is only a\nsmall amount of data. When not set, data is buffered until there is a\nsufficient amount to send out, thereby avoiding the frequent sending of\nsmall packets.</p>',
     '<p>如果设置，则此选项禁用 Nagle 算法。这意味着段会尽快发送，即使只有少量数据。当未设置时，数据会被缓冲，直到有足够的数据量再发送，从而避免频繁发送小数据包。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> and <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>SO_LINGER</code> is not specified, and the stream is closed, the system handles the call in a\nway that allows the process to continue as quickly as possible.</p>',
     '<p>如果未指定 <code>SO_LINGER</code>，并且流已关闭，系统会以允许进程尽快继续的方式处理此调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This option is deprecated because setting <code>SO_LINGER</code> on a socket used with Tokio is\nalways incorrect as it leads to blocking the thread when the socket is closed. For more\ndetails, please see:</p>',
     '<p>此选项已被弃用，因为在 Tokio 中使用的套接字上设置 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 始终是错误的，这会导致在套接字关闭时阻塞线程。有关更多详细信息，请参阅：</p>'),
    ('<p>Volumes of communications have been devoted to the intricacies of <code>SO_LINGER</code> versus\nnon-blocking (<code>O_NONBLOCK</code>) sockets. From what I can tell, the final word is: don’t\ndo it. Rely on the <code>shutdown()</code>-followed-by-<code>read()</code>-eof technique instead.</p>',
     '<p>关于 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 与非阻塞 (<code>O_NONBLOCK</code>) 套接字之间的复杂性，已有大量通信文献加以讨论。据我所知，最终结论是：不要这样做。而是依赖于 <code>shutdown()</code> 后接 <code>read()</code> 获得 EOF 的技术。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that the special case of setting <code>SO_LINGER</code> to zero does not lead to blocking.\nTokio provides <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a> for this purpose.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，将 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 设为零的特殊情况不会导致阻塞。Tokio 为此提供了 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_zero_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_zero_linger"><code>set_zero_linger</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This causes the connection to be forcefully aborted (“abortive close”) when the socket\nis dropped or closed. Instead of the normal TCP shutdown handshake (<code>FIN</code>/<code>ACK</code>), a TCP\n<code>RST</code> (reset) segment is sent to the peer, and the socket immediately discards any\nunsent data residing in the socket send buffer. This prevents the socket from entering\nthe <code>TIME_WAIT</code> state after closing it.</p>',
     '<p>这将导致在套接字被 drop 或关闭时强制中止连接（“abortive close”）。正常的 TCP 关闭握手（<code>FIN</code>/<code>ACK</code>）将不再发生，而是会向对等方发送一个 TCP <code>RST</code>（重置）段，并且套接字会立即丢弃驻留在套接字发送缓冲区中的任何未发送数据。这可以防止套接字在关闭后进入 <code>TIME_WAIT</code> 状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is a destructive action. Any data currently buffered by the OS but not yet\ntransmitted will be lost. The peer will likely receive a “Connection Reset” error\nrather than a clean end-of-stream.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个破坏性操作。操作系统当前已缓冲但尚未传输的任何数据都将丢失。对等方很可能会收到一个 “Connection Reset” 错误，而不是干净的流结束。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the documentation for <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a> for additional details on\nhow <code>SO_LINGER</code> works.</p>',
     '<p>有关 <code>SO_LINGER</code> 工作原理的更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_linger" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_linger"><code>set_linger</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is more efficient than <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a>, but the halves cannot be\nmoved into independently spawned tasks.</p>',
     '<p>此方法比 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a> 更高效，但拆分出的两半不能移动到独立生成的任务中。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a>, the owned halves can be moved to separate tasks, however\nthis comes at the cost of a heap allocation.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a> 不同，拥有的两半可以移动到单独的任务中，但这是以堆分配为代价的。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Note:</strong> Dropping the write half will shut down the write half of the TCP\nstream. This is equivalent to calling <a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::shutdown"><code>shutdown()</code></a> on the <code>TcpStream</code>.</p>',
     '<p><strong>注意：</strong> drop 写半部将关闭 TCP 流的写半部。这等效于在 <code>TcpStream</code> 上调用 <a href="fn@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::shutdown"><code>shutdown()</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to\n<a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpStream::from_std"><code>TcpStream::from_std(stream)</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpStream::from_std"><code>TcpStream::from_std(stream)</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Opens a TCP connection to a remote host.</p>', '<p>打开到远程主机的 TCP 连接。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 10: runtime/index (40 items) ============
    ('<p>Unlike other Rust programs, asynchronous applications require runtime\nsupport. In particular, the following runtime services are necessary:</p>',
     '<p>与其他 Rust 程序不同，异步应用程序需要运行时支持。特别是，需要以下运行时服务：</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio’s <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> bundles all of these services as a single type, allowing\nthem to be started, shut down, and configured together. However, often it is\nnot required to configure a <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> manually, and a user may just use the\n<a href="../attr.main.html"><code>tokio::main</code></a> attribute macro, which creates a <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> under the hood.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 的 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 将所有这些服务捆绑为单一类型，允许它们一起启动、关闭和配置。然而，通常不需要手动配置 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>，用户可以直接使用 <a href="../attr.main.html"><code>tokio::main</code></a> 属性宏，它会在底层创建一个 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Here is the rules of thumb to choose the right runtime for your application.</p>',
     '<p>以下是为你的应用程序选择合适运行时的经验法则。</p>'),
    ('<p>The above decision tree is not exhaustive. there are other factors that\nmay influence your decision.</p>',
     '<p>上述决策树并不详尽。还有其他因素可能会影响你的决策。</p>'),
    ('<p>See <a href="https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging">https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging</a> for details.</p>',
     '<p>有关详细信息，请参阅 <a href="https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging">https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The tokio runtime is not NUMA (Non-Uniform Memory Access) aware.\nYou may want to start multiple runtimes instead of a single runtime\nfor better performance on NUMA systems.</p>',
     '<p>tokio 运行时不支持 NUMA（非一致性内存访问）。在 NUMA 系统上，为了获得更好的性能，你可能希望启动多个运行时而不是单个运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>When no fine tuning is required, the <a href="../attr.main.html"><code>tokio::main</code></a> attribute macro can be\nused.</p>',
     '<p>当不需要微调时，可以使用 <a href="../attr.main.html"><code>tokio::main</code></a> 属性宏。</p>'),
    ('<p>From within the context of the runtime, additional tasks are spawned using\nthe <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> function. Futures spawned using this function will be\nexecuted on the same thread pool used by the <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>在运行时上下文中，可以使用 <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> 函数生成其他任务。使用此函数生成的 future 将在 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 使用的同一线程池上执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> instance can also be used directly.</p>',
     '<p>也可以直接使用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio provides multiple task scheduling strategies, suitable for different\napplications. The <a href="struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder">runtime builder</a> or <code>#[tokio::main]</code> attribute may be\nused to select which scheduler to use.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 提供多种任务调度策略，适用于不同的应用程序。<a href="struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder">运行时构建器</a>或 <code>#[tokio::main]</code> 属性可用于选择要使用的调度器。</p>'),
    ('<p>The multi-thread scheduler executes futures on a <em>thread pool</em>, using a\nwork-stealing strategy. By default, it will start a worker thread for each\nCPU core available on the system. This tends to be the ideal configuration\nfor most applications. The multi-thread scheduler requires the <code>rt-multi-thread</code>\nfeature flag, and is selected by default:</p>',
     '<p>多线程调度器在<em>线程池</em>上使用工作窃取策略执行 future。默认情况下，它会为系统上每个可用的 CPU 核心启动一个工作线程。这往往是大多数应用程序的理想配置。多线程调度器需要 <code>rt-multi-thread</code> 特性标志，并且默认选中：</p>'),
    ('<p>Most applications should use the multi-thread scheduler, except in some\nniche use-cases, such as when running only a single thread is required.</p>',
     '<p>除了一些小众用例（例如只需要运行单个线程时），大多数应用程序应使用多线程调度器。</p>'),
    ('<p>The current-thread scheduler provides a <em>single-threaded</em> future executor.\nAll tasks will be created and executed on the current thread. This requires\nthe <code>rt</code> feature flag.</p>',
     '<p>当前线程调度器提供一个<em>单线程</em>的 future 执行器。所有任务都将创建并在当前线程上执行。这需要 <code>rt</code> 特性标志。</p>'),
    ('<p>When configuring a runtime by hand, no resource drivers are enabled by\ndefault. In this case, attempting to use networking types or time types will\nfail. In order to enable these types, the resource drivers must be enabled.\nThis is done with <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_io" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_io"><code>Builder::enable_io</code></a> and <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_time" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_time"><code>Builder::enable_time</code></a>. As a\nshorthand, <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_all" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_all"><code>Builder::enable_all</code></a> enables both resource drivers.</p>',
     '<p>手动配置运行时时，默认不启用任何资源驱动程序。在这种情况下，尝试使用网络类型或时间类型将失败。为了启用这些类型，必须启用资源驱动程序。这是通过 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_io" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_io"><code>Builder::enable_io</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_time" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_time"><code>Builder::enable_time</code></a> 完成的。作为简写，<a href="struct.Builder.html#method.enable_all" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::enable_all"><code>Builder::enable_all</code></a> 启用这两个资源驱动程序。</p>'),
    ('<p>A Tokio runtime can only execute tasks if the runtime is running. Normally\nthis is not an issue as the default configuration of a runtime is always running,\nbut alternate configurations such as the current-thread runtime require that\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 运行时仅在运行时正在运行时才能执行任务。通常这不是问题，因为运行时的默认配置始终在运行，但是像当前线程运行时之类的替代配置要求必须调用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Please be aware that <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> does not drive the runtime.\nThere must be at least one call to <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> when using the current\nthread runtime. <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> is not enough.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，<a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 不会驱动运行时。在使用当前线程运行时时，必须至少调用一次 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>。仅调用 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 是不够的。</p>'),
    ('<p>The runtime may spawn threads depending on its configuration and usage. The\nmulti-thread scheduler spawns threads to schedule tasks and for <code>spawn_blocking</code>\ncalls.</p>',
     '<p>运行时可能会根据其配置和使用情况生成线程。多线程调度器生成线程以调度任务和用于 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>While the <code>Runtime</code> is active, threads may shut down after periods of being\nidle. Once <code>Runtime</code> is dropped, all runtime threads have usually been\nterminated, but in the presence of unstoppable spawned work are not\nguaranteed to have been terminated. See the\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">struct level documentation</a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>Runtime</code> 处于活动状态时，线程可能会在空闲一段时间后关闭。一旦 <code>Runtime</code> 被 drop，所有运行时线程通常已被终止，但是在存在无法停止的已生成工作的情况下，不能保证它们已被终止。有关更多详细信息，请参阅<a href="struct.Runtime.html#shutdown" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime">结构体级别文档</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This section gives more details into how the Tokio runtime will schedule\ntasks for execution.</p>',
     '<p>本节详细介绍了 Tokio 运行时将如何调度任务以供执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>At its most basic level, a runtime has a collection of tasks that need to be\nscheduled. It will repeatedly remove a task from that collection and\nschedule it (by calling <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html#tymethod.poll" title="method core::future::future::Future::poll"><code>poll</code></a>). When the collection is empty, the thread\nwill go to sleep until a task is added to the collection.</p>',
     '<p>在最基本层面上，运行时具有一组需要调度的任务。它会重复地从该集合中移除一个任务并调度它（通过调用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html#tymethod.poll" title="method core::future::future::Future::poll"><code>poll</code></a>）。当集合为空时，线程将进入睡眠状态，直到有新任务添加到集合中。</p>'),
    ('<p>However, the above is not sufficient to guarantee a well-behaved runtime.\nFor example, the runtime might have a single task that is always ready to be\nscheduled, and schedule that task every time. This is a problem because it\nstarves other tasks by not scheduling them. To solve this, Tokio provides\nthe following fairness guarantee:</p>',
     '<p>然而，仅有以上这些不足以保证运行时的良好行为。例如，运行时可能有一个始终准备好被调度的任务，并且每次都调度该任务。这是一个问题，因为它不调度其他任务会导致它们挨饿。为了解决这个问题，Tokio 提供了以下公平性保证：</p>'),
    ('<p>If the total number of tasks does not grow without bound, and no task is\n<a href="https://ryhl.io/blog/async-what-is-blocking/">blocking the thread</a>, then it is guaranteed that tasks are scheduled\nfairly.</p>',
     '<p>如果任务总数不会无限制地增长，并且没有任务<a href="https://ryhl.io/blog/async-what-is-blocking/">阻塞线程</a>，那么可以保证任务被公平地调度。</p>'),
    ('<p>Or, more formally:</p>', '<p>或者，更正式地讲：</p>'),
    ('<p>Under the following two assumptions:</p>', '<p>在以下两个假设下：</p>'),
    ('<p>Then, there is some number <code>MAX_DELAY</code> such that when a task is woken, it\nwill be scheduled by the runtime within <code>MAX_DELAY</code> time units.</p>',
     '<p>那么，存在某个数字 <code>MAX_DELAY</code>，使得当一个任务被唤醒时，它将在 <code>MAX_DELAY</code> 个时间单位内被运行时调度。</p>'),
    ('<p>(Here, <code>MAX_TASKS</code> and <code>MAX_SCHEDULE</code> can be any number and the user of\nthe runtime may choose them. The <code>MAX_DELAY</code> number is controlled by the\nruntime, and depends on the value of <code>MAX_TASKS</code> and <code>MAX_SCHEDULE</code>.)</p>',
     '<p>（这里，<code>MAX_TASKS</code> 和 <code>MAX_SCHEDULE</code> 可以是任何数字，运行时的用户可以选择它们。<code>MAX_DELAY</code> 数字由运行时控制，取决于 <code>MAX_TASKS</code> 和 <code>MAX_SCHEDULE</code> 的值。）</p>'),
    ('<p>Other than the above fairness guarantee, there is no guarantee about the\norder in which tasks are scheduled. There is also no guarantee that the\nruntime is equally fair to all tasks. For example, if the runtime has two\ntasks A and B that are both ready, then the runtime may schedule A five\ntimes before it schedules B. This is the case even if A yields using\n<a href="../task/fn.yield_now.html" title="fn tokio::task::yield_now"><code>yield_now</code></a>. All that is guaranteed is that it will schedule B eventually.</p>',
     '<p>除了上述公平性保证外，不保证任务调度的顺序。也不保证运行时对所有任务同样公平。例如，如果运行时有两个任务 A 和 B 都已就绪，那么运行时可能会先调度 A 五次，然后再调度 B。即使 A 使用 <a href="../task/fn.yield_now.html" title="fn tokio::task::yield_now"><code>yield_now</code></a> 屈服，也是如此。所保证的只是它最终会调度 B。</p>'),
    ('<p>Normally, tasks are scheduled only if they have been woken by calling\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Waker.html#method.wake" title="method core::task::wake::Waker::wake"><code>wake</code></a> on their waker. However, this is not guaranteed, and Tokio may\nschedule tasks that have not been woken under some circumstances. This is\ncalled a spurious wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>通常，仅当任务已通过对 waker 调用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Waker.html#method.wake" title="method core::task::wake::Waker::wake"><code>wake</code></a> 被唤醒时才会被调度。但是，这并不是保证的，在某些情况下，Tokio 可能会调度尚未被唤醒的任务。这称为伪唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Beyond just scheduling tasks, the runtime must also manage IO resources and\ntimers. It does this by periodically checking whether there are any IO\nresources or timers that are ready, and waking the relevant task so that\nit will be scheduled.</p>',
     '<p>除了调度任务之外，运行时还必须管理 IO 资源和计时器。它通过定期检查是否有任何就绪的 IO 资源或计时器，并唤醒相关任务以使其被调度，来实现这一点。</p>'),
    ('<p>These checks are performed periodically between scheduling tasks. Under the\nsame assumptions as the previous fairness guarantee, Tokio guarantees that\nit will wake tasks with an IO or timer event within some maximum number of\ntime units.</p>',
     '<p>这些检查在调度任务之间定期执行。在与之前公平性保证相同的假设下，Tokio 保证它将在某个最大时间单位数内唤醒具有 IO 或计时器事件的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>This section describes how the <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.new_current_thread" title="associated function tokio::runtime::Builder::new_current_thread">current thread runtime</a> behaves today. This\nbehavior may change in future versions of Tokio.</p>',
     '<p>本节描述了 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.new_current_thread" title="associated function tokio::runtime::Builder::new_current_thread">当前线程运行时</a> 当前的行为方式。此行为可能会在未来的 Tokio 版本中发生变化。</p>'),
    ('<p>The current thread runtime maintains two FIFO queues of tasks that are ready\nto be scheduled: the global queue and the local queue. The runtime will prefer\nto choose the next task to schedule from the local queue, and will only pick a\ntask from the global queue if the local queue is empty, or if it has picked\na task from the local queue 31 times in a row. The number 31 can be\nchanged using the <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> setting.</p>',
     '<p>当前线程运行时维护两个准备调度的任务的 FIFO 队列：全局队列和本地队列。运行时将优先从本地队列中选择要调度的下一个任务，并且仅在本地队列为空时或已连续从本地队列中选择任务 31 次时，才从全局队列中选择任务。数字 31 可以使用 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> 设置进行更改。</p>'),
    ('<p>When a task is woken from within a task running on the runtime, then the\nwoken task is added directly to the local queue. Otherwise, the task is\nadded to the global queue. The current thread runtime does not use <a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot">the lifo\nslot optimization</a>.</p>',
     '<p>当任务是从运行时上运行的任务内部被唤醒时，则唤醒的任务被直接添加到本地队列。否则，该任务被添加到全局队列。当前线程运行时不使用<a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot">lifo 槽优化</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This section describes how the <a href="crate::runtime::Builder::new_multi_thread">multi thread runtime</a> behaves today. This\nbehavior may change in future versions of Tokio.</p>',
     '<p>本节描述了 <a href="crate::runtime::Builder::new_multi_thread">多线程运行时</a> 当前的行为方式。此行为可能会在未来的 Tokio 版本中发生变化。</p>'),
    ('<p>A multi thread runtime has a fixed number of worker threads, which are all\ncreated on startup. The multi thread runtime maintains one global queue, and\na local queue for each worker thread. The local queue of a worker thread can\nfit at most 256 tasks. If more than 256 tasks are added to the local queue,\nthen half of them are moved to the global queue to make space.</p>',
     '<p>多线程运行时具有固定数量的工作线程，所有这些线程都是在启动时创建的。多线程运行时维护一个全局队列，以及每个工作线程的一个本地队列。一个工作线程的本地队列最多可以容纳 256 个任务。如果添加到本地队列的任务超过 256 个，则其中的一半将被移动到全局队列以腾出空间。</p>'),
    ('<p>The runtime will prefer to choose the next task to schedule from the local\nqueue, and will only pick a task from the global queue if the local queue is empty, or if it has picked a task from the local queue\n<a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> times in a row. If the value of\n<a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> is not explicitly set using the runtime builder,\nthen the runtime will dynamically compute it using a heuristic that targets\n10ms intervals between each check of the global queue (based on the\n<a href="crate::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::worker_mean_poll_time"><code>worker_mean_poll_time</code></a> metric).</p>',
     '<p>运行时将优先从本地队列中选择要调度的下一个任务，并且仅在本地队列为空时，或已连续从本地队列中选择任务 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> 次时，才从全局队列中选择任务。如果未使用运行时构建器显式设置 <a href="struct.Builder.html#method.global_queue_interval" title="method tokio::runtime::Builder::global_queue_interval"><code>global_queue_interval</code></a> 的值，那么运行时将使用一种启发式方法动态计算它，该启发式方法的目标是每次检查全局队列之间间隔 10 毫秒（基于 <a href="crate::runtime::RuntimeMetrics::worker_mean_poll_time"><code>worker_mean_poll_time</code></a> 指标）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If both the local queue and global queue is empty, then the worker thread\nwill attempt to steal tasks from the local queue of another worker thread.\nStealing is done by moving half of the tasks in one local queue to another\nlocal queue.</p>',
     '<p>如果本地队列和全局队列都为空，那么工作线程将尝试从其他工作线程的本地队列窃取任务。窃取是通过将一个本地队列中的一半任务移动到另一个本地队列来完成的。</p>'),
    ('<p>The multi thread runtime uses <a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot">the lifo slot optimization</a>: Whenever a task\nwakes up another task, the other task is added to the worker thread’s lifo slot instead of being added to a queue. If there was already a task in the\nlifo slot when this happened, then the lifo slot is replaced, and the task\nthat used to be in the lifo slot is placed in the thread’s local queue.\nWhen the runtime finishes scheduling a task, it will schedule the task in the\nlifo slot immediately, if any. When the lifo slot is used, the <a href="../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">coop\nbudget</a> is not reset. Furthermore, if a worker thread uses the lifo slot\nthree times in a row, it is temporarily disabled until the worker thread has\nscheduled a task that didn’t come from the lifo slot. The lifo slot can be\ndisabled using the <a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot"><code>disable_lifo_slot</code></a> setting. The lifo slot is separate\nfrom the local queue, so other worker threads cannot steal the task in the\nlifo slot.</p>',
     '<p>多线程运行时使用<a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot">lifo 槽优化</a>：每当一个任务唤醒另一个任务时，另一个任务被添加到工作线程的 lifo 槽中，而不是被添加到队列中。如果在发生这种情况时 lifo 槽中已有一个任务，则会替换该 lifo 槽，并且原先在 lifo 槽中的任务将被放入线程的本地队列中。当运行时完成调度一个任务时，如果有的话，它将立即调度 lifo 槽中的任务。当使用 lifo 槽时，<a href="../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">协作预算</a> 不会被重置。此外，如果一个工作线程连续三次使用 lifo 槽，则它会被临时禁用，直到该工作线程调度了一个并非来自 lifo 槽的任务。可以使用 <a href="struct.Builder.html#structfield.disable_lifo_slot" title="field tokio::runtime::Builder::disable_lifo_slot"><code>disable_lifo_slot</code></a> 设置禁用 lifo 槽。lifo 槽与本地队列是分开的，因此其他工作线程无法窃取 lifo 槽中的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>When a task is woken from a thread that is not a worker thread, then the\ntask is placed in the global queue.</p>',
     '<p>当任务是从非工作线程唤醒时，则该任务被放入全局队列中。</p>'),
    ('<p>On Linux, file descriptor table growth can stall worker threads. See the\n<a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/blob/master/examples/prewarm-fd-table.rs"><code>prewarm-fd-table</code></a> example.</p>',
     '<p>在 Linux 上，文件描述符表的增长可能会阻塞工作线程。请参阅 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/blob/master/examples/prewarm-fd-table.rs"><code>prewarm-fd-table</code></a> 示例。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 11: JoinSet (38 items) ============
    ('<p>A collection of tasks spawned on a Tokio runtime.</p>',
     '<p>在 Tokio 运行时上生成的任务的集合。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>JoinSet</code> can be used to await the completion of some or all of the tasks\nin the set. The set is not ordered, and the tasks will be returned in the\norder they complete.</p>',
     '<p><code>JoinSet</code> 可用于等待集合中部分或全部任务的完成。该集合是无序的，任务将按其完成的顺序返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the <code>JoinSet</code> is dropped, all tasks in the <code>JoinSet</code> are immediately aborted.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>JoinSet</code> 被 drop 时，<code>JoinSet</code> 中的所有任务都将立即中止。</p>'),
    ('<p>While a task is tracked in a <code>JoinSet</code>, that task’s ID is unique relative\nto all other running tasks in Tokio. For this purpose, tracking a task in a\n<code>JoinSet</code> is equivalent to holding a <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> to it. See the <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a>\ndocumentation for more info.</p>',
     '<p>当一个任务在 <code>JoinSet</code> 中被跟踪时，该任务的 ID 相对于 Tokio 中所有其他正在运行的任务是唯一的。为此，在 <code>JoinSet</code> 中跟踪任务等同于持有该任务的 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>。有关详细信息，请参阅<a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">任务 ID</a> 文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the provided task on the <code>JoinSet</code>, returning an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>\nthat can be used to remotely cancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>JoinSet</code> 上生成提供的任务，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the provided task on the provided runtime and store it in this\n<code>JoinSet</code> returning an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a> that can be used to remotely\ncancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在所提供的运行时上生成提供的任务，并将其存储在此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the provided task on the current <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> or <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a>\nand store it in this <code>JoinSet</code>, returning an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a> that can\nbe used to remotely cancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在当前 <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> 或 <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a> 上生成提供的任务，并将其存储在此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method panics if it is called outside of a <code>LocalSet</code> or <code>LocalRuntime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <code>LocalSet</code> 或 <code>LocalRuntime</code> 之外调用此方法，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the provided task on the provided <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> and store it in\nthis <code>JoinSet</code>, returning an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a> that can be used to\nremotely cancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在所提供的 <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> 上生成提供的任务，并将其存储在此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike the <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.spawn_local" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> method, this method may be used to spawn local\ntasks on a <code>LocalSet</code> that is <em>not</em> currently running. The provided\nfuture will start running whenever the <code>LocalSet</code> is next started.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.spawn_local" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> 方法不同，此方法可用于在<em>不</em>当前正在运行的 <code>LocalSet</code> 上生成本地任务。所提供的 future 将在下次启动 <code>LocalSet</code> 时开始运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the blocking code on the blocking threadpool and store\nit in this <code>JoinSet</code>, returning an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a> that can be\nused to remotely cancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在阻塞线程池上生成阻塞代码，并将其存储在此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn the blocking code on the blocking threadpool of the\nprovided runtime and store it in this <code>JoinSet</code>, returning an\n<a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a> that can be used to remotely cancel the task.</p>',
     '<p>在所提供的运行时的阻塞线程池上生成阻塞代码，并将其存储在此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中，返回一个可用于远程取消任务的 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits until one of the tasks in the set completes and returns its output.</p>',
     '<p>等待集合中某个任务完成并返回其输出。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>join_next</code> is used as the event in a <code>tokio::select!</code>\nstatement and some other branch completes first, it is guaranteed that no tasks were\nremoved from this <code>JoinSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <code>tokio::select!</code> 语句中将 <code>join_next</code> 用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证没有任务从此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中移除。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits until one of the tasks in the set completes and returns its\noutput, along with the <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a> of the completed task.</p>',
     '<p>等待集合中某个任务完成，并返回其输出以及已完成任务的<a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">任务 ID</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If <code>join_next_with_id</code> is used as the event in a <code>tokio::select!</code>\nstatement and some other branch completes first, it is guaranteed that no tasks were\nremoved from this <code>JoinSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <code>tokio::select!</code> 语句中将 <code>join_next_with_id</code> 用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证没有任务从此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中移除。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to join one of the tasks in the set that has completed and return its output.</p>',
     '<p>尝试连接集合中已完成的任务之一并返回其输出。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to join one of the tasks in the set that has completed and return its output,\nalong with the <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a> of the completed task.</p>',
     '<p>尝试连接集合中已完成的任务之一，并返回其输出以及已完成任务的<a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">任务 ID</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Aborts all tasks and waits for them to finish shutting down.</p>',
     '<p>中止所有任务并等待它们完成关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling this method is equivalent to calling <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.abort_all" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::abort_all"><code>abort_all</code></a> and then calling <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a> in\na loop until it returns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>调用此方法等效于先调用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.abort_all" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::abort_all"><code>abort_all</code></a>，然后循环调用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a> 直至其返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method ignores any panics in the tasks shutting down. When this call returns, the\n<code>JoinSet</code> will be empty.</p>',
     '<p>此方法会忽略正在关闭的任务中的任何 panic。当此调用返回时，<code>JoinSet</code> 将为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>Awaits the completion of all tasks in this <code>JoinSet</code>, returning a vector of their results.</p>',
     '<p>等待此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中所有任务的完成，并返回一个包含其结果的向量。</p>'),
    ('<p>The results will be stored in the order they completed not the order they were spawned.\nThis is a convenience method that is equivalent to calling <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a> in\na loop. If any tasks on the <code>JoinSet</code> fail with an <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a>, then this call\nto <code>join_all</code> will panic and all remaining tasks on the <code>JoinSet</code> are\ncancelled. To handle errors in any other way, manually call <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a>\nin a loop.</p>',
     '<p>结果将按其完成的顺序存储，而不是按其生成的顺序存储。这是一个便捷方法，等效于循环调用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a>。如果 <code>JoinSet</code> 上的任何任务以 <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a> 失败，则对 <code>join_all</code> 的此次调用将 panic，并且 <code>JoinSet</code> 上所有剩余的任务都将被取消。要以其他方式处理错误，请手动循环调用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Equivalent implementation of <code>join_all</code>, using <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a> and loop.</p>',
     '<p><code>join_all</code> 的等效实现，使用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html#method.join_next" title="method tokio::task::JoinSet::join_next"><code>join_next</code></a> 和循环。</p>'),
    ('<p>This does not remove the tasks from the <code>JoinSet</code>. To wait for the tasks to complete\ncancellation, you should call <code>join_next</code> in a loop until the <code>JoinSet</code> is empty.</p>',
     '<p>这不会从 <code>JoinSet</code> 中移除任务。要等待任务完成取消，你应该循环调用 <code>join_next</code> 直至 <code>JoinSet</code> 为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>Removes all tasks from this <code>JoinSet</code> without aborting them.</p>',
     '<p>从此 <code>JoinSet</code> 中移除所有任务，但不会中止它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>The tasks removed by this call will continue to run in the background even if the <code>JoinSet</code>\nis dropped.</p>',
     '<p>由此调用移除的任务将继续在后台运行，即使 <code>JoinSet</code> 已被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>Extend a <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a> with futures from an iterator.</p>',
     '<p>使用来自迭代器的 future 扩展 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Collect an iterator of futures into a <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将 future 的迭代器收集到 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a> 中。</p>'),
    ('<p>The main example from <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a>’s documentation can also be written using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html#method.collect" title="method core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator::collect"><code>collect</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>来自 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a> 文档的主要示例也可以使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/iter/traits/iterator/trait.Iterator.html#method.collect" title="method core::iter::traits::iterator::Iterator::collect"><code>collect</code></a> 来编写：</p>'),
    ('<p>All of the tasks must have the same return type <code>T</code>.</p>',
     '<p>所有任务必须具有相同的返回类型 <code>T</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn multiple tasks and wait for them.</p>', '<p>生成多个任务并等待它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn multiple blocking tasks and wait for them.</p>', '<p>生成多个阻塞任务并等待它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawn multiple tasks and <code>join_all</code> them.</p>', '<p>生成多个任务并 <code>join_all</code> 它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>Create a new <code>JoinSet</code>.</p>', '<p>创建一个新的 <code>JoinSet</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of tasks currently in the <code>JoinSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <code>JoinSet</code> 中当前的任务数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns whether the <code>JoinSet</code> is empty.</p>', '<p>返回 <code>JoinSet</code> 是否为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>Aborts all tasks on this <code>JoinSet</code>.</p>', '<p>中止此 <code>JoinSet</code> 上的所有任务。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 12: ServerOptions (34 items) ============
    ('<p>A builder structure for construct a named pipe with named pipe-specific\noptions. This is required to use for named pipe servers who wants to modify\npipe-related options.</p>',
     '<p>用于构造具有命名管道特定选项的命名管道的构建器结构。想要修改管道相关选项的命名管道服务器必须使用此结构。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to specifying <code>PIPE_TYPE_</code> and <code>PIPE_READMODE_</code> in  <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>dwPipeMode</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>dwPipeMode</code></a> 中指定 <code>PIPE_TYPE_</code> 和 <code>PIPE_READMODE_</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_access_inbound"><code>PIPE_ACCESS_INBOUND</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_access_inbound"><code>PIPE_ACCESS_INBOUND</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Server side prevents connecting by denying inbound access, client errors\nwith <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> when attempting to create\nthe connection.</p>',
     '<p>服务器端通过拒绝入站访问来阻止连接；客户端在尝试创建连接时会收到 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Disabling writing allows a client to connect, but errors with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> if a write is attempted.</p>',
     '<p>禁用写入允许客户端连接，但如果尝试写入则会收到 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>A unidirectional named pipe that only supports server-to-client\ncommunication.</p>',
     '<p>仅支持服务器到客户端通信的单向命名管道。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_access_outbound"><code>PIPE_ACCESS_OUTBOUND</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_access_outbound"><code>PIPE_ACCESS_OUTBOUND</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Server side prevents connecting by denying outbound access, client\nerrors with <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> when attempting to\ncreate the connection.</p>',
     '<p>服务器端通过拒绝出站访问来阻止连接；客户端在尝试创建连接时会收到 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Disabling reading allows a client to connect, but attempting to read\nwill error with <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>禁用读取允许客户端连接，但尝试读取将会返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>A unidirectional named pipe that only supports client-to-server\ncommunication.</p>',
     '<p>仅支持客户端到服务器通信的单向命名管道。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you attempt to create multiple instances of a pipe with this flag\nset, creation of the first server instance succeeds, but creation of any\nsubsequent instances will fail with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果尝试在设置了此标志的情况下创建管道的多个实例，则第一个服务器实例的创建会成功，但任何后续实例的创建都将失败，并返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This option is intended to be used with servers that want to ensure that\nthey are the only process listening for clients on a given named pipe.\nThis is accomplished by enabling it for the first server instance\ncreated in a process.</p>',
     '<p>此选项旨在与希望确保自己是给定命名管道上唯一监听客户端的服务器一起使用。这是通过在进程中创建的第一个服务器实例上启用它来实现的。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_first_pipe_instance"><code>FILE_FLAG_FIRST_PIPE_INSTANCE</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_first_pipe_instance"><code>FILE_FLAG_FIRST_PIPE_INSTANCE</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If this option is set and more than one instance of the server for a\ngiven named pipe exists, calling <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> will fail with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果设置了此选项并且给定命名管道的服务器存在多个实例，则调用 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> 将失败，并返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.PermissionDenied" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::PermissionDenied</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Requests permission to modify the pipe’s discretionary access control list.</p>',
     '<p>请求修改管道的自主访问控制列表的权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>WRITE_DAC</code></a> in dwOpenMode.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在 dwOpenMode 中设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>WRITE_DAC</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Requests permission to modify the pipe’s owner.</p>',
     '<p>请求修改管道所有者的权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>WRITE_OWNER</code></a> in dwOpenMode.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在 dwOpenMode 中设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>WRITE_OWNER</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Requests permission to modify the pipe’s system access control list.</p>',
     '<p>请求修改管道的系统访问控制列表的权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>ACCESS_SYSTEM_SECURITY</code></a> in dwOpenMode.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在 dwOpenMode 中设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>ACCESS_SYSTEM_SECURITY</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Indicates whether this server can accept remote clients or not. Remote\nclients are disabled by default.</p>',
     '<p>指示此服务器是否可以接受远程客户端。默认情况下禁用远程客户端。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_reject_remote_clients"><code>PIPE_REJECT_REMOTE_CLIENTS</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea#pipe_reject_remote_clients"><code>PIPE_REJECT_REMOTE_CLIENTS</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The maximum number of instances that can be created for this pipe. The\nfirst instance of the pipe can specify this value; the same number must\nbe specified for other instances of the pipe. Acceptable values are in\nthe range 1 through 254. The default value is unlimited.</p>',
     '<p>可为此管道创建的最大实例数。管道的第一个实例可以指定此值；管道的其他实例必须指定相同的数字。可接受的值范围为 1 到 254。默认值为无限制。</p>'),
    ('<p>The same numbers of <code>max_instances</code> have to be used by all servers. Any\nadditional servers trying to be built which uses a mismatching value\nmight error.</p>',
     '<p>所有服务器必须使用相同的 <code>max_instances</code> 数。任何尝试构建的使用不匹配值的额外服务器可能会出错。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will panic if more than 254 instances are specified. If\nyou do not wish to set an instance limit, leave it unspecified.</p>',
     '<p>如果指定的实例数超过 254，此函数将发生 panic。如果不希望设置实例限制，请将其留空。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to specifying <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nOutBufferSize</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于指定 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nOutBufferSize</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to specifying <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nInBufferSize</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于指定 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nInBufferSize</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This uses the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>CreateNamedPipe</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>这使用 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>CreateNamedPipe</code></a> 函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is the same as <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> except that it supports providing the raw\npointer to a structure of <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> which will be passed\nas the <code>lpSecurityAttributes</code> argument to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这与 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> 相同，只是它支持提供指向 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> 结构的原始指针，该指针将作为 <code>lpSecurityAttributes</code> 参数传递给 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>attrs</code> argument must either be null or point at a valid instance of\nthe <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> structure. If the argument is null, the\nbehavior is identical to calling the <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p><code>attrs</code> 参数必须为 null 或指向 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> 结构体的有效实例。如果该参数为 null，则行为与调用 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>create</code></a> 方法相同。</p>'),
    ('<p>See <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>ServerOptions::create</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>请参阅 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>ServerOptions::create</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The flow of data in the pipe goes from client to server only.</p>',
     '<p>管道中的数据流仅从客户端流向服务器。</p>'),
    ('<p>The flow of data in the pipe goes from server to client only.</p>',
     '<p>管道中的数据流仅从服务器流向客户端。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 13: sync/index (32 items) ============
    ('<p>Synchronization primitives for use in asynchronous contexts.</p>',
     '<p>用于异步上下文的同步原语。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio programs tend to be organized as a set of <a href="../task/index.html" title="mod tokio::task">tasks</a> where each task\noperates independently and may be executed on separate physical threads. The\nsynchronization primitives provided in this module permit these independent\ntasks to communicate together.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 程序往往被组织为一组<a href="../task/index.html" title="mod tokio::task">任务</a>，其中每个任务独立操作，可能在不同的物理线程上执行。本模块提供的同步原语允许这些独立任务彼此通信。</p>'),
    ('<p>The most common form of synchronization in a Tokio program is message\npassing. Two tasks operate independently and send messages to each other to\nsynchronize. Doing so has the advantage of avoiding shared state.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 程序中最常见的同步形式是消息传递。两个任务独立运行，并通过相互发送消息来进行同步。这样做的好处是避免了共享状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>Message passing is implemented using channels. A channel supports sending a\nmessage from one producer task to one or more consumer tasks. There are a\nfew flavors of channels provided by Tokio. Each channel flavor supports\ndifferent message passing patterns. When a channel supports multiple\nproducers, many separate tasks may <strong>send</strong> messages. When a channel\nsupports multiple consumers, many different separate tasks may <strong>receive</strong>\nmessages.</p>',
     '<p>消息传递使用通道来实现。通道支持将消息从一个生产者任务发送到一个或多个消费者任务。Tokio 提供了几种不同类型的通道。每种通道类型支持不同的消息传递模式。当通道支持多个生产者时，许多单独的任务可以<strong>发送</strong>消息。当通道支持多个消费者时，许多不同的单独任务可以<strong>接收</strong>消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio provides many different channel flavors as different message passing\npatterns are best handled with different implementations.</p>',
     '<p>由于不同的消息传递模式最适合用不同的实现来处理，因此 Tokio 提供了许多不同类型的通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code> channel</a> supports sending a <strong>single</strong> value from a\nsingle producer to a single consumer. This channel is usually used to send\nthe result of a computation to a waiter.</p>',
     '<p><a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code> 通道</a>支持从单个生产者向单个消费者发送<strong>单个</strong>值。该通道通常用于将计算结果发送给等待者。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong> using a <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code> channel</a> to receive the result of a\ncomputation.</p>',
     '<p><strong>示例：</strong>使用 <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code> 通道</a>接收计算结果。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note, if the task produces a computation result as its final\naction before terminating, the <a href="../task/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> can be used to\nreceive that value instead of allocating resources for the\n<code>oneshot</code> channel. Awaiting on <a href="../task/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> returns <code>Result</code>. If\nthe task panics, the <code>Joinhandle</code> yields <code>Err</code> with the panic\ncause.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果任务在终止之前的最后动作是产生计算结果，则可以使用 <a href="../task/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 来接收该值，而无需为 <code>oneshot</code> 通道分配资源。等待 <a href="../task/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 返回 <code>Result</code>。如果任务 panic，则 <code>Joinhandle</code> 会产生带有 panic 原因的 <code>Err</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code> channel</a> supports sending <strong>many</strong> values from <strong>many</strong>\nproducers to a single consumer. This channel is often used to send work to a\ntask or to receive the result of many computations.</p>',
     '<p><a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code> 通道</a>支持从<strong>多个</strong>生产者向单个消费者发送<strong>许多</strong>值。该通道通常用于将工作发送给任务，或接收许多计算的结果。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is also the channel you should use if you want to send many messages\nfrom a single producer to a single consumer. There is no dedicated spsc\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p>如果要将许多消息从单个生产者发送到单个消费者，也应该使用此通道。没有专用的 spsc 通道。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong> using an mpsc to incrementally stream the results of a series\nof computations.</p>',
     '<p><strong>示例：</strong>使用 mpsc 增量流式传输一系列计算的结果。</p>'),
    ('<p>The argument to <code>mpsc::channel</code> is the channel capacity. This is the maximum\nnumber of values that can be stored in the channel pending receipt at any\ngiven time. Properly setting this value is key in implementing robust\nprograms as the channel capacity plays a critical part in handling back\npressure.</p>',
     '<p><code>mpsc::channel</code> 的参数是通道容量。这是任何给定时间在通道中可以存储等待接收的最大值数。由于通道容量在处理背压方面起着关键作用，因此正确设置此值是实现健壮程序的关键。</p>'),
    ('<p>A common concurrency pattern for resource management is to spawn a task\ndedicated to managing that resource and using message passing between other\ntasks to interact with the resource. The resource may be anything that may\nnot be concurrently used. Some examples include a socket and program state.\nFor example, if multiple tasks need to send data over a single socket, spawn\na task to manage the socket and use a channel to synchronize.</p>',
     '<p>一种用于资源管理的常见并发模式是生成一个专门管理该资源的任务，并使用其他任务之间的消息传递来与该资源交互。该资源可以是任何不能被并发使用的事物。一些示例包括 socket 和程序状态。例如，如果多个任务需要通过单个 socket 发送数据，则生成一个任务来管理该 socket 并使用通道进行同步。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong> sending data from many tasks over a single socket using message\npassing.</p>',
     '<p><strong>示例：</strong>使用消息传递从许多任务通过单个 socket 发送数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> and <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code></a> channels can be combined to provide a request /\nresponse type synchronization pattern with a shared resource. A task is\nspawned to synchronize a resource and waits on commands received on a\n<a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> channel. Each command includes a <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code></a> <code>Sender</code> on which the\nresult of the command is sent.</p>',
     '<p><a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> 和 <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code></a> 通道可以组合在一起，以提供与共享资源的请求/响应类型同步模式。生成一个任务来同步资源，并等待通过 <a href="mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> 通道接收到的命令。每个命令都包含一个 <a href="oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot"><code>oneshot</code></a> <code>Sender</code>，命令的结果将通过它发送。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong> use a task to synchronize a <code>u64</code> counter. Each task sends an\n“fetch and increment” command. The counter value <strong>before</strong> the increment is\nsent over the provided <code>oneshot</code> channel.</p>',
     '<p><strong>示例：</strong>使用任务同步一个 <code>u64</code> 计数器。每个任务发送一个“获取并递增”命令。递增<strong>之前</strong>的计数器值通过所提供的 <code>oneshot</code> 通道发送。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="broadcast/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code> channel</a> supports sending <strong>many</strong> values from\n<strong>many</strong> producers to <strong>many</strong> consumers. Each consumer will receive\n<strong>each</strong> value. This channel can be used to implement “fan out” style\npatterns common with pub / sub or “chat” systems.</p>',
     '<p><a href="broadcast/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code> 通道</a>支持从<strong>多个</strong>生产者向<strong>多个</strong>消费者发送<strong>许多</strong>值。每个消费者都会收到<strong>每一条</strong>值。该通道可用于实现 pub/sub 或“聊天”系统中常见的“扇出”模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel tends to be used less often than <code>oneshot</code> and <code>mpsc</code> but still\nhas its use cases.</p>',
     '<p>该通道的使用频率通常低于 <code>oneshot</code> 和 <code>mpsc</code>，但仍有其使用场景。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is also the channel you should use if you want to broadcast values from\na single producer to many consumers. There is no dedicated spmc broadcast\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p>如果要将值从单个生产者广播到多个消费者，也应该使用此通道。没有专用的 spmc 广播通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> channel</a> supports sending <strong>many</strong> values from <strong>many</strong>\nproducers to <strong>many</strong> consumers. However, only the <strong>most recent</strong> value is\nstored in the channel. Consumers are notified when a new value is sent, but\nthere is no guarantee that consumers will see <strong>all</strong> values.</p>',
     '<p><a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> 通道</a>支持从<strong>多个</strong>生产者向<strong>多个</strong>消费者发送<strong>许多</strong>值。但是，通道中仅存储<strong>最近</strong>的值。消费者会在发送新值时收到通知，但不能保证消费者会看到<strong>所有</strong>值。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> channel</a> is similar to a <a href="broadcast/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code> channel</a> with capacity 1.</p>',
     '<p><a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> 通道</a>类似于容量为 1 的 <a href="broadcast/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code> 通道</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Use cases for the <a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> channel</a> include broadcasting configuration\nchanges or signalling program state changes, such as transitioning to\nshutdown.</p>',
     '<p><a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> 通道</a>的用例包括广播配置更改或发出程序状态更改的信号，例如转换到关闭状态。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong> use a <a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> channel</a> to notify tasks of configuration\nchanges. In this example, a configuration file is checked periodically. When\nthe file changes, the configuration changes are signalled to consumers.</p>',
     '<p><strong>示例：</strong>使用 <a href="watch/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code> 通道</a>向任务通知配置更改。在此示例中，定期检查配置文件。当文件发生更改时，会向消费者发出配置更改的信号。</p>'),
    ('<p>The remaining synchronization primitives focus on synchronizing state.\nThese are asynchronous equivalents to versions provided by <code>std</code>. They\noperate in a similar way as their <code>std</code> counterparts but will wait\nasynchronously instead of blocking the thread.</p>',
     '<p>其余的同步原语专注于同步状态。这些是 <code>std</code> 提供的版本的异步等价物。它们的工作方式与 <code>std</code> 对应物类似，但会异步等待而不是阻塞线程。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Barrier.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Barrier"><code>Barrier</code></a> Ensures multiple tasks will wait for each other to reach a\npoint in the program, before continuing execution all together.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Barrier.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Barrier"><code>Barrier</code></a> 确保多个任务相互等待到达程序中的某个点，然后再一起继续执行。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> Mutual Exclusion mechanism, which ensures that at most one\nthread at a time is able to access some data.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> 互斥机制，确保一次最多一个线程能够访问某些数据。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Notify.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Notify"><code>Notify</code></a> Basic task notification. <code>Notify</code> supports notifying a\nreceiving task without sending data. In this case, the task wakes up and\nresumes processing.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Notify.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Notify"><code>Notify</code></a> 基本任务通知。<code>Notify</code> 支持在不发送数据的情况下通知接收任务。在这种情况下，任务会唤醒并恢复处理。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> Provides a mutual exclusion mechanism which allows multiple\nreaders at the same time, while allowing only one writer at a time. In\nsome cases, this can be more efficient than a mutex.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 提供一种互斥机制，允许多个读者同时访问，但一次仅允许一个写入者。在某些情况下，这比互斥锁更高效。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> Limits the amount of concurrency. A semaphore holds a\nnumber of permits, which tasks may request in order to enter a critical\nsection. Semaphores are useful for implementing limiting or bounding of\nany kind.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> 限制并发量。信号量持有若干许可，任务可以请求这些许可以进入临界区。信号量对于实现任何类型的限制或约束非常有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>All synchronization primitives provided in this module are runtime agnostic.\nYou can freely move them between different instances of the Tokio runtime\nor even use them from non-Tokio runtimes.</p>',
     '<p>本模块提供的所有同步原语都与运行时无关。你可以在 Tokio 运行时的不同实例之间自由移动它们，甚至可以从非 Tokio 运行时使用它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>When used in a Tokio runtime, the synchronization primitives participate in\n<a href="../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">cooperative scheduling</a> to avoid\nstarvation. This feature does not apply when used from non-Tokio runtimes.</p>',
     '<p>在 Tokio 运行时中使用时，这些同步原语参与<a href="../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">协作调度</a>以避免饥饿。从非 Tokio 运行时使用时，此功能不适用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 14: watch Receiver (31 items) ============
    ('<p>Receives values from the associated <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>从关联的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 接收值。</p>'),
    ('<p>To turn this receiver into a <code>Stream</code>, you can use the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.WatchStream.html"><code>WatchStream</code></a>\nwrapper.</p>',
     '<p>要将此接收者转换为 <code>Stream</code>，可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.WatchStream.html"><code>WatchStream</code></a> 包装器。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the most recently sent value.</p>',
     '<p>返回对最近发送值的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method does not mark the returned value as seen, so future calls to\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> may return immediately even if you have already seen the\nvalue with a call to <code>borrow</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法不会将返回的值标记为已读，因此对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 的后续调用可能会立即返回，即使你已经通过调用 <code>borrow</code> 看到了该值。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information on when to use this method versus\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>borrow_and_update</code></a>, see <a href="index.html#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow" title="mod tokio::sync::watch">here</a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关何时使用此方法与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>borrow_and_update</code></a> 的更多信息，请参阅<a href="index.html#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow" title="mod tokio::sync::watch">此处</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the most recently sent value and marks that value\nas seen.</p>',
     '<p>返回对最近发送值的引用，并将该值标记为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method marks the current value as seen. Subsequent calls to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a>\nwill not return immediately until the <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> has modified the shared\nvalue again.</p>',
     '<p>此方法会将当前值标记为已读。在 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 再次修改共享值之前，对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 的后续调用不会立即返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information on when to use this method versus <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a>, see\n<a href="index.html#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow" title="mod tokio::sync::watch">here</a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关何时使用此方法与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a> 的更多信息，请参阅<a href="index.html#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow" title="mod tokio::sync::watch">此处</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if this channel contains a message that this receiver has not yet\nseen. The current value will not be marked as seen.</p>',
     '<p>检查此通道是否包含此接收者尚未看到的消息。当前值将不会被标记为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>Although this method is called <code>has_changed</code>, it does not check\nmessages for equality, so this call will return true even if the current\nmessage is equal to the previous message.</p>',
     '<p>虽然此方法称为 <code>has_changed</code>，但它不会检查消息的相等性，因此即使当前消息等于上一条消息，此调用也会返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a> if and only if the channel has been closed.</p>',
     '<p>当且仅当通道已关闭时返回 <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Marks the state as changed.</p>', '<p>将状态标记为已更改。</p>'),
    ('<p>After invoking this method <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed()</code></a>\nreturns <code>true</code> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed()</code></a> returns\nimmediately, regardless of whether a new value has been sent.</p>',
     '<p>调用此方法后，无论是否发送了新值，<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed()</code></a> 都会返回 <code>true</code>，并且 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed()</code></a> 会立即返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is useful for triggering an initial change notification after\nsubscribing to synchronize new receivers.</p>',
     '<p>这对于在订阅以同步新接收者之后触发初始更改通知很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Marks the state as unchanged.</p>', '<p>将状态标记为未更改。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is useful if you are not interested in the current value\nvisible in the receiver.</p>',
     '<p>如果你对接收者中可见的当前值不感兴趣，这将很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for a change notification, then marks the current value as seen.</p>',
     '<p>等待更改通知，然后将当前值标记为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the current value in the channel has not yet been marked seen when\nthis method is called, the method marks that value seen and returns\nimmediately. If the newest value has already been marked seen, then the\nmethod sleeps until a new message is sent by a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> connected to\nthis <code>Receiver</code>, or until all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>s are dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果调用此方法时通道中的当前值尚未标记为已读，则该方法会将该值标记为已读并立即返回。如果最新值已标记为已读，则该方法将休眠，直到与此 <code>Receiver</code> 连接的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 发送新消息，或者直到所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 都已 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information, see\n<a href="index.html#change-notifications" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><em>Change notifications</em></a> in the module-level documentation.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多信息，请参阅模块级文档中的 <a href="index.html#change-notifications" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><em>更改通知</em></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a> if the channel has been closed <strong>AND</strong>\nthe current value is seen.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已关闭<strong>并且</strong>当前值已读，则返回 <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If you use it as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that no values have been marked\nseen by this call to <code>changed</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将此方法用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证对 <code>changed</code> 的此次调用未将任何值标记为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for a value that satisfies the provided condition.</p>',
     '<p>等待满足所提供条件的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method will call the provided closure whenever something is sent on\nthe channel. Once the closure returns <code>true</code>, this method will return a\nreference to the value that was passed to the closure.</p>',
     '<p>每当通道上发送了某些内容时，此方法都会调用所提供的闭包。一旦闭包返回 <code>true</code>，此方法将返回传递给闭包的值的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Before <code>wait_for</code> starts waiting for changes, it will call the closure\non the current value. If the closure returns <code>true</code> when given the\ncurrent value, then <code>wait_for</code> will immediately return a reference to\nthe current value. This is the case even if the current value is already\nconsidered seen.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>wait_for</code> 开始等待更改之前，它将对当前值调用该闭包。如果对当前值调用时闭包返回 <code>true</code>，则 <code>wait_for</code> 将立即返回对当前值的引用。即使当前值已被视为已读，也是如此。</p>'),
    ('<p>The watch channel only keeps track of the most recent value, so if\nseveral messages are sent faster than <code>wait_for</code> is able to call the\nclosure, then it may skip some updates. Whenever the closure is called,\nit will be called with the most recent value.</p>',
     '<p>watch 通道仅跟踪最近的值，因此如果发送多条消息的速度快于 <code>wait_for</code> 调用闭包的速度，则它可能会跳过某些更新。每当调用闭包时，都会使用最近的值来调用它。</p>'),
    ('<p>When this function returns, the value that was passed to the closure\nwhen it returned <code>true</code> will be considered seen.</p>',
     '<p>当此函数返回时，当闭包返回 <code>true</code> 时传递给闭包的值将被视为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel is closed, then <code>wait_for</code> will return a <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>.\nOnce this happens, no more messages can ever be sent on the channel.\nWhen an error is returned, it is guaranteed that the closure has been\ncalled on the last value, and that it returned <code>false</code> for that value.\n(If the closure returned <code>true</code>, then the last value would have been\nreturned instead of the error.)</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已关闭，则 <code>wait_for</code> 将返回 <a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>。一旦发生这种情况，通道上就不会再发送任何消息。当返回错误时，可以保证已对最后一个值调用了闭包，并且它对该值返回了 <code>false</code>。（如果闭包返回了 <code>true</code>，那么将返回最后一个值而不是错误。）</p>'),
    ('<p>Like the <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a> method, the returned borrow holds a read lock on the\ninner value. This means that long-lived borrows could cause the producer\nhalf to block. It is recommended to keep the borrow as short-lived as\npossible. See the documentation of <code>borrow</code> for more information on\nthis.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a> 方法一样，返回的借用对内部值持有读锁。这意味着长时间的借用可能会导致生产者一半阻塞。建议将借用的生命周期保持尽可能短。有关这方面的更多信息，请参阅 <code>borrow</code> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If you use it as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that the last seen value <code>val</code>\n(if any) satisfies <code>f(val) == false</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将此方法用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证最后看到的值 <code>val</code>（如果有）满足 <code>f(val) == false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If and only if the closure <code>f</code> panics. In that case, no resource owned\nor shared by this <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> will be poisoned.</p>',
     '<p>当且仅当闭包 <code>f</code> 发生 panic。在这种情况下，此 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 拥有或共享的任何资源都不会被污染。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 15: Notify (30 items) ============
    ('<p>Notifies a single task to wake up.</p>', '<p>通知单个任务唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Notify</code> provides a basic mechanism to notify a single task of an event.\n<code>Notify</code> itself does not carry any data. Instead, it is to be used to signal\nanother task to perform an operation.</p>',
     '<p><code>Notify</code> 提供了一种用于向单个任务通知事件的基本机制。<code>Notify</code> 本身不携带任何数据。相反，它用于向另一个任务发出执行操作的信号。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>Notify</code> can be thought of as a <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> starting with 0 permits. The\n<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> method waits for a permit to become available, and\n<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> sets a permit <strong>if there currently are no available\npermits</strong>.</p>',
     '<p>可以将 <code>Notify</code> 视为一个以 0 个许可开始的 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a>。<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> 方法等待许可变为可用，而 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> <strong>在当前没有可用许可时</strong>设置一个许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>The synchronization details of <code>Notify</code> are similar to\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.park.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::park"><code>thread::park</code></a> and <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/thread/struct.Thread.html#method.unpark" title="method std::thread::thread::Thread::unpark"><code>Thread::unpark</code></a> from std. A <a href="struct.Notify.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Notify"><code>Notify</code></a>\nvalue contains a single permit. <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> waits for the permit to\nbe made available, consumes the permit, and resumes.  <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> sets\nthe permit, waking a pending task if there is one.</p>',
     '<p><code>Notify</code> 的同步细节类似于 std 中的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.park.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::park"><code>thread::park</code></a> 和 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/thread/struct.Thread.html#method.unpark" title="method std::thread::thread::Thread::unpark"><code>Thread::unpark</code></a>。<a href="struct.Notify.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Notify"><code>Notify</code></a> 值包含单个许可。<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> 等待许可可用，消费该许可，然后恢复运行。<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> 设置许可，如果有挂起的任务则唤醒它。</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>notify_one()</code> is called <strong>before</strong> <code>notified().await</code>, then the next\ncall to <code>notified().await</code> will complete immediately, consuming the permit.\nAny subsequent calls to <code>notified().await</code> will wait for a new permit.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <code>notified().await</code> <strong>之前</strong>调用 <code>notify_one()</code>，则下一次调用 <code>notified().await</code> 将立即完成，消费该许可。对 <code>notified().await</code> 的任何后续调用都将等待新的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>notify_one()</code> is called <strong>multiple</strong> times before <code>notified().await</code>,\nonly a <strong>single</strong> permit is stored. The next call to <code>notified().await</code> will\ncomplete immediately, but the one after will wait for a new permit.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <code>notified().await</code> 之前<strong>多次</strong>调用 <code>notify_one()</code>，则仅存储<strong>单个</strong>许可。下一次调用 <code>notified().await</code> 将立即完成，但再下一次调用将等待新的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unbound multi-producer single-consumer (mpsc) channel.</p>',
     '<p>无界多生产者单消费者 (mpsc) 通道。</p>'),
    ('<p>No wakeups can be lost when using this channel because the call to\n<code>notify_one()</code> will store a permit in the <code>Notify</code>, which the following call\nto <code>notified()</code> will consume.</p>',
     '<p>使用此通道时不会丢失任何唤醒，因为对 <code>notify_one()</code> 的调用会将许可存储在 <code>Notify</code> 中，随后的 <code>notified()</code> 调用将消费该许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>The call to <a href="futures/struct.Notified.html#method.enable" title="method tokio::sync::futures::Notified::enable"><code>enable</code></a> is important because otherwise if you have two\ncalls to <code>recv</code> and two calls to <code>send</code> in parallel, the following could\nhappen:</p>',
     '<p>调用 <a href="futures/struct.Notified.html#method.enable" title="method tokio::sync::futures::Notified::enable"><code>enable</code></a> 很重要，因为否则如果你并行调用两个 <code>recv</code> 和两个 <code>send</code>，则可能会发生以下情况：</p>'),
    ('<p>Notice that this failure can only happen if there are two concurrent calls\nto <code>recv</code>. This is why the mpsc example above does not require a call to\n<code>enable</code>.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，只有在存在两个对 <code>recv</code> 的并发调用时才会发生此失败。这就是为什么上面的 mpsc 示例不需要调用 <code>enable</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>Notify</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Notify::new"><code>Notify::new</code></a> should be used to create\nan instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定特性</a>时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>Notify</code> 将不会被检测。因此，它将不会出现在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Notify::new"><code>Notify::new</code></a> 创建一个已检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Each <code>Notify</code> value holds a single permit. If a permit is available from\nan earlier call to <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a>, then <code>notified().await</code> will complete\nimmediately, consuming that permit. Otherwise, <code>notified().await</code> waits\nfor a permit to be made available by the next call to <code>notify_one()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>每个 <code>Notify</code> 值都持有一个许可。如果通过先前调用 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> 已有可用许可，则 <code>notified().await</code> 将立即完成，消费该许可。否则，<code>notified().await</code> 将等待通过下一次调用 <code>notify_one()</code> 提供许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Notified</code> future is not guaranteed to receive wakeups from calls to\n<code>notify_one()</code> if it has not yet been polled. See the documentation for\n<a href="futures/struct.Notified.html#method.enable" title="method tokio::sync::futures::Notified::enable"><code>Notified::enable()</code></a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Notified</code> future 尚未被 poll，则不能保证它会收到来自对 <code>notify_one()</code> 调用的唤醒。有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="futures/struct.Notified.html#method.enable" title="method tokio::sync::futures::Notified::enable"><code>Notified::enable()</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Notified</code> future is guaranteed to receive wakeups from\n<code>notify_waiters()</code> as soon as it has been created, even if it has not\nyet been polled.</p>',
     '<p><code>Notified</code> future 保证在创建后立即就能收到来自 <code>notify_waiters()</code> 的唤醒，即使它尚未被 poll。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute notifications in the order\nthey were requested. Cancelling a call to <code>notified</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发通知。取消对 <code>notified</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Wait for a notification with an owned <code>Future</code>.</p>',
     '<p>使用拥有的 <code>Future</code> 等待通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Self::notified</code></a> which returns a future tied to the <code>Notify</code>’s\nlifetime, <code>notified_owned</code> creates a self-contained future that owns its\nnotification state, making it safe to move between threads.</p>',
     '<p>与返回绑定到 <code>Notify</code> 生命周期的 future 的 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Self::notified</code></a> 不同，<code>notified_owned</code> 创建了一个拥有其通知状态的独立 future，使其可以在线程之间安全移动。</p>'),
    ('<p>See <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Self::notified</code></a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Self::notified</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute notifications in the order\nthey were requested. Cancelling a call to <code>notified_owned</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发通知。取消对 <code>notified_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Notifies the first waiting task.</p>', '<p>通知第一个等待任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a task is currently waiting, that task is notified. Otherwise, a\npermit is stored in this <code>Notify</code> value and the <strong>next</strong> call to\n<a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> will complete immediately consuming the permit made\navailable by this call to <code>notify_one()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果有任务当前正在等待，则会通知该任务。否则，许可将存储在此 <code>Notify</code> 值中，并且<strong>下一次</strong>调用 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>notified().await</code></a> 将立即完成，消费此次调用 <code>notify_one()</code> 提供的许可。</p>'),
    ('<p>At most one permit may be stored by <code>Notify</code>. Many sequential calls to\n<code>notify_one</code> will result in a single permit being stored. The next call to\n<code>notified().await</code> will complete immediately, but the one after that\nwill wait.</p>',
     '<p><code>Notify</code> 最多可以存储一个许可。对 <code>notify_one</code> 的多次顺序调用将导致存储单个许可。下一次调用 <code>notified().await</code> 将立即完成，但再下一次调用将等待。</p>'),
    ('<p>Notifies the last waiting task.</p>', '<p>通知最后一个等待任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function behaves similar to <code>notify_one</code>. The only difference is that it wakes\nthe most recently added waiter instead of the oldest waiter.</p>',
     '<p>此函数的行为类似于 <code>notify_one</code>。唯一的区别是它唤醒最近添加的等待者，而不是最早的等待者。</p>'),
    ('<p>Check the <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> documentation for more info and\nexamples.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多信息和示例，请参阅 <a href="struct.Notify.html#method.notify_one" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_one"><code>notify_one()</code></a> 文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Notifies all waiting tasks.</p>', '<p>通知所有等待任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a task is currently waiting, that task is notified. Unlike with\n<code>notify_one()</code>, no permit is stored to be used by the next call to\n<code>notified().await</code>. The purpose of this method is to notify all\nalready registered waiters. Registering for notification is done by\nacquiring an instance of the <code>Notified</code> future via calling <code>notified()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果有任务当前正在等待，则会通知该任务。与 <code>notify_one()</code> 不同，此方法不会存储许可供下一次调用 <code>notified().await</code> 使用。此方法的目的是通知所有已注册的等待者。通过调用 <code>notified()</code> 获取 <code>Notified</code> future 实例即可完成通知注册。</p>'),
    ('<p>Basic usage.</p>', '<p>基本用法。</p>'),
    ('<p>Wait for a notification.</p>', '<p>等待通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Equivalent to:</p>', '<p>等效于：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 16: AsyncWrite (28 items) ============
    ('<p>This trait is analogous to the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>std::io::Write</code></a> trait, but integrates with\nthe asynchronous task system. In particular, the <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> method,\nunlike <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html#tymethod.write" title="method std::io::Write::write"><code>Write::write</code></a>, will automatically queue the current task for wakeup\nand return if data is not yet available, rather than blocking the calling\nthread.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 类似于 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>std::io::Write</code></a> trait，但它与异步任务系统集成。具体而言，<a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> 方法与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html#tymethod.write" title="method std::io::Write::write"><code>Write::write</code></a> 不同，如果数据尚不可用，它会自动将当前任务排队等待唤醒并返回，而不是阻塞调用线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>Specifically, this means that the <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> function will return one of\nthe following:</p>',
     '<p>具体来说，这意味着 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> 函数将返回以下之一：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(n))</code> means that <code>n</code> bytes of data was immediately\nwritten.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(n))</code> 意味着立即写入了 <code>n</code> 字节的数据。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> means that no data was written from the buffer\nprovided. The I/O object is not currently writable but may become writable\nin the future. Most importantly, <strong>the current future’s task is scheduled\nto get unparked when the object is writable</strong>. This means that like\n<code>Future::poll</code> you’ll receive a notification when the I/O object is\nwritable again.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> 意味着没有从所提供的缓冲区写入任何数据。I/O 对象当前不可写，但将来可能变得可写。最重要的是，<strong>当对象可写时，当前 future 的任务会被调度以获得 unpark 通知</strong>。这意味着与 <code>Future::poll</code> 类似，当 I/O 对象再次可写时，你将收到通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Utilities for working with <code>AsyncWrite</code> values are provided by\n<a href="crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a>. Most users will interact with <code>AsyncWrite</code> types through\nthese extension methods, which provide ergonomic async functions such as\n<code>write_all</code> and <code>flush</code>.</p>',
     '<p>用于处理 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 值的实用工具由 <a href="crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> 提供。大多数用户将通过这些扩展方法与 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 类型进行交互，这些方法提供了符合人体工程学的异步函数，例如 <code>write_all</code> 和 <code>flush</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempt to write bytes from <code>buf</code> into the object.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将字节从 <code>buf</code> 写入对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, returns <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(num_bytes_written))</code>. If successful,\nthen it must be guaranteed that <code>n &lt;= buf.len()</code>. A return value of <code>0</code>\ntypically means that the underlying object is no longer able to accept\nbytes and will likely not be able to in the future as well, or that the\nbuffer provided is empty.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(num_bytes_written))</code>。如果成功，则必须保证 <code>n &lt;= buf.len()</code>。返回值 <code>0</code> 通常意味着底层对象不再能够接受字节，并且将来很可能也无法接受，或者所提供的缓冲区为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to flush the object, ensuring that any buffered data reach\ntheir destination.</p>',
     '<p>尝试刷新对象，确保任何已缓冲的数据都到达其目标。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, returns <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code>.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If flushing cannot immediately完成, this method returns\n<code>Poll::Pending</code> and arranges for the current task (via\n<code>cx.waker()</code>) to receive a notification when the object can make\nprogress towards flushing.</p>',
     '<p>如果刷新无法立即完成，此方法将返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排当前任务（通过 <code>cx.waker()</code>）在对象能够推进刷新时收到通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Initiates or attempts to shut down this writer, returning success when\nthe I/O connection has completely shut down.</p>',
     '<p>启动或尝试关闭此写入器，在 I/O 连接完全关闭时返回成功。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is intended to be used for asynchronous shutdown of I/O\nconnections. For example this is suitable for implementing shutdown of a\nTLS connection or calling <code>TcpStream::shutdown</code> on a proxied connection.\nProtocols sometimes need to flush out final pieces of data or otherwise\nperform a graceful shutdown handshake, reading/writing more data as\nappropriate. This method is the hook for such protocols to implement the\ngraceful shutdown logic.</p>',
     '<p>此方法旨在用于 I/O 连接的异步关闭。例如，这适用于实现 TLS 连接的关闭，或在代理连接上调用 <code>TcpStream::shutdown</code>。协议有时需要刷新最后的数据片段或执行优雅的关闭握手，根据需要读/写更多数据。此方法是此类协议实现优雅关闭逻辑的钩子。</p>'),
    ('<p>This <code>shutdown</code> method is required by implementers of the\n<code>AsyncWrite</code> trait. Wrappers typically just want to proxy this call\nthrough to the wrapped type, and base types will typically implement\nshutdown logic here or just return <code>Ok(().into())</code>. Note that if you’re\nwrapping an underlying <code>AsyncWrite</code> a call to <code>shutdown</code> implies that\ntransitively the entire stream has been shut down. After your wrapper’s\nshutdown logic has been executed you should shut down the underlying\nstream.</p>',
     '<p><code>AsyncWrite</code> trait 的实现者必须实现此 <code>shutdown</code> 方法。包装器通常只想将此调用代理到被包装的类型，而基本类型通常在此处实现关闭逻辑或仅返回 <code>Ok(().into())</code>。请注意，如果你正在包装底层的 <code>AsyncWrite</code>，则对 <code>shutdown</code> 的调用意味着整个流已被传递性地关闭。在执行完包装器的关闭逻辑后，你应该关闭底层流。</p>'),
    ('<p>Invocation of a <code>shutdown</code> implies an invocation of <code>flush</code>. Once this\nmethod returns <code>Ready</code> it implies that a flush successfully happened\nbefore the shutdown happened. That is, callers don’t need to call\n<code>flush</code> before calling <code>shutdown</code>. They can rely that by calling\n<code>shutdown</code> any pending buffered data will be written out.</p>',
     '<p>调用 <code>shutdown</code> 意味着调用了 <code>flush</code>。一旦此方法返回 <code>Ready</code>，就意味着在关闭发生之前已成功执行了刷新。也就是说，调用者无需在调用 <code>shutdown</code> 之前调用 <code>flush</code>。他们可以相信通过调用 <code>shutdown</code>，任何挂起的已缓冲数据都将被写出。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function returns a <code>Poll&lt;io::Result&lt;()&gt;&gt;</code> classified as such:</p>',
     '<p>此函数返回 <code>Poll&lt;io::Result&lt;()&gt;&gt;</code>，分类如下：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> - indicates that the connection was\nsuccessfully shut down and is now safe to deallocate/drop/close\nresources associated with it. This method means that the current task\nwill no longer receive any notifications due to this method and the\nI/O object itself is likely no longer usable.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> - 表示连接已成功关闭，现在可以安全地释放/丢弃/关闭与其关联的资源。此方法意味着当前任务将不再收到由此方法导致的任何通知，并且 I/O 对象本身很可能不再可用。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> - indicates that shutdown is initiated but could\nnot complete just yet. This may mean that more I/O needs to happen to\ncontinue this shutdown operation. The current task is scheduled to\nreceive a notification when it’s otherwise ready to continue the\nshutdown operation. When woken up this method should be called again.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> - 表示关闭已启动但目前无法完成。这可能意味着需要更多 I/O 才能继续此关闭操作。当前任务被调度为在其他条件允许继续关闭操作时收到通知。唤醒时应再次调用此方法。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Ready(Err(e))</code> - indicates a fatal error has happened with shutdown,\nindicating that the shutdown operation did not complete successfully.\nThis typically means that the I/O object is no longer usable.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Ready(Err(e))</code> - 表示关闭过程中发生了致命错误，表明关闭操作未成功完成。这通常意味着 I/O 对象不再可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function can return normal I/O errors through <code>Err</code>, described\nabove. Additionally this method may also render the underlying\n<code>Write::write</code> method no longer usable (e.g. will return errors in the\nfuture). It’s recommended that once <code>shutdown</code> is called the\n<code>write</code> method is no longer called.</p>',
     '<p>此函数可以通过 <code>Err</code> 返回正常的 I/O 错误，如上所述。此外，此方法还可能导致底层的 <code>Write::write</code> 方法不再可用（例如，将来会返回错误）。建议一旦调用了 <code>shutdown</code>，就不再调用 <code>write</code> 方法。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will panic if not called within the context of a future’s\ntask.</p>',
     '<p>如果未在 future 任务的上下文中调用，此函数将发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Like <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a>, except that it writes from a slice of buffers.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> 类似，只是它从一个缓冲区切片写入。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied from each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nread from possibly being only partially consumed. This method must\nbehave as a call to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/macro.write.html" title="macro core::write"><code>write</code></a> with the buffers concatenated would.</p>',
     '<p>数据按顺序从每个缓冲区复制，最后读取的缓冲区可能仅被部分消费。此方法的行为必须与使用连接后的缓冲区对 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/macro.write.html" title="macro core::write"><code>write</code></a> 的调用相同。</p>'),
    ('<p>The default implementation calls <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a> with either the first nonempty\nbuffer provided, or an empty one if none exists.</p>',
     '<p>默认实现使用所提供的第一个非空缓冲区（如果不存在则使用空缓冲区）调用 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_write" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write"><code>poll_write</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, returns <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(num_bytes_written))</code>.</p>',
     '<p>成功时返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(num_bytes_written))</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This should be implemented as a single “atomic” write action. If any\ndata has been partially written, it is wrong to return an error or\npending.</p>',
     '<p>这应实现为单个“原子”写入操作。如果已部分写入了任何数据，则返回错误或 pending 是错误的。</p>'),
    ('<p>Determines if this writer has an efficient <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#method.poll_write_vectored" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write_vectored"><code>poll_write_vectored</code></a>\nimplementation.</p>',
     '<p>确定此写入器是否具有高效的 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#method.poll_write_vectored" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write_vectored"><code>poll_write_vectored</code></a> 实现。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a writer does not override the default <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#method.poll_write_vectored" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write_vectored"><code>poll_write_vectored</code></a>\nimplementation, code using it may want to avoid the method all together\nand coalesce writes into a single buffer for higher performance.</p>',
     '<p>如果写入器未覆盖默认的 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html#method.poll_write_vectored" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_write_vectored"><code>poll_write_vectored</code></a> 实现，则使用它的代码可能希望完全避免该方法，并将写入合并到单个缓冲区中以获得更高的性能。</p>'),
    ('<p>The default implementation returns <code>false</code>.</p>', '<p>默认实现返回 <code>false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to specifying <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nMaxInstances</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于指定 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winbase/nf-winbase-createnamedpipea"><code>nMaxInstances</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>', '<p><strong>示例：</strong></p>'),
    ('<p>The current value will be considered seen by the receiver.</p>',
     '<p>当前值将被接收者视为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>If flushing cannot immediately complete, this method returns\n<code>Poll::Pending</code> and arranges for the current task (via\n<code>cx.waker()</code>) to receive a notification when the object can make\nprogress towards flushing.</p>',
     '<p>如果刷新无法立即完成，此方法将返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排当前任务（通过 <code>cx.waker()</code>）在对象能够推进刷新时收到通知。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 17: LocalSet (26 items) ============
    ('<p>A set of tasks which are executed on the same thread.</p>',
     '<p>在同一线程上执行的任务的集合。</p>'),
    ('<p>In some cases, it is necessary to run one or more futures that do not\nimplement <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a> and thus are unsafe to send between threads. In these\ncases, a <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet">local task set</a> may be used to schedule one or more <code>!Send</code>\nfutures to run together on the same thread.</p>',
     '<p>在某些情况下，有必要运行一个或多个未实现 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a> 的 future，因此在线程之间发送它们是不安全的。在这些情况下，可以使用<a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet">本地任务集</a>来调度一个或多个 <code>!Send</code> future 在同一线程上一起运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>To spawn <code>!Send</code> futures, we can use a local task set to schedule them\non the thread calling <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>. When running inside of the\nlocal task set, we can use <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>task::spawn_local</code></a>, which can spawn\n<code>!Send</code> futures. For example:</p>',
     '<p>要生成 <code>!Send</code> future，我们可以使用本地任务集来在调用 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> 的线程上调度它们。在本地任务集中运行时，我们可以使用 <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>task::spawn_local</code></a>，它可以生成 <code>!Send</code> future。例如：</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <code>run_until</code> method can only be used in <code>#[tokio::main]</code>,\n<code>#[tokio::test]</code> or directly inside a call to <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>. It\ncannot be used inside a task spawned with <code>tokio::spawn</code>.</p>',
     '<p><strong>注意：</strong><code>run_until</code> 方法只能在 <code>#[tokio::main]</code>、<code>#[tokio::test]</code> 中使用，或者直接在 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> 调用中使用。它不能在通过 <code>tokio::spawn</code> 生成的任务内部使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Additionally, a <code>LocalSet</code> itself implements <code>Future</code>, completing when\n<em>all</em> tasks spawned on the <code>LocalSet</code> complete. This can be used to run\nseveral futures on a <code>LocalSet</code> and drive the whole set until they\ncomplete. For example,</p>',
     '<p>此外，<code>LocalSet</code> 本身实现了 <code>Future</code>，当在 <code>LocalSet</code> 上生成的<em>所有</em>任务都完成时完成。这可用于在 <code>LocalSet</code> 上运行多个 future 并驱动整个集合直至它们完成。例如：</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Note:</strong> Awaiting a <code>LocalSet</code> can only be done inside\n<code>#[tokio::main]</code>, <code>#[tokio::test]</code> or directly inside a call to\n<a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>. It cannot be used inside a task spawned with\n<code>tokio::spawn</code>.</p>',
     '<p><strong>注意：</strong>等待 <code>LocalSet</code> 只能在 <code>#[tokio::main]</code>、<code>#[tokio::test]</code> 中进行，或者直接在 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> 调用中进行。它不能在通过 <code>tokio::spawn</code> 生成的任务内部使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The two methods mentioned above cannot be used inside <code>tokio::spawn</code>, so\nto spawn <code>!Send</code> futures from inside <code>tokio::spawn</code>, we need to do\nsomething else. The solution is to create the <code>LocalSet</code> somewhere else,\nand communicate with it using an <a href="../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> channel.</p>',
     '<p>上面提到的两个方法不能在 <code>tokio::spawn</code> 内部使用，因此要在 <code>tokio::spawn</code> 内部生成 <code>!Send</code> future，我们需要采用其他方法。解决方案是在其他地方创建 <code>LocalSet</code>，并使用 <a href="../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc</code></a> 通道与之通信。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> method will spawn tasks on the <code>LocalSet</code> whose\ncontext you are inside.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> 方法将在你所处的上下文中的 <code>LocalSet</code> 上生成任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawns a <code>!Send</code> task onto the local task set.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>!Send</code> 任务生成本地任务集上。</p>'),
    ('<p>This task is guaranteed to be run on the current thread.</p>',
     '<p>此任务保证在当前线程上运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike the free function <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a>, this method may be used to\nspawn local tasks when the <code>LocalSet</code> is <em>not</em> running. The provided\nfuture will start running once the <code>LocalSet</code> is next started, even if\nyou don’t await the returned <code>JoinHandle</code>.</p>',
     '<p>与自由函数 <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> 不同，此方法可在 <code>LocalSet</code> <em>未</em>运行时用于生成本地任务。一旦下次启动 <code>LocalSet</code>，所提供的 future 将开始运行，即使你没有等待返回的 <code>JoinHandle</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs a future to completion on the provided runtime, driving any local\nfutures spawned on this task set on the current thread.</p>',
     '<p>在所提供的运行时上运行 future 直至完成，并在当前线程上驱动此任务集上生成的任何本地 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runs the given future on the runtime, blocking until it is\ncomplete, and yielding its resolved result. Any tasks or timers which\nthe future spawns internally will be executed on the runtime. The future\nmay also call <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> to <code>spawn_local</code> additional local futures on the\ncurrent thread.</p>',
     '<p>此函数在运行时上运行给定的 future，阻塞直至完成，并产生其已解析的结果。future 在内部生成的任何任务或计时器都将在运行时上执行。该 future 也可以调用 <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> 在当前线程上 <code>spawn_local</code> 额外的本地 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method should not be called from an asynchronous context.</p>',
     '<p>此方法不应在异步上下文中调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function panics if the executor is at capacity, if the provided\nfuture panics, or if called within an asynchronous execution context.</p>',
     '<p>如果执行器已满、所提供的 future 发生 panic，或者在异步执行上下文中调用，则此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since this function internally calls <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>, and drives\nfutures in the local task set inside that call to <code>block_on</code>, the local\nfutures may not use <a href="fn@crate::task::block_in_place">in-place blocking</a>. If a blocking call needs to be\nissued from a local task, the <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> API may be used instead.</p>',
     '<p>由于此函数在内部调用 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>，并在 <code>block_on</code> 调用内部驱动本地任务集中的 future，因此本地 future 不能使用<a href="fn@crate::task::block_in_place">就地阻塞</a>。如果需要从本地任务发出阻塞调用，则可以使用 <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> API。</p>'),
    ('<p>This returns a future that runs the given future with a local set,\nallowing it to call <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> to spawn additional <code>!Send</code> futures.\nAny local futures spawned on the local set will be driven in the\nbackground until the future passed to <code>run_until</code> completes. When the future\npassed to <code>run_until</code> finishes, any local futures which have not completed\nwill remain on the local set, and will be driven on subsequent calls to\n<code>run_until</code> or when <a href="#awaiting-a-localset">awaiting the local set</a> itself.</p>',
     '<p>此方法返回一个 future，它使用本地集运行给定的 future，允许它调用 <a href="fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>spawn_local</code></a> 生成额外的 <code>!Send</code> future。在本地集上生成的任何本地 future 都将在后台驱动，直至传递给 <code>run_until</code> 的 future 完成。当传递给 <code>run_until</code> 的 future 完成时，任何尚未完成的本地 future 将保留在本地集上，并将在后续对 <code>run_until</code> 的调用中或<a href="#awaiting-a-localset">等待本地集本身</a>时被驱动。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe when <code>future</code> is cancel safe.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>future</code> 可安全取消时，此方法是可安全取消的。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the <a href="../runtime/struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Id"><code>Id</code></a> of the current <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> runtime.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前 <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> 运行时的 <a href="../runtime/struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Id"><code>Id</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example, the following code will not compile:</p>',
     '<p>例如，以下代码将无法编译：</p>'),
    ('<p>The following example puts the <code>LocalSet</code> inside a new thread.</p>',
     '<p>下面的示例将 <code>LocalSet</code> 放在一个新线程中。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a new local task set.</p>', '<p>返回一个新的本地任务集。</p>'),
    ('<p>Enters the context of this <code>LocalSet</code>.</p>', '<p>进入此 <code>LocalSet</code> 的上下文。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example, this will panic:</p>', '<p>例如，这将会发生 panic：</p>'),
    ('<p>This, however, will not panic:</p>', '<p>但是，这不会发生 panic：</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs a future to completion on the local set, returning its output.</p>',
     '<p>在本地集上运行 future 直至完成，并返回其输出。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 18: watch Sender (26 items) ============
    ('<p>Sends values to the associated <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将值发送给关联的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates the sending-half of the <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code></a> channel.</p>',
     '<p>创建 <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch</code></a> 通道的发送端。</p>'),
    ('<p>See documentation of <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch::channel</code></a> for errors when calling this function.\nBeware that attempting to send a value when there are no receivers will\nreturn an error.</p>',
     '<p>有关调用此函数时的错误，请参阅 <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::watch"><code>watch::channel</code></a> 的文档。请注意，当没有接收者时尝试发送值将返回错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends a new value via the channel, notifying all receivers.</p>',
     '<p>通过通道发送一个新值，通知所有接收者。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method fails if the channel is closed, which is the case when\nevery receiver has been dropped. It is possible to reopen the channel\nusing the <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a> method. However, when <code>send</code> fails, the value\nisn’t made available for future receivers (but returned with the\n<a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a>).</p>',
     '<p>如果通道已关闭（即所有接收者都已 drop），则此方法将失败。可以使用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a> 方法重新打开通道。但是，当 <code>send</code> 失败时，该值不会提供给未来的接收者（但会随 <a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a> 返回）。</p>'),
    ('<p>To always make a new value available for future receivers, even if no\nreceiver currently exists, one of the other send methods\n(<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_if_modified" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_if_modified"><code>send_if_modified</code></a>, <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_modify" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_modify"><code>send_modify</code></a>, or <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_replace" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_replace"><code>send_replace</code></a>) can be\nused instead.</p>',
     '<p>为了始终为未来的接收者提供一个新值，即使当前没有接收者，也可以使用其他发送方法之一（<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_if_modified" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_if_modified"><code>send_if_modified</code></a>、<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_modify" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_modify"><code>send_modify</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_replace" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_replace"><code>send_replace</code></a>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>Modifies the watched value <strong>unconditionally</strong> in-place,\nnotifying all receivers.</p>',
     '<p>在原地<strong>无条件</strong>修改被监视的值，通知所有接收者。</p>'),
    ('<p>Prefer to use the more versatile function <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_if_modified" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_if_modified"><code>Self::send_if_modified()</code></a>\nif the value is only modified conditionally during the mutable borrow\nto prevent unneeded change notifications for unmodified values.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值仅在可变借用期间被有条件地修改，则首选使用更通用的函数 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send_if_modified" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::send_if_modified"><code>Self::send_if_modified()</code></a>，以防止对未修改的值发出不必要的更改通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Modifies the watched value <strong>conditionally</strong> in-place,\nnotifying all receivers only if modified.</p>',
     '<p>在原地<strong>有条件</strong>修改被监视的值，仅在修改后通知所有接收者。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>modify</code> closure must return <code>true</code> if the value has actually\nbeen modified during the mutable borrow. It should only return <code>false</code>\nif the value is guaranteed to be unmodified despite the mutable\nborrow.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值在可变借用期间确实已被修改，则 <code>modify</code> 闭包必须返回 <code>true</code>。仅当尽管进行了可变借用但保证该值未被修改时，它才应返回 <code>false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Receivers are only notified if the closure returned <code>true</code>. If the\nclosure has modified the value but returned <code>false</code> this results\nin a <em>silent modification</em>, i.e. the modified value will be visible\nin subsequent calls to <code>borrow</code>, but receivers will not receive\na change notification.</p>',
     '<p>仅当闭包返回 <code>true</code> 时，接收者才会收到通知。如果闭包已修改该值但返回了 <code>false</code>，则会导致<em>静默修改</em>，即修改后的值在后续对 <code>borrow</code> 的调用中可见，但接收者不会收到更改通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the result of the closure, i.e. <code>true</code> if the value has\nbeen modified and <code>false</code> otherwise.</p>',
     '<p>返回闭包的结果，即如果值已被修改则为 <code>true</code>，否则为 <code>false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sends a new value via the channel, notifying all receivers and returning\nthe previous value in the channel.</p>',
     '<p>通过通道发送一个新值，通知所有接收者，并返回通道中的上一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This can be useful for reusing the buffers inside a watched value.\nAdditionally, this method permits sending values even when there are no\nreceivers.</p>',
     '<p>这对于重用被监视值内部的缓冲区非常有用。此外，即使没有接收者，此方法也允许发送值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the most recently sent value</p>',
     '<p>返回对最近发送值的引用</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if the channel has been closed. This happens when all receivers\nhave dropped.</p>',
     '<p>检查通道是否已关闭。当所有接收者都已 drop 时会发生这种情况。</p>'),
    ('<p>Completes when all receivers have dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当所有接收者都已 drop 时完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This allows the producer to get notified when interest in the produced\nvalues is canceled and immediately stop doing work. Once a channel is\nclosed, the only way to reopen it is to call <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a> to\nget a new receiver.</p>',
     '<p>这允许生产者在对所产生值的兴趣被取消时收到通知，并立即停止工作。通道关闭后，重新打开它的唯一方法是调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a> 以获取新的接收者。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the channel becomes closed for a brief amount of time (e.g., the last\nreceiver is dropped and then <code>subscribe</code> is called), then this call to\n<code>closed</code> might return, but it is also possible that it does not “notice”\nthat the channel was closed for a brief amount of time.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道在短时间内关闭（例如，最后一个接收者被 drop，然后调用 <code>subscribe</code>），那么此次对 <code>closed</code> 的调用可能会返回，但也可能不会“注意到”通道在短时间内已关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> connected to this <code>Sender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个连接到此 <code>Sender</code> 的新 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>All messages sent before this call to <code>subscribe</code> are initially marked\nas seen by the new <code>Receiver</code>.</p>',
     '<p>在此次调用 <code>subscribe</code> 之前发送的所有消息最初都被新的 <code>Receiver</code> 标记为已读。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method can be called even if there are no other receivers. In this\ncase, the channel is reopened.</p>',
     '<p>即使没有其他接收者，也可以调用此方法。在这种情况下，通道将被重新打开。</p>'),
    ('<p>The new channel will receive messages sent on this <code>Sender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>新通道将接收通过此 <code>Sender</code> 发送的消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>The most recent message is considered seen by the channel, so this test\nis guaranteed to pass.</p>',
     '<p>最近的消息被视为已被通道读取，因此保证此测试通过。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of receivers that currently exist.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存在的接收者数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of senders that currently exist.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存在的发送者数量。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 19: Mutex (26 items) ============
    ('<p>An asynchronous <code>Mutex</code>-like type.</p>',
     '<p>异步的类似 <code>Mutex</code> 的类型。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type acts similarly to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>std::sync::Mutex</code></a>, with two major\ndifferences: <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> is an async method so does not block, and the lock\nguard is designed to be held across <code>.await</code> points.</p>',
     '<p>此类型的行为类似于 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>std::sync::Mutex</code></a>，但有两个主要区别：<a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> 是一个异步方法，因此不会阻塞，并且锁保护器被设计为可以跨 <code>.await</code> 点持有。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio’s Mutex operates on a guaranteed FIFO basis.\nThis means that the order in which tasks call the <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> method is\nthe exact order in which they will acquire the lock.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 的 Mutex 在保证 FIFO（先进先出）的基础上运行。这意味着任务调用 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> 方法的顺序正是它们获取锁的顺序。</p>'),
    ('<p>Contrary to popular belief, it is ok and often preferred to use the ordinary\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> from the standard library in asynchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>与普遍的看法相反，在异步代码中使用标准库的普通 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> 是可以的，而且通常是首选。</p>'),
    ('<p>The feature that the async mutex offers over the blocking mutex is the\nability to keep it locked across an <code>.await</code> point. This makes the async\nmutex more expensive than the blocking mutex, so the blocking mutex should\nbe preferred in the cases where it can be used. The primary use case for the\nasync mutex is to provide shared mutable access to IO resources such as a\ndatabase connection. If the value behind the mutex is just data, it’s\nusually appropriate to use a blocking mutex such as the one in the standard\nlibrary or <a href="https://docs.rs/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>异步互斥锁相对于阻塞互斥锁提供的特性是能够跨 <code>.await</code> 点保持锁定。这使得异步互斥锁比阻塞互斥锁更昂贵，因此在使用阻塞互斥锁可行的场景下应首选阻塞互斥锁。异步互斥锁的主要用例是为 IO 资源（例如数据库连接）提供共享的可变访问。如果互斥锁后面的值只是数据，通常适合使用阻塞互斥锁，例如标准库中的互斥锁或 <a href="https://docs.rs/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that, although the compiler will not prevent the std <code>Mutex</code> from holding\nits guard across <code>.await</code> points in situations where the task is not movable\nbetween threads, this virtually never leads to correct concurrent code in\npractice as it can easily lead to deadlocks.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，尽管编译器不会阻止 std <code>Mutex</code> 在任务在线程之间不可移动的情况下跨 <code>.await</code> 点持有其保护器，但在实践中这几乎从不会产生正确的并发代码，因为它很容易导致死锁。</p>'),
    ('<p>A common pattern is to wrap the <code>Arc&lt;Mutex&lt;...&gt;&gt;</code> in a struct that provides\nnon-async methods for performing operations on the data within, and only\nlock the mutex inside these methods. The <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/mini-redis/blob/master/src/db.rs">mini-redis</a> example provides an\nillustration of this pattern.</p>',
     '<p>一种常见的模式是将 <code>Arc&lt;Mutex&lt;...&gt;&gt;</code> 包装在一个结构体中，该结构体提供用于对其中的数据执行操作的非异步方法，并且仅在这些方法内部锁定互斥锁。<a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/mini-redis/blob/master/src/db.rs">mini-redis</a> 示例提供了此模式的说明。</p>'),
    ('<p>Additionally, when you <em>do</em> want shared access to an IO resource, it is\noften better to spawn a task to manage the IO resource, and to use message\npassing to communicate with that task.</p>',
     '<p>此外，当你<em>确实</em>需要对 IO 资源的共享访问时，通常更好的做法是生成一个任务来管理 IO 资源，并使用消息传递与该任务通信。</p>'),
    ('<p>There are a few things of note here to pay attention to in this example.</p>',
     '<p>在此示例中有几点需要注意。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio’s Mutex works in a simple FIFO (first in, first out) style where all\ncalls to <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> complete in the order they were performed. In that way the\nMutex is “fair” and predictable in how it distributes the locks to inner\ndata. Locks are released and reacquired after every iteration, so basically,\neach thread goes to the back of the line after it increments the value once.\nNote that there’s some unpredictability to the timing between when the\nthreads are started, but once they are going they alternate predictably.\nFinally, since there is only a single valid lock at any given time, there is\nno possibility of a race condition when mutating the inner value.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 的 Mutex 以简单的 FIFO（先进先出）方式工作，其中所有对 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> 的调用都按其执行的顺序完成。这样，Mutex 在如何将锁分配给内部数据方面是“公平”且可预测的。每次迭代后都会释放并重新获取锁，所以基本上，每个线程在将值递增一次后都会回到队尾。请注意，线程启动的时序存在一些不可预测性，但一旦它们开始运行，它们就会以可预测的方式交替。最后，由于任何给定时间都只有一个有效的锁，因此在变更内部值时不可能发生竞态条件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that in contrast to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>std::sync::Mutex</code></a>, this implementation does not\npoison the mutex when a thread holding the <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a> panics. In such a\ncase, the mutex will be unlocked. If the panic is caught, this might leave\nthe data protected by the mutex in an inconsistent state.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/poison/mutex/struct.Mutex.html" title="struct std::sync::poison::mutex::Mutex"><code>std::sync::Mutex</code></a> 相反，当持有 <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a> 的线程发生 panic 时，此实现不会使互斥锁中毒。在这种情况下，互斥锁将被解锁。如果 panic 被捕获，则受互斥锁保护的数据可能会处于不一致的状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>Mutex</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Mutex::new"><code>Mutex::new</code></a> should be used to create\nan instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定特性</a>时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>Mutex</code> 将不会被检测。因此，它将不会出现在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::Mutex::new"><code>Mutex::new</code></a> 创建一个已检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Locks this mutex, causing the current task to yield until the lock has\nbeen acquired.  When the lock has been acquired, function returns a\n<a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>锁定此互斥锁，使当前任务让出，直到获取到锁为止。获取锁后，函数返回一个 <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>lock</code> makes you lose your place in\nthe queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发锁。取消对 <code>lock</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blockingly locks this <code>Mutex</code>. When the lock has been acquired, function returns a\n<a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>阻塞地锁定此 <code>Mutex</code>。获取锁后，函数返回一个 <a href="struct.MutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MutexGuard"><code>MutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is intended for use cases where you\nneed to use this mutex in asynchronous code as well as in synchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>此方法适用于需要在异步代码以及同步代码中使用此互斥锁的场景。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blockingly locks this <code>Mutex</code>. When the lock has been acquired, function returns an\n<a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>阻塞地锁定此 <code>Mutex</code>。获取锁后，函数返回一个 <a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.blocking_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::blocking_lock"><code>Mutex::blocking_lock</code></a>, except that the returned\nguard references the <code>Mutex</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by borrowing\nit. Therefore, the <code>Mutex</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to call this\nmethod, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime, as it keeps\nthe <code>Mutex</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.blocking_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::blocking_lock"><code>Mutex::blocking_lock</code></a> 相同，只是返回的保护器使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 而不是通过借用引用 <code>Mutex</code>。因此，<code>Mutex</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中才能调用此方法，并且保护器将在 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期内有效，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>Mutex</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>Locks this mutex, causing the current task to yield until the lock has\nbeen acquired. When the lock has been acquired, this returns an\n<a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>锁定此互斥锁，使当前任务让出，直到获取到锁为止。获取锁后，此方法返回一个 <a href="struct.OwnedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>Mutex::lock</code></a>, except that the returned\nguard references the <code>Mutex</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by borrowing\nit. Therefore, the <code>Mutex</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to call this\nmethod, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime, as it keeps\nthe <code>Mutex</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>Mutex::lock</code></a> 相同，只是返回的保护器使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 而不是通过借用引用 <code>Mutex</code>。因此，<code>Mutex</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中才能调用此方法，并且保护器将在 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期内有效，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>Mutex</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>lock_owned</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用一个队列来按请求顺序公平地分发锁。取消对 <code>lock_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to acquire the lock, and returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a> if the\nlock is currently held somewhere else.</p>',
     '<p>尝试获取锁，如果锁当前在其他位置被持有，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since this call borrows the <code>Mutex</code> mutably, no actual locking needs to\ntake place – the mutable borrow statically guarantees no locks exist.</p>',
     '<p>由于此调用可变地借用 <code>Mutex</code>，因此无需进行实际锁定——可变借用在静态上保证不存在锁。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to acquire the lock, and returns <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a> if the lock\nis currently held somewhere else.</p>',
     '<p>尝试获取锁，如果锁当前在其他位置被持有，则返回 <a href="struct.TryLockError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::TryLockError"><code>TryLockError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>Mutex::try_lock</code></a>, except that the\nreturned  guard references the <code>Mutex</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by\nborrowing it. Therefore, the <code>Mutex</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to call\nthis method, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime, as it\nkeeps the <code>Mutex</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>Mutex::try_lock</code></a> 相同，只是返回的保护器使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 而不是通过借用引用 <code>Mutex</code>。因此，<code>Mutex</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中才能调用此方法，并且保护器将在 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期内有效，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>Mutex</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes the mutex, returning the underlying data.</p>',
     '<p>消费互斥锁，返回底层数据。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 20: task/index (25 items) ============
    ('<p>Asynchronous green-threads.</p>', '<p>异步绿色线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <em>task</em> is a light weight, non-blocking unit of execution. A task is similar\nto an OS thread, but rather than being managed by the OS scheduler, they are\nmanaged by the <a href="../runtime/index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">Tokio runtime</a>. Another name for this general pattern is\n<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Green_threads">green threads</a>. If you are familiar with <a href="https://tour.golang.org/concurrency/1">Go’s goroutines</a>, <a href="https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/coroutines-overview.html">Kotlin’s\ncoroutines</a>, or <a href="http://erlang.org/doc/getting_started/conc_prog.html#processes">Erlang’s processes</a>, you can think of Tokio’s tasks as\nsomething similar.</p>',
     '<p><em>任务</em>是一个轻量级、非阻塞的执行单元。任务类似于 OS 线程，但它们不是由 OS 调度器管理，而是由 <a href="../runtime/index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">Tokio 运行时</a>管理。这种通用模式的另一个名称是<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Green_threads">绿色线程</a>。如果你熟悉 <a href="https://tour.golang.org/concurrency/1">Go 的 goroutine</a>、<a href="https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/coroutines-overview.html">Kotlin 的协程</a>或 <a href="http://erlang.org/doc/getting_started/conc_prog.html#processes">Erlang 的进程</a>，则可以将 Tokio 的任务视为类似的东西。</p>'),
    ('<p>Key points about tasks include:</p>', '<p>关于任务的关键点包括：</p>'),
    ('<p>Tasks are <strong>light weight</strong>. Because tasks are scheduled by the Tokio\nruntime rather than the operating system, creating new tasks or switching\nbetween tasks does not require a context switch and has fairly low\noverhead. Creating, running, and destroying large numbers of tasks is\nquite cheap, especially compared to OS threads.</p>',
     '<p>任务是<strong>轻量级</strong>的。由于任务是由 Tokio 运行时而非操作系统调度的，因此创建新任务或在任务之间切换不需要上下文切换，开销相当低。创建、运行和销毁大量任务是相当廉价的，尤其是与 OS 线程相比。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tasks are scheduled <strong>cooperatively</strong>. Most operating systems implement\n<em>preemptive multitasking</em>. This is a scheduling technique where the\noperating system allows each thread to run for a period of time, and then\n<em>preempts</em> it, temporarily pausing that thread and switching to another.\nTasks, on the other hand, implement <em>cooperative multitasking</em>. In\ncooperative multitasking, a task is allowed to run until it <em>yields</em>,\nindicating to the Tokio runtime’s scheduler that it cannot currently\ncontinue executing. When a task yields, the Tokio runtime switches to\nexecuting the next task.</p>',
     '<p>任务被<strong>协作式</strong>调度。大多数操作系统实现<em>抢占式多任务</em>。这是一种调度技术，操作系统允许每个线程运行一段时间，然后<em>抢占</em>它，临时暂停该线程并切换到另一个线程。而任务实现的是<em>协作式多任务</em>。在协作式多任务中，任务被允许一直运行，直至它<em>让步</em>，向 Tokio 运行时的调度器表明它当前无法继续执行。当任务让步时，Tokio 运行时将切换执行下一个任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tasks are <strong>non-blocking</strong>. Typically, when an OS thread performs I/O or\nmust synchronize with another thread, it <em>blocks</em>, allowing the OS to\nschedule another thread. When a task cannot continue executing, it must\nyield instead, allowing the Tokio runtime to schedule another task. Tasks\nshould generally not perform system calls or other operations that could\nblock a thread, as this would prevent other tasks running on the same\nthread from executing as well. Instead, this module provides APIs for\nrunning blocking operations in an asynchronous context.</p>',
     '<p>任务是<strong>非阻塞</strong>的。通常，当 OS 线程执行 I/O 或必须与另一个线程同步时，它会<em>阻塞</em>，允许 OS 调度另一个线程。当任务无法继续执行时，它必须让步，从而允许 Tokio 运行时调度另一个任务。任务通常不应执行可能阻塞线程的系统调用或其他操作，因为这会阻止在同一线程上运行的其他任务的执行。相反，本模块提供了在异步上下文中运行阻塞操作的 API。</p>'),
    ('<p>This module provides the following APIs for working with tasks:</p>',
     '<p>本模块提供以下用于处理任务的 API：</p>'),
    ('<p>Perhaps the most important function in this module is <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a>. This\nfunction can be thought of as an async equivalent to the standard library’s\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a>. It takes an <code>async</code> block or other\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future">future</a>, and creates a new task to run that work concurrently:</p>',
     '<p>本模块中最重要的函数可能是 <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a>。可以将此函数视为标准库 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a> 的异步等价物。它接受一个 <code>async</code> 块或其他 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future">future</a>，并创建一个新任务以并发运行该工作：</p>'),
    ('<p>Like <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>std::thread::spawn</code></a>, <code>task::spawn</code> returns a <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> struct.\nA <code>JoinHandle</code> is itself a future which may be used to await the output of\nthe spawned task. For example:</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>std::thread::spawn</code></a> 一样，<code>task::spawn</code> 返回一个 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 结构体。<code>JoinHandle</code> 本身是一个 future，可用于等待已生成任务的输出。例如：</p>'),
    ('<p>Again, like <code>std::thread</code>’s <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/join_handle/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct std::thread::join_handle::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code> type</a>, if the spawned\ntask panics, awaiting its <code>JoinHandle</code> will return a <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a>. For\nexample:</p>',
     '<p>同样，与 <code>std::thread</code> 的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/join_handle/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct std::thread::join_handle::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code> 类型</a> 一样，如果已生成的任务发生 panic，则等待其 <code>JoinHandle</code> 将返回 <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a>。例如：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>spawn</code>, <code>JoinHandle</code>, and <code>JoinError</code> are present when the “rt”\nfeature flag is enabled.</p>',
     '<p>启用 “rt” 特性标志时，存在 <code>spawn</code>、<code>JoinHandle</code> 和 <code>JoinError</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawned tasks may be cancelled using the <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> or\n<a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::abort"><code>AbortHandle::abort</code></a> methods. When one of these methods are called, the\ntask is signalled to shut down next time it yields at an <code>.await</code> point. If\nthe task is already idle, then it will be shut down as soon as possible\nwithout running again before being shut down. Additionally, shutting down a\nTokio runtime (e.g. by returning from <code>#[tokio::main]</code>) immediately cancels\nall tasks on it.</p>',
     '<p>可以使用 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::abort"><code>AbortHandle::abort</code></a> 方法取消已生成的任务。当调用这些方法之一时，任务被发出信号，以在下次于 <code>.await</code> 点让步时关闭。如果任务已空闲，则它将在不再次运行的情况下尽快关闭。此外，关闭 Tokio 运行时（例如通过从 <code>#[tokio::main]</code> 返回）会立即取消其上的所有任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>When tasks are shut down, it will stop running at whichever <code>.await</code> it has\nyielded at. All local variables are destroyed by running their destructor.\nOnce shutdown has completed, awaiting the <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> will fail with a\n<a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">cancelled error</a>.</p>',
     '<p>当任务关闭时，它将在其所让步的 <code>.await</code> 处停止运行。所有局部变量都通过运行其析构函数被销毁。一旦关闭完成，等待 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 将失败并返回<a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">已取消错误</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that aborting a task does not guarantee that it fails with a cancelled\nerror, since it may complete normally first. For example, if the task does\nnot yield to the runtime at any point between the call to <code>abort</code> and the\nend of the task, then the <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> will instead report that the task\nexited normally.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，中止任务并不能保证它会以已取消错误失败，因为它可能先正常完成。例如，如果任务在 <code>abort</code> 调用与任务结束之间的任何时候都没有向运行时让步，那么 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 将改为报告任务正常退出。</p>'),
    ('<p>Be aware that calls to <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> just schedule the task for\ncancellation, and will return before the cancellation has completed. To wait\nfor cancellation to complete, wait for the task to finish by awaiting the\n<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>. Similarly, the <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::is_finished"><code>JoinHandle::is_finished</code></a> method does not\nreturn <code>true</code> until the cancellation has finished.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，对 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> 的调用只是将任务调度为取消，并将在取消完成之前返回。要等待取消完成，请通过等待 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 等待任务完成。同样，<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::is_finished"><code>JoinHandle::is_finished</code></a> 方法在取消完成之前不会返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> multiple times has the same effect as calling\nit once.</p>',
     '<p>多次调用 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a> 与调用一次的效果相同。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio also provides an <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>, which is like the <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>,\nexcept that it does not provide a mechanism to wait for the task to finish.\nEach task can only have one <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>, but it can have more than one\n<a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 还提供 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>，它类似于 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>，但不提供等待任务完成的机制。每个任务只能有一个 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>，但可以有多个 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::AbortHandle"><code>AbortHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>As we discussed above, code running in asynchronous tasks should not perform\noperations that can block. A blocking operation performed in a task running\non a thread that is also running other tasks would block the entire thread,\npreventing other tasks from running.</p>',
     '<p>正如我们上面讨论的，在异步任务中运行的代码不应执行可能阻塞的操作。在也运行其他任务的线程上运行的任务中执行的阻塞操作将阻塞整个线程，从而阻止其他任务的运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Instead, Tokio provides two APIs for running blocking operations in an\nasynchronous context: <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a> and <a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>相反，Tokio 提供了两个用于在异步上下文中运行阻塞操作的 API：<a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a> 和 <a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Be aware that if you call a non-async method from async code, that non-async\nmethod is still inside the asynchronous context, so you should also avoid\nblocking operations there. This includes destructors of objects destroyed in\nasync code.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果你从异步代码中调用非异步方法，则该非异步方法仍处于异步上下文中，因此你也应避免在其中进行阻塞操作。这包括在异步代码中销毁的对象的析构函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>task::spawn_blocking</code> function is similar to the <code>task::spawn</code> function\ndiscussed in the previous section, but rather than spawning a\n<em>non-blocking</em> future on the Tokio runtime, it instead spawns a\n<em>blocking</em> function on a dedicated thread pool for blocking tasks. For\nexample:</p>',
     '<p><code>task::spawn_blocking</code> 函数类似于上一节讨论的 <code>task::spawn</code> 函数，但它不是在 Tokio 运行时上生成<em>非阻塞</em> future，而是在专用于阻塞任务的线程池上生成<em>阻塞</em>函数。例如：</p>'),
    ('<p>Just like <code>task::spawn</code>, <code>task::spawn_blocking</code> returns a <code>JoinHandle</code>\nwhich we can use to await the result of the blocking operation:</p>',
     '<p>就像 <code>task::spawn</code> 一样，<code>task::spawn_blocking</code> 返回一个 <code>JoinHandle</code>，我们可以使用它等待阻塞操作的结果：</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <a href="../runtime/index.html#threaded-scheduler">multi-threaded runtime</a>, the <a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a>\nfunction is also available. Like <code>task::spawn_blocking</code>, this function\nallows running a blocking operation from an asynchronous context. Unlike\n<code>spawn_blocking</code>, however, <code>block_in_place</code> works by transitioning the\n<em>current</em> worker thread to a blocking thread, moving other tasks running on\nthat thread to another worker thread. This can improve performance by avoiding\ncontext switches.</p>',
     '<p>使用<a href="../runtime/index.html#threaded-scheduler">多线程运行时</a>时，<a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a> 函数也可用。与 <code>task::spawn_blocking</code> 一样，此函数允许从异步上下文运行阻塞操作。但是，与 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 不同，<code>block_in_place</code> 通过将<em>当前</em>工作线程转换为阻塞线程来工作，并将该线程上运行的其他任务移动到另一个工作线程。这可以通过避免上下文切换来提高性能。</p>'),
    ('<p>In addition, this module provides a <a href="fn.yield_now.html" title="fn tokio::task::yield_now"><code>task::yield_now</code></a> async function\nthat is analogous to the standard library’s <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.yield_now.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::yield_now"><code>thread::yield_now</code></a>. Calling\nand <code>await</code>ing this function will cause the current task to yield to the\nTokio runtime’s scheduler, allowing other tasks to be\nscheduled. Eventually, the yielding task will be polled again, allowing it\nto execute. For example:</p>',
     '<p>此外，本模块还提供了一个 <a href="fn.yield_now.html" title="fn tokio::task::yield_now"><code>task::yield_now</code></a> 异步函数，它类似于标准库的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.yield_now.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::yield_now"><code>thread::yield_now</code></a>。调用并 <code>await</code> 此函数将使当前任务向 Tokio 运行时的调度器让步，从而允许调度其他任务。最终，让步的任务将被再次 poll，从而允许它执行。例如：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 21: oneshot Receiver (25 items) ============
    ('<p>Receives a value from the associated <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>从关联的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 接收一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel has no <code>recv</code> method because the receiver itself implements the\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> trait. To receive a <code>Result&lt;T, </code><a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::error::RecvError"><code>error::RecvError</code></a><code>&gt;</code>, <code>.await</code> the <code>Receiver</code> object directly.</p>',
     '<p>此通道没有 <code>recv</code> 方法，因为接收者本身实现了 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> trait。要接收 <code>Result&lt;T, </code><a href="error/struct.RecvError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::error::RecvError"><code>error::RecvError</code></a><code>&gt;</code>，请直接 <code>.await</code> <code>Receiver</code> 对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>poll</code> method on the <code>Future</code> trait is allowed to spuriously return\n<code>Poll::Pending</code> even if the message has been sent. If such a spurious\nfailure happens, then the caller will be woken when the spurious failure has\nbeen resolved so that the caller can attempt to receive the message again.\nNote that receiving such a wakeup does not guarantee that the next call will\nsucceed — it could fail with another spurious failure. (A spurious failure\ndoes not mean that the message is lost. It is just delayed.)</p>',
     '<p>即使消息已发送，<code>Future</code> trait 上的 <code>poll</code> 方法也可能伪返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>。如果发生此类伪失败，则当伪失败已解决时，调用者将被唤醒，以便调用者可以再次尝试接收消息。请注意，收到此类唤醒并不能保证下一次调用会成功——它可能以另一个伪失败而失败。（伪失败并不意味着消息已丢失。它只是被延迟了。）</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Receiver</code> is cancel safe. If it is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, it is guaranteed that no message was received on this\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p><code>Receiver</code> 可安全取消。如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将其用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证此通道上未接收到任何消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>To use a <code>Receiver</code> in a <code>tokio::select!</code> loop, add <code>&amp;mut</code> in front of the\nchannel.</p>',
     '<p>要在 <code>tokio::select!</code> 循环中使用 <code>Receiver</code>，请在通道前面添加 <code>&amp;mut</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Prevents the associated <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handle from sending a value.</p>',
     '<p>阻止关联的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄发送值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Any <code>send</code> operation which happens after calling <code>close</code> is guaranteed\nto fail. After calling <code>close</code>, <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> should be called to\nreceive a value if one was sent <strong>before</strong> the call to <code>close</code>\ncompleted.</p>',
     '<p>调用 <code>close</code> 之后发生的任何 <code>send</code> 操作都保证会失败。调用 <code>close</code> 后，如果有一个值在调用 <code>close</code> <strong>之前</strong>已发送，则应调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> 来接收该值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is useful to perform a graceful shutdown and ensure that a\nvalue will not be sent into the channel and never received.</p>',
     '<p>此函数可用于执行优雅关闭，并确保不会将值发送到通道中而永远不会被接收。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>close</code> is no-op if a message is already received or the channel\nis already closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果已接收到消息或通道已关闭，则 <code>close</code> 是空操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Prevent a value from being sent</p>', '<p>防止值被发送</p>'),
    ('<p>Receive a value sent <strong>before</strong> calling <code>close</code></p>',
     '<p>接收在调用 <code>close</code> <strong>之前</strong>发送的值</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if this receiver is terminated.</p>', '<p>检查此接收者是否已终止。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function returns true if this receiver has already yielded a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/poll/enum.Poll.html#variant.Ready" title="variant core::task::poll::Poll::Ready"><code>Poll::Ready</code></a> result.\nIf so, this receiver should no longer be polled.</p>',
     '<p>如果此接收者已产生一个 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/poll/enum.Poll.html#variant.Ready" title="variant core::task::poll::Poll::Ready"><code>Poll::Ready</code></a> 结果，则此函数返回 true。如果是这样，则不应再对此接收者进行 poll。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sending a value and polling it.</p>', '<p>发送一个值并对其轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Dropping sender。</p>', '<p>Drop sender。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is not necessarily safe to poll an empty receiver, which may have\nalready yielded a value. Use <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.is_terminated" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::is_terminated"><code>is_terminated()</code></a>\nto check whether or not a receiver can be safely polled, instead.</p>',
     '<p>对一个空的接收者（可能已产生一个值）进行 poll 不一定是安全的。请改用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.is_terminated" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::is_terminated"><code>is_terminated()</code></a> 来检查接收者是否可以安全地 poll。</p>'),
    ('<p>Terminated channels are empty.</p>', '<p>已终止的通道为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to receive a value.</p>', '<p>尝试接收一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a pending value exists in the channel, it is returned. If no value\nhas been sent, the current task <strong>will not</strong> be registered for\nfuture notification.</p>',
     '<p>如果通道中存在挂起的值，则返回该值。如果尚未发送任何值，则当前任务<strong>不会</strong>被注册以接收未来的通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is useful to call from outside the context of an\nasynchronous task.</p>',
     '<p>此函数在异步任务上下文之外调用时非常有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that unlike the <code>poll</code> method, the <code>try_recv</code> method cannot fail\nspuriously. Any send or close event that happens before this call to\n<code>try_recv</code> will be correctly returned to the caller.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，与 <code>poll</code> 方法不同，<code>try_recv</code> 方法不会伪失败。在此次调用 <code>try_recv</code> 之前发生的任何发送或关闭事件都将正确返回给调用者。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>try_recv</code> before a value is sent, then after.</p>',
     '<p>在值发送之前调用 <code>try_recv</code>，然后在值发送之后调用。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>try_recv</code> when the sender dropped before sending a value</p>',
     '<p>当 sender 在发送值之前被 drop 时调用 <code>try_recv</code></p>'),
    ('<p>Sending a value.</p>', '<p>发送一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Drop sender。</p>', '<p>Drop sender。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example:</p>', '<p>例如：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 22: ReadBuf (25 items) ============
    ('<p>This type is a sort of “double cursor”. It tracks three regions in the\nbuffer: a region at the beginning of the buffer that has been logically\nfilled with data, a region that has been initialized at some point but not\nyet logically filled, and a region at the end that may be uninitialized.\nThe filled region is guaranteed to be a subset of the initialized region.</p>',
     '<p>此类型是一种“双游标”。它跟踪缓冲区中的三个区域：缓冲区开头已逻辑填充数据的区域、已在某个时刻初始化但尚未逻辑填充的区域，以及末尾可能未初始化的区域。填充区域保证是初始化区域的子集。</p>'),
    ('<p>In summary, the contents of the buffer can be visualized as:</p>',
     '<p>总之，缓冲区的内容可以可视化为：</p>'),
    ('<p>It is undefined behavior to de-initialize any bytes from the uninitialized\nregion, since it is merely unknown whether this region is uninitialized or\nnot, and if part of it turns out to be initialized, it must stay initialized.</p>',
     '<p>从未初始化区域取消初始化任何字节属于未定义行为，因为这仅仅是未知此区域是否未初始化，并且如果其一部分实际上是已初始化的，则它必须保持已初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>ReadBuf</code> from a fully initialized buffer.</p>',
     '<p>从完全初始化的缓冲区创建一个新的 <code>ReadBuf</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>ReadBuf</code> from a buffer that may be uninitialized.</p>',
     '<p>从可能未初始化的缓冲区创建一个新的 <code>ReadBuf</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The internal cursor will mark the entire buffer as uninitialized. If\nthe buffer is known to be partially initialized, then use <code>assume_init</code>\nto move the internal cursor.</p>',
     '<p>内部游标会将整个缓冲区标记为未初始化。如果已知缓冲区已部分初始化，则使用 <code>assume_init</code> 移动内部游标。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a new <code>ReadBuf</code> comprised of the unfilled section up to <code>n</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个新的 <code>ReadBuf</code>，由最多 <code>n</code> 的未填充部分组成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the entire buffer, without ensuring that it has been fully\ninitialized.</p>',
     '<p>返回对整个缓冲区的可变引用，而不确保它已完全初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>The elements between 0 and <code>self.filled().len()</code> are filled, and those between 0 and\n<code>self.initialized().len()</code> are initialized (and so can be converted to a <code>&amp;mut [u8]</code>).</p>',
     '<p>0 到 <code>self.filled().len()</code> 之间的元素是已填充的，而 0 到 <code>self.initialized().len()</code> 之间的元素是已初始化的（因此可以转换为 <code>&amp;mut [u8]</code>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller of this method must ensure that these invariants are upheld. For example, if the\ncaller initializes some of the uninitialized section of the buffer, it must call\n<a href="struct.ReadBuf.html#method.assume_init" title="method tokio::io::ReadBuf::assume_init"><code>assume_init</code></a> with the number of bytes initialized.</p>',
     '<p>此方法的调用者必须确保这些不变量得到遵守。例如，如果调用者初始化了缓冲区未初始化部分的某些内容，则必须使用已初始化的字节数调用 <a href="struct.ReadBuf.html#method.assume_init" title="method tokio::io::ReadBuf::assume_init"><code>assume_init</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the unfilled part of the buffer without ensuring that it has been fully\ninitialized.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区未填充部分的可变引用，而不确保它已完全初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the unfilled part of the buffer, ensuring it is fully initialized.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区未填充部分的可变引用，确保它已完全初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since <code>ReadBuf</code> tracks the region of the buffer that has been initialized, this is effectively “free” after\nthe first use.</p>',
     '<p>由于 <code>ReadBuf</code> 跟踪缓冲区中已初始化的区域，因此在首次使用之后，这实际上是“免费”的。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the first <code>n</code> bytes of the unfilled part of the buffer, ensuring it is\nfully initialized.</p>',
     '<p>返回对缓冲区未填充部分前 <code>n</code> 个字节的可变引用，确保它已完全初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Panics if <code>self.remaining()</code> is less than <code>n</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>self.remaining()</code> 小于 <code>n</code>，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Clears the buffer, resetting the filled region to empty.</p>',
     '<p>清空缓冲区，将填充区域重置为空。</p>'),
    ('<p>The number of initialized bytes is not changed, and the contents of the buffer are not modified.</p>',
     '<p>已初始化的字节数不变，缓冲区的内容也不会被修改。</p>'),
    ('<p>Advances the size of the filled region of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>推进缓冲区填充区域的大小。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the size of the filled region of the buffer.</p>',
     '<p>设置缓冲区填充区域的大小。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that this can be used to <em>shrink</em> the filled region of the buffer in addition to growing it (for\nexample, by a <code>AsyncRead</code> implementation that compresses data in-place).</p>',
     '<p>请注意，除了可以扩大缓冲区填充区域之外，这还可用于<em>缩小</em>它（例如，由就地压缩数据的 <code>AsyncRead</code> 实现使用）。</p>'),
    ('<p>Asserts that the first <code>n</code> unfilled bytes of the buffer are initialized.</p>',
     '<p>断言缓冲区的前 <code>n</code> 个未填充字节已初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>ReadBuf</code> assumes that bytes are never de-initialized, so this method does nothing when called with fewer\nbytes than are already known to be initialized.</p>',
     '<p><code>ReadBuf</code> 假定字节永远不会被取消初始化，因此当使用少于已知已初始化的字节数调用此方法时，它不会执行任何操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller must ensure that <code>n</code> unfilled bytes of the buffer have already been initialized.</p>',
     '<p>调用者必须确保缓冲区的 <code>n</code> 个未填充字节已初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Appends data to the buffer, advancing the written position and possibly also the initialized position.</p>',
     '<p>将数据追加到缓冲区，推进写入位置，可能也会推进初始化位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Panics if <code>self.remaining()</code> is less than <code>buf.len()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>self.remaining()</code> 小于 <code>buf.len()</code>，则会发生 panic。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 23: TcpListener (24 items) ============
    ('<p>You can accept a new connection by using the <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept"><code>accept</code></a>\nmethod.</p>',
     '<p>你可以使用 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.accept" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::accept"><code>accept</code></a> 方法接受新连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>TcpListener</code> can be turned into a <code>Stream</code> with <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.TcpListenerStream.html"><code>TcpListenerStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><code>TcpListener</code> 可以通过 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.TcpListenerStream.html"><code>TcpListenerStream</code></a> 转换为 <code>Stream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The socket will be closed when the value is dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当该值被 drop 时，套接字将被关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that accepting a connection can lead to various errors and not all\nof them are necessarily fatal ‒ for example having too many open file\ndescriptors or the other side closing the connection while it waits in\nan accept queue. These would terminate the stream if not handled in any\nway.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，接受连接可能会导致各种错误，并非所有错误都一定是致命的——例如打开的文件描述符过多，或者对端在等待接受队列时关闭连接。如果不以任何方式处理这些情况，它们将终止流。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>TcpListener</code>, which will be bound to the specified address.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <code>TcpListener</code>，它将绑定到指定的地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>The returned listener is ready for accepting connections.</p>',
     '<p>返回的监听器已准备好接受连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>The address type can be any implementor of the <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait.\nIf <code>addr</code> yields multiple addresses, bind will be attempted with each of\nthe addresses until one succeeds and returns the listener. If none of\nthe addresses succeed in creating a listener, the error returned from\nthe last attempt (the last address) is returned.</p>',
     '<p>地址类型可以是 <a href="trait.ToSocketAddrs.html" title="trait tokio::net::ToSocketAddrs"><code>ToSocketAddrs</code></a> trait 的任何实现者。如果 <code>addr</code> 产生多个地址，则会依次尝试与每个地址进行绑定，直到其中一个成功并返回监听器。如果没有任何地址成功创建监听器，则返回最后一次尝试（最后一个地址）的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function sets the <code>SO_REUSEADDR</code> option on the socket on Unix.</p>',
     '<p>此函数在 Unix 上的套接字上设置 <code>SO_REUSEADDR</code> 选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>To configure the socket before binding, you can use the <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a>\ntype.</p>',
     '<p>要在绑定之前配置套接字，可以使用 <a href="struct.TcpSocket.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpSocket"><code>TcpSocket</code></a> 类型。</p>'),
    ('<p>Accepts a new incoming connection from this listener.</p>',
     '<p>从此监听器接受一个新的传入连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will yield once a new TCP connection is established. When\nestablished, the corresponding <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> and the remote peer’s\naddress will be returned.</p>',
     '<p>一旦建立新的 TCP 连接，此函数就会让步。连接建立后，将返回相应的 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 和远程对等方的地址。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancel safe. If the method is used as the event in a\n<a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then it is guaranteed that no new connections were\naccepted by this method.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 语句中将此方法用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证此方法未接受任何新连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polls to accept a new incoming connection to this listener.</p>',
     '<p>轮询以接受到此监听器的新传入连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there is no connection to accept, <code>Poll::Pending</code> is returned and the\ncurrent task will be notified by a waker.  Note that on multiple calls\nto <code>poll_accept</code>, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed to the most\nrecent call is scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有连接可接受，则返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并且当前任务将由 waker 通知。请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_accept</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 会被调度接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates new <code>TcpListener</code> from a <code>std::net::TcpListener</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>std::net::TcpListener</code> 创建一个新的 <code>TcpListener</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended to be used to wrap a TCP listener from the\nstandard library in the Tokio equivalent.</p>',
     '<p>此函数旨在用于将标准库的 TCP 监听器包装为 Tokio 等价物。</p>'),
    ('<p>This API is typically paired with the <code>socket2</code> crate and the <code>Socket</code>\ntype to build up and customize a listener before it’s shipped off to the\nbacking event loop. This allows configuration of options like\n<code>SO_REUSEPORT</code>, binding to multiple addresses, etc.</p>',
     '<p>此 API 通常与 <code>socket2</code> crate 和 <code>Socket</code> 类型配对使用，以便在将监听器交给底层事件循环之前构建并自定义它。这允许配置诸如 <code>SO_REUSEPORT</code>、绑定到多个地址等选项。</p>'),
    ('<p>The caller is responsible for ensuring that the listener is in\nnon-blocking mode. Otherwise all I/O operations on the listener\nwill block the thread, which will cause unexpected behavior.\nNon-blocking mode can be set using <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpListener::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>调用者负责确保监听器处于非阻塞模式。否则，对监听器的所有 I/O 操作都会阻塞线程，从而导致意外行为。可以使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpListener::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 设置非阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Turns a <a href="struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpListener"><code>tokio::net::TcpListener</code></a> into a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpListener"><code>std::net::TcpListener</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpListener"><code>tokio::net::TcpListener</code></a> 转换为 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpListener"><code>std::net::TcpListener</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The returned <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpListener"><code>std::net::TcpListener</code></a> will have nonblocking mode set as\n<code>true</code>.  Use <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpListener::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> to change the blocking mode if needed.</p>',
     '<p>返回的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html" title="struct std::net::tcp::TcpListener"><code>std::net::TcpListener</code></a> 将 nonblocking 模式设置为 <code>true</code>。如果需要，使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/net/tcp/struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_nonblocking" title="method std::net::tcp::TcpListener::set_nonblocking"><code>set_nonblocking</code></a> 更改阻塞模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>This can be useful, for example, when binding to port 0 to figure out\nwhich port was actually bound.</p>',
     '<p>例如，在绑定到端口 0 以找出实际绑定了哪个端口时，这可能很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information about this option, see <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关此选项的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.set_ttl" title="method tokio::net::TcpListener::set_ttl"><code>set_ttl</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to\n<a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpListener::from_std"><code>TcpListener::from_std(stream)</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于 <a href="struct.TcpListener.html#method.from_std" title="associated function tokio::net::TcpListener::from_std"><code>TcpListener::from_std(stream)</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Using <code>accept</code>:</p>', '<p>使用 <code>accept</code>：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 24: Runtime (23 items) ============
    ('<p>The runtime provides an I/O driver, task scheduler, <a href="../time/index.html" title="mod tokio::time">timer</a>, and\nblocking pool, necessary for running asynchronous tasks.</p>',
     '<p>运行时提供了运行异步任务所需的 I/O 驱动、任务调度器、<a href="../time/index.html" title="mod tokio::time">计时器</a> 以及阻塞线程池。</p>'),
    ('<p>Instances of <code>Runtime</code> can be created using <a href="method@Self::new"><code>new</code></a>, or <a href="struct@Builder"><code>Builder</code></a>.\nHowever, most users will use the <a href="macro@crate::main"><code>#[tokio::main]</code></a> annotation on\ntheir entry point instead.</p>',
     '<p><code>Runtime</code> 实例可以使用 <a href="method@Self::new"><code>new</code></a> 或 <a href="struct@Builder"><code>Builder</code></a> 创建。不过，大多数用户会在入口点使用 <a href="macro@crate::main"><code>#[tokio::main]</code></a> 属性注解。</p>'),
    ('<p>Shutting down the runtime is done by dropping the value, or calling\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> or <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>关闭运行时是通过 drop 该值或调用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> 来完成的。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tasks spawned through <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn"><code>Runtime::spawn</code></a> keep running until they yield.\nThen they are dropped. They are not <em>guaranteed</em> to run to completion, but\n<em>might</em> do so if they do not yield until completion.</p>',
     '<p>通过 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn"><code>Runtime::spawn</code></a> 生成的任务会一直运行，直到它们让步。然后它们会被 drop。它们<em>不保证</em>会运行到完成，但如果它们在完成之前不让步，则<em>可能</em>会运行到完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blocking functions spawned through <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn_blocking" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn_blocking"><code>Runtime::spawn_blocking</code></a> keep running\nuntil they return.</p>',
     '<p>通过 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn_blocking" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn_blocking"><code>Runtime::spawn_blocking</code></a> 生成的阻塞函数会一直运行，直到它们返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>The thread initiating the shutdown blocks until all spawned work has been\nstopped. This can take an indefinite amount of time. The <code>Drop</code>\nimplementation waits forever for this.</p>',
     '<p>发起关闭的线程会一直阻塞，直到所有生成的工作都已停止。这可能需要无限长的时间。<code>Drop</code> 实现会永远等待这一过程。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> and <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> methods can be used if\nwaiting forever is undesired. When the timeout is reached, spawned work that\ndid not stop in time and threads running it are leaked. The work continues\nto run until one of the stopping conditions is fulfilled, but the thread\ninitiating the shutdown is unblocked.</p>',
     '<p>如果不想永远等待，可以使用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> 方法。当达到超时时，未及时停止的已生成工作以及运行它们的线程会被泄漏。工作会继续运行，直到满足停止条件之一，但发起关闭的线程将不再阻塞。</p>'),
    ('<p>Once the runtime has been dropped, any outstanding I/O resources bound to\nit will no longer function. Calling any method on them will result in an\nerror.</p>',
     '<p>一旦运行时被 drop，绑定到它的所有未完成的 I/O 资源将不再可用。对它们调用任何方法都将导致错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>There are several ways to establish shared access to a Tokio runtime:</p>',
     '<p>有几种方法可以建立对 Tokio 运行时的共享访问：</p>'),
    ('<p>Using an <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> or <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> allows you to do various\nthings with the runtime such as spawning new tasks or entering the runtime\ncontext. Both types can be cloned to create a new handle that allows access\nto the same runtime. By passing clones into different tasks or threads, you\nwill be able to access the runtime from those tasks or threads.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> 或 <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> 允许你对运行时执行各种操作，例如生成新任务或进入运行时上下文。这两种类型都可以克隆，以创建一个允许访问同一运行时的新句柄。通过将克隆传递到不同的任务或线程，你将能够从这些任务或线程访问运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>The difference between <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> and <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> is that\nan <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> will prevent the runtime from shutting down,\nwhereas a <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> does not prevent that. This is because shutdown of the\nruntime happens when the destructor of the <code>Runtime</code> object runs.</p>',
     '<p><code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> 与 <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> 之间的区别在于，<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> 会阻止运行时关闭，而 <a href="struct.Handle.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Handle"><code>Handle</code></a> 则不会阻止。这是因为运行时的关闭发生在 <code>Runtime</code> 对象的析构函数运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calls to <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> and <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> require exclusive\nownership of the <code>Runtime</code> type. When using an <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code>,\nthis can be achieved via <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.try_unwrap" title="associated function alloc::sync::Arc::try_unwrap"><code>Arc::try_unwrap</code></a> when only one strong count\nreference is left over.</p>',
     '<p>对 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>shutdown_background</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> 的调用需要 <code>Runtime</code> 类型的独占所有权。在使用 <code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc">Arc</a>&lt;Runtime&gt;</code> 时，当只剩下一个强引用计数时，可以通过 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html#method.try_unwrap" title="associated function alloc::sync::Arc::try_unwrap"><code>Arc::try_unwrap</code></a> 来实现这一点。</p>'),
    ('<p>The runtime context is entered using the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> or\n<a href="struct.Handle.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::enter"><code>Handle::enter</code></a> methods, which use a thread-local variable to store the\ncurrent runtime. Whenever you are inside the runtime context, methods such\nas <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> will use the runtime whose context you are inside.</p>',
     '<p>运行时上下文是通过 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::enter"><code>Handle::enter</code></a> 方法进入的，这些方法使用线程局部变量来存储当前运行时。只要你在运行时上下文中，像 <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> 这样的方法将使用你所在上下文中的运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> on a handle to a <code>current_thread</code> runtime is error-prone.\nRefer to the documentation of <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> for more.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>current_thread</code> 运行时的句柄上调用 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 容易出错。有关更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs the provided function on an executor dedicated to blocking operations.</p>',
     '<p>在专用于阻塞操作的执行器上运行所提供的函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runs the given future on the current thread, blocking until it is\ncomplete, and yielding its resolved result. Any tasks or timers\nwhich the future spawns internally will be executed on the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>这会在当前线程上运行给定的 future，阻塞直到它完成，并产生其解析结果。future 内部生成的任何任务或计时器都将在运行时上执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that the future required by this function does not run as a\nworker. The expectation is that other tasks are spawned by the future here.\nAwaiting on other futures from the future provided here will not\nperform as fast as those spawned as workers.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，此函数所需的 future 不会作为 worker 运行。期望此处的 future 生成其他任务。在此提供的 future 上等待其他 future 的性能不会像作为 worker 生成的那些一样快。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the multi thread scheduler is used this will allow futures\nto run within the io driver and timer context of the overall runtime.</p>',
     '<p>当使用多线程调度器时，这将允许 future 在整体运行时的 io 驱动和计时器上下文中运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Any spawned tasks will continue running after <code>block_on</code> returns.</p>',
     '<p>任何已生成的任务将在 <code>block_on</code> 返回后继续运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the current thread scheduler is enabled <code>block_on</code>\ncan be called concurrently from multiple threads. The first call\nwill take ownership of the io and timer drivers. This means\nother threads which do not own the drivers will hook into that one.\nWhen the first <code>block_on</code> completes, other threads will be able to\n“steal” the driver to allow continued execution of their futures.</p>',
     '<p>当启用当前线程调度器时，可以从多个线程并发调用 <code>block_on</code>。第一次调用将取得 io 和计时器驱动的所有权。这意味着不拥有驱动的其他线程将挂接到该驱动。当第一个 <code>block_on</code> 完成时，其他线程将能够“窃取”该驱动以允许继续执行其 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Any spawned tasks will be suspended after <code>block_on</code> returns. Calling\n<code>block_on</code> again will resume previously spawned tasks.</p>',
     '<p>任何已生成的任务将在 <code>block_on</code> 返回后被挂起。再次调用 <code>block_on</code> 将恢复先前生成的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function panics if the provided future panics, or if called within an\nasynchronous execution context.</p>',
     '<p>如果提供的 future 发生 panic，或者在异步执行上下文中调用，则此函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note however, that because we do not wait for any blocking tasks to complete, this\nmay result in a resource leak (in that any blocking tasks are still running until they\nreturn.</p>',
     '<p>但请注意，因为我们不等待任何阻塞任务完成，这可能会导致资源泄漏（即任何阻塞任务仍在运行，直到它们返回。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 25: LocalRuntime (21 items) ============
    ('<p>This runtime is capable of driving tasks which are not <code>Send + Sync</code> without the use of a\n<code>LocalSet</code>, and thus supports <code>spawn_local</code> without the need for a <code>LocalSet</code> context.</p>',
     '<p>此运行时能够在不使用 <code>LocalSet</code> 的情况下驱动不是 <code>Send + Sync</code> 的任务，因此支持 <code>spawn_local</code> 而无需 <code>LocalSet</code> 上下文。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runtime cannot be moved between threads or driven from different threads.</p>',
     '<p>此运行时不能在线程之间移动，也不能从不同线程驱动。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runtime is incompatible with <code>LocalSet</code>. You should not attempt to drive a <code>LocalSet</code> within a\n<code>LocalRuntime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此运行时与 <code>LocalSet</code> 不兼容。你不应尝试在 <code>LocalRuntime</code> 内驱动 <code>LocalSet</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Currently, this runtime supports one flavor, which is internally identical to <code>current_thread</code>,\nsave for the aforementioned differences related to <code>spawn_local</code>.</p>',
     '<p>目前，此运行时支持一种风格，其内部与 <code>current_thread</code> 完全相同，只是与 <code>spawn_local</code> 相关的上述差异除外。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more general information on how to use runtimes, see the <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">module</a> docs.</p>',
     '<p>有关如何使用运行时的更多一般信息，请参阅 <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">模块</a> 文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new local runtime instance with default configuration values.</p>',
     '<p>使用默认配置值创建一个新的本地运行时实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>This results in the scheduler, I/O driver, and time driver being\ninitialized.</p>',
     '<p>这将导致调度器、I/O 驱动和时间驱动被初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>When a more complex configuration is necessary, the <a href="struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder">runtime builder</a> may be used.</p>',
     '<p>当需要更复杂的配置时，可以使用 <a href="struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder">运行时构建器</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>See <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">module level</a> documentation for more details.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多详细信息，请参阅<a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::runtime">模块级</a>文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creating a new <code>LocalRuntime</code> with default configuration values.</p>',
     '<p>使用默认配置值创建一个新的 <code>LocalRuntime</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>As the handle can be sent to other threads, it can only be used to spawn tasks that are <code>Send</code>.</p>',
     '<p>由于该句柄可以发送到其他线程，因此它只能用于生成 <code>Send</code> 的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> on a handle to a <code>LocalRuntime</code> is error-prone.\nRefer to the documentation of <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> for more.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>LocalRuntime</code> 的句柄上调用 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 容易出错。有关更多信息，请参阅 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::block_on"><code>Handle::block_on</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawns a task on the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>在运行时上生成一个任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is analogous to the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn"><code>spawn</code></a> method on the standard <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>, but works even if the task is not thread-safe.</p>',
     '<p>这类似于标准 <a href="struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn"><code>spawn</code></a> 方法，但即使任务不是线程安全的也能工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs the provided function on a thread from a dedicated blocking thread pool.</p>',
     '<p>在专用阻塞线程池中的某个线程上运行所提供的函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function <em>will</em> be run on another thread.</p>',
     '<p>此函数<em>将</em>在另一个线程上运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn_blocking" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn_blocking">documentation in the non-local runtime</a> for more\ninformation.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多信息，请参阅<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.spawn_blocking" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::spawn_blocking">非本地运行时中的文档</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the documentation for <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on">the equivalent method on Runtime</a>\nfor more information.</p>',
     '<p>有关更多信息，请参阅<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on">Runtime 上等价方法的文档</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If this is a handle to a <a href="struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a>, and this function is being invoked from the same\nthread that the runtime was created on, you will also be able to call\n<a href="../task/fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>tokio::task::spawn_local</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果这是 <a href="struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a> 的句柄，并且此函数是从创建运行时的同一线程调用的，那么你也能够调用 <a href="../task/fn.spawn_local.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_local"><code>tokio::task::spawn_local</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that <code>spawn_blocking</code> tasks, and only <code>spawn_blocking</code> tasks, can get left behind if\nthe timeout expires.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果超时到期，<code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务（且只有 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务）可能会被遗留。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note however, that because we do not wait for any blocking tasks to complete, this\nmay result in a resource leak (in that any blocking tasks are still running until they\nreturn. No other tasks will leak.</p>',
     '<p>但请注意，因为我们不等待任何阻塞任务完成，这可能会导致资源泄漏（即任何阻塞任务仍在运行，直到它们返回。其他任务不会泄漏。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 26: Handle (21 items) ============
    ('<p>The handle is internally reference-counted and can be freely cloned. A handle can be\nobtained using the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.handle" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::handle"><code>Runtime::handle</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>该句柄内部是引用计数的，可以自由克隆。可以使用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.handle" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::handle"><code>Runtime::handle</code></a> 方法获取句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>Enters the runtime context. This allows you to construct types that must\nhave an executor available on creation such as <a href="../time/struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> or\n<a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>. It will also allow you to call methods such as\n<a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> and <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.current" title="associated function tokio::runtime::Handle::current"><code>Handle::current</code></a> without panicking.</p>',
     '<p>进入运行时上下文。这允许你构造在创建时必须有可用的执行器的类型，例如 <a href="../time/struct.Sleep.html" title="struct tokio::time::Sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> 或 <a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。它还允许你调用 <a href="../task/fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.current" title="associated function tokio::runtime::Handle::current"><code>Handle::current</code></a> 等方法而不会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>When calling <code>Handle::enter</code> multiple times, the returned guards\n<strong>must</strong> be dropped in the reverse order that they were acquired.\nFailure to do so will result in a panic and possible memory leaks.</p>',
     '<p>当多次调用 <code>Handle::enter</code> 时，返回的 guard <strong>必须</strong>以获取它们的相反顺序 drop。否则将导致 panic 和可能的内存泄漏。</p>'),
    ('<p>Do <strong>not</strong> do the following, this shows a scenario that will result in a\npanic and possible memory leak.</p>',
     '<p><strong>不要</strong>执行以下操作，这显示了一个会导致 panic 和可能的内存泄漏的场景。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Handle</code> view over the currently running <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前正在运行的 <code>Runtime</code> 的 <code>Handle</code> 视图。</p>'),
    ('<p>This will panic if called outside the context of a Tokio runtime. That means that you must\ncall this on one of the threads <strong>being run by the runtime</strong>, or from a thread with an active\n<code>EnterGuard</code>. Calling this from within a thread created by <code>std::thread::spawn</code> (for example)\nwill cause a panic unless that thread has an active <code>EnterGuard</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 Tokio 运行时的上下文之外调用此函数，则会发生 panic。这意味着你必须在<strong>由运行时运行的</strong>某个线程上调用它，或者从具有活动 <code>EnterGuard</code> 的线程调用。例如，从 <code>std::thread::spawn</code> 创建的线程中调用会导致 panic，除非该线程具有活动的 <code>EnterGuard</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This can be used to obtain the handle of the surrounding runtime from an async\nblock or function running on that runtime.</p>',
     '<p>这可用于从在该运行时上运行的 async 块或函数获取周围运行时的句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a Handle view over the currently running Runtime</p>',
     '<p>返回当前正在运行的 Runtime 的 Handle 视图</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns an error if no Runtime has been started</p>',
     '<p>如果尚未启动 Runtime，则返回错误</p>'),
    ('<p>Contrary to <code>current</code>, this never panics</p>',
     '<p>与 <code>current</code> 不同，此函数从不发生 panic</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs the provided function on an executor dedicated to blocking\noperations.</p>',
     '<p>在专用于阻塞操作的执行器上运行所提供的函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>Runs a future to completion on this <code>Handle</code>’s associated <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>在此 <code>Handle</code> 关联的 <code>Runtime</code> 上将一个 future 运行到完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runs the given future on the current thread, blocking until it is\ncomplete, and yielding its resolved result. Any tasks or timers which the future spawns internally will be executed on the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>这会在当前线程上运行给定的 future，阻塞直到它完成，并产生其解析结果。future 内部生成的任何任务或计时器都将在运行时上执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>When this is used on a <code>current_thread</code> runtime, only the\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> method can drive the IO and timer drivers, but the\n<code>Handle::block_on</code> method cannot drive them. This means that, when using\nthis method on a <code>current_thread</code> runtime, anything that relies on IO or\ntimers will not work unless there is another thread currently calling\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> on the same runtime.</p>',
     '<p>当在 <code>current_thread</code> 运行时上使用时，只有 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a> 方法可以驱动 IO 和计时器驱动，但 <code>Handle::block_on</code> 方法不能驱动它们。这意味着，在 <code>current_thread</code> 运行时上使用此方法时，除非有另一个线程正在同一运行时上调用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>，否则任何依赖于 IO 或计时器的功能都无法工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>Handle</code>’s associated <code>Runtime</code> has been shut down (through\n<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>Runtime::shutdown_background</code></a>, <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>Runtime::shutdown_timeout</code></a>, or by\ndropping it) and <code>Handle::block_on</code> is used it might return an error or\npanic. Specifically IO resources will return an error and timers will\npanic. Runtime independent futures will run as normal.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Handle</code> 关联的 <code>Runtime</code> 已关闭（通过 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_background" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_background"><code>Runtime::shutdown_background</code></a>、<a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>Runtime::shutdown_timeout</code></a> 或 drop 它），然后使用 <code>Handle::block_on</code> 可能会返回错误或发生 panic。具体来说，IO 资源将返回错误，计时器将发生 panic。独立于运行时的 future 将正常运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function will panic if any of the following conditions are met:</p>',
     '<p>如果满足以下任何条件，此函数将发生 panic：</p>'),
    ('<p>Or using <code>Handle::current</code>:</p>',
     '<p>或使用 <code>Handle::current</code>：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Handle::block_on</code> may be combined with <a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a> to\nre-enter the async context of a multi-thread scheduler runtime:</p>',
     '<p><code>Handle::block_on</code> 可以与 <a href="crate::task::block_in_place"><code>task::block_in_place</code></a> 结合使用，以重新进入多线程调度器运行时的异步上下文：</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the flavor of the current <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前 <code>Runtime</code> 的风格。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Id"><code>Id</code></a> of the current <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前 <code>Runtime</code> 的 <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Id"><code>Id</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the name of the current <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前 <code>Runtime</code> 的名称。</p>'),
    ('<p>This runs the given future on the current thread, blocking until it is\ncomplete, and yielding its resolved result. Any tasks or timers which\nthe future spawns internally will be executed on the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>这会在当前线程上运行给定的 future，阻塞直到它完成，并产生其解析结果。future 内部生成的任何任务或计时器都将在运行时上执行。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 27: Interval (19 items) ============
    ('<p>This runs the given future on the current thread, blocking until it is\ncomplete, and yielding its resolved result. Any tasks or timers which\nthe future spawns internally will be executed on the runtime.</p>',
     '<p>这会在当前线程上运行给定的 future，阻塞直到它完成，并产生其解析结果。future 内部生成的任何任务或计时器都将在运行时上执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Interval returned by <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> and <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>由 <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a> 返回的 Interval。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type allows you to wait on a sequence of instants with a certain\nduration between each instant. Unlike calling <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> in a loop, this lets\nyou count the time spent between the calls to <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> as well.</p>',
     '<p>此类型允许你等待一系列瞬时，每个瞬时之间有一定的时间间隔。与在循环中调用 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> 不同，这还允许你计算两次调用 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> 之间所花费的时间。</p>'),
    ('<p>An <code>Interval</code> can be turned into a <code>Stream</code> with <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/latest/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.IntervalStream.html"><code>IntervalStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><code>Interval</code> 可以通过 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/latest/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.IntervalStream.html"><code>IntervalStream</code></a> 转换为 <code>Stream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Completes when the next instant in the interval has been reached.</p>',
     '<p>当达到间隔中的下一个瞬时时完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancellation safe. If <code>tick</code> is used as the branch in a <code>tokio::select!</code> and\nanother branch completes first, then no tick has been consumed.</p>',
     '<p>此方法是可安全取消的。如果 <code>tick</code> 用作 <code>tokio::select!</code> 中的分支，并且另一个分支先完成，则不会消耗任何 tick。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polls for the next instant in the interval to be reached.</p>',
     '<p>轮询以达到间隔中的下一个瞬时。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method can return the following values:</p>',
     '<p>此方法可以返回以下值：</p>'),
    ('<p>When this method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>, the current task is scheduled\nto receive a wakeup when the instant has elapsed. Note that on multiple\ncalls to <code>poll_tick</code>, only the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Waker.html" title="struct core::task::wake::Waker"><code>Waker</code></a> from the\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Context.html" title="struct core::task::wake::Context"><code>Context</code></a> passed to the most recent call is scheduled to receive a\nwakeup.</p>',
     '<p>当此方法返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code> 时，当前任务被调度以在该瞬时到达时接收唤醒。请注意，在多次调用 <code>poll_tick</code> 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Context.html" title="struct core::task::wake::Context"><code>Context</code></a> 中的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/wake/struct.Waker.html" title="struct core::task::wake::Waker"><code>Waker</code></a> 会被调度接收唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>Resets the interval to complete one period after the current time.</p>',
     '<p>重置间隔，使其在当前时间之后的一个周期完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <code>reset_at(Instant::now() + period)</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于调用 <code>reset_at(Instant::now() + period)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Resets the interval immediately.</p>',
     '<p>立即重置间隔。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <code>reset_at(Instant::now())</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于调用 <code>reset_at(Instant::now())</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Resets the interval after the specified <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>std::time::Duration</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>在指定的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>std::time::Duration</code></a> 之后重置间隔。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <code>reset_at(Instant::now() + after)</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于调用 <code>reset_at(Instant::now() + after)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Resets the interval to a <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>crate::time::Instant</code></a> deadline.</p>',
     '<p>将间隔重置为 <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>crate::time::Instant</code></a> 截止时间。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the next tick to expire at the given instant. If the instant is in\nthe past, then the <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> strategy will be used to\ncatch up. If the instant is in the future, then the next tick will\ncomplete at the given instant, even if that means that it will sleep for\nlonger than the duration of this <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a>. If the <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> had\nany missed ticks before calling this method, then those are discarded.</p>',
     '<p>将下一个 tick 设置为在给定的瞬时到期。如果该瞬时在过去，则将使用 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 策略进行追赶。如果该瞬时在未来，则下一个 tick 将在给定的瞬时完成，即使这意味着它将睡眠超过此 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 的持续时间。如果在调用此方法之前 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 已有任何丢失的 tick，那么这些 tick 将被丢弃。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> strategy currently being used.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前正在使用的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 策略。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> strategy that should be used.</p>',
     '<p>设置应使用的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 策略。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the period of the interval.</p>',
     '<p>返回间隔的周期。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 28: RwLock (19 items) ============
    ('<p>An asynchronous reader-writer lock.</p>',
     '<p>异步读写锁。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type of lock allows a number of readers or at most one writer at any\npoint in time. The write portion of this lock typically allows modification\nof the underlying data (exclusive access) and the read portion of this lock\ntypically allows for read-only access (shared access).</p>',
     '<p>这种类型的锁允许任意数量的读者或在任意时刻最多一个写者。此锁的写部分通常允许修改底层数据（独占访问），而读部分通常允许只读访问（共享访问）。</p>'),
    ('<p>In comparison, a <a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> does not distinguish between readers or writers\nthat acquire the lock, therefore causing any tasks waiting for the lock to\nbecome available to yield. An <code>RwLock</code> will allow any number of readers to\nacquire the lock as long as a writer is not holding the lock.</p>',
     '<p>相比之下，<a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> 不区分获取锁的读者或写者，因此会导致任何等待锁变得可用的任务让步。只要没有写者持有锁，<code>RwLock</code> 就允许任意数量的读者获取该锁。</p>'),
    ('<p>The priority policy of Tokio’s read-write lock is <em>fair</em> (or\n<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Readers%E2%80%93writer_lock#Priority_policies"><em>write-preferring</em></a>), in order to ensure that readers cannot starve\nwriters. Fairness is ensured using a first-in, first-out queue for the tasks\nawaiting the lock; a read lock will not be given out until all write lock\nrequests that were queued before it have been acquired and released. This is\nin contrast to the Rust standard library’s <code>std::sync::RwLock</code>, where the\npriority policy is dependent on the operating system’s implementation.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 读写锁的优先级策略是<em>公平的</em>（或<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Readers%E2%80%93writer_lock#Priority_policies"><em>优先写者</em></a>），以确保读者不会饿死写者。公平性通过对等待锁的任务使用先进先出队列来保证；在其之前排队的所有写锁请求被获取并释放之前，不会发出读锁。这与 Rust 标准库的 <code>std::sync::RwLock</code> 形成对比，后者的优先级策略取决于操作系统的实现。</p>'),
    ('<p>The type parameter <code>T</code> represents the data that this lock protects. It is\nrequired that <code>T</code> satisfies <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a> to be shared across threads. The RAII guards\nreturned from the locking methods implement <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/ops/deref/trait.Deref.html" title="trait core::ops::deref::Deref"><code>Deref</code></a>\n(and <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/ops/deref/trait.DerefMut.html" title="trait core::ops::deref::DerefMut"><code>DerefMut</code></a>\nfor the <code>write</code> methods) to allow access to the content of the lock.</p>',
     '<p>类型参数 <code>T</code> 表示此锁保护的数据。要求 <code>T</code> 满足 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a> 才能跨线程共享。加锁方法返回的 RAII guard 实现了 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/ops/deref/trait.Deref.html" title="trait core::ops::deref::Deref"><code>Deref</code></a>（以及 <code>write</code> 方法的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/ops/deref/trait.DerefMut.html" title="trait core::ops::deref::DerefMut"><code>DerefMut</code></a>），以允许访问锁的内容。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>RwLock</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLock::new"><code>RwLock::new</code></a> should be used to create\nan instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定功能</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>RwLock</code> 不会被检测。因此，它在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中不可见。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLock::new"><code>RwLock::new</code></a> 创建被检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>read</code> makes you lose your place in\nthe queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用队列按请求的顺序公平地分配锁。取消对 <code>read</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blockingly locks this <code>RwLock</code> with shared read access.</p>',
     '<p>以共享读访问阻塞方式锁定此 <code>RwLock</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns an RAII guard which will drop the read access of this <code>RwLock</code> when dropped.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 RAII guard，当 drop 时将释放此 <code>RwLock</code> 的读访问权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read"><code>RwLock::read</code></a>, except that the returned\nguard references the <code>RwLock</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by borrowing\nit. Therefore, the <code>RwLock</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to call this\nmethod, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime, as it keeps\nthe <code>RwLock</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read"><code>RwLock::read</code></a> 相同，只是返回的 guard 通过 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 引用 <code>RwLock</code> 而不是借用它。因此，要调用此方法，<code>RwLock</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中，并且 guard 的生命周期为 <code>\'static</code>，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>RwLock</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>read_owned</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用队列按请求的顺序公平地分配锁。取消对 <code>read_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_read"><code>RwLock::try_read</code></a>, except that the\nreturned guard references the <code>RwLock</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by\nborrowing it. Therefore, the <code>RwLock</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to\ncall this method, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime,\nas it keeps the <code>RwLock</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_read"><code>RwLock::try_read</code></a> 相同，只是返回的 guard 通过 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 引用 <code>RwLock</code> 而不是借用它。因此，要调用此方法，<code>RwLock</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中，并且 guard 的生命周期为 <code>\'static</code>，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>RwLock</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>write</code> makes you lose your place\nin the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用队列按请求的顺序公平地分配锁。取消对 <code>write</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Blockingly locks this <code>RwLock</code> with exclusive write access.</p>',
     '<p>以独占写访问阻塞方式锁定此 <code>RwLock</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write"><code>RwLock::write</code></a>, except that the returned\nguard references the <code>RwLock</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by borrowing\nit. Therefore, the <code>RwLock</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to call this\nmethod, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime, as it keeps\nthe <code>RwLock</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write"><code>RwLock::write</code></a> 相同，只是返回的 guard 通过 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 引用 <code>RwLock</code> 而不是借用它。因此，要调用此方法，<code>RwLock</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中，并且 guard 的生命周期为 <code>\'static</code>，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>RwLock</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method uses a queue to fairly distribute locks in the order they\nwere requested. Cancelling a call to <code>write_owned</code> makes you lose your\nplace in the queue.</p>',
     '<p>此方法使用队列按请求的顺序公平地分配锁。取消对 <code>write_owned</code> 的调用会使你失去在队列中的位置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is identical to <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_write"><code>RwLock::try_write</code></a>, except that the\nreturned guard references the <code>RwLock</code> with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> rather than by\nborrowing it. Therefore, the <code>RwLock</code> must be wrapped in an <code>Arc</code> to\ncall this method, and the guard will live for the <code>\'static</code> lifetime,\nas it keeps the <code>RwLock</code> alive by holding an <code>Arc</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法与 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_write"><code>RwLock::try_write</code></a> 相同，只是返回的 guard 通过 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 引用 <code>RwLock</code> 而不是借用它。因此，要调用此方法，<code>RwLock</code> 必须包装在 <code>Arc</code> 中，并且 guard 的生命周期为 <code>\'static</code>，因为它通过持有 <code>Arc</code> 来保持 <code>RwLock</code> 存活。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since this call borrows the <code>RwLock</code> mutably, no actual locking needs to\ntake place – the mutable borrow statically guarantees no locks exist.</p>',
     '<p>由于此调用可变地借用 <code>RwLock</code>，因此无需实际进行锁定——可变借用在静态上保证不存在锁。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes the lock, returning the underlying data.</p>',
     '<p>消费该锁，返回底层数据。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 29: watch/index (19 items) ============
    ('<p>A multi-producer, multi-consumer channel that only retains the <em>last</em> sent\nvalue.</p>',
     '<p>多生产者、多消费者 channel，仅保留<em>最后</em>发送的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel is useful for watching for changes to a value from multiple\npoints in the code base, for example, changes to configuration values.</p>',
     '<p>此 channel 对于从代码库中的多个位置监视值的更改非常有用，例如配置值的更改。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::watch::channel"><code>channel</code></a> returns a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> / <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> pair. These are the producer\nand consumer halves of the channel. The channel is created with an initial\nvalue.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::watch::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 返回一个 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> / <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 对。它们是 channel 的生产者和消费者两半。该 channel 以初始值创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Each <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> independently tracks the last value <em>seen</em> by its caller.</p>',
     '<p>每个 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 独立跟踪其调用者<em>看到的</em>最后一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>To access the <strong>current</strong> value stored in the channel and mark it as <em>seen</em>\nby a given <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>, use <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>要访问 channel 中存储的<strong>当前</strong>值并将其标记为由给定 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> <em>看到的</em>，请使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>To access the current value <strong>without</strong> marking it as <em>seen</em>, use\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>. (If the value has already been marked <em>seen</em>,\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a> is equivalent to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a>.)</p>',
     '<p>要访问当前值<strong>而不</strong>将其标记为<em>已查看</em>，请使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>。（如果该值已被标记为<em>已查看</em>，则 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a> 等效于 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a>。）</p>'),
    ('<p>For more information on when to use these methods, see\n<a href="#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow">here</a>.</p>',
     '<p>有关何时使用这些方法的更多信息，请参阅<a href="#borrow_and_update-versus-borrow">此处</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> half provides an asynchronous <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> method. This\nmethod is ready when a new, <em>unseen</em> value is sent via the <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> half.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 一半提供了一个异步 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 方法。当通过 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 一半发送新的<em>未见过的</em>值时，此方法就绪。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> half provides two methods for checking for changes\nin the channel, <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 一半提供了两种方法来检查 channel 中的更改：<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a> is a <em>synchronous</em> method that checks whether the current\nvalue is seen or not and returns a boolean. This method does <strong>not</strong> mark the\nvalue as seen.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a> 是一个<em>同步</em>方法，用于检查当前值是否已被查看，并返回一个布尔值。此方法<strong>不会</strong>将该值标记为已查看。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> is an <em>asynchronous</em> method that will return once an unseen\nvalue is in the channel. This method does mark the value as seen.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 是一个<em>异步</em>方法，一旦 channel 中出现未见过的值，它就会返回。此方法确实会将该值标记为已查看。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note there are two behavioral differences on when these two methods return\nan error.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，这两种方法在何时返回错误方面存在两个行为差异。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the example below that shows how these methods have different fallibility.</p>',
     '<p>请参阅下面的示例，该示例展示了这些方法具有不同的可失败性。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the receiver intends to await notifications from <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> in a loop,\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a> should be preferred over\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>.  This avoids a potential race where a new value is\nsent between <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> being ready and the value being read. (If\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a> is used, the loop may run twice with the same value.)</p>',
     '<p>如果接收者打算在循环中等待来自 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 的通知，则应优先使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>Receiver::borrow_and_update()</code></a> 而非 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>。这避免了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 就绪和读取该值之间可能发送新值的竞争条件。（如果使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>，则循环可能会使用相同的值运行两次。）</p>'),
    ('<p>If the receiver is only interested in the current value, and does not intend\nto wait for changes, then <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a> can be used. It may be more\nconvenient to use <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a> since it’s an <code>&amp;self</code>\nmethod—<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>borrow_and_update</code></a> requires <code>&amp;mut self</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果接收者只对当前值感兴趣，并且不打算等待更改，那么可以使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>Receiver::borrow()</code></a>。使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow"><code>borrow</code></a> 可能更方便，因为它是 <code>&amp;self</code> 方法——<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.borrow_and_update" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::borrow_and_update"><code>borrow_and_update</code></a> 需要 <code>&amp;mut self</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Difference on fallibility of <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> versus <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> 与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>has_changed</code></a> 在可失败性方面的差异。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Sender.html#method.is_closed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::is_closed"><code>Sender::is_closed</code></a> and <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.closed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::closed"><code>Sender::closed</code></a> allow the producer to detect\nwhen all <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles have been dropped. This indicates that there\nis no further interest in the values being produced and work can be stopped.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Sender.html#method.is_closed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::is_closed"><code>Sender::is_closed</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.closed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::closed"><code>Sender::closed</code></a> 允许生产者检测何时所有 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop。这表明对正在生成的值不再有兴趣，可以停止工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>The value in the channel will not be dropped until all senders and all\nreceivers have been dropped.</p>',
     '<p>在所有 sender 和 receiver 都 drop 之前，channel 中的值不会被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>Both <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> are thread safe. They can be moved to other\nthreads and can be used in a concurrent environment. Clones of <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>\nhandles may be moved to separate threads and also used concurrently.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 都是线程安全的。它们可以移动到其他线程，也可以在并发环境中使用。<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄的克隆可以移动到单独的线程，也可以并发使用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 30: broadcast Sender (19 items) ============
    ('<p>Sending-half of the <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel.</p>',
     '<p><a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel 的发送端。</p>'),
    ('<p>May be used from many threads. Messages can be sent with\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>可以从多个线程使用。可以使用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 发送消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates the sending-half of the <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel.</p>',
     '<p>创建 <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel 的发送端。</p>'),
    ('<p>See the documentation of <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>broadcast::channel</code></a> for more information on this method.</p>',
     '<p>有关此方法的更多信息，请参阅 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>broadcast::channel</code></a> 的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to send a value to all active <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles, returning\nit back if it could not be sent.</p>',
     '<p>尝试向所有活动的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄发送一个值，如果无法发送则将其返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>A successful send occurs when there is at least one active <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>\nhandle. An unsuccessful send would be one where all associated\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles have already been dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当至少有一个活动的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄时，发送成功。发送失败是指所有关联的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, the number of subscribed <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles is returned.\nThis does not mean that this number of receivers will see the message as\na receiver may drop or lag (<a href="index.html#lagging" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast">see lagging</a>) before receiving\nthe message.</p>',
     '<p>成功时，返回已订阅的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄数。这并不意味着这么多接收者将看到该消息，因为接收者可能在接收消息之前 drop 或滞后（<a href="index.html#lagging" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast">参见滞后</a>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>A return value of <code>Ok</code> <strong>does not</strong> mean that the sent value will be\nobserved by all or any of the active <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles. <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>\nhandles may be dropped before receiving the sent message.</p>',
     '<p><code>Ok</code> 的返回值<strong>并不</strong>意味着所发送的值将被所有或任何活动的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄观察到。<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄可能在接收到发送的消息之前被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>A return value of <code>Err</code> <strong>does not</strong> mean that future calls to <code>send</code>\nwill fail. New <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles may be created by calling\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><code>Err</code> 的返回值<strong>并不</strong>意味着未来对 <code>send</code> 的调用会失败。可以通过调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a> 来创建新的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle that will receive values sent <strong>after</strong>\nthis call to <code>subscribe</code>.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄，该句柄将接收在此次调用 <code>subscribe</code> <strong>之后</strong>发送的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts the <code>Sender</code> to a <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> that does not count\ntowards RAII semantics, i.e. if all <code>Sender</code> instances of the\nchannel were dropped and only <code>WeakSender</code> instances remain,\nthe channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>Sender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a>，它不计入 RAII 语义，即如果 channel 的所有 <code>Sender</code> 实例都已被 drop，并且只剩下 <code>WeakSender</code> 实例，则 channel 已关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of queued values.</p>',
     '<p>返回已排队值的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>A value is queued until it has either been seen by all receivers that were alive at the time\nit was sent, or has been evicted from the queue by subsequent sends that exceeded the\nqueue’s capacity.</p>',
     '<p>一个值在发送时被所有当时活动的接收者看到之前，或被超出队列容量的后续发送从队列中驱逐之前，一直处于排队状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>In contrast to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.len" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::len"><code>Receiver::len</code></a>, this method only reports queued values and not values that\nhave been evicted from the queue before being seen by all receivers.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.len" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::len"><code>Receiver::len</code></a> 相比，此方法仅报告已排队的值，而不报告在被所有接收者看到之前已从队列中驱逐的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if there are no queued values.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有排队的值，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of active receivers.</p>',
     '<p>返回活动接收者的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>An active receiver is a <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle returned from <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a> or\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a>. These are the handles that will receive values sent on\nthis <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>活动接收者是从 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>subscribe</code></a> 返回的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄。这些句柄将接收在此 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 上发送的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is not guaranteed that a sent message will reach this number of\nreceivers. Active receivers may never call <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> again before\ndropping.</p>',
     '<p>不能保证发送的消息会到达此数量的接收者。活动接收者在 drop 之前可能再也不会调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>A future which completes when the number of <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver">Receiver</a>s subscribed to this <code>Sender</code> reaches\nzero.</p>',
     '<p>当订阅此 <code>Sender</code> 的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver">Receiver</a> 数量达到零时完成的 future。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 31: JoinHandle (18 items) ============
    ('<p>An owned permission to join on a task (await its termination).</p>',
     '<p>用于加入任务（等待其终止）的所有权权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>This can be thought of as the equivalent of <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/join_handle/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct std::thread::join_handle::JoinHandle"><code>std::thread::JoinHandle</code></a>\nfor a Tokio task rather than a thread. Note that the background task\nassociated with this <code>JoinHandle</code> started running immediately when you\ncalled spawn, even if you have not yet awaited the <code>JoinHandle</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这可以看作是 Tokio 任务的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/join_handle/struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct std::thread::join_handle::JoinHandle"><code>std::thread::JoinHandle</code></a> 等价物，而不是线程的等价物。请注意，与此 <code>JoinHandle</code> 关联的后台任务在你调用 spawn 时立即开始运行，即使你尚未 await 此 <code>JoinHandle</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>JoinHandle</code> <em>detaches</em> the associated task when it is dropped, which\nmeans that there is no longer any handle to the task, and no way to <code>join</code>\non it.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>JoinHandle</code> 被 drop 时，它会<em>分离</em>关联的任务，这意味着不再有该任务的句柄，也无法再 <code>join</code> 它。</p>'),
    ('<p>This <code>struct</code> is created by the <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a> and <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a>\nfunctions.</p>',
     '<p>此 <code>struct</code> 由 <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a> 函数创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is guaranteed that the destructor of the spawned task has finished\nbefore task completion is observed via <code>JoinHandle</code> <code>await</code>,\n<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::is_finished"><code>JoinHandle::is_finished</code></a> or <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::is_finished"><code>AbortHandle::is_finished</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>保证在通过 <code>JoinHandle</code> <code>await</code>、<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::is_finished"><code>JoinHandle::is_finished</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.is_finished" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::is_finished"><code>AbortHandle::is_finished</code></a> 观察到任务完成之前，已生成任务的析构函数已经运行完毕。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>&amp;mut JoinHandle&lt;T&gt;</code> type is cancel safe. If it is used as the event\nin a <code>tokio::select!</code> statement and some other branch completes first,\nthen it is guaranteed that the output of the task is not lost.</p>',
     '<p><code>&amp;mut JoinHandle&lt;T&gt;</code> 类型是取消安全的。如果在 <code>tokio::select!</code> 语句中将其用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则可以保证任务的输出不会丢失。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a <code>JoinHandle</code> is dropped, then the task continues running in the\nbackground and its return value is lost.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>JoinHandle</code> 被 drop，则任务将继续在后台运行，并且其返回值将丢失。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creation from <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>task::spawn</code></a> 创建：</p>'),
    ('<p>Creation from <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>task::spawn_blocking</code></a> 创建：</p>'),
    ('<p>The generic parameter <code>T</code> in <code>JoinHandle&lt;T&gt;</code> is the return type of the spawned task.\nIf the return value is an <code>i32</code>, the join handle has type <code>JoinHandle&lt;i32&gt;</code>:</p>',
     '<p><code>JoinHandle&lt;T&gt;</code> 中的泛型参数 <code>T</code> 是已生成任务的返回类型。如果返回值是 <code>i32</code>，则 join handle 的类型为 <code>JoinHandle&lt;i32&gt;</code>：</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task does not have a return value, the join handle has type <code>JoinHandle&lt;()&gt;</code>:</p>',
     '<p>如果任务没有返回值，则 join handle 的类型为 <code>JoinHandle&lt;()&gt;</code>：</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that <code>handle.await</code> doesn’t give you the return type directly. It is wrapped in a\n<code>Result</code> because panics in the spawned task are caught by Tokio. The <code>?</code> operator has\nto be double chained to extract the returned value:</p>',
     '<p>请注意，<code>handle.await</code> 不会直接给出返回类型。它被包装在 <code>Result</code> 中，因为已生成任务中的 panic 会被 Tokio 捕获。必须双重链接 <code>?</code> 运算符才能提取返回值：</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task panics, the error is a <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a> that contains the panic:</p>',
     '<p>如果任务发生 panic，则错误是包含该 panic 的 <a href="struct.JoinError.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinError"><code>JoinError</code></a>：</p>'),
    ('<p>Child being detached and outliving its parent:</p>',
     '<p>子任务被分离并比其父任务活得更久：</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if the task associated with this <code>JoinHandle</code> has finished.</p>',
     '<p>检查与此 <code>JoinHandle</code> 关联的任务是否已完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Please note that this method can return <code>false</code> even if <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>abort</code></a> has been\ncalled on the task. This is because the cancellation process may take\nsome time, and this method does not return <code>true</code> until it has\ncompleted.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，即使已对任务调用 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>abort</code></a>，此方法也可能返回 <code>false</code>。这是因为取消过程可能需要一些时间，并且此方法在取消完成之前不会返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a new <code>AbortHandle</code> that can be used to remotely abort this task.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个新的 <code>AbortHandle</code>，可用于远程中止此任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Awaiting a task cancelled by the <code>AbortHandle</code> might complete as usual if the task was\nalready completed at the time it was cancelled, but most likely it\nwill fail with a <a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">cancelled</a> <code>JoinError</code>.</p>',
     '<p>await 由 <code>AbortHandle</code> 取消的任务，如果该任务在被取消时已经完成，则可能照常完成，但很可能以 <a href="struct.JoinError.html#method.is_cancelled" title="method tokio::task::JoinError::is_cancelled">已取消</a> 的 <code>JoinError</code> 失败。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 32: OnceCell (18 items) ============
    ('<p>A <code>OnceCell</code> is typically used for global variables that need to be\ninitialized once on first use, but need no further changes. The <code>OnceCell</code>\nin Tokio allows the initialization procedure to be asynchronous.</p>',
     '<p><code>OnceCell</code> 通常用于需要在首次使用时初始化一次但不需要进一步更改的全局变量。Tokio 中的 <code>OnceCell</code> 允许异步执行初始化过程。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is often useful to write a wrapper method for accessing the value.</p>',
     '<p>编写用于访问值的包装方法通常很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Equivalent to <code>OnceCell::new</code>, except that it can be used in static\nvariables.</p>',
     '<p>等效于 <code>OnceCell::new</code>，但可以在静态变量中使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>OnceCell</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::OnceCell::new"><code>OnceCell::new</code></a> should be used to\ncreate an instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定功能</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>OnceCell</code> 不会被检测。因此，它在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中不可见。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::OnceCell::new"><code>OnceCell::new</code></a> 创建被检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>OnceCell</code> that contains the provided value, if any.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <code>OnceCell</code>，其中包含所提供的值（如果有）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>Option</code> is <code>None</code>, this is equivalent to <code>OnceCell::new</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Option</code> 为 <code>None</code>，则等效于 <code>OnceCell::new</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>OnceCell</code> that contains the provided value.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个包含所提供值的新 <code>OnceCell</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>OnceCell</code> created with\n<code>const_new_with</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be\nvisible in <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.new_with" title="associated function tokio::sync::OnceCell::new_with"><code>OnceCell::new_with</code></a> should be\nused to create an instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定功能</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new_with</code> 创建的 <code>OnceCell</code> 不会被检测。因此，它在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中不可见。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.new_with" title="associated function tokio::sync::OnceCell::new_with"><code>OnceCell::new_with</code></a> 创建被检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the <code>OnceCell</code> currently contains a value, and <code>false</code>\notherwise.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 当前包含值，则返回 <code>true</code>，否则返回 <code>false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the value currently stored in the <code>OnceCell</code>, or\n<code>None</code> if the <code>OnceCell</code> is empty.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存储在 <code>OnceCell</code> 中的值的引用，如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 为空则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the value currently stored in the\n<code>OnceCell</code>, or <code>None</code> if the <code>OnceCell</code> is empty.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存储在 <code>OnceCell</code> 中的值的可变引用，如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 为空则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since this call borrows the <code>OnceCell</code> mutably, it is safe to mutate the\nvalue inside the <code>OnceCell</code> — the mutable borrow statically guarantees\nno other references exist.</p>',
     '<p>由于此调用可变地借用 <code>OnceCell</code>，因此可以安全地变更 <code>OnceCell</code> 中的值——可变借用在静态上保证不存在其他引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>OnceCell</code> to the given value if the <code>OnceCell</code> is\nempty.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 为空，则将其值设置为给定值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>OnceCell</code> already has a value, this call will fail with an\n<a href="enum.SetError.html#variant.AlreadyInitializedError" title="variant tokio::sync::SetError::AlreadyInitializedError"><code>SetError::AlreadyInitializedError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 已经有值，则此调用将失败并返回 <a href="enum.SetError.html#variant.AlreadyInitializedError" title="variant tokio::sync::SetError::AlreadyInitializedError"><code>SetError::AlreadyInitializedError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>OnceCell</code> is empty, but some other task is currently trying to\nset the value, this call will fail with <a href="enum.SetError.html#variant.InitializingError" title="variant tokio::sync::SetError::InitializingError"><code>SetError::InitializingError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>OnceCell</code> 为空，但其他某个任务当前正在尝试设置值，则此调用将失败并返回 <a href="enum.SetError.html#variant.InitializingError" title="variant tokio::sync::SetError::InitializingError"><code>SetError::InitializingError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the provided operation is cancelled or panics, the initialization\nattempt is cancelled. If there are other tasks waiting for the value to\nbe initialized, one of them will start another attempt at initializing\nthe value.</p>',
     '<p>如果所提供的操作被取消或发生 panic，则初始化尝试将被取消。如果有其他任务正在等待值的初始化，那么其中一个将开始另一次初始化该值的尝试。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the provided operation returns an error, is cancelled or panics, the\ninitialization attempt is cancelled. If there are other tasks waiting for the value to\nbe initialized, one of them will start another attempt at initializing\nthe value.</p>',
     '<p>如果所提供的操作返回错误、被取消或发生 panic，则初始化尝试将被取消。如果有其他任务正在等待值的初始化，那么其中一个将开始另一次初始化该值的尝试。</p>'),
    ('<p>Takes ownership of the current value, leaving the cell empty.  Returns\n<code>None</code> if the cell is empty.</p>',
     '<p>取得当前值的所有权，使 cell 留空。如果 cell 为空，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 33: io/index (18 items) ============
    ('<p>Traits, helpers, and type definitions for asynchronous I/O functionality.</p>',
     '<p>用于异步 I/O 功能的 trait、辅助函数和类型定义。</p>'),
    ('<p>This module is the asynchronous version of <code>std::io</code>. Primarily, it\ndefines two traits, <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> and <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a>, which are asynchronous\nversions of the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>Read</code></a> and <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>Write</code></a> traits in the standard library.</p>',
     '<p>此模块是 <code>std::io</code> 的异步版本。它主要定义了两个 trait：<a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 和 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a>，它们是标准库中 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>Read</code></a> 和 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>Write</code></a> trait 的异步版本。</p>'),
    ('<p>Like the standard library’s <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>Read</code></a> and <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>Write</code></a> traits, <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> and\n<a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> provide the most general interface for reading and writing\ninput and output. Unlike the standard library’s traits, however, they are\n<em>asynchronous</em> — meaning that reading from or writing to a <code>tokio::io</code>\ntype will <em>yield</em> to the Tokio scheduler when IO is not ready, rather than\nblocking. This allows other tasks to run while waiting on IO.</p>',
     '<p>与标准库的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>Read</code></a> 和 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Write.html" title="trait std::io::Write"><code>Write</code></a> trait 一样，<a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 和 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> 提供了用于读写输入和输出的最通用接口。然而，与标准库的 trait 不同，它们是<em>异步的</em>——这意味着从 <code>tokio::io</code> 类型读取或写入时，当 IO 未就绪时将<em>让步</em>给 Tokio 调度器，而不是阻塞。这允许在等待 IO 时运行其他任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Another difference is that <code>AsyncRead</code> and <code>AsyncWrite</code> only contain\ncore methods needed to provide asynchronous reading and writing\nfunctionality. Instead, utility methods are defined in the <a href="trait@AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a>\nand <a href="trait@AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> extension traits. These traits are automatically\nimplemented for all values that implement <code>AsyncRead</code> and <code>AsyncWrite</code>\nrespectively.</p>',
     '<p>另一个区别是，<code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 仅包含提供异步读写功能所需的核心方法。实用方法在 <a href="trait@AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> 和 <a href="trait@AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> 扩展 trait 中定义。这些 trait 会自动为分别实现了 <code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 的所有值实现。</p>'),
    ('<p>End users will rarely interact directly with <code>AsyncRead</code> and\n<code>AsyncWrite</code>. Instead, they will use the async functions defined in the\nextension traits. Library authors are expected to implement <code>AsyncRead</code>\nand <code>AsyncWrite</code> in order to provide types that behave like byte streams.</p>',
     '<p>最终用户很少会直接与 <code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 交互。相反，他们将使用扩展 trait 中定义的异步函数。库作者应实现 <code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 以提供表现为字节流的类型。</p>'),
    ('<p>Even with these differences, Tokio’s <code>AsyncRead</code> and <code>AsyncWrite</code> traits\ncan be used in almost exactly the same manner as the standard library’s\n<code>Read</code> and <code>Write</code>. Most types in the standard library that implement <code>Read</code>\nand <code>Write</code> have asynchronous equivalents in <code>tokio</code> that implement\n<code>AsyncRead</code> and <code>AsyncWrite</code>, such as <a href="crate::fs::File"><code>File</code></a> and <a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>即使存在这些差异，Tokio 的 <code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> trait 几乎可以与标准库的 <code>Read</code> 和 <code>Write</code> 完全相同的方式使用。标准库中实现 <code>Read</code> 和 <code>Write</code> 的大多数类型在 <code>tokio</code> 中都有实现 <code>AsyncRead</code> 和 <code>AsyncWrite</code> 的异步等价物，例如 <a href="crate::fs::File"><code>File</code></a> 和 <a href="../net/struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example, the standard library documentation introduces <code>Read</code> by\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/index.html#read-and-write" title="mod std::io">demonstrating</a> reading some bytes from a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/fs/struct.File.html" title="struct std::fs::File"><code>std::fs::File</code></a>. We\ncan do the same with <a href="crate::fs::File"><code>tokio::fs::File</code></a>:</p>',
     '<p>例如，标准库文档通过<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/index.html#read-and-write" title="mod std::io">演示</a>从 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/fs/struct.File.html" title="struct std::fs::File"><code>std::fs::File</code></a> 读取一些字节来介绍 <code>Read</code>。我们可以使用 <a href="crate::fs::File"><code>tokio::fs::File</code></a> 做同样的事情：</p>'),
    ('<p>Byte-based interfaces are unwieldy and can be inefficient, as we’d need to be\nmaking near-constant calls to the operating system. To help with this,\n<code>std::io</code> comes with <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/index.html#bufreader-and-bufwriter" title="mod std::io">support for <em>buffered</em> readers and writers</a>,\nand therefore, <code>tokio::io</code> does as well.</p>',
     '<p>基于字节的接口笨拙且效率低下，因为我们需要不断调用操作系统。为了解决这个问题，<code>std::io</code> 提供了对<em>缓冲</em>读写器的<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/index.html#bufreader-and-bufwriter" title="mod std::io">支持</a>，因此 <code>tokio::io</code> 也提供了支持。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio provides an async version of the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html" title="trait std::io::BufRead"><code>std::io::BufRead</code></a> trait,\n<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncBufRead"><code>AsyncBufRead</code></a>; and async <a href="crate::io::BufReader"><code>BufReader</code></a> and <a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> structs, which\nwrap readers and writers. These wrappers use a buffer, reducing the number\nof calls and providing nicer methods for accessing exactly what you want.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 提供了 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html" title="trait std::io::BufRead"><code>std::io::BufRead</code></a> trait 的异步版本 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncBufRead"><code>AsyncBufRead</code></a>；以及异步的 <a href="crate::io::BufReader"><code>BufReader</code></a> 和 <a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> 结构体，它们包装读写器。这些包装器使用缓冲区，减少了调用次数，并提供了更好的方法来访问你所需的内容。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example, <a href="crate::io::BufReader"><code>BufReader</code></a> works with the <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncBufRead"><code>AsyncBufRead</code></a> trait to add\nextra methods to any async reader:</p>',
     '<p>例如，<a href="crate::io::BufReader"><code>BufReader</code></a> 与 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncBufRead"><code>AsyncBufRead</code></a> trait 一起工作，为任何异步读取器添加额外的方法：</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> doesn’t add any new ways of writing; it just buffers every call\nto <a href="crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::write"><code>write</code></a>. However, you <strong>must</strong> flush\n<a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> to ensure that any buffered data is written.</p>',
     '<p><a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> 没有添加任何新的写入方式；它只是缓冲对 <a href="crate::io::AsyncWriteExt::write"><code>write</code></a> 的每次调用。但是，你<strong>必须</strong> flush <a href="crate::io::BufWriter"><code>BufWriter</code></a> 以确保任何缓冲的数据都已写入。</p>'),
    ('<p>Because they are traits, we can implement <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> and <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> for\nour own types, as well. Note that these traits must only be implemented for\nnon-blocking I/O types that integrate with the futures type system. In\nother words, these types must never block the thread, and instead the\ncurrent task is notified when the I/O resource is ready.</p>',
     '<p>因为它们是 trait，我们也可以为我们自己的类型实现 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 和 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a>。请注意，这些 trait 只能为与 futures 类型系统集成的非阻塞 I/O 类型实现。换句话说，这些类型绝不能阻塞线程，而是在 I/O 资源就绪时通知当前任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is often convenient to encapsulate the reading and writing of bytes in a\n<a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a> or <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/sink/trait.Sink.html"><code>Sink</code></a> of data.</p>',
     '<p>将字节的读写封装在数据的 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a> 或 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/sink/trait.Sink.html"><code>Sink</code></a> 中通常很方便。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio provides simple wrappers for converting <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> to <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a>\nand vice-versa in the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util">tokio-util</a> crate, see <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.ReaderStream.html"><code>ReaderStream</code></a> and\n<a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.StreamReader.html"><code>StreamReader</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 在 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util">tokio-util</a> crate 中提供了简单的包装器，用于在 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 和 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a> 之间相互转换，请参阅 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.ReaderStream.html"><code>ReaderStream</code></a> 和 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.StreamReader.html"><code>StreamReader</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>There are also utility traits that abstract the asynchronous buffering\nnecessary to write your own adaptors for encoding and decoding bytes to/from\nyour structured data, allowing to transform something that implements\n<a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a>/<a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> into a <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a>/<a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/sink/trait.Sink.html"><code>Sink</code></a>, see <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/trait.Decoder.html"><code>Decoder</code></a> and\n<a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/trait.Encoder.html"><code>Encoder</code></a> in the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/index.html">tokio-util::codec</a> module.</p>',
     '<p>还有一些实用 trait 抽象了编写自己的字节与结构化数据编码/解码适配器所需的异步缓冲，允许将实现了 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a>/<a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> 的内容转换为 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/stream/trait.Stream.html"><code>Stream</code></a>/<a href="https://docs.rs/futures/0.3/futures/sink/trait.Sink.html"><code>Sink</code></a>，请参阅 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/index.html">tokio-util::codec</a> 模块中的 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/trait.Decoder.html"><code>Decoder</code></a> 和 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/codec/trait.Encoder.html"><code>Encoder</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio provides asynchronous APIs to standard <a href="fn@stdin">input</a>, <a href="fn@stdout">output</a>, and <a href="fn@stderr">error</a>.\nThese APIs are very similar to the ones provided by <code>std</code>, but they also\nimplement <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> and <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>Tokio 为标准<a href="fn@stdin">输入</a>、<a href="fn@stdout">输出</a>和<a href="fn@stderr">错误</a>提供了异步 API。这些 API 与 <code>std</code> 提供的 API 非常相似，但它们还实现了 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 和 <a href="trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that the standard input / output APIs  <strong>must</strong> be used from the\ncontext of the Tokio runtime, as they require Tokio-specific features to\nfunction. Calling these functions outside of a Tokio runtime will panic.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，标准输入/输出 API <strong>必须</strong>在 Tokio 运行时的上下文中使用，因为它们需要 Tokio 特定的功能才能工作。在 Tokio 运行时之外调用这些函数会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Additionally, <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/struct.Error.html" title="struct std::io::error::Error"><code>Error</code></a>, <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html" title="enum std::io::error::ErrorKind"><code>ErrorKind</code></a>, <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/type.Result.html" title="type std::io::error::Result"><code>Result</code></a>, and <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/enum.SeekFrom.html" title="enum std::io::SeekFrom"><code>SeekFrom</code></a> are\nre-exported from <code>std::io</code> for ease of use.</p>',
     '<p>此外，<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/struct.Error.html" title="struct std::io::error::Error"><code>Error</code></a>、<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html" title="enum std::io::error::ErrorKind"><code>ErrorKind</code></a>、<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/type.Result.html" title="type std::io::error::Result"><code>Result</code></a> 和 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/enum.SeekFrom.html" title="enum std::io::SeekFrom"><code>SeekFrom</code></a> 从 <code>std::io</code> 重新导出，以方便使用。</p>'),
    # ============ Round 34: mpsc Receiver (17 items) ============
    ('<p>This receiver can be turned into a <code>Stream</code> using <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.ReceiverStream.html"><code>ReceiverStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此接收器可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.ReceiverStream.html"><code>ReceiverStream</code></a> 转换为 <code>Stream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are no messages in the channel’s buffer, but the channel has\nnot yet been closed, this method will sleep until a message is sent or\nthe channel is closed.  Note that if <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called, but there are\nstill outstanding <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a> from before it was closed, the channel is\nnot considered closed by <code>recv</code> until the permits are released.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的缓冲区中没有消息，但 channel 尚未关闭，则此方法将休眠，直到有消息被发送或 channel 被关闭。请注意，如果调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>，但仍有之前未完成的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a>，则 <code>recv</code> 不会认为 channel 已关闭，直到这些 permit 被释放。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method extends <code>buffer</code> by no more than a fixed number of values\nas specified by <code>limit</code>. If <code>limit</code> is zero, the function immediately\nreturns <code>0</code>. The return value is the number of values added to <code>buffer</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法以不超过 <code>limit</code> 指定的固定值数量扩展 <code>buffer</code>。如果 <code>limit</code> 为零，则函数立即返回 <code>0</code>。返回值是添加到 <code>buffer</code> 的值的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>For <code>limit &gt; 0</code>, if there are no messages in the channel’s queue, but\nthe channel has not yet been closed, this method will sleep until a\nmessage is sent or the channel is closed. Note that if <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is\ncalled, but there are still outstanding <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a> from before it was\nclosed, the channel is not considered closed by <code>recv_many</code> until the\npermits are released.</p>',
     '<p>对于 <code>limit &gt; 0</code>，如果 channel 队列中没有消息，但 channel 尚未关闭，则此方法将休眠，直到有消息被发送或 channel 被关闭。请注意，如果调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>，但仍有之前未完成的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a>，则 <code>recv_many</code> 不会认为 channel 已关闭，直到这些 permit 被释放。</p>'),
    ('<p>For non-zero values of <code>limit</code>, this method will never return <code>0</code> unless\nthe channel has been closed and there are no remaining messages in the\nchannel’s queue. This indicates that no further values can ever be\nreceived from this <code>Receiver</code>. The channel is closed when all senders\nhave been dropped, or when <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>对于 <code>limit</code> 的非零值，此方法永远不会返回 <code>0</code>，除非 channel 已关闭并且 channel 队列中没有剩余消息。这表明永远无法从此 <code>Receiver</code> 接收更多值。当所有 sender 都已被 drop 或调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike the <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.poll_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::poll_recv"><code>poll_recv</code></a> method, this method will never return an\n<a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> error spuriously.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.poll_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::poll_recv"><code>poll_recv</code></a> 方法不同，此方法绝不会虚假地返回 <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are no messages in the channel’s buffer, but the channel has\nnot yet been closed, this method will block until a message is sent or\nthe channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的缓冲区中没有消息，但 channel 尚未关闭，则此方法将阻塞，直到有消息被发送或 channel 被关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is intended for use cases where you are sending from\nasynchronous code to synchronous code, and will work even if the sender\nis not using <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.blocking_send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::blocking_send"><code>blocking_send</code></a> to send the message.</p>',
     '<p>此方法用于从异步代码向同步代码发送的用例，即使发送方没有使用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.blocking_send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::blocking_send"><code>blocking_send</code></a> 发送消息也能工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that if <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called, but there are still outstanding\n<a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a> from before it was closed, the channel is not considered\nclosed by <code>blocking_recv</code> until the permits are released.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果调用了 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a>，但仍有之前未完成的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permits</code></a>，则 <code>blocking_recv</code> 不会认为 channel 已关闭，直到这些 permit 被释放。</p>'),
    ('<p>Variant of <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::recv_many"><code>Self::recv_many</code></a> for blocking contexts.</p>',
     '<p>用于阻塞上下文的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::recv_many"><code>Self::recv_many</code></a> 变体。</p>'),
    ('<p>The same conditions as in <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>Self::blocking_recv</code></a> apply.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>Self::blocking_recv</code></a> 中的相同条件适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Closes the receiving half of a channel without dropping it.</p>',
     '<p>关闭 channel 的接收端，但不 drop 它。</p>'),
    ('<p>This prevents any further messages from being sent on the channel while\nstill enabling the receiver to drain messages that are buffered. Any\noutstanding <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> values will still be able to send messages.</p>',
     '<p>这可以防止任何进一步的消息在 channel 上发送，同时仍然允许接收器排出已缓冲的消息。任何未完成的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 值仍然能够发送消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>To guarantee that no messages are dropped, after calling <code>close()</code>,\n<code>recv()</code> must be called until <code>None</code> is returned. If there are\noutstanding <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> or <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> values, the <code>recv</code> method will\nnot return <code>None</code> until those are released.</p>',
     '<p>为了保证不会丢失消息，在调用 <code>close()</code> 之后，必须调用 <code>recv()</code> 直到返回 <code>None</code>。如果有未完成的 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.OwnedPermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::OwnedPermit"><code>OwnedPermit</code></a> 值，则 <code>recv</code> 方法在这些值被释放之前不会返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns <code>true</code> if the channel has been closed. The channel is closed\nwhen all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> have been dropped, or when <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 已关闭，则此方法返回 <code>true</code>。当所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 都已被 drop 或调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::close"><code>Receiver::close</code></a> 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>The capacity goes down when the sender sends a value by calling <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>Sender::send</code></a> or by reserving\ncapacity with <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>Sender::reserve</code></a>. The capacity goes up when values are received.\nThis is distinct from <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a>, which always returns buffer capacity initially\nspecified when calling <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>当 sender 通过调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>Sender::send</code></a> 或通过 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve"><code>Sender::reserve</code></a> 预留容量发送值时，容量会减少。当接收值时，容量会增加。这与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> 不同，后者始终返回调用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 时最初指定的缓冲区容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>The maximum capacity is the buffer capacity initially specified when calling\n<a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a>. This is distinct from <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a>, which returns the <em>current</em>\navailable buffer capacity: as messages are sent and received, the value\nreturned by <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> will go up or down, whereas the value\nreturned by <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> will remain constant.</p>',
     '<p>最大容量是调用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::mpsc::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 时最初指定的缓冲区容量。这与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> 不同，后者返回<em>当前</em>可用的缓冲区容量：随着消息的发送和接收，<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::capacity"><code>capacity</code></a> 返回的值会上下波动，而 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.max_capacity" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::max_capacity"><code>max_capacity</code></a> 返回的值保持不变。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 35: broadcast Receiver (17 items) ============
    ('<p>Receiving-half of the <a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel.</p>',
     '<p><a href="index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::broadcast"><code>broadcast</code></a> channel 的接收端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Must not be used concurrently. Messages may be retrieved using\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>不能并发使用。可以使用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 检索消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>To turn this receiver into a <code>Stream</code>, you can use the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.BroadcastStream.html"><code>BroadcastStream</code></a>\nwrapper.</p>',
     '<p>要将此接收器转换为 <code>Stream</code>，可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.BroadcastStream.html"><code>BroadcastStream</code></a> 包装器。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of messages that were sent into the channel and that\nthis <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> has yet to receive.</p>',
     '<p>返回已发送到 channel 中但此 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 尚未接收的消息数。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the returned value from <code>len</code> is larger than the next largest power of 2\nof the capacity of the channel any call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> will return an\n<code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code> and any call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> will return an\n<code>Err(TryRecvError::Lagged)</code>, e.g. if the capacity of the channel is 10,\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> will start to return <code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code> once <code>len</code> returns\nvalues larger than 16.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>len</code> 返回的值大于 channel 容量的下一个最大 2 的幂，则对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 的任何调用都将返回 <code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code>，并且对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> 的任何调用都将返回 <code>Err(TryRecvError::Lagged)</code>。例如，如果 channel 的容量为 10，则一旦 <code>len</code> 返回大于 16 的值，<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 将开始返回 <code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if there aren’t any messages in the channel that the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>\nhas yet to receive.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 中没有任何 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 尚未接收的消息，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns <code>true</code> if the channel has been closed. The channel is closed\nwhen all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> have been dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 已关闭，则此方法返回 <code>true</code>。当所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 都已被 drop 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Re-subscribes to the channel starting from the current tail element.</p>',
     '<p>从当前尾部元素开始重新订阅 channel。</p>'),
    ('<p>This <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle will receive a clone of all values sent\n<strong>after</strong> it has resubscribed. This will not include elements that are\nin the queue of the current receiver. Consider the following example.</p>',
     '<p>此 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄将接收在重新订阅<strong>之后</strong>发送的所有值的克隆。这不包括当前接收器队列中的元素。请考虑以下示例。</p>'),
    ('<p>Each <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle will receive a clone of all values sent\n<strong>after</strong> it has subscribed.</p>',
     '<p>每个 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄将接收在订阅<strong>之后</strong>发送的所有值的克隆。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Err(RecvError::Closed)</code> is returned when all <code>Sender</code> halves have\ndropped, indicating that no further values can be sent on the channel.</p>',
     '<p>当所有 <code>Sender</code> 端都已被 drop 时，返回 <code>Err(RecvError::Closed)</code>，表示无法再在 channel 上发送任何值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle falls behind, once the channel is full, newly\nsent values will overwrite old values. At this point, a call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>\nwill return with <code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code> and the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>’s\ninternal cursor is updated to point to the oldest value still held by\nthe channel. A subsequent call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> will return this value\n<strong>unless</strong> it has been since overwritten.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄滞后，一旦 channel 已满，新发送的值将覆盖旧值。此时，对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 的调用将返回 <code>Err(RecvError::Lagged)</code>，并且 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 的内部游标将更新为指向 channel 中仍保存的最旧值。随后对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 的调用将返回此值，<strong>除非</strong>它此后已被覆盖。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to return a pending value on this receiver without awaiting.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在不等待的情况下返回此接收器上的待处理值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is useful for a flavor of “optimistic check” before deciding to\nawait on a receiver.</p>',
     '<p>这对于在决定等待接收器之前的"乐观检查"很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Compared with <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>, this function has three failure cases instead of two\n(one for closed, one for an empty buffer, one for a lagging receiver).</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 相比，此函数有三种失败情况而不是两种（关闭、空缓冲区和滞后接收器各一种）。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Err(TryRecvError::Closed)</code> is returned when all <code>Sender</code> halves have\ndropped, indicating that no further values can be sent on the channel.</p>',
     '<p>当所有 <code>Sender</code> 端都已被 drop 时，返回 <code>Err(TryRecvError::Closed)</code>，表示无法再在 channel 上发送任何值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle falls behind, once the channel is full, newly\nsent values will overwrite old values. At this point, a call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>\nwill return with <code>Err(TryRecvError::Lagged)</code> and the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>’s\ninternal cursor is updated to point to the oldest value still held by\nthe channel. A subsequent call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> will return this value\n<strong>unless</strong> it has been since overwritten. If there are no values to\nreceive, <code>Err(TryRecvError::Empty)</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄滞后，一旦 channel 已满，新发送的值将覆盖旧值。此时，对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 的调用将返回 <code>Err(TryRecvError::Lagged)</code>，并且 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 的内部游标将更新为指向 channel 中仍保存的最旧值。随后对 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.try_recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::try_recv"><code>try_recv</code></a> 的调用将返回此值，<strong>除非</strong>它此后已被覆盖。如果没有可接收的值，则返回 <code>Err(TryRecvError::Empty)</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 36: NamedPipeServer (17 items) ============
    ('<p>A <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/ipc/named-pipes">Windows named pipe</a> server.</p>',
     '<p><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/ipc/named-pipes">Windows 命名管道</a> 服务器。</p>'),
    ('<p>Accepting client connections involves creating a server with\n<a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>ServerOptions::create</code></a> and waiting for clients to connect using\n<a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::connect"><code>NamedPipeServer::connect</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>接受客户端连接涉及使用 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.create" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::create"><code>ServerOptions::create</code></a> 创建服务器，并使用 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::connect"><code>NamedPipeServer::connect</code></a> 等待客户端连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>To avoid having clients sporadically fail with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.NotFound" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::NotFound"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::NotFound</code></a> when they connect to a server, we must\nensure that at least one server instance is available at all times. This\nmeans that the typical listen loop for a server is a bit involved, because\nwe have to ensure that we never drop a server accidentally while a client\nmight connect.</p>',
     '<p>为避免客户端在连接服务器时偶尔因 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.NotFound" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::NotFound"><code>std::io::ErrorKind::NotFound</code></a> 而失败，我们必须确保始终至少有一个服务器实例可用。这意味着服务器的典型监听循环有点复杂，因为我们必须确保在客户端可能连接时永远不会意外地 drop 服务器。</p>'),
    ('<p>So a correctly implemented server looks like this:</p>',
     '<p>因此，正确实现的服务器如下所示：</p>'),
    ('<p>Constructs a new named pipe server from the specified raw handle.</p>',
     '<p>从指定的原始句柄构造一个新的命名管道服务器。</p>'),
    ('<p>Retrieves information about the named pipe the server is associated\nwith.</p>',
     '<p>检索与服务器关联的命名管道的信息。</p>'),
    ('<p>Enables a named pipe server process to wait for a client process to\nconnect to an instance of a named pipe. A client process connects by\ncreating a named pipe with the same name.</p>',
     '<p>使命名管道服务器进程能够等待客户端进程连接到命名管道的实例。客户端进程通过创建具有相同名称的命名管道来连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/namedpipeapi/nf-namedpipeapi-connectnamedpipe"><code>ConnectNamedPipe</code></a> system call.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/namedpipeapi/nf-namedpipeapi-connectnamedpipe"><code>ConnectNamedPipe</code></a> 系统调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is cancellation safe in the sense that if it is used as the\nevent in a <a href="crate::select"><code>select!</code></a> statement and some other branch\ncompletes first, then no connection events have been lost.</p>',
     '<p>在某种意义上此方法是取消安全的：如果在 <a href="crate::select"><code>select!</code></a> 语句中将其用作事件，并且其他某个分支先完成，则不会丢失任何连接事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Disconnects the server end of a named pipe instance from a client\nprocess.</p>',
     '<p>将命名管道实例的服务器端与客户端进程断开连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序复制数据以填充每个缓冲区，最后写入的缓冲区可能只被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序从每个缓冲区写入数据，最后读取的缓冲区可能只被部分使用。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the\nmethods defined on the Tokio <code>NamedPipeServer</code> type, as this will mess with\nthe readiness flag and can cause the pipe to behave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包不应使用 Tokio <code>NamedPipeServer</code> 类型上定义的任何方法执行 IO 操作，因为这会干扰就绪标志并可能导致管道行为异常。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>, <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>、<a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.NamedPipeServer.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeServer::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数一起使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The closure should not perform the IO operation using any of the methods\ndefined on the Tokio <code>NamedPipeServer</code> type, as this will mess with the\nreadiness flag and can cause the pipe to behave incorrectly.</p>',
     '<p>闭包不应使用 Tokio <code>NamedPipeServer</code> 类型上定义的任何方法执行 IO 操作，因为这会干扰就绪标志并可能导致管道行为异常。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 37: spawn_blocking (16 items) ============
    ('<p>Runs the provided closure on a thread where blocking is acceptable.</p>',
     '<p>在可以接受阻塞的线程上运行所提供的闭包。</p>'),
    ('<p>In general, issuing a blocking call or performing a lot of compute in a\nfuture without yielding is problematic, as it may prevent the executor from\ndriving other futures forward. This function runs the provided closure on a\nthread dedicated to blocking operations. See the <a href="../index.html#cpu-bound-tasks-and-blocking-code">CPU-bound tasks and\nblocking code</a> section for more information.</p>',
     '<p>一般来说，在不让步的 future 中发出阻塞调用或执行大量计算是有问题的，因为它可能会阻止执行器驱动其他 future 向前。此函数在专用于阻塞操作的线程上运行所提供的闭包。有关更多信息，请参阅<a href="../index.html#cpu-bound-tasks-and-blocking-code">CPU-bound 任务和阻塞代码</a>部分。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tokio will spawn more blocking threads when they are requested through this\nfunction until the upper limit configured on the <a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder"><code>Builder</code></a> is reached.\nAfter reaching the upper limit, the tasks are put in a queue.\nThe thread limit is very large by default, because <code>spawn_blocking</code> is often\nused for various kinds of IO operations that cannot be performed\nasynchronously.  When you run CPU-bound code using <code>spawn_blocking</code>, you\nshould keep this large upper limit in mind. When running many CPU-bound\ncomputations, a semaphore or some other synchronization primitive should be\nused to limit the number of computations executed in parallel. Specialized\nCPU-bound executors, such as <a href="https://docs.rs/rayon">rayon</a>, may also be a good fit.</p>',
     '<p>当通过此函数请求阻塞线程时，Tokio 将生成更多的阻塞线程，直到达到 <a href="../runtime/struct.Builder.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Builder"><code>Builder</code></a> 上配置的上限为止。达到上限后，任务将放入队列中。默认情况下，线程上限非常大，因为 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 通常用于无法异步执行的各种 IO 操作。当你使用 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 运行 CPU-bound 代码时，应牢记这个大上限。当运行许多 CPU-bound 计算时，应使用信号量或其他同步原语来限制并行执行的计算数量。专门的 CPU-bound 执行器（例如 <a href="https://docs.rs/rayon">rayon</a>）也可能是合适的选择。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for non-async operations that eventually finish on\ntheir own. If you want to spawn an ordinary thread, you should use\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a> instead.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于最终自行完成的非异步操作。如果要生成普通线程，应改用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Be aware that tasks spawned using <code>spawn_blocking</code> cannot be aborted\nbecause they are not async. If you call <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>abort</code></a> on a <code>spawn_blocking</code>\ntask, then this <em>will not have any effect</em>, and the task will continue\nrunning normally. The exception is if the task has not started running\nyet; in that case, calling <code>abort</code> may prevent the task from starting.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，使用 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 生成的任务无法中止，因为它们不是异步的。如果对 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务调用 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>abort</code></a>，那么<em>这将没有任何效果</em>，任务将继续正常运行。例外情况是如果任务尚未开始运行；在这种情况下，调用 <code>abort</code> 可能会阻止任务启动。</p>'),
    ('<p>When you shut down the executor, it will attempt to <code>abort</code> all tasks\nincluding <code>spawn_blocking</code> tasks. However, <code>spawn_blocking</code> tasks\ncannot be aborted once they start running, which means that runtime\nshutdown will wait indefinitely for all started <code>spawn_blocking</code> to\nfinish running. You can use <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> to stop waiting for\nthem after a certain timeout. Be aware that this will still not cancel\nthe tasks — they are simply allowed to keep running after the method\nreturns. It is possible for a blocking task to be cancelled if it has\nnot yet started running, but this is not guaranteed.</p>',
     '<p>关闭执行器时，它将尝试 <code>abort</code> 所有任务，包括 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务。但是，<code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务一旦开始运行就无法中止，这意味着运行时关闭将无限期地等待所有已开始的 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 完成运行。你可以使用 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.shutdown_timeout" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::shutdown_timeout"><code>shutdown_timeout</code></a> 在某个超时后停止等待它们。请注意，这仍然不会取消任务——只是允许它们在该方法返回后继续运行。如果阻塞任务尚未开始运行，则可能会被取消，但这并不能保证。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>spawn_blocking</code> is intended for <em>bounded</em> blocking work that eventually finishes.\nEach call occupies a thread from the runtime’s blocking thread pool for the duration\nof the task. Long-lived tasks therefore reduce the pool’s effective capacity, which\ncan delay other blocking operations once the pool is saturated and work is queued.</p>',
     '<p><code>spawn_blocking</code> 用于最终完成的<em>有界</em>阻塞工作。每次调用都会在任务的整个持续时间内占用运行时阻塞线程池中的一个线程。因此，长期运行的任务会降低线程池的有效容量，一旦线程池饱和并且工作被排队，这可能会延迟其他阻塞操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>For workloads that run indefinitely or for extended periods (for example,\nbackground workers or persistent processing loops), prefer a dedicated thread created with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对于无限运行或长时间运行的负载（例如后台工作进程或持久处理循环），首选使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/functions/fn.spawn.html" title="fn std::thread::functions::spawn"><code>thread::spawn</code></a> 创建的专用线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>As a rule of thumb:</p>',
     '<p>经验法则是：</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that if you are using the single threaded runtime, this function will\nstill spawn additional threads for blocking operations. The current-thread\nscheduler’s single thread is only used for asynchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果你使用的是单线程运行时，此函数仍会为阻塞操作生成其他线程。当前线程调度器的单个线程仅用于异步代码。</p>'),
    ('<p>In simple cases, it is sufficient to have the closure accept input\nparameters at creation time and return a single value (or struct/tuple, etc.).</p>',
     '<p>在简单情况下，让闭包在创建时接受输入参数并返回单个值（或结构体/元组等）就足够了。</p>'),
    ('<p>For more complex situations in which it is desirable to stream data to or from\nthe synchronous context, the <a href="../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc channel</code></a> has <code>blocking_send</code> and\n<code>blocking_recv</code> methods for use in non-async code such as the thread created\nby <code>spawn_blocking</code>.</p>',
     '<p>对于希望将数据流入或流出同步上下文的更复杂情况，<a href="../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>mpsc channel</code></a> 具有 <code>blocking_send</code> 和 <code>blocking_recv</code> 方法，可用于由 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 创建的线程等非异步代码。</p>'),
    ('<p>Another option is <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.SyncIoBridge.html"><code>SyncIoBridge</code></a> for cases where the synchronous context\nis operating on byte streams.  For example, you might use an asynchronous\nHTTP client such as <a href="https://docs.rs/hyper">hyper</a> to fetch data, but perform complex parsing\nof the payload body using a library written for synchronous I/O.</p>',
     '<p>另一种选择是 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-util/latest/tokio_util/io/struct.SyncIoBridge.html"><code>SyncIoBridge</code></a>，用于同步上下文在字节流上操作的情况。例如，你可能使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/hyper">hyper</a> 等异步 HTTP 客户端获取数据，但使用为同步 I/O 编写的库对有效负载正文执行复杂的解析。</p>'),
    ('<p>Finally, see also <a href="https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging">Bridging with sync code</a> for discussions\naround the opposite case of using Tokio as part of a larger synchronous\ncodebase.</p>',
     '<p>最后，另请参阅<a href="https://tokio.rs/tokio/topics/bridging">与同步代码桥接</a>，其中讨论了将 Tokio 作为更大同步代码库一部分使用的相反情况。</p>'),
    ('<p>Pass an input value and receive result of computation:</p>',
     '<p>传递输入值并接收计算结果：</p>'),
    ('<p>Use a channel:</p>',
     '<p>使用 channel：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 38: spawn (15 items) ============
    ('<p>Spawns a new asynchronous task, returning a\n<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> for it.</p>',
     '<p>生成一个新的异步任务，并为其返回一个 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen <code>spawn</code> is called, even if you don’t await the returned\n<a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>调用 <code>spawn</code> 时，所提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你没有 await 返回的 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Spawning a task enables the task to execute concurrently to other tasks. The\nspawned task may execute on the current thread, or it may be sent to a\ndifferent thread to be executed. The specifics depend on the current\n<a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> configuration. In a\n<a href="../runtime/index.html#driving-the-runtime">running runtime</a>, the task will start immediately in the\nbackground. On a blocked runtime, the user must drive the runtime forward (for\nexample, by calling <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>).</p>',
     '<p>生成任务使该任务能够与其他任务并发执行。生成的任务可能在当前线程上执行，也可能被发送到另一个线程执行。具体细节取决于当前的 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 配置。在<a href="../runtime/index.html#driving-the-runtime">正在运行的运行时</a>中，任务将立即在后台启动。在阻塞的运行时上，用户必须推动运行时向前（例如，通过调用 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.block_on" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::block_on"><code>Runtime::block_on</code></a>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is guaranteed that spawn will not synchronously poll the task being spawned.\nThis means that calling spawn while holding a lock does not pose a risk of\ndeadlocking with the spawned task.</p>',
     '<p>保证 spawn 不会同步轮询正在生成的任务。这意味着在持有锁时调用 spawn 不会与生成的任务产生死锁风险。</p>'),
    ('<p>There is no guarantee that a spawned task will execute to completion.\nWhen a runtime is shutdown, all outstanding tasks are dropped,\nregardless of the lifecycle of that task.</p>',
     '<p>不能保证生成的任务一定会执行到完成。关闭运行时时，所有未完成的任务都将被 drop，无论该任务的生命周期如何。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function must be called from the context of a Tokio runtime. Tasks running on\nthe Tokio runtime are always inside its context, but you can also enter the context\nusing the <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>此函数必须从 Tokio 运行时的上下文中调用。在 Tokio 运行时上运行的任务始终在其上下文中，但你也可以使用 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html#method.enter" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::enter"><code>Runtime::enter</code></a> 方法进入该上下文。</p>'),
    ('<p>In this example, a server is started and <code>spawn</code> is used to start a new task\nthat processes each received connection.</p>',
     '<p>在此示例中，启动了服务器，并使用 <code>spawn</code> 启动一个新任务来处理每个接收到的连接。</p>'),
    ('<p>To run multiple tasks in parallel and receive their results, join\nhandles can be stored in a vector.</p>',
     '<p>要并行运行多个任务并接收它们的结果，可以将 join handle 存储在向量中。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example pushes the tasks to <code>outputs</code> in the order they were\nstarted in. If you do not care about the ordering of the outputs, then\nyou can also use a <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此示例按任务启动顺序将任务推送到 <code>outputs</code>。如果你不关心输出的顺序，则也可以使用 <a href="struct.JoinSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinSet"><code>JoinSet</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Panics if called from <strong>outside</strong> of the Tokio runtime.</p>',
     '<p>如果从 Tokio 运行时的<strong>外部</strong>调用，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>The task supplied to <code>spawn</code> must implement <code>Send</code>. However, it is\npossible to <strong>use</strong> <code>!Send</code> values from the task as long as they only\nexist between calls to <code>.await</code>.</p>',
     '<p>提供给 <code>spawn</code> 的任务必须实现 <code>Send</code>。但是，只要 <code>!Send</code> 值仅存在于对 <code>.await</code> 的调用之间，就可以从任务中<strong>使用</strong>它们。</p>'),
    ('<p>For example, this will work:</p>',
     '<p>例如，这是可行的：</p>'),
    ('<p>This will <strong>not</strong> work:</p>',
     '<p>这是<strong>不可行</strong>的：</p>'),
    ('<p>Holding on to a <code>!Send</code> value across calls to <code>.await</code> will result in\nan unfriendly compile error message similar to:</p>',
     '<p>在跨 <code>.await</code> 调用之间持有 <code>!Send</code> 值将导致类似于以下的、不友好的编译错误消息：</p>'),
    ('<p>or:</p>',
     '<p>或：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 39: Interest (15 items) ============
    ('<p>Specifies the readiness events the caller is interested in when awaiting on\nI/O resource readiness states.</p>',
     '<p>指定调用者在等待 I/O 资源就绪状态时所感兴趣的就绪事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Interest in all readable events.</p>',
     '<p>对所有可读事件感兴趣。</p>'),
    ('<p>Readable interest includes read-closed events.</p>',
     '<p>可读兴趣包括读取关闭事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Interest in all writable events.</p>',
     '<p>对所有可写事件感兴趣。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writable interest includes write-closed events.</p>',
     '<p>可写兴趣包括写入关闭事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Interest in error events.</p>',
     '<p>对错误事件感兴趣。</p>'),
    ('<p>Passes error interest to the underlying OS selector.\nBehavior is platform-specific, read your platform’s documentation.</p>',
     '<p>将错误兴趣传递给底层 OS 选择器。行为是平台特定的，请阅读你所在平台的文档。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the value includes readable interest.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括可读兴趣，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the value includes writable interest.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括可写兴趣，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the value includes error interest.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括错误兴趣，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Add together two <code>Interest</code> values.</p>',
     '<p>将两个 <code>Interest</code> 值相加。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function works from a <code>const</code> context.</p>',
     '<p>此函数可在 <code>const</code> 上下文中工作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Remove <code>Interest</code> from <code>self</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>self</code> 中移除 <code>Interest</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Interests present in <code>other</code> but <em>not</em> in <code>self</code> are ignored.</p>',
     '<p>出现在 <code>other</code> 中但<em>不</em>在 <code>self</code> 中的兴趣将被忽略。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>None</code> if the set would be empty after removing <code>Interest</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在移除 <code>Interest</code> 后集合为空，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 40: MissedTickBehavior (14 items) ============
    ('<p>Defines the behavior of an <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> when it misses a tick.</p>',
     '<p>定义 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 错过 tick 时的行为。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sometimes, an <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a>’s tick is missed. For example, consider the\nfollowing:</p>',
     '<p>有时，<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 的 tick 会被错过。例如，请考虑以下情况：</p>'),
    ('<p>Generally, a tick is missed if too much time is spent without calling\n<a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>Interval::tick()</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>一般来说，如果在调用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>Interval::tick()</code></a> 之前花费了太多时间，则会错过 tick。</p>'),
    ('<p>By default, when a tick is missed, <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> fires ticks as quickly as it\ncan until it is “caught up” in time to where it should be.\n<code>MissedTickBehavior</code> can be used to specify a different behavior for\n<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> to exhibit. Each variant represents a different strategy.</p>',
     '<p>默认情况下，当错过 tick 时，<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 会尽快触发 tick，直到它在时间上"赶上"它应该在的位置。可以使用 <code>MissedTickBehavior</code> 来为 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 指定不同的行为。每个变体代表一种不同的策略。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that because the executor cannot guarantee exact precision with timers,\nthese strategies will only apply when the delay is greater than 5\nmilliseconds.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，由于执行器无法保证计时器的精确精度，因此这些策略仅在延迟大于 5 毫秒时适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Ticks as fast as possible until caught up.</p>',
     '<p>尽可能快地触发 tick，直到赶上为止。</p>'),
    ('<p>When this strategy is used, <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> schedules ticks “normally” (the\nsame as it would have if the ticks hadn’t been delayed), which results\nin it firing ticks as fast as possible until it is caught up in time to\nwhere it should be. Unlike <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a> and <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a>, the ticks yielded\nwhen <code>Burst</code> is used (the <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>Instant</code></a>s that <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a>\nyields) aren’t different than they would have been if a tick had not\nbeen missed. Like <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a>, and unlike <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a>, the ticks may be\nshortened.</p>',
     '<p>当使用此策略时，<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 以"正常"方式调度 tick（与 tick 没有延迟时的方式相同），这会导致它尽快触发 tick，直到它在时间上赶上它应该在的位置。与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a> 和 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a> 不同，使用 <code>Burst</code> 时产生的 tick（<a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a> 产生的 <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>Instant</code></a>）与未错过 tick 时没什么不同。与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a> 类似，与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a> 不同，tick 可能会被缩短。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is the default behavior when <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> is created with\n<a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> and <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是使用 <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a> 创建 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 时的默认行为。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tick at multiples of <code>period</code> from when <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a> was called, rather than\nfrom <code>start</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从调用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a> 开始以 <code>period</code> 的倍数触发 tick，而不是从 <code>start</code> 开始。</p>'),
    ('<p>When this strategy is used and <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> has missed a tick, instead\nof scheduling ticks to fire at multiples of <code>period</code> from <code>start</code> (the\ntime when the first tick was fired), it schedules all future ticks to\nhappen at a regular <code>period</code> from the point when <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a> was called.\nUnlike <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> and <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a>, ticks are not shortened, and they aren’t\nguaranteed to happen at a multiple of <code>period</code> from <code>start</code> any longer.</p>',
     '<p>当使用此策略并且 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 错过一个 tick 时，它不会从 <code>start</code>（第一个 tick 触发的时间）开始以 <code>period</code> 的倍数调度 tick 触发，而是将所有未来的 tick 调度为从调用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>tick</code></a> 的点开始以规则 <code>period</code> 发生。与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 和 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Skip" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Skip"><code>Skip</code></a> 不同，tick 不会被缩短，也不再保证以从 <code>start</code> 开始的 <code>period</code> 的倍数发生。</p>'),
    ('<p>Skips missed ticks and tick on the next multiple of <code>period</code> from\n<code>start</code>.</p>',
     '<p>跳过错过的 tick，并在从 <code>start</code> 开始的下一个 <code>period</code> 倍数上 tick。</p>'),
    ('<p>When this strategy is used, <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> schedules the next tick to fire\nat the next-closest tick that is a multiple of <code>period</code> away from\n<code>start</code> (the point where <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> first ticked). Like <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>, all\nticks remain multiples of <code>period</code> away from <code>start</code>, but unlike\n<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>, the ticks may not be <em>one</em> multiple of <code>period</code> away from the\nlast tick. Like <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a>, the ticks are no longer the same as they\nwould have been if ticks had not been missed, but unlike <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a>, and\nlike <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>, the ticks may be shortened to be less than one <code>period</code>\naway from each other.</p>',
     '<p>当使用此策略时，<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 将下一个 tick 调度为在距离 <code>start</code>（<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 第一次 tick 的点）的 <code>period</code> 下一个最近倍数处触发。与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 类似，所有 tick 都保持距 <code>start</code> 的 <code>period</code> 的倍数，但与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 不同，tick 可能距上一个 tick 不是 <code>period</code> 的<em>一个</em>倍数。与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a> 类似，tick 不再与未错过 tick 时相同，但与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Delay" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Delay"><code>Delay</code></a> 不同且与 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 类似，tick 可能会被缩短到彼此相隔不到一个 <code>period</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>MissedTickBehavior::Burst</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>返回 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>MissedTickBehavior::Burst</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For most usecases, the <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> strategy is what is desired.\nAdditionally, to preserve backwards compatibility, the <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>\nstrategy must be the default. For these reasons,\n<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>MissedTickBehavior::Burst</code></a> is the default for <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a>.\nSee <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> for more details.</p>',
     '<p>对于大多数用例，<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 策略正是所需要的。此外，为了保持向后兼容性，<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a> 策略必须是默认策略。出于这些原因，<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>MissedTickBehavior::Burst</code></a> 是 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 的默认值。有关更多详细信息，请参阅 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 41: oneshot Sender (14 items) ============
    ('<p>Sends a value to the associated <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>向关联的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 发送一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to send a value on this channel, returning it back if it could\nnot be sent.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在此 channel 上发送一个值，如果无法发送则将其返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method consumes <code>self</code> as only one value may ever be sent on a <code>oneshot</code>\nchannel. It is not marked async because sending a message to a <code>oneshot</code>\nchannel never requires any form of waiting.  Because of this, the <code>send</code>\nmethod can be used in both synchronous and asynchronous code without\nproblems.</p>',
     '<p>此方法会消费 <code>self</code>，因为 <code>oneshot</code> channel 上只能发送一个值。它未标记为 async，因为向 <code>oneshot</code> channel 发送消息永远不需要任何形式的等待。因此，<code>send</code> 方法可以在同步和异步代码中使用而不会出现问题。</p>'),
    ('<p>A successful send occurs when it is determined that the other end of the\nchannel has not hung up already. An unsuccessful send would be one where\nthe corresponding receiver has already been deallocated. Note that a\nreturn value of <code>Err</code> means that the data will never be received, but\na return value of <code>Ok</code> does <em>not</em> mean that the data will be received.\nIt is possible for the corresponding receiver to hang up immediately\nafter this function returns <code>Ok</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当确定 channel 的另一端尚未挂起时，发送成功。发送失败是指相应的接收器已被释放。请注意，返回值 <code>Err</code> 意味着数据将永远不会被接收，但返回值 <code>Ok</code> <em>并不</em>意味着数据将被接收。相应的接收器可能会在此函数返回 <code>Ok</code> 后立即挂起。</p>'),
    ('<p>Send a value to another task</p>',
     '<p>将值发送到另一个任务</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for the associated <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle to close.</p>',
     '<p>等待关联的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is useful when paired with <code>select!</code> to abort a\ncomputation when the receiver is no longer interested in the result.</p>',
     '<p>当与 <code>select!</code> 配合使用时，此函数很有用，可在接收器不再对结果感兴趣时中止计算。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Future</code> which must be awaited on.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个必须被 await 的 <code>Future</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Paired with select</p>',
     '<p>与 select 配合使用</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the associated <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle has been dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果关联的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄已被 drop，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If <code>true</code> is returned, a call to <code>send</code> will always result in an error.</p>',
     '<p>如果返回 <code>true</code>，则对 <code>send</code> 的调用将始终导致错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks whether the <code>oneshot</code> channel has been closed, and if not, schedules the\n<code>Waker</code> in the provided <code>Context</code> to receive a notification when the channel is\nclosed.</p>',
     '<p>检查 <code>oneshot</code> channel 是否已关闭，如果没有关闭，则在提供的 <code>Context</code> 中调度 <code>Waker</code>，以在 channel 关闭时接收通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is closed by either calling <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> explicitly, or when the\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> value is dropped.</p>',
     '<p>通过显式调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 或当 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 值被 drop 时，<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that on multiple calls to poll, only the <code>Waker</code> from the <code>Context</code> passed\nto the most recent call will be scheduled to receive a wakeup.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在多次调用 poll 时，只有传递给最近一次调用的 <code>Context</code> 中的 <code>Waker</code> 才会被调度接收唤醒。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 42: UnboundedReceiver (14 items) ============
    ('<p>Receive values from the associated <code>UnboundedSender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从关联的 <code>UnboundedSender</code> 接收值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This receiver can be turned into a <code>Stream</code> using <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.UnboundedReceiverStream.html"><code>UnboundedReceiverStream</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此接收器可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream/0.1/tokio_stream/wrappers/struct.UnboundedReceiverStream.html"><code>UnboundedReceiverStream</code></a> 转换为 <code>Stream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns <code>None</code> if the channel has been closed and there are\nno remaining messages in the channel’s buffer. This indicates that no\nfurther values can ever be received from this <code>Receiver</code>. The channel is\nclosed when all senders have been dropped, or when <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 已关闭并且 channel 缓冲区中没有剩余消息，则此方法返回 <code>None</code>。这表明永远无法从此 <code>Receiver</code> 接收更多值。当所有 sender 都已被 drop 或调用 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>If there are no messages in the channel’s buffer, but the channel has\nnot yet been closed, this method will sleep until a message is sent or\nthe channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的缓冲区中没有消息，但 channel 尚未关闭，则此方法将休眠，直到有消息被发送或 channel 被关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method extends <code>buffer</code> by no more than a fixed number of values\nas specified by <code>limit</code>. If <code>limit</code> is zero, the function returns\nimmediately with <code>0</code>. The return value is the number of values added to\n<code>buffer</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此方法以不超过 <code>limit</code> 指定的固定值数量扩展 <code>buffer</code>。如果 <code>limit</code> 为零，则函数立即返回 <code>0</code>。返回值是添加到 <code>buffer</code> 的值的数量。</p>'),
    ('<p>For <code>limit &gt; 0</code>, if there are no messages in the channel’s queue,\nbut the channel has not yet been closed, this method will sleep\nuntil a message is sent or the channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>对于 <code>limit &gt; 0</code>，如果 channel 队列中没有消息，但 channel 尚未关闭，则此方法将休眠，直到有消息被发送或 channel 被关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>For non-zero values of <code>limit</code>, this method will never return <code>0</code> unless\nthe channel has been closed and there are no remaining messages in the\nchannel’s queue. This indicates that no further values can ever be\nreceived from this <code>Receiver</code>. The channel is closed when all senders\nhave been dropped, or when <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>对于 <code>limit</code> 的非零值，此方法永远不会返回 <code>0</code>，除非 channel 已关闭并且 channel 队列中没有剩余消息。这表明永远无法从此 <code>Receiver</code> 接收更多值。当所有 sender 都已被 drop 或调用 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike the <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.poll_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::poll_recv"><code>poll_recv</code></a> method, this method will never return an\n<a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> error spuriously.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.poll_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::poll_recv"><code>poll_recv</code></a> 方法不同，此方法绝不会虚假地返回 <a href="error/enum.TryRecvError.html#variant.Empty" title="variant tokio::sync::mpsc::error::TryRecvError::Empty"><code>Empty</code></a> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Variant of <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.recv_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::recv_many"><code>Self::recv_many</code></a> for blocking contexts.</p>',
     '<p>用于阻塞上下文的 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.recv_many" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::recv_many"><code>Self::recv_many</code></a> 变体。</p>'),
    ('<p>The same conditions as in <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::blocking_recv"><code>Self::blocking_recv</code></a> apply.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::blocking_recv"><code>Self::blocking_recv</code></a> 中的相同条件适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Closes the receiving half of a channel, without dropping it.</p>',
     '<p>关闭 channel 的接收端，但不 drop 它。</p>'),
    ('<p>This prevents any further messages from being sent on the channel while\nstill enabling the receiver to drain messages that are buffered.</p>',
     '<p>这可以防止任何进一步的消息在 channel 上发送，同时仍然允许接收器排出已缓冲的消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>To guarantee that no messages are dropped, after calling <code>close()</code>,\n<code>recv()</code> must be called until <code>None</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>为了保证不会丢失消息，在调用 <code>close()</code> 之后，必须调用 <code>recv()</code> 直到返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns <code>true</code> if the channel has been closed. The channel is closed\nwhen all <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> have been dropped, or when <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>UnboundedReceiver::close</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 已关闭，则此方法返回 <code>true</code>。当所有 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 都已被 drop 或调用 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>UnboundedReceiver::close</code></a> 时，channel 关闭。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 43: mpsc/index (14 items) ============
    ('<p>This module provides two variants of the channel: bounded and unbounded. The\nbounded variant has a limit on the number of messages that the channel can\nstore, and if this limit is reached, trying to send another message will\nwait until a message is received from the channel. An unbounded channel has\nan infinite capacity, so the <code>send</code> method will always complete immediately.\nThis makes the <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> usable from both synchronous and\nasynchronous code.</p>',
     '<p>此模块提供两种 channel 变体：有界和无界。有界变体对 channel 可以存储的消息数量有限制，如果达到此限制，则尝试发送另一条消息将等待，直到从 channel 接收一条消息为止。无界 channel 具有无限容量，因此 <code>send</code> 方法将始终立即完成。这使得 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 可用于同步和异步代码。</p>'),
    ('<p>Similar to the <code>mpsc</code> channels provided by <code>std</code>, the channel constructor\nfunctions provide separate send and receive handles, <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> for the bounded channel, <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a> for the unbounded channel. If there is no message to read,\nthe current task will be notified when a new value is sent. <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> allow sending values into the channel. If the bounded\nchannel is at capacity, the send is rejected and the task will be notified\nwhen additional capacity is available. In other words, the channel provides\nbackpressure.</p>',
     '<p>与 <code>std</code> 提供的 <code>mpsc</code> channel 类似，channel 构造函数提供单独的发送和接收句柄：有界 channel 的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>，无界 channel 的 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a>。如果没有可读取的消息，则在发送新值时将通知当前任务。<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 允许将值发送到 channel。如果有界 channel 已达到容量，则发送将被拒绝，并在有额外容量可用时通知该任务。换句话说，channel 提供了背压。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel is also suitable for the single-producer single-consumer\nuse-case. (Unless you only need to send one message, in which case you\nshould use the <a href="../oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot">oneshot</a> channel.)</p>',
     '<p>此 channel 也适用于单生产者单消费者用例。（除非你只需要发送一条消息，在这种情况下，你应该使用 <a href="../oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot">oneshot</a> channel。）</p>'),
    ('<p>When all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles have been dropped, it is no longer\npossible to send values into the channel. This is considered the termination\nevent of the stream. Once all senders have been dropped and any remaining\nbuffered values have been received, <code>Receiver::recv</code> returns <code>None</code>\n(and <code>Receiver::poll_recv</code> returns <code>Poll::Ready(None)</code>).</p>',
     '<p>当所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop 时，就不再可能向 channel 发送值。这被视为流的终止事件。一旦所有 sender 都已被 drop 并且任何剩余的缓冲值都已接收，<code>Receiver::recv</code> 将返回 <code>None</code>（并且 <code>Receiver::poll_recv</code> 返回 <code>Poll::Ready(None)</code>）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle is dropped, then messages can no longer\nbe read out of the channel. In this case, all further attempts to send will\nresult in an error. Additionally, all unread messages will be drained from the\nchannel and dropped.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄被 drop，则无法再从 channel 中读取消息。在这种情况下，所有进一步的发送尝试都将导致错误。此外，所有未读消息都将从 channel 中排出并被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is dropped, it is possible for unprocessed messages to\nremain in the channel. Instead, it is usually desirable to perform a “clean”\nshutdown. To do this, the receiver first calls <code>close</code>, which will prevent\nany further messages to be sent into the channel. Then, the receiver\nconsumes the channel to completion, at which point the receiver can be\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>当 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 被 drop 时，未处理的消息可能会保留在 channel 中。相反，通常最好执行"干净"的关闭。为此，接收器首先调用 <code>close</code>，这将阻止任何进一步的消息发送到 channel。然后，接收器将 channel 消费到完成，此时可以 drop 接收器。</p>'),
    ('<p>When you want to communicate between synchronous and asynchronous code, there\nare two situations to consider:</p>',
     '<p>当你希望在同步和异步代码之间通信时，需要考虑两种情况：</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Bounded channel</strong>: If you need a bounded channel, you should use a bounded\nTokio <code>mpsc</code> channel for both directions of communication. Instead of calling\nthe async <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> or <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> methods, in\nsynchronous code you will need to use the <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.blocking_send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::blocking_send"><code>blocking_send</code></a> or\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>blocking_recv</code></a> methods.</p>',
     '<p><strong>有界 channel</strong>：如果你需要有界 channel，则应在两个通信方向上都使用有界 Tokio <code>mpsc</code> channel。在同步代码中，你将需要使用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.blocking_send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::blocking_send"><code>blocking_send</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.blocking_recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::blocking_recv"><code>blocking_recv</code></a> 方法，而不是调用异步的 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::send"><code>send</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 方法。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Unbounded channel</strong>: You should use the kind of channel that matches where\nthe receiver is. So for sending a message <em>from async to sync</em>, you should\nuse <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/mpsc/fn.channel.html" title="fn std::sync::mpsc::channel">the standard library unbounded channel</a> or\n<a href="https://docs.rs/crossbeam/*/crossbeam/channel/fn.unbounded.html">crossbeam</a>.  Similarly, for sending a message <em>from sync\nto async</em>, you should use an unbounded Tokio <code>mpsc</code> channel.</p>',
     '<p><strong>无界 channel</strong>：你应该使用与接收器所在位置匹配的 channel 类型。因此，要<em>从 async 发送消息到 sync</em>，你应该使用<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/sync/mpsc/fn.channel.html" title="fn std::sync::mpsc::channel">标准库无界 channel</a>或 <a href="https://docs.rs/crossbeam/*/crossbeam/channel/fn.unbounded.html">crossbeam</a>。类似地，要<em>从 sync 发送消息到 async</em>，你应该使用无界 Tokio <code>mpsc</code> channel。</p>'),
    ('<p>Please be aware that the above remarks were written with the <code>mpsc</code> channel\nin mind, but they can also be generalized to other kinds of channels. In\ngeneral, any channel method that isn’t marked async can be called anywhere,\nincluding outside of the runtime. For example, sending a message on a\n<a href="../oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot">oneshot</a> channel from outside the runtime is perfectly fine.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，以上注释是针对 <code>mpsc</code> channel 编写的，但它们也可以推广到其他类型的 channel。一般来说，任何未标记为 async 的 channel 方法都可以在任何地方调用，包括运行时外部。例如，在运行时外部的 <a href="../oneshot/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::oneshot">oneshot</a> channel 上发送消息是完全可以的。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>mpsc</code> channel is runtime agnostic. You can freely move it between\ndifferent instances of the Tokio runtime or even use it from non-Tokio\nruntimes.</p>',
     '<p><code>mpsc</code> channel 是与运行时无关的。你可以在不同的 Tokio runtime 实例之间自由移动它，甚至可以从非 Tokio runtime 中使用它。</p>'),
    ('<p>When used in a Tokio runtime, it participates in\n<a href="../../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">cooperative scheduling</a> to avoid\nstarvation. This feature does not apply when used from non-Tokio runtimes.</p>',
     '<p>在 Tokio runtime 中使用时，它参与<a href="../../task/coop/index.html#cooperative-scheduling" title="mod tokio::task::coop">协作调度</a>以避免饥饿。从非 Tokio runtime 使用时，此功能不适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The mpsc channel stores elements in blocks. Blocks are organized in a linked list. Sending\npushes new elements onto the block at the front of the list, and receiving pops them off the\none at the back. A block can hold 32 messages on a 64-bit target and 16 messages on a 32-bit\ntarget. This number is independent of channel and message size. Each block also stores 4\npointer-sized values for bookkeeping (so on a 64-bit machine, each message has 1 byte of\noverhead).</p>',
     '<p>mpsc channel 以块的形式存储元素。块以链表形式组织。发送将新元素推入链表前端的块，接收则从后端的块弹出元素。在 64 位目标上，一个块可以容纳 32 条消息；在 32 位目标上可以容纳 16 条消息。此数量与 channel 和消息大小无关。每个块还存储 4 个指针大小的值用于簿记（因此在 64 位机器上，每条消息有 1 字节的开销）。</p>'),
    ('<p>When all values in a block have been received, it becomes empty. It will then be freed, unless\nthe channel’s first block (where newly-sent elements are being stored) has no next block. In\nthat case, the empty block is reused as the next block.</p>',
     '<p>当块中的所有值都已接收后，它变为空。然后它将被释放，除非 channel 的第一个块（正在存储新发送元素的块）没有下一个块。在这种情况下，空块将被重用作下一个块。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 44: SetOnce (14 items) ============
    ('<p>A <code>SetOnce</code> is inspired from python’s <a href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html#asyncio.Event"><code>asyncio.Event</code></a> type. It can be\nused to wait until the value of the <code>SetOnce</code> is set like a “Event” mechanism.</p>',
     '<p><code>SetOnce</code> 灵感来自 Python 的 <a href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html#asyncio.Event"><code>asyncio.Event</code></a> 类型。它可用于等待 <code>SetOnce</code> 的值被设置，类似于"事件"机制。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>SetOnce</code> is typically used for global variables that need to be\ninitialized once on first use, but need no further changes. The <code>SetOnce</code>\nin Tokio allows the initialization procedure to be asynchronous.</p>',
     '<p><code>SetOnce</code> 通常用于需要在首次使用时初始化一次但不需要进一步更改的全局变量。Tokio 中的 <code>SetOnce</code> 允许异步执行初始化过程。</p>'),
    ('<p>Equivalent to <code>SetOnce::new</code>, except that it can be used in static\nvariables.</p>',
     '<p>等效于 <code>SetOnce::new</code>，但可以在静态变量中使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>SetOnce</code> created with\n<code>const_new</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be visible\nin <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::SetOnce::new"><code>SetOnce::new</code></a> should be used to\ncreate an instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定功能</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new</code> 创建的 <code>SetOnce</code> 不会被检测。因此，它在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中不可见。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.new" title="associated function tokio::sync::SetOnce::new"><code>SetOnce::new</code></a> 创建被检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>SetOnce</code> that contains the provided value, if any.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <code>SetOnce</code>，其中包含所提供的值（如果有）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>Option</code> is <code>None</code>, this is equivalent to <code>SetOnce::new</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Option</code> 为 <code>None</code>，则等效于 <code>SetOnce::new</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>SetOnce</code> that contains the provided value.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个包含所提供值的新 <code>SetOnce</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When using the <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">unstable feature</a>, a <code>SetOnce</code> created with\n<code>const_new_with</code> will not be instrumented. As such, it will not be\nvisible in <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a>. Instead, <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.new_with" title="associated function tokio::sync::SetOnce::new_with"><code>SetOnce::new_with</code></a> should be\nused to create an instrumented object if that is needed.</p>',
     '<p>当使用 <code>tracing</code> <a href="../index.html#unstable-features" title="mod tokio">不稳定功能</a> 时，使用 <code>const_new_with</code> 创建的 <code>SetOnce</code> 不会被检测。因此，它在 <a href="https://github.com/tokio-rs/console"><code>tokio-console</code></a> 中不可见。如果需要，应改用 <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.new_with" title="associated function tokio::sync::SetOnce::new_with"><code>SetOnce::new_with</code></a> 创建被检测的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the <code>SetOnce</code> currently contains a value, and <code>false</code>\notherwise.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>SetOnce</code> 当前包含值，则返回 <code>true</code>，否则返回 <code>false</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the value currently stored in the <code>SetOnce</code>, or\n<code>None</code> if the <code>SetOnce</code> is empty.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存储在 <code>SetOnce</code> 中的值的引用，如果 <code>SetOnce</code> 为空则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets the value of the <code>SetOnce</code> to the given value if the <code>SetOnce</code> is\nempty.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>SetOnce</code> 为空，则将其值设置为给定值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>SetOnce</code> already has a value, this call will fail with an\n<a href="struct.SetOnceError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SetOnceError"><code>SetOnceError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>SetOnce</code> 已经有值，则此调用将失败并返回 <a href="struct.SetOnceError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SetOnceError"><code>SetOnceError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits until the value is set.</p>',
     '<p>等待直到值被设置。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>SetOnce</code> is already initialized, it will return the value\nimmediately.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>SetOnce</code> 已初始化，它将立即返回值。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 45: io/struct.Ready (14 items) ============
    ('<p><code>Ready</code> tracks which operation an I/O resource is ready to perform.</p>',
     '<p><code>Ready</code> 跟踪 I/O 资源准备好执行的操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the empty <code>Ready</code> set.</p>',
     '<p>返回空的 <code>Ready</code> 集合。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing readable readiness.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示可读就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing writable readiness.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示可写就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing read closed readiness.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示读取关闭就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing write closed readiness.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示写入关闭就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing error readiness.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示错误就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <code>Ready</code> representing readiness for all operations.</p>',
     '<p>返回表示所有操作就绪状态的 <code>Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if <code>Ready</code> is the empty set.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Ready</code> 是空集合，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the value includes <code>readable</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括 <code>readable</code>（可读），则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the value includes writable <code>readiness</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括可写 <code>readiness</code>（就绪），则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the value includes read-closed <code>readiness</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括读取关闭 <code>readiness</code>（就绪），则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the value includes write-closed <code>readiness</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括写入关闭 <code>readiness</code>（就绪），则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the value includes error <code>readiness</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果该值包括错误 <code>readiness</code>（就绪），则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 46: ClientOptions (14 items) ============
    ('<p>See <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>参见 <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the client supports reading data. This is enabled by default.</p>',
     '<p>如果客户端支持读取数据。默认情况下这是启用的。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/secauthz/generic-access-rights"><code>GENERIC_READ</code></a> in the call to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在调用 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a> 时设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/secauthz/generic-access-rights"><code>GENERIC_READ</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the created pipe supports writing data. This is enabled by default.</p>',
     '<p>如果创建的管道支持写入数据。默认情况下这是启用的。</p>'),
    ('<p>This corresponds to setting <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/secauthz/generic-access-rights"><code>GENERIC_WRITE</code></a> in the call to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这对应于在调用 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a> 时设置 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/secauthz/generic-access-rights"><code>GENERIC_WRITE</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets qos flags which are combined with other flags and attributes in the\ncall to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilea"><code>CreateFile</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>设置 qos 标志，这些标志会与 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilea"><code>CreateFile</code></a> 调用中的其他标志和属性组合在一起。</p>'),
    ('<p>By default <code>security_qos_flags</code> is set to <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Storage/FileSystem/constant.SECURITY_IDENTIFICATION.html"><code>SECURITY_IDENTIFICATION</code></a>,\ncalling this function would override that value completely with the\nargument specified.</p>',
     '<p>默认情况下，<code>security_qos_flags</code> 被设置为 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Storage/FileSystem/constant.SECURITY_IDENTIFICATION.html"><code>SECURITY_IDENTIFICATION</code></a>，调用此函数将完全使用指定的参数覆盖该值。</p>'),
    ('<p>When <code>security_qos_flags</code> is not set, a malicious program can gain the\nelevated privileges of a privileged Rust process when it allows opening\nuser-specified paths, by tricking it into opening a named pipe. So\narguably <code>security_qos_flags</code> should also be set when opening arbitrary\npaths. However the bits can then conflict with other flags, specifically\n<code>FILE_FLAG_OPEN_NO_RECALL</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当 <code>security_qos_flags</code> 未设置时，如果允许打开用户指定的路径，则恶意程序可以通过欺骗特权 Rust 进程打开命名管道来获得该进程的提升特权。因此，在打开任意路径时，也应该设置 <code>security_qos_flags</code>。但是，这些位可能与其他标志冲突，特别是 <code>FILE_FLAG_OPEN_NO_RECALL</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>For information about possible values, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winnt/ne-winnt-security_impersonation_level">Impersonation Levels</a> on the\nWindows Dev Center site. The <code>SECURITY_SQOS_PRESENT</code> flag is set\nautomatically when using this method.</p>',
     '<p>有关可能的值的信息，请参阅 Windows 开发人员中心网站上的<a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winnt/ne-winnt-security_impersonation_level">模拟级别</a>。使用此方法时会自动设置 <code>SECURITY_SQOS_PRESENT</code> 标志。</p>'),
    ('<p>This opens the client using <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilea"><code>CreateFile</code></a> with the\n<code>dwCreationDisposition</code> option set to <code>OPEN_EXISTING</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这使用 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilea"><code>CreateFile</code></a> 打开客户端，并将 <code>dwCreationDisposition</code> 选项设置为 <code>OPEN_EXISTING</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>There are a few errors you need to take into account when creating a\nnamed pipe on the client side:</p>',
     '<p>在客户端创建命名管道时，需要考虑一些错误：</p>'),
    ('<p>A connect loop that waits until a pipe becomes available looks like\nthis:</p>',
     '<p>一个等待管道可用的连接循环如下所示：</p>'),
    ('<p>This is the same as <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>open</code></a> except that it supports providing the raw\npointer to a structure of <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> which will be passed\nas the <code>lpSecurityAttributes</code> argument to <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这与 <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>open</code></a> 相同，只是它支持提供指向 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> 结构的原始指针，该指针将作为 <code>lpSecurityAttributes</code> 参数传递给 <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/fileapi/nf-fileapi-createfilew"><code>CreateFile</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>attrs</code> argument must either be null or point at a valid instance of\nthe <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> structure. If the argument is null, the\nbehavior is identical to calling the <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>open</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p><code>attrs</code> 参数必须为 null 或指向 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Security/struct.SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES.html"><code>SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES</code></a> 结构体的有效实例。如果该参数为 null，则其行为与调用 <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>open</code></a> 方法完全相同。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 47: time/struct.Sleep (13 items) ============
    ('<p>Future returned by <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> and <a href="fn.sleep_until.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep_until"><code>sleep_until</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>由 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.sleep_until.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep_until"><code>sleep_until</code></a> 返回的 Future。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type does not implement the <code>Unpin</code> trait, which means that if you\nuse it with <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a> or by calling <code>poll</code>, you have to pin it first.\nIf you use it with <code>.await</code>, this does not apply.</p>',
     '<p>此类型不实现 <code>Unpin</code> trait，这意味着如果将其与 <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a> 一起使用或通过调用 <code>poll</code> 来使用，则必须先将其 pin。如果使用 <code>.await</code>，则不适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Use with <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a>. Pinning the <code>Sleep</code> with <a href="../macro.pin.html"><code>tokio::pin!</code></a> is\nnecessary when the same <code>Sleep</code> is selected on multiple times.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a> 一起使用。当对同一个 <code>Sleep</code> 进行多次选择时，需要使用 <a href="../macro.pin.html"><code>tokio::pin!</code></a> 将其 pin。</p>'),
    ('<p>Use in a struct with boxing. By pinning the <code>Sleep</code> with a <code>Box</code>, the\n<code>HasSleep</code> struct implements <code>Unpin</code>, even though <code>Sleep</code> does not.</p>',
     '<p>在带装箱的结构体中使用。通过使用 <code>Box</code> 将 <code>Sleep</code> pin，<code>HasSleep</code> 结构体实现 <code>Unpin</code>，即使 <code>Sleep</code> 没有实现。</p>'),
    ('<p>Use in a struct with pin projection. This method avoids the <code>Box</code>, but\nthe <code>HasSleep</code> struct will not be <code>Unpin</code> as a consequence.</p>',
     '<p>在带 pin 投影的结构体中使用。这种方法避免了 <code>Box</code>，但 <code>HasSleep</code> 结构体因此将不实现 <code>Unpin</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the instant at which the future will complete.</p>',
     '<p>返回 future 将完成的时刻。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if <code>Sleep</code> has elapsed.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Sleep</code> 已过去，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>A <code>Sleep</code> instance is elapsed when the requested duration has elapsed.</p>',
     '<p>当所请求的持续时间已过去时，<code>Sleep</code> 实例已过去。</p>'),
    ('<p>Resets the <code>Sleep</code> instance to a new deadline.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>Sleep</code> 实例重置为新的截止时间。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calling this function allows changing the instant at which the <code>Sleep</code>\nfuture completes without having to create new associated state.</p>',
     '<p>调用此函数允许在不创建新的关联状态的情况下，更改 <code>Sleep</code> future 完成的时间点。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function can be called both before and after the future has\ncompleted.</p>',
     '<p>此函数可以在 future 完成之前和之后调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>To call this method, you will usually combine the call with\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.as_mut" title="method core::pin::Pin::as_mut"><code>Pin::as_mut</code></a>, which lets you call the method without consuming the\n<code>Sleep</code> itself.</p>',
     '<p>要调用此方法，通常需要将调用与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.as_mut" title="method core::pin::Pin::as_mut"><code>Pin::as_mut</code></a> 结合使用，这样可以调用方法而无需消费 <code>Sleep</code> 本身。</p>'),
    ('<p>See also the top-level examples.</p>',
     '<p>另请参阅顶级示例。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 48: time/struct.Instant (13 items) ============
    ('<p>A measurement of a monotonically nondecreasing clock.\nOpaque and useful only with <code>Duration</code>.</p>',
     '<p>单调不减时钟的测量值。不透明，仅与 <code>Duration</code> 配合使用时有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Instants are always guaranteed to be no less than any previously measured\ninstant when created, and are often useful for tasks such as measuring\nbenchmarks or timing how long an operation takes.</p>',
     '<p>在创建时，Instant 始终保证不小于任何先前测量的 Instant，并且通常用于测量基准测试或操作耗时之类的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note, however, that instants are not guaranteed to be <strong>steady</strong>. In other\nwords, each tick of the underlying clock may not be the same length (e.g.\nsome seconds may be longer than others). An instant may jump forwards or\nexperience time dilation (slow down or speed up), but it will never go\nbackwards.</p>',
     '<p>但请注意，Instant 不保证是<strong>稳定</strong>的。换句话说，底层时钟的每个 tick 长度可能不同（例如，某些秒可能比其他秒长）。Instant 可能会向前跳跃或经历时间膨胀（变慢或变快），但绝不会向后走。</p>'),
    ('<p>Instants are opaque types that can only be compared to one another. There is\nno method to get “the number of seconds” from an instant. Instead, it only\nallows measuring the duration between two instants (or comparing two\ninstants).</p>',
     '<p>Instant 是不透明类型，只能相互比较。没有方法可以从 Instant 获取"秒数"。相反，它只允许测量两个 Instant 之间的持续时间（或比较两个 Instant）。</p>'),
    ('<p>The size of an <code>Instant</code> struct may vary depending on the target operating\nsystem.</p>',
     '<p><code>Instant</code> 结构体的大小可能因目标操作系统而异。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type wraps the inner <code>std</code> variant and is used to align the Tokio\nclock for uses of <code>now()</code>. This can be useful for testing where you can\ntake advantage of <code>time::pause()</code> and <code>time::advance()</code>.</p>',
     '<p>此类型包装内部的 <code>std</code> 变体，用于对齐 Tokio 时钟以用于 <code>now()</code>。这对于测试非常有用，你可以利用 <code>time::pause()</code> 和 <code>time::advance()</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns an instant corresponding to “now”.</p>',
     '<p>返回对应于"现在"的 Instant。</p>'),
    ('<p>Create a <code>tokio::time::Instant</code> from a <code>std::time::Instant</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>std::time::Instant</code> 创建 <code>tokio::time::Instant</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Convert the value into a <code>std::time::Instant</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将该值转换为 <code>std::time::Instant</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the amount of time elapsed from another instant to this one, or\nNone if that instant is later than this one.</p>',
     '<p>返回从另一个 Instant 到此 Instant 已经过去的时间量；如果那个 Instant 比此 Instant 晚，则返回 None。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the amount of time elapsed since this instant was created,\nor zero duration if this instant is in the future.</p>',
     '<p>返回自创建此 Instant 以来已经过去的时间量；如果此 Instant 在未来，则返回零持续时间。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>Some(t)</code> where <code>t</code> is the time <code>self + duration</code> if <code>t</code> can be\nrepresented as <code>Instant</code> (which means it’s inside the bounds of the\nunderlying data structure), <code>None</code> otherwise.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>t</code> 可以表示为 <code>Instant</code>（这意味着它位于底层数据结构的边界内），则返回 <code>Some(t)</code>，其中 <code>t</code> 是时间 <code>self + duration</code>；否则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>Some(t)</code> where <code>t</code> is the time <code>self - duration</code> if <code>t</code> can be\nrepresented as <code>Instant</code> (which means it’s inside the bounds of the\nunderlying data structure), <code>None</code> otherwise.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>t</code> 可以表示为 <code>Instant</code>（这意味着它位于底层数据结构的边界内），则返回 <code>Some(t)</code>，其中 <code>t</code> 是时间 <code>self - duration</code>；否则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 49: RuntimeMetrics (13 items) ============
    ('<p>This handle is internally reference-counted and can be freely cloned. A\n<code>RuntimeMetrics</code> handle is obtained using the <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.metrics" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::metrics"><code>Runtime::metrics</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>此句柄内部使用引用计数，可以自由克隆。可使用 <a href="struct.Runtime.html#method.metrics" title="method tokio::runtime::Runtime::metrics"><code>Runtime::metrics</code></a> 方法获取 <code>RuntimeMetrics</code> 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>The number of workers is set by configuring <code>worker_threads</code> on\n<code>runtime::Builder</code>. When using the <code>current_thread</code> runtime, the return\nvalue is always <code>1</code>.</p>',
     '<p>工作线程数通过在 <code>runtime::Builder</code> 上配置 <code>worker_threads</code> 来设置。使用 <code>current_thread</code> 运行时时，返回值始终为 <code>1</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This counter increases when a task is spawned and decreases when a\ntask exits.</p>',
     '<p>当任务生成时此计数器增加，当任务退出时此计数器减少。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note: When using the multi-threaded runtime this number may not\nnot have strong consistency i.e. no tasks may be running but the metric\nreports otherwise.</p>',
     '<p>注意：在使用多线程运行时时，此数字可能不具有强一致性，即可能没有任务在运行，但指标却报告有任务运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tasks that are spawned or notified from a non-runtime thread are\nscheduled using the runtime’s global queue. This metric returns the\n<strong>current</strong> number of tasks pending in the global queue. As such, the\nreturned value may increase or decrease as new tasks are scheduled and\nprocessed.</p>',
     '<p>从非运行时线程生成或通知的任务使用运行时的全局队列进行调度。此指标返回全局队列中当前挂起任务的数量。因此，随着新任务的调度和处理，返回值可能会增加或减少。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the amount of time the given worker thread has been busy.</p>',
     '<p>返回给定工作线程处于忙碌状态的时间量。</p>'),
    ('<p>The worker busy duration starts at zero when the runtime is created and\nincreases whenever the worker is spending time processing work. Using\nthis value can indicate the load of the given worker. If a lot of time\nis spent busy, then the worker is under load and will check for inbound\nevents less often.</p>',
     '<p>工作线程忙碌持续时间在运行时创建时从零开始，并在工作线程花费时间处理工作时增加。使用此值可以指示给定工作线程的负载。如果花费大量时间处于忙碌状态，则工作线程处于负载状态，并且将更少地检查入站事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>The timer is monotonically increasing. It is never decremented or reset\nto zero.</p>',
     '<p>计时器单调递增。它永远不会减少或重置为零。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the total number of times the given worker thread has parked.</p>',
     '<p>返回给定工作线程已 park 的总次数。</p>'),
    ('<p>The worker park count starts at zero when the runtime is created and\nincreases by one each time the worker parks the thread waiting for new\ninbound events to process. This usually means the worker has processed\nall pending work and is currently idle.</p>',
     '<p>工作线程 park 计数在运行时创建时从零开始，每次工作线程 park 线程等待新的入站事件处理时增加一。这通常意味着工作线程已处理完所有挂起的工作，当前处于空闲状态。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the total number of times the given worker thread has parked\nand unparked.</p>',
     '<p>返回给定工作线程已 park 和 unpark 的总次数。</p>'),
    ('<p>The worker park/unpark count starts at zero when the runtime is created and\nincreases by one each time the worker parks the thread waiting for new\ninbound events to process. This usually means the worker has processed\nall pending work and is currently idle. When new work becomes available,\nthe worker is unparked and the park/unpark count is again increased by one.</p>',
     '<p>工作线程 park/unpark 计数在运行时创建时从零开始，每次工作线程 park 线程等待新的入站事件处理时增加一。这通常意味着工作线程已处理完所有挂起的工作，当前处于空闲状态。当新工作变得可用时，工作线程被 unpark，park/unpark 计数再次增加一。</p>'),
    ('<p>An odd count means that the worker is currently parked.\nAn even count means that the worker is currently active.</p>',
     '<p>奇数计数表示工作线程当前已 park。偶数计数表示工作线程当前处于活动状态。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 50: RwLockWriteGuard (12 items) ============
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write"><code>write</code></a> method\non <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write"><code>write</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>RwLockWriteGuard::map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods of\nthe same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockWriteGuard::map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods of\nthe same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to a combination of asynchronous <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::map</code></a> and <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade</code></a>\nfrom the <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于来自 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 的异步 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::map</code></a> 和 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade</code></a> 的组合。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of\nthe locked data. The original guard is returned if the closure returns\n<code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_downgrade_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_downgrade_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to a combination of asynchronous <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.try_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::try_map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map</code></a> and <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade</code></a>\nfrom the <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于来自 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 的异步 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.try_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::try_map"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::try_map</code></a> 和 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade"><code>RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade</code></a> 的组合。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts this <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> into an <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>. This\nmethod can be used to store a non-mapped guard in a struct field that\nexpects a mapped guard.</p>',
     '<p>将此 <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> 转换为 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>。此方法可用于将非映射 guard 存储在期望映射 guard 的结构体字段中。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <code>RwLockWriteGuard::map(guard, |me| me)</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于调用 <code>RwLockWriteGuard::map(guard, |me| me)</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 51: broadcast/index (12 items) ============
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> is used to broadcast values to <strong>all</strong> connected <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>\nvalues. <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles are clone-able, allowing concurrent send and\nreceive actions. <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> are both <code>Send</code> and <code>Sync</code> as\nlong as <code>T</code> is <code>Send</code>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 用于将值广播给<strong>所有</strong>连接的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄是可克隆的，允许并发发送和接收操作。只要 <code>T</code> 是 <code>Send</code>，<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 都实现 <code>Send</code> 和 <code>Sync</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When a value is sent, <strong>all</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles are notified and will\nreceive the value. The value is stored once inside the channel and cloned on\ndemand for each receiver. Once all receivers have received a clone of the\nvalue, the value is released from the channel.</p>',
     '<p>当发送一个值时，<strong>所有</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄都将收到通知并接收该值。该值在 channel 内存储一次，并根据需要为每个接收器克隆。一旦所有接收器都收到了该值的克隆，该值就会从 channel 中释放。</p>'),
    ('<p>A channel is created by calling <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a>, specifying the maximum number\nof messages the channel can retain at any given time.</p>',
     '<p>通过调用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 创建 channel，指定 channel 在任何给定时间可以保留的最大消息数。</p>'),
    ('<p>New <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles are created by calling <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a>. The\nreturned <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> will receive values sent <strong>after</strong> the call to\n<code>subscribe</code>.</p>',
     '<p>通过调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a> 创建新的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄。返回的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 将接收在调用 <code>subscribe</code> <strong>之后</strong>发送的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This channel is also suitable for the single-producer multi-consumer\nuse-case, where a single sender broadcasts values to many receivers.</p>',
     '<p>此 channel 也适用于单生产者多消费者用例，其中单个 sender 向许多 receiver 广播值。</p>'),
    ('<p>As sent messages must be retained until <strong>all</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles receive\na clone, broadcast channels are susceptible to the “slow receiver” problem.\nIn this case, all but one receiver are able to receive values at the rate\nthey are sent. Because one receiver is stalled, the channel starts to fill\nup.</p>',
     '<p>由于发送的消息必须保留到<strong>所有</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄都接收到一个克隆，因此 broadcast channel 容易出现"慢接收者"问题。在这种情况下，除一个接收者外，所有接收者都能够以发送速率接收值。因为一个接收者停滞不前，channel 开始填满。</p>'),
    ('<p>This broadcast channel implementation handles this case by setting a hard\nupper bound on the number of values the channel may retain at any given\ntime. This upper bound is passed to the <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function as an argument.</p>',
     '<p>此 broadcast channel 实现通过设置 channel 在任何给定时间可以保留的值的硬上限来处理这种情况。此上限作为参数传递给 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::broadcast::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>If a value is sent when the channel is at capacity, the oldest value\ncurrently held by the channel is released. This frees up space for the new\nvalue. Any receiver that has not yet seen the released value will return\n<a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Lagged" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Lagged"><code>RecvError::Lagged</code></a> the next time <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> is called.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 达到容量时发送一个值，则会释放 channel 当前持有的最旧值。这为新值腾出了空间。任何尚未看到已释放值的接收器在下一次调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 时将返回 <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Lagged" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Lagged"><code>RecvError::Lagged</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Once <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Lagged" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Lagged"><code>RecvError::Lagged</code></a> is returned, the lagging receiver’s position is\nupdated to the oldest value contained by the channel. The next call to\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> will return this value.</p>',
     '<p>一旦返回 <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Lagged" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Lagged"><code>RecvError::Lagged</code></a>，滞后接收器的位置将更新为 channel 中包含的最旧值。下一次调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 将返回此值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This behavior enables a receiver to detect when it has lagged so far behind\nthat data has been dropped. The caller may decide how to respond to this:\neither by aborting its task or by tolerating lost messages and resuming\nconsumption of the channel.</p>',
     '<p>此行为使接收器能够检测到何时已经滞后到数据已被丢弃的程度。调用者可以决定如何响应：要么中止其任务，要么容忍丢失的消息并恢复 channel 的消费。</p>'),
    ('<p>When <strong>all</strong> <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles have been dropped, no new values may be\nsent. At this point, the channel is “closed”. Once a receiver has received\nall values retained by the channel, the next call to <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> will return\nwith <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Closed"><code>RecvError::Closed</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>当<strong>所有</strong> <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop 时，不能再发送新值。此时，channel 已"关闭"。一旦接收器已接收 channel 保留的所有值，则下次调用 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 将返回 <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html#variant.Closed" title="variant tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError::Closed"><code>RecvError::Closed</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>When a <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle is dropped, any messages not read by the receiver\nwill be marked as read. If this receiver was the only one not to have read\nthat message, the message will be dropped at this point.</p>',
     '<p>当 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄被 drop 时，接收器尚未读取的任何消息都将标记为已读。如果该接收器是唯一尚未读取该消息的接收器，则此时该消息将被丢弃。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 52: time/index (11 items) ============
    ('<p>Utilities for tracking time.</p>',
     '<p>用于跟踪时间的实用工具。</p>'),
    ('<p>This module provides a number of types for executing code after a set period\nof time.</p>',
     '<p>此模块提供了多种类型，用于在设定的时间段后执行代码。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> is a future that does no work and completes at a specific <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>Instant</code></a>\nin time.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>Sleep</code></a> 是一个不执行任何工作并在特定 <a href="struct.Instant.html" title="struct tokio::time::Instant"><code>Instant</code></a> 时刻完成的 future。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>Interval</code></a> is a stream yielding a value at a fixed period. It is\ninitialized with a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>Duration</code></a> and repeatedly yields each time the duration\nelapses.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 是一个以固定周期产生值的流。它使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>Duration</code></a> 进行初始化，并在每次持续时间过去时重复产生值。</p>'),
    ('<p><a href="struct.Timeout.html" title="struct tokio::time::Timeout"><code>Timeout</code></a>: Wraps a future or stream, setting an upper bound to the amount\nof time it is allowed to execute. If the future or stream does not\ncomplete in time, then it is canceled and an error is returned.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Timeout.html" title="struct tokio::time::Timeout"><code>Timeout</code></a>：包装 future 或流，限制其允许执行的最长时间。如果 future 或流未能在规定时间内完成，则它将被取消并返回错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>These types are sufficient for handling a large number of scenarios\ninvolving time.</p>',
     '<p>这些类型足以处理涉及时间的大量场景。</p>'),
    ('<p>These types must be used from within the context of the <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这些类型必须在 <a href="../runtime/struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 的上下文中使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Wait 100ms and print “100 ms have elapsed”</p>',
     '<p>等待 100ms 并打印"已经过去 100 ms"</p>'),
    ('<p>Require that an operation takes no more than 1s.</p>',
     '<p>要求某个操作不超过 1 秒。</p>'),
    ('<p>A simple example using <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> to execute a task every two seconds.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> 每两秒执行一个任务的简单示例。</p>'),
    ('<p>The difference between <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> and <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> is that an <a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a>\nmeasures the time since the last tick, which means that <code>.tick().await</code> may\nwait for a shorter time than the duration specified for the interval\nif some time has passed between calls to <code>.tick().await</code>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> 之间的区别在于，<a href="fn.interval.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval"><code>interval</code></a> 度量的是自上一个 tick 以来经过的时间，这意味着如果在两次调用 <code>.tick().await</code> 之间已经过去了一些时间，则 <code>.tick().await</code> 等待的时间可能比为 interval 指定的时间短。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 53: task/LocalKey (11 items) ============
    ('<p>A key for task-local data.</p>',
     '<p>用于任务本地数据的键。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type is generated by the <a href="../macro.task_local.html"><code>task_local!</code></a> macro.</p>',
     '<p>此类型由 <a href="../macro.task_local.html"><code>task_local!</code></a> 宏生成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/local/struct.LocalKey.html" title="struct std::thread::LocalKey"><code>std::thread::LocalKey</code></a>, <code>tokio::task::LocalKey</code> will\n<em>not</em> lazily initialize the value on first access. Instead, the\nvalue is first initialized when the future containing\nthe task-local is first polled by a futures executor, like Tokio.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/thread/local/struct.LocalKey.html" title="struct std::thread::LocalKey"><code>std::thread::LocalKey</code></a> 不同，<code>tokio::task::LocalKey</code> <em>不会</em>在首次访问时惰性初始化该值。而是在包含任务本地的 future 首次由 futures 执行器（如 Tokio）poll 时才初始化该值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets a value <code>T</code> as the task-local value for the future <code>F</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将值 <code>T</code> 设置为 future <code>F</code> 的任务本地值。</p>'),
    ('<p>On completion of <code>scope</code>, the task-local will be dropped.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>scope</code> 完成时，任务本地将被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you poll the returned future inside a call to <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::with"><code>with</code></a> or\n<a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.try_with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::try_with"><code>try_with</code></a> on the same <code>LocalKey</code>, then the call to <code>poll</code> will panic.</p>',
     '<p>如果在同一个 <code>LocalKey</code> 上调用 <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::with"><code>with</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.try_with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::try_with"><code>try_with</code></a> 时 poll 返回的 future，则对 <code>poll</code> 的调用将发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Sets a value <code>T</code> as the task-local value for the closure <code>F</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将值 <code>T</code> 设置为闭包 <code>F</code> 的任务本地值。</p>'),
    ('<p>On completion of <code>sync_scope</code>, the task-local will be dropped.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>sync_scope</code> 完成时，任务本地将被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method panics if called inside a call to <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::with"><code>with</code></a> or <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.try_with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::try_with"><code>try_with</code></a>\non the same <code>LocalKey</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在同一个 <code>LocalKey</code> 上调用 <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::with"><code>with</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.LocalKey.html#method.try_with" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::try_with"><code>try_with</code></a> 时调用此方法，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task-local with the associated key is not present, this\nmethod will return an <code>AccessError</code>. For a panicking variant,\nsee <code>with</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果具有关联键的任务本地不存在，则此方法将返回 <code>AccessError</code>。有关 panicking 变体，请参见 <code>with</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task-local with the associated key is not present, this\nmethod will return an <code>AccessError</code>. For a panicking variant,\nsee <code>get</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果具有关联键的任务本地不存在，则此方法将返回 <code>AccessError</code>。有关 panicking 变体，请参见 <code>get</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 54: NamedPipeClient (11 items) ============
    ('<p>A <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/ipc/named-pipes">Windows named pipe</a> client.</p>',
     '<p><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/ipc/named-pipes">Windows 命名管道</a>客户端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Constructed using <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a> 构造。</p>'),
    ('<p>Connecting a client correctly involves a few steps. When connecting through\n<a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a>, it might error indicating one of two things:</p>',
     '<p>正确连接客户端涉及几个步骤。当通过 <a href="struct.ClientOptions.html#method.open" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ClientOptions::open"><code>ClientOptions::open</code></a> 连接时，它可能会出错，表示以下两种情况之一：</p>'),
    ('<p>So a correctly implemented client looks like this:</p>',
     '<p>因此，正确实现的客户端如下所示：</p>'),
    ('<p>Constructs a new named pipe client from the specified raw handle.</p>',
     '<p>从指定的原始句柄构造一个新的命名管道客户端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Retrieves information about the named pipe the client is associated\nwith.</p>',
     '<p>检索与客户端关联的命名管道的信息。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序复制数据以填充每个缓冲区，最后写入的缓冲区可能只被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序从每个缓冲区写入数据，最后读取的缓冲区可能只被部分使用。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Usually, <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>, <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> or <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> is used with this function.</p>',
     '<p>通常，<a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>、<a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> 或 <a href="struct.NamedPipeClient.html#method.ready" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::NamedPipeClient::ready"><code>ready()</code></a> 与此函数一起使用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 55: time/error/Error (10 items) ============
    ('<p>Errors encountered by the timer implementation.</p>',
     '<p>计时器实现遇到的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Currently, there are two different errors that can occur:</p>',
     '<p>目前，可能发生两种不同的错误：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>shutdown</code> occurs when a timer operation is attempted, but the timer\ninstance has been dropped. In this case, the operation will never be able\nto complete and the <code>shutdown</code> error is returned. This is a permanent\nerror, i.e., once this error is observed, timer operations will never\nsucceed in the future.</p>',
     '<p>当尝试计时器操作，但计时器实例已被 drop 时，会发生 <code>shutdown</code>。在这种情况下，操作将永远无法完成，并返回 <code>shutdown</code> 错误。这是一个永久性错误，即一旦观察到该错误，将来计时器操作将永远不会成功。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>at_capacity</code> occurs when a timer operation is attempted, but the timer\ninstance is currently handling its maximum number of outstanding sleep instances.\nIn this case, the operation is not able to be performed at the current\nmoment, and <code>at_capacity</code> is returned. This is a transient error, i.e., at\nsome point in the future, if the operation is attempted again, it might\nsucceed. Callers that observe this error should attempt to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Load_Shedding">shed load</a>. One\nway to do this would be dropping the future that issued the timer operation.</p>',
     '<p>当尝试计时器操作，但计时器实例当前正在处理最大数量的未完成 sleep 实例时，会发生 <code>at_capacity</code>。在这种情况下，操作当前无法执行，并返回 <code>at_capacity</code>。这是一个暂时性错误，即在将来的某个时刻，如果再次尝试该操作，它可能会成功。观察到该错误的调用者应尝试<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Load_Shedding">减载</a>。一种方法是 drop 发出计时器操作的 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates an error representing a shutdown timer.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个表示已关闭计时器的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the error was caused by the timer being shutdown.</p>',
     '<p>如果错误是由计时器关闭引起的，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates an error representing a timer at capacity.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个表示计时器已达到容量的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the error was caused by the timer being at capacity.</p>',
     '<p>如果错误是由计时器达到容量引起的，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates an error representing a misconfigured timer.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个表示计时器配置错误的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the error was caused by the timer being misconfigured.</p>',
     '<p>如果错误是由计时器配置错误引起的，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 56: OwnedRwLockWriteGuard (10 items) ============
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write_owned" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write_owned"><code>write_owned</code></a> method\non <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.write_owned" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::write_owned"><code>write_owned</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked\ndata.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods of\nthe same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component\nof the locked data. The original guard is returned if the closure\nreturns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere\nwith methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of\nthe locked data. The original guard is returned if the closure returns\n<code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::try_downgrade_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::try_downgrade_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts this <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> into an\n<code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>. This method can be used to store a\nnon-mapped guard in a struct field that expects a mapped guard.</p>',
     '<p>将此 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> 转换为 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>。此方法可用于将非映射 guard 存储在期望映射 guard 的结构体字段中。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is equivalent to calling <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map(guard, |me| me)</code>.</p>',
     '<p>这等效于调用 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map(guard, |me| me)</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 57: macro.pin (10 items) ============
    ('<p>Pins a value on the stack.</p>',
     '<p>在栈上 pin 一个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Calls to <code>async fn</code> return anonymous <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> values that are <code>!Unpin</code>.\nThese values must be pinned before they can be polled. Calling <code>.await</code> will\nhandle this, but consumes the future. If it is required to call <code>.await</code> on\na <code>&amp;mut _</code> reference, the caller is responsible for pinning the future.</p>',
     '<p>对 <code>async fn</code> 的调用返回的是匿名的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> 值，这些值是 <code>!Unpin</code> 的。必须先将这些值 pin 才能 poll。调用 <code>.await</code> 会处理这一点，但会消费 future。如果需要在 <code>&amp;mut _</code> 引用上调用 <code>.await</code>，则调用者负责 pin 该 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Pinning may be done by allocating with <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/boxed/struct.Box.html#method.pin" title="associated function alloc::boxed::Box::pin"><code>Box::pin</code></a> or by using the stack\nwith the <code>pin!</code> macro.</p>',
     '<p>可以通过使用 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/boxed/struct.Box.html#method.pin" title="associated function alloc::boxed::Box::pin"><code>Box::pin</code></a> 分配来 pin，也可以使用 <code>pin!</code> 宏在栈上 pin。</p>'),
    ('<p>The following will <strong>fail to compile</strong>:</p>',
     '<p>下面的代码将<strong>无法编译</strong>：</p>'),
    ('<p>To make this work requires pinning:</p>',
     '<p>要使其工作，需要 pin：</p>'),
    ('<p>Pinning is useful when using <code>select!</code> and stream operators that require <code>T: Stream + Unpin</code>.</p>',
     '<p>在使用需要 <code>T: Stream + Unpin</code> 的 <code>select!</code> 和流操作符时，pin 很有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>pin!</code> macro takes <strong>identifiers</strong> as arguments. It does <strong>not</strong> work\nwith expressions.</p>',
     '<p><code>pin!</code> 宏以<strong>标识符</strong>作为参数。它<strong>不能</strong>与表达式一起使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The following does not compile as an expression is passed to <code>pin!</code>.</p>',
     '<p>下面的代码无法编译，因为将表达式传递给了 <code>pin!</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Using with select:</p>',
     '<p>与 select 一起使用：</p>'),
    ('<p>Because assigning to a variable followed by pinning is common, there is also\na variant of the macro that supports doing both in one go.</p>',
     '<p>由于先赋值给变量然后 pin 很常见，所以该宏还有一个变体，支持一次性完成这两个操作。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 58: AsyncSeek (10 items) ============
    ('<p>This trait is analogous to the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Seek.html" title="trait std::io::Seek"><code>std::io::Seek</code></a> trait, but integrates\nwith the asynchronous task system. In particular, the <code>start_seek</code>\nmethod, unlike <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Seek.html#tymethod.seek" title="method std::io::Seek::seek"><code>Seek::seek</code></a>, will not block the calling thread.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 类似于 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Seek.html" title="trait std::io::Seek"><code>std::io::Seek</code></a> trait，但与异步任务系统集成。特别地，与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Seek.html#tymethod.seek" title="method std::io::Seek::seek"><code>Seek::seek</code></a> 不同，<code>start_seek</code> 方法不会阻塞调用线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>Utilities for working with <code>AsyncSeek</code> values are provided by\n<a href="crate::io::AsyncSeekExt"><code>AsyncSeekExt</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>用于处理 <code>AsyncSeek</code> 值的实用工具由 <a href="crate::io::AsyncSeekExt"><code>AsyncSeekExt</code></a> 提供。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to seek to an offset, in bytes, in a stream.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在流中以字节为单位 seek 到一个偏移量。</p>'),
    ('<p>A seek beyond the end of a stream is allowed, but behavior is defined\nby the implementation.</p>',
     '<p>允许 seek 超出流的末尾，但行为由实现定义。</p>'),
    ('<p>If this function returns successfully, then the job has been submitted.\nTo find out when it completes, call <code>poll_complete</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果此函数成功返回，则作业已提交。要了解何时完成，请调用 <code>poll_complete</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function can return <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.Other" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::Other"><code>io::ErrorKind::Other</code></a> in case there is\nanother seek in progress. To avoid this, it is advisable that any call\nto <code>start_seek</code> is preceded by a call to <code>poll_complete</code> to ensure all\npending seeks have completed.</p>',
     '<p>如果还有另一个 seek 正在进行，此函数可能返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/error/enum.ErrorKind.html#variant.Other" title="variant std::io::error::ErrorKind::Other"><code>io::ErrorKind::Other</code></a>。为避免这种情况，建议在调用 <code>start_seek</code> 之前先调用 <code>poll_complete</code>，以确保所有挂起的 seek 都已完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Waits for a seek operation to complete.</p>',
     '<p>等待 seek 操作完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the seek operation completed successfully, this method returns the\nnew position from the start of the stream. That position can be used\nlater with <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/enum.SeekFrom.html#variant.Start" title="variant std::io::SeekFrom::Start"><code>SeekFrom::Start</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 seek 操作成功完成，此方法返回从流开头开始的新位置。该位置稍后可与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/enum.SeekFrom.html#variant.Start" title="variant std::io::SeekFrom::Start"><code>SeekFrom::Start</code></a> 一起使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The position returned by calling this method can only be relied on right\nafter <code>start_seek</code>. If you have changed the position by e.g. reading or\nwriting since calling <code>start_seek</code>, then it is unspecified whether the\nreturned position takes that position change into account. Similarly, if\n<code>start_seek</code> has never been called, then it is unspecified whether\n<code>poll_complete</code> returns the actual position or some other placeholder\nvalue (such as 0).</p>',
     '<p>此方法返回的位置只能在调用 <code>start_seek</code> 之后立即依赖。如果自调用 <code>start_seek</code> 以来已经通过例如读取或写入更改了位置，则返回的位置是否考虑了该位置变化是未指定的。类似地，如果从未调用过 <code>start_seek</code>，则 <code>poll_complete</code> 返回的是实际位置还是其他占位值（如 0）是未指定的。</p>'),
    ('<p>Seeking to a negative offset is considered an error.</p>',
     '<p>seek 到负偏移量被视为错误。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 59: AsyncBufRead (10 items) ============
    ('<p>This trait is analogous to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html" title="trait std::io::BufRead"><code>std::io::BufRead</code></a>, but integrates with\nthe asynchronous task system. In particular, the <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> method,\nunlike <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html#tymethod.fill_buf" title="method std::io::BufRead::fill_buf"><code>BufRead::fill_buf</code></a>, will automatically queue the current task for wakeup\nand return if data is not yet available, rather than blocking the calling\nthread.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 类似于 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html" title="trait std::io::BufRead"><code>std::io::BufRead</code></a>，但与异步任务系统集成。特别地，与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.BufRead.html#tymethod.fill_buf" title="method std::io::BufRead::fill_buf"><code>BufRead::fill_buf</code></a> 不同，<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> 方法将在数据尚未可用时自动将当前任务排队等待唤醒并返回，而不是阻塞调用线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>Utilities for working with <code>AsyncBufRead</code> values are provided by\n<a href="crate::io::AsyncBufReadExt"><code>AsyncBufReadExt</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>用于处理 <code>AsyncBufRead</code> 值的实用工具由 <a href="crate::io::AsyncBufReadExt"><code>AsyncBufReadExt</code></a> 提供。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to return the contents of the internal buffer, filling it with more data\nfrom the inner reader if it is empty.</p>',
     '<p>尝试返回内部缓冲区的内容，如果为空，则使用内部 reader 中的更多数据填充它。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, returns <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(buf))</code>.</p>',
     '<p>成功时，返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(buf))</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If no data is available for reading, the method returns\n<code>Poll::Pending</code> and arranges for the current task (via\n<code>cx.waker().wake_by_ref()</code>) to receive a notification when the object becomes\nreadable or is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有可读取的数据，该方法将返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排当前任务（通过 <code>cx.waker().wake_by_ref()</code>）在对象变为可读或关闭时接收通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is a lower-level call. It needs to be paired with the\n<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.consume" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::consume"><code>consume</code></a> method to function properly. When calling this\nmethod, none of the contents will be “read” in the sense that later\ncalling <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a> may return the same contents. As such, <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.consume" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::consume"><code>consume</code></a> must\nbe called with the number of bytes that are consumed from this buffer to\nensure that the bytes are never returned twice.</p>',
     '<p>此函数是较低级别的调用。它需要与 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.consume" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::consume"><code>consume</code></a> 方法配对才能正常工作。调用此方法时，不会"读取"任何内容，因为稍后调用 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a> 可能会返回相同的内容。因此，必须使用从此缓冲区消费的字节数调用 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.consume" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::consume"><code>consume</code></a>，以确保字节永远不会被返回两次。</p>'),
    ('<p>An empty buffer returned indicates that the stream has reached EOF.</p>',
     '<p>返回空缓冲区表示流已到达 EOF。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tells this buffer that <code>amt</code> bytes have been consumed from the buffer,\nso they should no longer be returned in calls to <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>告诉此缓冲区已从缓冲区中消费了 <code>amt</code> 字节，因此它们不应再在对 <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a> 的调用中返回。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is a lower-level call. It needs to be paired with the\n<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> method to function properly. This function does\nnot perform any I/O, it simply informs this object that some amount of\nits buffer, returned from <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a>, has been consumed and should\nno longer be returned. As such, this function may do odd things if\n<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> isn’t called before calling it.</p>',
     '<p>此函数是较低级别的调用。它需要与 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> 方法配对才能正常工作。此函数不执行任何 I/O，它只是通知此对象，其从 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> 返回的缓冲区中已消费了某些数量，并且不应再返回。因此，如果在调用之前没有调用 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a>，则此函数可能会做奇怪的事情。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>amt</code> must be <code>&lt;=</code> the number of bytes in the buffer returned by\n<a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><code>amt</code> 必须 <code>&lt;=</code> 由 <a href="trait.AsyncBufRead.html#tymethod.poll_fill_buf" title="method tokio::io::AsyncBufRead::poll_fill_buf"><code>poll_fill_buf</code></a> 返回的缓冲区中的字节数。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 60: AsyncRead (9 items) ============
    ('<p>This trait is analogous to the <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>std::io::Read</code></a> trait, but integrates with\nthe asynchronous task system. In particular, the <a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a> method,\nunlike <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html#tymethod.read" title="method std::io::Read::read"><code>Read::read</code></a>, will automatically queue the current task for wakeup\nand return if data is not yet available, rather than blocking the calling\nthread.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 类似于 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html" title="trait std::io::Read"><code>std::io::Read</code></a> trait，但与异步任务系统集成。特别地，与 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/std/io/trait.Read.html#tymethod.read" title="method std::io::Read::read"><code>Read::read</code></a> 不同，<a href="trait.AsyncRead.html#tymethod.poll_read" title="method tokio::io::AsyncRead::poll_read"><code>poll_read</code></a> 方法将在数据尚未可用时自动将当前任务排队等待唤醒并返回，而不是阻塞调用线程。</p>'),
    ('<p>Specifically, this means that the <code>poll_read</code> function will return one of\nthe following:</p>',
     '<p>具体来说，这意味着 <code>poll_read</code> 函数将返回以下之一：</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> means that data was immediately read and placed into\nthe output buffer. The amount of data read can be determined by the\nincrease in the length of the slice returned by <code>ReadBuf::filled</code>. If the\ndifference is 0, either EOF has been reached, or the output buffer had zero\ncapacity (i.e. <code>buf.remaining()</code> == 0).</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> 表示已立即读取数据并将其放入输出缓冲区中。读取的数据量可以通过 <code>ReadBuf::filled</code> 返回的切片长度的增加来确定。如果差值为 0，则表示已到达 EOF，或者输出缓冲区的容量为零（即 <code>buf.remaining()</code> == 0）。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> means that no data was read into the buffer\nprovided. The I/O object is not currently readable but may become readable\nin the future. Most importantly, <strong>the current future’s task is scheduled\nto get unparked when the object is readable</strong>. This means that like\n<code>Future::poll</code> you’ll receive a notification when the I/O object is\nreadable again.</p>',
     '<p><code>Poll::Pending</code> 表示没有数据被读入所提供的缓冲区。I/O 对象当前不可读，但将来可能变为可读。最重要的是，<strong>当前 future 的任务被安排在对象可读时获得 unpark</strong>。这意味着与 <code>Future::poll</code> 一样，当 I/O 对象再次可读时，你将收到通知。</p>'),
    ('<p>This trait importantly means that the <code>read</code> method only works in the\ncontext of a future’s task. The object may panic if used outside of a task.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 重要的是意味着 <code>read</code> 方法只能在 future 任务的上下文中工作。如果在任务外使用，该对象可能会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Utilities for working with <code>AsyncRead</code> values are provided by\n<a href="crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>用于处理 <code>AsyncRead</code> 值的实用工具由 <a href="crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> 提供。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to read from the <code>AsyncRead</code> into <code>buf</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试从 <code>AsyncRead</code> 读取到 <code>buf</code> 中。</p>'),
    ('<p>On success, returns <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> and places data in the\nunfilled portion of <code>buf</code>. If no data was read (<code>buf.filled().len()</code> is\nunchanged), it implies that EOF has been reached, or the output buffer\nhad zero capacity (i.e. <code>buf.remaining()</code> == 0).</p>',
     '<p>成功时，返回 <code>Poll::Ready(Ok(()))</code> 并将数据放入 <code>buf</code> 的未填充部分。如果没有读取数据（<code>buf.filled().len()</code> 未变化），则表示已到达 EOF，或者输出缓冲区的容量为零（即 <code>buf.remaining()</code> == 0）。</p>'),
    ('<p>If no data is available for reading, the method returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>\nand arranges for the current task (via <code>cx.waker()</code>) to receive a\nnotification when the object becomes readable or is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果没有可读取的数据，该方法将返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排当前任务（通过 <code>cx.waker()</code>）在对象变为可读或关闭时接收通知。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 61: JoinError (8 items) ============
    ('<p>Task failed to execute to completion.</p>',
     '<p>任务未能执行完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the error was caused by the task being cancelled.</p>',
     '<p>如果错误是由任务被取消引起的，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>See <a href="index.html#cancellation" title="mod tokio::task">the module level docs</a> for more information on cancellation.</p>',
     '<p>有关取消的更多信息，请参阅<a href="index.html#cancellation" title="mod tokio::task">模块级文档</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns true if the error was caused by the task panicking.</p>',
     '<p>如果错误是由任务 panic 引起的，则返回 true。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes the join error, returning the object with which the task panicked.</p>',
     '<p>消费 join error，返回任务 panic 的对象。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>into_panic()</code> panics if the <code>Error</code> does not represent the underlying\ntask terminating with a panic. Use <code>is_panic</code> to check the error reason\nor <code>try_into_panic</code> for a variant that does not panic.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Error</code> 不表示底层任务以 panic 终止，则 <code>into_panic()</code> 会 panic。使用 <code>is_panic</code> 检查错误原因，或使用 <code>try_into_panic</code> 获取不会 panic 的变体。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes the join error, returning the object with which the task\npanicked if the task terminated due to a panic. Otherwise, <code>self</code> is\nreturned.</p>',
     '<p>消费 join error，如果任务因 panic 而终止，则返回任务 panic 的对象。否则，返回 <code>self</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a> that identifies the task which errored relative to\nother currently spawned tasks.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 <a href="struct.Id.html" title="struct tokio::task::Id">task ID</a>，用于标识相对于其他当前已生成任务出错的 task。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 62: AbortHandle (8 items) ============
    ('<p>An owned permission to abort a spawned task, without awaiting its completion.</p>',
     '<p>中止已生成任务的所拥有权限，无需等待其完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike a <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a>, an <code>AbortHandle</code> does <em>not</em> represent the\npermission to await the task’s completion, only to terminate it.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html" title="struct tokio::task::JoinHandle"><code>JoinHandle</code></a> 不同，<code>AbortHandle</code> <em>不</em>表示等待任务完成的权限，只表示终止它的权限。</p>'),
    ('<p>The task may be aborted by calling the <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::abort"><code>AbortHandle::abort</code></a> method.\nDropping an <code>AbortHandle</code> releases the permission to terminate the task\n— it does <em>not</em> abort the task.</p>',
     '<p>可以通过调用 <a href="struct.AbortHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::AbortHandle::abort"><code>AbortHandle::abort</code></a> 方法中止任务。Drop <code>AbortHandle</code> 会释放终止任务的权限——它<em>不会</em>中止任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Be aware that tasks spawned using <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> cannot be aborted\nbecause they are not async. If you call <code>abort</code> on a <code>spawn_blocking</code> task,\nthen this <em>will not have any effect</em>, and the task will continue running\nnormally. The exception is if the task has not started running yet; in that\ncase, calling <code>abort</code> may prevent the task from starting.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，使用 <a href="fn.spawn_blocking.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn_blocking"><code>spawn_blocking</code></a> 生成的任务无法中止，因为它们不是异步的。如果对 <code>spawn_blocking</code> 任务调用 <code>abort</code>，那么<em>这将没有任何效果</em>，任务将继续正常运行。例外情况是如果任务尚未开始运行；在这种情况下，调用 <code>abort</code> 可能会阻止任务启动。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task was already cancelled, such as by <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a>,\nthis method will do nothing.</p>',
     '<p>如果任务已被取消（例如通过 <a href="struct.JoinHandle.html#method.abort" title="method tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort"><code>JoinHandle::abort</code></a>），则此方法将不执行任何操作。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if the task associated with this <code>AbortHandle</code> has finished.</p>',
     '<p>检查与此 <code>AbortHandle</code> 关联的任务是否已完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Please note that this method can return <code>false</code> even if <code>abort</code> has been\ncalled on the task. This is because the cancellation process may take\nsome time, and this method does not return <code>true</code> until it has\ncompleted.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，即使已对任务调用了 <code>abort</code>，此方法也可能返回 <code>false</code>。这是因为取消过程可能需要一些时间，并且此方法在取消完成之前不会返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a cloned <code>AbortHandle</code> that can be used to remotely abort this task.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个克隆的 <code>AbortHandle</code>，可用于远程中止此任务。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 63: spawn_local (8 items) ============
    ('<p>Spawns a <code>!Send</code> future on the current <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> or <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>在当前 <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> 或 <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a> 上生成一个 <code>!Send</code> future。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is possible when either using one of these types explicitly, or by\nopting to use the <code>"local"</code> runtime flavor in <code>tokio::main</code>:</p>',
     '<p>当显式使用这些类型之一，或者选择在 <code>tokio::main</code> 中使用 <code>"local"</code> 运行时风格时，这是可能的：</p>'),
    ('<p>The spawned future will run on the same thread that called <code>spawn_local</code>.</p>',
     '<p>生成的 future 将在调用 <code>spawn_local</code> 的同一线程上运行。</p>'),
    ('<p>The provided future will start running in the background immediately\nwhen <code>spawn_local</code> is called, even if you don’t await the returned\n<code>JoinHandle</code>.</p>',
     '<p>当调用 <code>spawn_local</code> 时，所提供的 future 将立即开始在后台运行，即使你没有 await 返回的 <code>JoinHandle</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function panics if called outside of a <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> or <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果在 <a href="struct.LocalSet.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalSet"><code>LocalSet</code></a> 或 <a href="../runtime/struct.LocalRuntime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::LocalRuntime"><code>LocalRuntime</code></a> 之外调用此函数，则会发生 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that if <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a> is used from within a <code>LocalSet</code>, the\nresulting new task will <em>not</em> be inside the <code>LocalSet</code>, so you must use\n<code>spawn_local</code> if you want to stay within the <code>LocalSet</code>.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，如果在 <code>LocalSet</code> 内使用 <a href="fn.spawn.html" title="fn tokio::task::spawn"><code>tokio::spawn</code></a>，则生成的新任务将<em>不会</em>位于 <code>LocalSet</code> 内，因此如果你想停留在 <code>LocalSet</code> 内，必须使用 <code>spawn_local</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>With <code>LocalSet</code>:</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code>LocalSet</code>：</p>'),
    ('<p>With local runtime flavor.</p>',
     '<p>使用 local 运行时风格。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 64: RwLockReadGuard (8 items) ============
    ('<p>RAII structure used to release the shared read access of a lock when\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>RAII 结构体，用于在 drop 时释放锁的共享读访问。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read"><code>read</code></a> method on\n<a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read"><code>read</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <code>RwLockReadGuard</code> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <code>RwLockReadGuard</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>RwLockReadGuard::map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockReadGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an asynchronous version of <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockReadGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockReadGuard::map</code></a> from the\n<a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 中 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockReadGuard.html#method.map"><code>RwLockReadGuard::map</code></a> 的异步版本。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of the\nlocked data. The original guard is returned if the closure returns\n<code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockReadGuard"><code>RwLockReadGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>RwLockReadGuard::try_map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods of the\nsame name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockReadGuard::try_map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an asynchronous version of <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockReadGuard.html#method.try_map"><code>RwLockReadGuard::try_map</code></a> from the\n<a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是 <a href="https://crates.io/crates/parking_lot"><code>parking_lot</code> crate</a> 中 <a href="https://docs.rs/lock_api/latest/lock_api/struct.RwLockReadGuard.html#method.try_map"><code>RwLockReadGuard::try_map</code></a> 的异步版本。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 65: OwnedRwLockReadGuard (7 items) ============
    ('<p>Owned RAII structure used to release the shared read access of a lock when\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>Owned RAII 结构体，用于在 drop 时释放锁的共享读访问。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read_owned" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read_owned"><code>read_owned</code></a> method on\n<a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.RwLock.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLock"><code>RwLock</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.read_owned" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::read_owned"><code>read_owned</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code> for a component of the locked data.\nThis operation cannot fail as the <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code> passed in\nalready locked the data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code>。此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code> 已锁定数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard::map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a> for a component of the\nlocked data. The original guard is returned if the closure returns\n<code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockReadGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockReadGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code></a>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This operation cannot fail as the <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code> passed in\nalready locked the data.</p>',
     '<p>此操作不会失败，因为传入的 <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard</code> 已锁定数据。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard::try_map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockReadGuard::try_map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 66: Barrier (7 items) ============
    ('<p>A barrier enables multiple tasks to synchronize the beginning of some computation.</p>',
     '<p>barrier 使多个任务能够同步某些计算的开始。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new barrier that can block a given number of tasks.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 barrier，可以阻塞给定数量的任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>A barrier will block <code>n</code>-1 tasks which call <a href="struct.Barrier.html#method.wait" title="method tokio::sync::Barrier::wait"><code>Barrier::wait</code></a> and then wake up all\ntasks at once when the <code>n</code>th task calls <code>wait</code>.</p>',
     '<p>barrier 将阻塞调用 <a href="struct.Barrier.html#method.wait" title="method tokio::sync::Barrier::wait"><code>Barrier::wait</code></a> 的 <code>n</code>-1 个任务，然后在第 <code>n</code> 个任务调用 <code>wait</code> 时立即唤醒所有任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>Does not resolve until all tasks have rendezvoused here.</p>',
     '<p>在所有任务都在此会合并之前不会解析。</p>'),
    ('<p>Barriers are re-usable after all tasks have rendezvoused once, and can\nbe used continuously.</p>',
     '<p>barrier 在所有任务都已合并一次后可重用，并且可以连续使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>A single (arbitrary) future will receive a <a href="struct.BarrierWaitResult.html" title="struct tokio::sync::BarrierWaitResult"><code>BarrierWaitResult</code></a> that returns <code>true</code> from\n<a href="struct.BarrierWaitResult.html#method.is_leader" title="method tokio::sync::BarrierWaitResult::is_leader"><code>BarrierWaitResult::is_leader</code></a> when returning from this function, and all other tasks\nwill receive a result that will return <code>false</code> from <code>is_leader</code>.</p>',
     '<p>单个（任意的）future 将收到一个 <a href="struct.BarrierWaitResult.html" title="struct tokio::sync::BarrierWaitResult"><code>BarrierWaitResult</code></a>，从此函数返回时该结果从 <a href="struct.BarrierWaitResult.html#method.is_leader" title="method tokio::sync::BarrierWaitResult::is_leader"><code>BarrierWaitResult::is_leader</code></a> 返回 <code>true</code>，而所有其他任务将收到从 <code>is_leader</code> 返回 <code>false</code> 的结果。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is not cancel safe.</p>',
     '<p>此方法不是取消安全的。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 67: OwnedPermit (7 items) ============
    ('<p>Owned permit to send one value into the channel.</p>',
     '<p>用于向 channel 发送一个值的 owned permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is identical to the <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> type, except that it moves the sender\nrather than borrowing it.</p>',
     '<p>这与 <a href="struct.Permit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit"><code>Permit</code></a> 类型相同，只是它移动 sender 而不是借用它。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>OwnedPermit</code> values are returned by <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_owned"><code>Sender::reserve_owned()</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve_owned"><code>Sender::try_reserve_owned()</code></a> and are used to guarantee channel capacity\nbefore generating a message to send.</p>',
     '<p><code>OwnedPermit</code> 值由 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::reserve_owned"><code>Sender::reserve_owned()</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.try_reserve_owned" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender::try_reserve_owned"><code>Sender::try_reserve_owned()</code></a> 返回，用于在生成要发送的消息之前保证 channel 容量。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a>, this method returns the <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> from which\nthe <code>OwnedPermit</code> was reserved.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Permit.html#method.send" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::Permit::send"><code>Permit::send</code></a> 不同，此方法返回预留 <code>OwnedPermit</code> 的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Releases the reserved capacity <em>without</em> sending a message, returning the\n<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><em>不</em>发送消息就释放预留的容量，并返回 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if permits belong to the same channel.</p>',
     '<p>如果这些 permit 属于同一个 channel，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if this permit belongs to the same channel as the given <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果此 permit 与给定的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 属于同一个 channel，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 68: broadcast/channel (7 items) ============
    ('<p>Create a bounded, multi-producer, multi-consumer channel where each sent\nvalue is broadcasted to all active receivers.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个有界、多生产者、多消费者的 channel，其中每个发送的值都会广播给所有活动的接收器。</p>'),
    ('<p><strong>Note:</strong> The actual capacity may be greater than the provided <code>capacity</code>.</p>',
     '<p><strong>注意：</strong>实际容量可能大于所提供的 <code>capacity</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>All data sent on <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> will become available on every active\n<a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> in the same order as it was sent.</p>',
     '<p>在 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 上发送的所有数据将按发送顺序在每个活动的 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 上可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Sender</code> can be cloned to <code>send</code> to the same channel from multiple\npoints in the process or it can be used concurrently from an <code>Arc</code>. New\n<code>Receiver</code> handles are created by calling <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>可以克隆 <code>Sender</code>，以便从进程中的多个位置 <code>send</code> 到同一 channel，也可以从 <code>Arc</code> 中并发使用。通过调用 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.subscribe" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender::subscribe"><code>Sender::subscribe</code></a> 创建新的 <code>Receiver</code> 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>If all <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handles are dropped, the <code>send</code> method will return a\n<a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a>. Similarly, if all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handles are dropped, the <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a>\nmethod will return a <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果所有 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop，则 <code>send</code> 方法将返回 <a href="error/struct.SendError.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::error::SendError"><code>SendError</code></a>。类似地，如果所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄都已被 drop，则 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.recv" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::Receiver::recv"><code>recv</code></a> 方法将返回 <a href="error/enum.RecvError.html" title="enum tokio::sync::broadcast::error::RecvError"><code>RecvError</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This will panic if <code>capacity</code> is equal to <code>0</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>capacity</code> 等于 <code>0</code>，这将 panic。</p>'),
    ('<p>This pre-allocates space for <code>capacity</code> messages. Allocation failure may result in a panic or\n<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/alloc/fn.handle_alloc_error.html" title="fn alloc::alloc::handle_alloc_error">an allocation error</a>.</p>',
     '<p>这会为 <code>capacity</code> 条消息预分配空间。分配失败可能导致 panic 或<a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/alloc/fn.handle_alloc_error.html" title="fn alloc::alloc::handle_alloc_error">分配错误</a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 69: yield_now (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Yields execution back to the Tokio runtime.</p>',
     '<p>将执行权让回 Tokio 运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>A task yields by awaiting on <code>yield_now()</code>, and may resume when that future\ncompletes (with no output.) The current task will be re-added as a pending\ntask at the <em>back</em> of the pending queue. Any other pending tasks will be\nscheduled. No other waking is required for the task to continue.</p>',
     '<p>任务通过 await <code>yield_now()</code> 让步，并可能在该 future 完成时恢复（无输出）。当前任务将作为挂起任务重新添加到挂起队列的<em>末尾</em>。任何其他挂起任务都将被调度。任务继续不需要其他唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>See also the usage example in the <a href="index.html#yield_now">task module</a>.</p>',
     '<p>另请参阅 <a href="index.html#yield_now">task 模块</a>中的使用示例。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function may not yield all the way up to the executor if there are any\nspecial combinators above it in the call stack. For example, if a\n<a href="macro@crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> has another branch complete during the same poll as the\n<code>yield_now()</code>, then the yield is not propagated all the way up to the\nruntime.</p>',
     '<p>如果调用栈中此函数之上有任何特殊的组合器，则该函数可能不会一直让步到执行器。例如，如果 <a href="macro@crate::select"><code>tokio::select!</code></a> 在与 <code>yield_now()</code> 相同的 poll 期间有另一个分支完成，则让步不会一直传播到运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>It is generally not guaranteed that the runtime behaves like you expect it\nto when deciding which task to schedule next after a call to <code>yield_now()</code>.\nIn particular, the runtime may choose to poll the task that just ran\n<code>yield_now()</code> again immediately without polling any other tasks first. For\nexample, the runtime will not drive the IO driver between every poll of a\ntask, and this could result in the runtime polling the current task again\nimmediately even if there is another task that could make progress if that\nother task is waiting for a notification from the IO driver.</p>',
     '<p>通常不能保证运行时的行为符合你的预期，特别是在调用 <code>yield_now()</code> 后决定下一个调度哪个任务时。尤其运行时可能选择立即再次 poll 刚刚运行 <code>yield_now()</code> 的任务，而不先 poll 任何其他任务。例如，运行时不会在每次 poll 任务之间驱动 IO 驱动，这可能导致运行时立即再次 poll 当前任务，即使有另一个任务可以通过 IO 驱动的通知取得进展。</p>'),
    ('<p>In general, changes to the order in which the runtime polls tasks is not\nconsidered a breaking change, and your program should be correct no matter\nwhich order the runtime polls your tasks in.</p>',
     '<p>一般来说，更改运行时 poll 任务的顺序不被视为破坏性更改，你的程序应该在运行时以任何顺序 poll 你的任务时都是正确的。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 70: coop/index (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Utilities for improved cooperative scheduling.</p>',
     '<p>改进协作调度的实用工具。</p>'),
    ('<p>A single call to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html#tymethod.poll" title="method core::future::future::Future::poll"><code>poll</code></a> on a top-level task may potentially do a lot of\nwork before it returns <code>Poll::Pending</code>. If a task runs for a long period of\ntime without yielding back to the executor, it can starve other tasks\nwaiting on that executor to execute them, or drive underlying resources.\nSince Rust does not have a runtime, it is difficult to forcibly preempt a\nlong-running task. Instead, this module provides an opt-in mechanism for\nfutures to collaborate with the executor to avoid starvation.</p>',
     '<p>对顶层任务的一次 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html#tymethod.poll" title="method core::future::future::Future::poll"><code>poll</code></a> 调用在返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code> 之前可能会做大量工作。如果任务长时间运行而不让步回执行器，则会饿死等待该执行器执行它们的其他任务，或无法驱动底层资源。由于 Rust 没有运行时，因此很难强制抢占长时间运行的任务。相反，此模块提供了一种 opt-in 机制，让 future 与执行器协作以避免饥饿。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consider a future like this one:</p>',
     '<p>考虑这样的 future：</p>'),
    ('<p>It may look harmless, but consider what happens under heavy load if the\ninput stream is <em>always</em> ready. If we spawn <code>drop_all</code>, the task will never\nyield, and will starve other tasks and resources on the same executor.</p>',
     '<p>它看起来无害，但考虑在高负载下如果输入流<em>始终</em>就绪会发生什么。如果我们生成 <code>drop_all</code>，任务将永远不会让步，并会饿死同一执行器上的其他任务和资源。</p>'),
    ('<p>To account for this, Tokio has explicit yield points in a number of library\nfunctions, which force tasks to return to the executor periodically.</p>',
     '<p>为了解决此问题，Tokio 在许多库函数中具有显式的让步点，强制任务定期返回到执行器。</p>'),
    ('<p>If necessary, <a href="fn.unconstrained.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::unconstrained"><code>task::unconstrained</code></a> lets you opt a future out of Tokio’s cooperative\nscheduling. When a future is wrapped with <code>unconstrained</code>, it will never be forced to yield to\nTokio. For example:</p>',
     '<p>如有必要，<a href="fn.unconstrained.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::unconstrained"><code>task::unconstrained</code></a> 允许你将 future 从 Tokio 的协作调度中排除。当 future 使用 <code>unconstrained</code> 包装时，它将永远不会被强制让步给 Tokio。例如：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 71: OwnedSemaphorePermit (6 items) ============
    ('<p>An owned permit from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>来自信号量的 owned permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type is created by the <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire_owned"><code>acquire_owned</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>此类型由 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire_owned"><code>acquire_owned</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Merge two <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> instances together, consuming <code>other</code>\nwithout releasing the permits it holds.</p>',
     '<p>将两个 <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> 实例合并在一起，消费 <code>other</code> 而不释放它持有的 permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>Splits <code>n</code> permits from <code>self</code> and returns a new <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> instance that holds <code>n</code> permits.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>self</code> 拆分 <code>n</code> 个 permit，并返回一个持有 <code>n</code> 个 permit 的新 <a href="struct.OwnedSemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedSemaphorePermit"><code>OwnedSemaphorePermit</code></a> 实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>It will clone the owned <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code> to construct the new instance.</p>',
     '<p>它将克隆所拥有的 <code>Arc&lt;Semaphore&gt;</code> 以构造新实例。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> from which this permit was acquired.</p>',
     '<p>返回获取此 permit 的 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 72: UnboundedSender (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Send values to the associated <code>UnboundedReceiver</code>.</p>',
     '<p>向关联的 <code>UnboundedReceiver</code> 发送值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to send a message on this <code>UnboundedSender</code> without blocking.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在不阻塞的情况下通过此 <code>UnboundedSender</code> 发送消息。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method is not marked as <code>async</code> because sending a message to an unbounded channel\nnever requires any form of waiting. This is due to the channel’s infinite capacity,\nallowing the <code>send</code> operation to complete immediately. As a result, the <code>send</code> method can be\nused in both synchronous and asynchronous code without issues.</p>',
     '<p>此方法未标记为 <code>async</code>，因为向无界 channel 发送消息永远不需要任何形式的等待。这是由于 channel 的无限容量，允许 <code>send</code> 操作立即完成。因此，<code>send</code> 方法可以在同步和异步代码中使用而不会出现问题。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the receive half of the channel is closed, either due to <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a>\nbeing called or the <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a> having been dropped, this\nfunction returns an error. The error includes the value passed to <code>send</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的接收端已关闭（无论是由于调用了 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>close</code></a> 还是 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a> 已被 drop），则此函数返回错误。错误包括传递给 <code>send</code> 的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Checks if the channel has been closed. This happens when the\n<a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a> is dropped, or when the\n<a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>UnboundedReceiver::close</code></a> method is called.</p>',
     '<p>检查 channel 是否已关闭。当 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver"><code>UnboundedReceiver</code></a> 被 drop，或调用 <a href="struct.UnboundedReceiver.html#method.close" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver::close"><code>UnboundedReceiver::close</code></a> 方法时，会发生这种情况。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts the <code>UnboundedSender</code> to a <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a> that does not count\ntowards RAII semantics, i.e. if all <code>UnboundedSender</code> instances of the\nchannel were dropped and only <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> instances remain,\nthe channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>将 <code>UnboundedSender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a>，后者不计入 RAII 语义，即如果 channel 的所有 <code>UnboundedSender</code> 实例都已被 drop，仅剩下 <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> 实例，则 channel 关闭。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 73: mpsc/channel (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Creates a bounded mpsc channel for communicating between asynchronous tasks\nwith backpressure.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个有界 mpsc channel，用于在异步任务之间通信，并提供背压。</p>'),
    ('<p>The channel will buffer up to the provided number of messages.  Once the\nbuffer is full, attempts to send new messages will wait until a message is\nreceived from the channel. The provided buffer capacity must be at least 1.</p>',
     '<p>channel 将缓冲最多提供数量的消息。一旦缓冲区已满，尝试发送新消息将等待，直到从 channel 接收一条消息为止。提供的缓冲区容量必须至少为 1。</p>'),
    ('<p>All data sent on <code>Sender</code> will become available on <code>Receiver</code> in the same\norder as it was sent.</p>',
     '<p>在 <code>Sender</code> 上发送的所有数据将按发送顺序在 <code>Receiver</code> 上可用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Sender</code> can be cloned to <code>send</code> to the same channel from multiple code\nlocations. Only one <code>Receiver</code> is supported.</p>',
     '<p>可以克隆 <code>Sender</code> 以便从多个代码位置 <code>send</code> 到同一 channel。仅支持一个 <code>Receiver</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <code>Receiver</code> is disconnected while trying to <code>send</code>, the <code>send</code> method\nwill return a <code>SendError</code>. Similarly, if <code>Sender</code> is disconnected while\ntrying to <code>recv</code>, the <code>recv</code> method will return <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果尝试 <code>send</code> 时 <code>Receiver</code> 已断开连接，则 <code>send</code> 方法将返回 <code>SendError</code>。类似地，如果尝试 <code>recv</code> 时 <code>Sender</code> 已断开连接，则 <code>recv</code> 方法将返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Panics if the buffer capacity is 0, or too large. Currently the maximum\ncapacity is <a href="../struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>如果缓冲区容量为 0 或过大，则会 panic。目前最大容量为 <a href="../struct.Semaphore.html#associatedconstant.MAX_PERMITS" title="associated constant tokio::sync::Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS"><code>Semaphore::MAX_PERMITS</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 74: Notified (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Future returned from <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Notify::notified()</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notified" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notified"><code>Notify::notified()</code></a> 返回的 Future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Polling the future also adds it to the list, so this method should only\nbe used if you want to add the future to the list before the first call\nto <code>poll</code>. (In fact, this method is equivalent to calling <code>poll</code> except\nthat no <code>Waker</code> is registered.)</p>',
     '<p>poll future 也会将其添加到列表中，因此仅当你想在第一次调用 <code>poll</code> 之前将 future 添加到列表中时才应使用此方法。（实际上，此方法等效于调用 <code>poll</code>，只是未注册 <code>Waker</code>。）</p>'),
    ('<p>This has no effect on notifications sent using <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notify_waiters" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_waiters"><code>notify_waiters</code></a>, which\nare received as long as they happen after the creation of the <code>Notified</code>\nregardless of whether <code>enable</code> or <code>poll</code> has been called.</p>',
     '<p>这对使用 <a href="../struct.Notify.html#method.notify_waiters" title="method tokio::sync::Notify::notify_waiters"><code>notify_waiters</code></a> 发送的通知没有影响，只要它们发生在 <code>Notified</code> 创建之后，就会被接收，无论是否已调用 <code>enable</code> 或 <code>poll</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method returns true if the <code>Notified</code> is ready. This happens in the\nfollowing situations:</p>',
     '<p>如果 <code>Notified</code> 已就绪，则此方法返回 true。在以下情况下会发生这种情况：</p>'),
    ('<p>If this method returns true, any future calls to poll on the same future\nwill immediately return <code>Poll::Ready</code>.</p>',
     '<p>如果此方法返回 true，则对同一 future 的任何后续 poll 调用将立即返回 <code>Poll::Ready</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The call to <code>enable</code> is important because otherwise if you have two\ncalls to <code>recv</code> and two calls to <code>send</code> in parallel, the following could\nhappen:</p>',
     '<p>对 <code>enable</code> 的调用很重要，因为否则如果你并行进行两次 <code>recv</code> 调用和两次 <code>send</code> 调用，则可能发生以下情况：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 75: OwnedWriteHalf (6 items) ============
    ('<p>Owned write half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的 owned 写半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that in the <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> implementation of this type, <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> will\nshut down the TCP stream in the write direction.  Dropping the write half\nwill also shut down the write half of the TCP stream.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在此类型的 <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> 实现中，<a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> 将关闭 TCP 流的写方向。Drop 写半部也会关闭 TCP 流的写半部。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writing to an <code>OwnedWriteHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found\non the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>写入 <code>OwnedWriteHalf</code> 通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Destroys the write half, but don’t close the write half of the stream\nuntil the read half is dropped. If the read half has already been\ndropped, this closes the stream.</p>',
     '<p>销毁写半部，但在读半部被 drop 之前不会关闭流的写半部。如果读半部已被 drop，则这会关闭流。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a>. It can be used instead\nof <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> to check the returned ready set for <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITABLE"><code>Ready::WRITABLE</code></a>\nand <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITE_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITE_CLOSED"><code>Ready::WRITE_CLOSED</code></a> events.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 配合使用。它可以用来代替 <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::writable"><code>writable()</code></a>，以检查返回的就绪集中的 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITABLE"><code>Ready::WRITABLE</code></a> 和 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITE_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITE_CLOSED"><code>Ready::WRITE_CLOSED</code></a> 事件。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序从每个缓冲区写入数据，最后读取的缓冲区可能只被部分使用。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.OwnedWriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedWriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 76: TaskLocalFuture (5 items) ============
    ('<p>A future that sets a value <code>T</code> of a task local for the future <code>F</code> during\nits execution.</p>',
     '<p>在 future <code>F</code> 执行期间为其设置任务本地值 <code>T</code> 的 future。</p>'),
    ("<p>The value of the task-local must be <code>'static</code> and will be dropped on the\ncompletion of the future.</p>",
     "<p>任务本地的值必须为 <code>'static</code>，并将在 future 完成时被 drop。</p>"),
    ('<p>Created by the function <a href="../struct.LocalKey.html#method.scope" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::scope"><code>LocalKey::scope</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>由函数 <a href="../struct.LocalKey.html#method.scope" title="method tokio::task::LocalKey::scope"><code>LocalKey::scope</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the value stored in the task local by this <code>TaskLocalFuture</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回此 <code>TaskLocalFuture</code> 存储在任务本地中的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that this function attempts to take the task local value even if\nthe future has not yet completed. In that case, the value will no longer\nbe available via the task local after the call to <code>take_value</code>.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，即使 future 尚未完成，此函数也会尝试获取任务本地值。在这种情况下，在调用 <code>take_value</code> 之后，该值将不再可通过任务本地获得。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 77: OwnedMutexGuard (5 items) ============
    ('<p>An owned handle to a held Mutex.</p>',
     '<p>对所持有 Mutex 的 owned 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock_owned"><code>lock_owned</code></a> method\non <a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock_owned" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock_owned"><code>lock_owned</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedMappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedMappedMutexGuard"><code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedMutexGuard::map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedMutexGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts this <code>OwnedMutexGuard</code> into an <code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code>. This method can\nbe used to store a non-mapped guard in a struct field that expects a\nmapped guard.</p>',
     '<p>将此 <code>OwnedMutexGuard</code> 转换为 <code>OwnedMappedMutexGuard</code>。此方法可用于将非映射 guard 存储在期望映射 guard 的结构体字段中。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 78: MutexGuard (5 items) ============
    ('<p>RAII structure used to release the exclusive access of a lock when dropped.</p>',
     '<p>RAII 结构体，用于在 drop 时释放锁的独占访问。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> method on\n<a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.Mutex.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Mutex"><code>Mutex</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::lock"><code>lock</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.MappedMutexGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::MappedMutexGuard"><code>MappedMutexGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>MutexGuard::map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>MutexGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Converts this <code>MutexGuard</code> into an <code>MappedMutexGuard</code>. This method can\nbe used to store a non-mapped guard in a struct field that expects a\nmapped guard.</p>',
     '<p>将此 <code>MutexGuard</code> 转换为 <code>MappedMutexGuard</code>。此方法可用于将非映射 guard 存储在期望映射 guard 的结构体字段中。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 79: oneshot/index (5 items) ============
    ('<p>A <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> is used to send a single value to <strong>one</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>.\nThe <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> handle can be cloned, but only one <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is\nsupported. <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> are both <code>Send</code> and <code>Sync</code> as long as\n<code>T</code> is <code>Send</code>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 用于向<strong>一个</strong> <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 发送单个值。<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 句柄可以克隆，但仅支持一个 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。只要 <code>T</code> 是 <code>Send</code>，<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 都实现 <code>Send</code> 和 <code>Sync</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>A channel is created using the <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数创建 channel。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> can be moved or cloned, but only one <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is supported per\nchannel. Each <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> can send <strong>only one</strong> value. After a value is sent,\nthe <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> is consumed, and cannot be used further. If you need to send\nmultiple values, use a <a href="../mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc">multi-producer channel</a> instead.</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 可以移动或克隆，但每个 channel 仅支持一个 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a>。每个 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 只能发送<strong>一个</strong>值。发送值后，<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 将被消费，不能再使用。如果需要发送多个值，请改用<a href="../mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc">多生产者 channel</a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is closed (either explicitly or by being dropped), the\n<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> will observe this and return an error.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 已关闭（无论是显式关闭还是被 drop），则 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 将观察到这一点并返回错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is used to await a value sent by the <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>. If no value\nis available yet, the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> will wait until a value is provided, or\nuntil the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is closed (either explicitly or by dropping the\n<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>).</p>',
     '<p><a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 用于等待 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 发送的值。如果尚无可用值，则 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 将等待，直到提供一个值，或直到 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 关闭（无论是显式关闭还是 drop <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>）。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 80: SetError (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Errors that can be returned from <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::SetOnce::set"><code>SetOnce::set</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>可从 <a href="struct.SetOnce.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::SetOnce::set"><code>SetOnce::set</code></a> 返回的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This error is returned if the <a href="struct.SetOnce.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SetOnce"><code>SetOnce</code></a> already contains a value.</p>',
     '<p>如果 <a href="struct.SetOnce.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SetOnce"><code>SetOnce</code></a> 已经包含值，则返回此错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>SetOnce</code> error.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <code>SetOnce</code> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Creates a new <code>SetOnce</code> error from the value that was attempted to be set.</p>',
     '<p>从尝试设置的值创建一个新的 <code>SetOnce</code> 错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes the error, returning the value that was attempted to be set.</p>',
     '<p>消费错误，返回尝试设置的值。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 81: PipeMode (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Indicates the pipe mode of a named pipe.</p>',
     '<p>指示命名管道的管道模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written to the pipe as a stream of bytes. The pipe does not\npreserve boundaries between writes.</p>',
     '<p>数据作为字节流写入管道。管道不保留写入之间的边界。</p>'),
    ('<p>The pipe maintains boundaries between writes. Use this mode if you need\nto preserve message boundaries.</p>',
     '<p>管道在写入之间维护边界。如果需要保留消息边界，请使用此模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Determines if the pipe is currently in message mode.</p>',
     '<p>确定管道当前是否处于消息模式。</p>'),
    ('<p>Determines if the pipe is currently in byte mode.</p>',
     '<p>确定管道当前是否处于字节模式。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 82: WriteHalf (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Write half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的写半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that in the <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> implementation of this type, <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> will\nshut down the TCP stream in the write direction.  Dropping the write half\nwill also shut down the write half of the TCP stream.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在此类型的 <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> 实现中，<a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> 将关闭 TCP 流的写方向。Drop 写半部也会关闭 TCP 流的写半部。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writing to a <code>WriteHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found\non the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>写入 <code>WriteHalf</code> 通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Destroys the write half, but don’t close the write half of the stream\nuntil the read half is dropped. If the read half has already been\ndropped, this closes the stream.</p>',
     '<p>销毁写半部，但在读半部被 drop 之前不会关闭流的写半部。如果读半部已被 drop，则这会关闭流。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a>. It can be used instead\nof <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::writable"><code>writable()</code></a> to check the returned ready set for <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITABLE"><code>Ready::WRITABLE</code></a>\nand <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITE_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITE_CLOSED"><code>Ready::WRITE_CLOSED</code></a> events.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 配合使用。它可以用来代替 <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.writable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::writable"><code>writable()</code></a>，以检查返回的就绪集中的 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITABLE"><code>Ready::WRITABLE</code></a> 和 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.WRITE_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::WRITE_CLOSED"><code>Ready::WRITE_CLOSED</code></a> 事件。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 83: OwnedReadHalf (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Owned read half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的 owned 读半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.into_split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::into_split"><code>into_split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reading from an <code>OwnedReadHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found\non the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>OwnedReadHalf</code> 读取通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Closes the read half of the TCP stream.</p>',
     '<p>关闭 TCP 流的读半部。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序复制数据以填充每个缓冲区，最后写入的缓冲区可能只被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 84: Timeout (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Future returned by <a href="fn.timeout.html" title="fn tokio::time::timeout"><code>timeout</code></a> and <a href="fn.timeout_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::timeout_at"><code>timeout_at</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>由 <a href="fn.timeout.html" title="fn tokio::time::timeout"><code>timeout</code></a> 和 <a href="fn.timeout_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::timeout_at"><code>timeout_at</code></a> 返回的 Future。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type does not implement the <code>Unpin</code> trait, which means that if you\nuse it with <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a> or by calling <code>poll</code>, you have to pin it first.\nIf you use it with <code>.await</code>, this does not apply.</p>',
     '<p>此类型不实现 <code>Unpin</code> trait，这意味着如果将其与 <a href="../macro.select.html"><code>select!</code></a> 一起使用或通过调用 <code>poll</code> 来使用，则必须先将其 pin。如果使用 <code>.await</code>，则不适用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the inner future.</p>',
     '<p>返回对内部 future 的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a mutable reference to the inner future.</p>',
     '<p>返回对内部 future 的可变引用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 85: timeout fn (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Require a <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> to complete before the specified duration has elapsed.</p>',
     '<p>要求 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a> 在指定的持续时间过去之前完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the future completes before the duration has elapsed, then the\ncompleted future is returned. Otherwise, an error is returned and the\nfuture is canceled.</p>',
     '<p>如果 future 在持续时间过去之前完成，则返回已完成的 future。否则，返回错误并取消该 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>When the <a href="../struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> shuts down, the timer that drives timeouts is informed, and\nthe futures outstanding are dropped.</p>',
     '<p>当 <a href="../struct.Runtime.html" title="struct tokio::runtime::Runtime"><code>Runtime</code></a> 关闭时，驱动超时的计时器将收到通知，并 drop 未完成的 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Canceling a timeout: <a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.is_elapsed" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::is_elapsed"><code>Timeout</code>::is_elapsed</a> can be used to tell whether the timeout\nhas been reached. If <a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.is_elapsed" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::is_elapsed"><code>Timeout</code>::is_elapsed</a> returns false, then the timeout\nhas not been reached and the future can still be canceled by dropping the\nfuture.</p>',
     '<p>取消超时：<a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.is_elapsed" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::is_elapsed"><code>Timeout</code>::is_elapsed</a> 可用于判断是否已达到超时。如果 <a href="struct.Timeout.html#method.is_elapsed" title="method tokio::time::Timeout::is_elapsed"><code>Timeout</code>::is_elapsed</a> 返回 false，则尚未达到超时，并且仍然可以通过 drop 该 future 来取消它。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 86: interval fn (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Creates a new <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> that yields with the specified <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>Duration</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a>，它以指定的 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/time/struct.Duration.html" title="struct core::time::Duration"><code>Duration</code></a> 产生值。</p>'),
    ('<p>The first tick completes immediately. The default <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> is\n<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>, which will cause ticks to be emitted in quick succession if they\nhave been delayed.</p>',
     '<p>第一个 tick 立即完成。默认的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 是 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>，如果 tick 已被延迟，它将导致 tick 快速连续发出。</p>'),
    ('<p>To handle <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> other than the default, use\n<a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a> to set the initial date, and\n<a href="struct.Interval.html#method.set_missed_tick_behavior" title="method tokio::time::Interval::set_missed_tick_behavior"><code>set_missed_tick_behavior</code></a> to set the behavior.</p>',
     '<p>要处理默认以外的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a>，请使用 <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a> 设置初始日期，并使用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.set_missed_tick_behavior" title="method tokio::time::Interval::set_missed_tick_behavior"><code>set_missed_tick_behavior</code></a> 设置行为。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to\n<code><a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a>(<a href="struct.Instant.html#method.now" title="associated function tokio::time::Instant::now"><code>Instant::now</code></a>() + period, period)</code> when using the default\n<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>在使用默认的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 时，此函数等效于 <code><a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at</code></a>(<a href="struct.Instant.html#method.now" title="associated function tokio::time::Instant::now"><code>Instant::now</code></a>() + period, period)</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 87: poll_proceed (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Polls the budget to determine whether the task should continue executing.</p>',
     '<p>轮询预算以确定任务是否应继续执行。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is called by the Tokio runtime at points where a future\nmight otherwise consume an unbounded amount of time or resources without\nyielding back to the executor.</p>',
     '<p>在 future 可能消耗无限时间或资源而不让步回执行器的位置，Tokio 运行时会调用此函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the budget has been depleted, this returns <code>Poll::Pending</code> and arranges\nfor the current task to be woken up when the budget is replenished.</p>',
     '<p>如果预算已用尽，则返回 <code>Poll::Pending</code>，并安排在预算补充时唤醒当前任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the task has remaining budget, this returns immediately.</p>',
     '<p>如果任务还有剩余预算，则立即返回。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 88: cooperative (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Returns a future that requires the runtime to yield to other tasks after\nthe future completes.</p>',
     '<p>返回一个 future，要求运行时在该 future 完成后让步给其他任务。</p>'),
    ('<p>This future wraps the provided future and forces it to yield back to the\nexecutor after it completes. This is useful for ensuring that long-running\nor expensive computations do not starve other tasks.</p>',
     '<p>此 future 包装所提供的 future，并强制其在完成后让步回执行器。这对于确保长时间运行或昂贵的计算不会饿死其他任务非常有用。</p>'),
    ('<p>The output of the future is the same as the wrapped future.</p>',
     '<p>future 的输出与包装的 future 相同。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is useful when writing your own futures that may run for\nan extended period, but should still cooperate with the Tokio scheduler.</p>',
     '<p>在编写自己可能长时间运行的 future，但仍应与 Tokio 调度器协作时，此函数非常有用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 89: watch Ref (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the most recently sent value.</p>',
     '<p>返回对最近发送的值的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This method will not mark the value as seen, so future calls to\n<a href="struct.Sender.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::borrow"><code>Sender::borrow</code></a> will return the same value.</p>',
     '<p>此方法不会将值标记为已读取，因此未来对 <a href="struct.Sender.html#method.borrow" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Sender::borrow"><code>Sender::borrow</code></a> 的调用将返回相同的值。</p>'),
    ('<p>If two values have been sent since the last time the value was marked\nseen, the <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> future will resolve to the most recent of the two\nvalues.</p>',
     '<p>如果自上次将值标记为已读取以来已发送两个值，则 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::changed"><code>changed</code></a> future 将解析为这两个值中最近的一个。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the most recently sent value and marks that value\nas seen.</p>',
     '<p>返回对最近发送的值的引用，并将该值标记为已读取。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 90: TryLockError (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Error returned from the <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>try_lock</code></a> function.</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>try_lock</code></a> 函数返回的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>This error is returned when the mutex is already locked.</p>',
     '<p>当 mutex 已被锁定时返回此错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the lock was acquired.</p>',
     '<p>如果已获取锁，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the mutex was already locked.</p>',
     '<p>如果 mutex 已被锁定，则返回 <code>true</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 91: SemaphorePermit (4 items) ============
    ('<p>A permit from the semaphore.</p>',
     '<p>来自信号量的 permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>This type is created by the <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire"><code>acquire</code></a> method.</p>',
     '<p>此类型由 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html#method.acquire" title="method tokio::sync::Semaphore::acquire"><code>acquire</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Merge two <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> instances together, consuming <code>other</code>\nwithout releasing the permits it holds.</p>',
     '<p>将两个 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> 实例合并在一起，消费 <code>other</code> 而不释放它持有的 permit。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a> from which this permit was acquired.</p>',
     '<p>返回获取此 permit 的 <a href="struct.Semaphore.html" title="struct tokio::sync::Semaphore"><code>Semaphore</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 92: RwLockMappedWriteGuard (4 items) ============
    ('<p>RAII structure used to release the exclusive write access of a lock when\ndropped.</p>',
     '<p>RAII 结构体，用于在 drop 时释放锁的独占写访问。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::map"><code>map</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map"><code>downgrade_map</code></a> methods on <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard"><code>RwLockWriteGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard"><code>RwLockWriteGuard</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::map"><code>map</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map"><code>downgrade_map</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.RwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods of\nthe same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 93: OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Owned RAII structure used to release the exclusive write access of a lock\nwhen dropped.</p>',
     '<p>Owned RAII 结构体，用于在 drop 时释放锁的独占写访问。</p>'),
    ('<p>This structure is created by the <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map"><code>map</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map"><code>downgrade_map</code></a> methods on\n<a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体由 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code></a> 上的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map"><code>map</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.downgrade_map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::downgrade_map"><code>downgrade_map</code></a> 方法创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a> for a component of the locked\ndata.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(...)</code>. A method would interfere\nwith methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 94: WeakUnboundedSender (4 items) ============
    ('<p>A weak reference to an <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 的弱引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is a weak reference to the sender half of a channel. The channel\nis closed when all <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> instances are dropped, even if\n<a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a> instances exist.</p>',
     '<p>这是 channel 的 sender 端的弱引用。当所有 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop 时，channel 将关闭，即使存在 <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender"><code>WeakUnboundedSender</code></a> 实例也是如此。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to convert the <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> into a <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a>.\nReturns <code>None</code> if all <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> instances have been dropped, and\nthe channel has been closed.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将 <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a>。如果所有 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop 且 channel 已关闭，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> instances currently alive.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存活的 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 实例数。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 95: WeakSender (4 items) ============
    ('<p>A weak reference to a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 的弱引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is a weak reference to the sender half of a broadcast channel. The\nchannel is closed when all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> instances are dropped, even if\n<a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> instances exist.</p>',
     '<p>这是 broadcast channel 的 sender 端的弱引用。当所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop 时，channel 将关闭，即使存在 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender"><code>WeakSender</code></a> 实例也是如此。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to convert the <code>WeakSender</code> into a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.\nReturns <code>None</code> if all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> instances have been dropped, and the\nchannel has been closed.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将 <code>WeakSender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>。如果所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop 且 channel 已关闭，则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns the number of <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> instances currently alive.</p>',
     '<p>返回当前存活的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 实例数。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 96: stream/index (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Utilities for working with <code>Stream</code>s.</p>',
     '<p>用于处理 <code>Stream</code> 的实用工具。</p>'),
    ('<p>Many concepts in async/await Rust are pulled from <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a>, and\n<code>Stream</code> is one of them. A <code>Stream</code> is an asynchronous iterator, yielding\nzero or more values until the stream is exhausted.</p>',
     '<p>async/await Rust 中的许多概念都来自 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future"><code>Future</code></a>，<code>Stream</code> 是其中之一。<code>Stream</code> 是一个异步迭代器，在流耗尽之前生成零个或多个值。</p>'),
    ('<p>This module provides helpers for working with <code>Stream</code>s. It is\nintentionally analogous to the <a href="../io/trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> module, which provides\nhelpers for working with the asynchronous reader trait.</p>',
     '<p>此模块提供了用于处理 <code>Stream</code> 的辅助函数。它有意地类似于 <a href="../io/trait.AsyncRead.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncRead"><code>AsyncRead</code></a> 模块，后者提供了用于处理异步 reader trait 的辅助函数。</p>'),
    ('<p>A typical stream might look like this:</p>',
     '<p>典型的流可能如下所示：</p>'),

    # ============ Round 97: RuntimeFlavor (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Specifies the flavor of runtime to use.</p>',
     '<p>指定要使用的运行时风格。</p>'),
    ('<p>The runtime flavor is selected at runtime construction.</p>',
     '<p>运行时风格在运行时构造时选择。</p>'),
    ('<p>A single-threaded runtime.</p>',
     '<p>单线程运行时。</p>'),
    ('<p>A multi-threaded runtime.</p>',
     '<p>多线程运行时。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 98: PipeEnd (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Indicates the end of a named pipe.</p>',
     '<p>指示命名管道的端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Used to indicate whether a named pipe is the client end or the server end.</p>',
     '<p>用于指示命名管道是客户端还是服务器端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Indicates that the named pipe is the client end.</p>',
     '<p>指示命名管道是客户端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Indicates that the named pipe is the server end.</p>',
     '<p>指示命名管道是服务器端。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 99: ToSocketAddrs (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Conversion to a <a href="../struct.SocketAddr.html" title="struct tokio::net::SocketAddr"><code>SocketAddr</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>转换为 <a href="../struct.SocketAddr.html" title="struct tokio::net::SocketAddr"><code>SocketAddr</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Implementing this trait allows for converting a value to a\n<a href="../struct.SocketAddr.html" title="struct tokio::net::SocketAddr"><code>SocketAddr</code></a>. This trait is used when establishing network connections,\nsuch as with <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::connect"><code>TcpStream::connect</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>实现此 trait 允许将值转换为 <a href="../struct.SocketAddr.html" title="struct tokio::net::SocketAddr"><code>SocketAddr</code></a>。在建立网络连接时（例如使用 <a href="struct.TcpStream.html#method.connect" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::connect"><code>TcpStream::connect</code></a>）会使用此 trait。</p>'),
    ('<p>Currently, this trait is sealed and cannot be implemented outside of\n<code>tokio</code>.</p>',
     '<p>目前，此 trait 是封闭的，无法在 <code>tokio</code> 之外实现。</p>'),
    ('<p>Performs the conversion.</p>',
     '<p>执行转换。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 100: ReadHalf (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Read half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的读半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reading from a <code>ReadHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found\non the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>ReadHalf</code> 读取通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is intended for cases where creating and pinning a future\nvia <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is not feasible. Where possible, using <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> is\npreferred, as this supports polling from multiple tasks at once.</p>',
     '<p>此函数用于通过 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a> 创建和固定 future 不可行的情况。在可能的情况下，首选使用 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable</code></a>，因为它支持同时从多个任务进行轮询。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is copied to fill each buffer in order, with the final buffer\nwritten to possibly being only partially filled. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序复制数据以填充每个缓冲区，最后写入的缓冲区可能只被部分填充。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 101: MutexGuard (5 items) ============
    ('<p>A handle to a held <code>Mutex</code>. The guard can be held across any <code>.await</code> point\nas it is <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对持有 <code>Mutex</code> 的句柄。该 guard 可以跨越任何 <code>.await</code> 点，因为它实现了 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/marker/trait.Send.html" title="trait core::marker::Send"><code>Send</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>As long as you have this guard, you have exclusive access to the underlying\n<code>T</code>. The guard internally borrows the <code>Mutex</code>, so the mutex will not be\ndropped while a guard exists.</p>',
     '<p>只要你拥有此 guard，你就可以独占访问底层的 <code>T</code>。该 guard 在内部借用 <code>Mutex</code>，因此只要 guard 存在，mutex 就不会被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as <code>MutexGuard::map(...)</code>. A method\nwould interfere with methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>MutexGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as <code>MutexGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A\nmethod would interfere with methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>MutexGuard::try_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the original <code>Mutex</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回对原始 <code>Mutex</code> 的引用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 102: OwnedMutexGuard (5 items) ============
    ('<p>An owned handle to a held <code>Mutex</code>.</p>',
     '<p>对持有 <code>Mutex</code> 的 owned 句柄。</p>'),
    ('<p>This guard is only available from a <code>Mutex</code> that is wrapped in an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a>. It\nis identical to <code>MutexGuard</code>, except that rather than borrowing the <code>Mutex</code>,\nit clones the <code>Arc</code>, incrementing the reference count. This means that\nunlike <code>MutexGuard</code>, it will have the <code>\'static</code> lifetime.</p>',
     '<p>此 guard 仅适用于包装在 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/alloc/sync/struct.Arc.html" title="struct alloc::sync::Arc"><code>Arc</code></a> 中的 <code>Mutex</code>。它与 <code>MutexGuard</code> 相同，只是它不借用 <code>Mutex</code>，而是克隆 <code>Arc</code>，增加引用计数。这意味着与 <code>MutexGuard</code> 不同，它将具有 <code>\'static</code> 生命周期。</p>'),
    ('<p>As long as you have this guard, you have exclusive access to the underlying\n<code>T</code>. The guard internally keeps a reference-counted pointer to the original\n<code>Mutex</code>, so even if the lock goes away, the guard remains valid.</p>',
     '<p>只要你拥有此 guard，你就可以独占访问底层的 <code>T</code>。该 guard 在内部保持指向原始 <code>Mutex</code> 的引用计数指针，因此即使锁消失了，guard 仍然有效。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as <code>OwnedMutexGuard::map(...)</code>. A method\nwould interfere with methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedMutexGuard::map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the original <code>Arc&lt;Mutex&gt;</code>.</p>',
     '<p>返回对原始 <code>Arc&lt;Mutex&gt;</code> 的引用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 103: oneshot/index (5 items) ============
    ('<p>A one-shot channel is used for sending a single message between\nasynchronous tasks. The <a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> function is used to create a\n<a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> and <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> handle pair that form the channel.</p>',
     '<p>一次性 channel 用于在异步任务之间发送单个消息。<a href="fn.channel.html" title="fn tokio::sync::oneshot::channel"><code>channel</code></a> 函数用于创建组成 channel 的 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 句柄对。</p>'),
    ('<p>The <code>Sender</code> handle is used by the producer to send the value.\nThe <code>Receiver</code> handle is used by the consumer to receive the value.</p>',
     '<p><code>Sender</code> 句柄由生产者用于发送值。<code>Receiver</code> 句柄由消费者用于接收值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Since the <code>send</code> method is not async, it can be used anywhere. This includes\nsending between two runtimes, and using it from non-async code.</p>',
     '<p>由于 <code>send</code> 方法不是 async 的，因此可以在任何地方使用。这包括在两个运行时之间发送，以及在非异步代码中使用。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> is closed before receiving a message which has already\nbeen sent, the message will remain in the channel until the receiver is\ndropped, at which point the message will be dropped immediately.</p>',
     '<p>如果在已发送但尚未接收消息之前 <a href="struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::oneshot::Receiver"><code>Receiver</code></a> 已关闭，则该消息将保留在 channel 中，直到 receiver 被 drop，此时消息将立即被 drop。</p>'),
    ('<p>To use a <code>oneshot</code> channel in a <code>tokio::select!</code> loop, add <code>&amp;mut</code> in front of\nthe channel.</p>',
     '<p>要在 <code>tokio::select!</code> 循环中使用 <code>oneshot</code> channel，请在 channel 前面添加 <code>&amp;mut</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 104: SetError (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Errors that can be returned from <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::OnceCell::set"><code>OnceCell::set</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>可从 <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::OnceCell::set"><code>OnceCell::set</code></a> 返回的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>The cell was already initialized when <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::OnceCell::set"><code>OnceCell::set</code></a> was called.</p>',
     '<p>调用 <a href="struct.OnceCell.html#method.set" title="method tokio::sync::OnceCell::set"><code>OnceCell::set</code></a> 时，单元格已被初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>The cell is currently being initialized.</p>',
     '<p>该单元格当前正在被初始化。</p>'),
    ('<p>Whether <code>SetError</code> is <code>SetError::AlreadyInitializedError</code>.</p>',
     '<p><code>SetError</code> 是否为 <code>SetError::AlreadyInitializedError</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Whether <code>SetError</code> is <code>SetError::InitializingError</code></p>',
     '<p><code>SetError</code> 是否为 <code>SetError::InitializingError</code></p>'),

    # ============ Round 105: PipeMode (5 items) ============
    ('<p>Set through <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.pipe_mode" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::pipe_mode"><code>ServerOptions::pipe_mode</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>通过 <a href="struct.ServerOptions.html#method.pipe_mode" title="method tokio::net::windows::named_pipe::ServerOptions::pipe_mode"><code>ServerOptions::pipe_mode</code></a> 设置。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written to the pipe as a stream of bytes. The pipe does not\ndistinguish bytes written during different write operations.</p>',
     '<p>数据作为字节流写入管道。管道不区分不同写入操作期间写入的字节。</p>'),
    ('<p>Corresponds to <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_TYPE_BYTE.html"><code>PIPE_TYPE_BYTE</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对应 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_TYPE_BYTE.html"><code>PIPE_TYPE_BYTE</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written to the pipe as a stream of messages. The pipe treats the\nbytes written during each write operation as a message unit. Any reading\non a named pipe returns <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Foundation/constant.ERROR_MORE_DATA.html"><code>ERROR_MORE_DATA</code></a> when a message is not read\ncompletely.</p>',
     '<p>数据作为消息流写入管道。管道将每次写入操作期间写入的字节视为一个消息单元。在命名管道上的任何读取操作，当消息未被完全读取时，会返回 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/Foundation/constant.ERROR_MORE_DATA.html"><code>ERROR_MORE_DATA</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Corresponds to <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_TYPE_MESSAGE.html"><code>PIPE_TYPE_MESSAGE</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对应 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_TYPE_MESSAGE.html"><code>PIPE_TYPE_MESSAGE</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 106: WriteHalf (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Borrowed write half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的借用写半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that in the <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> implementation of this type, <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> will\nshut down the TCP stream in the write direction.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，在此类型的 <a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html" title="trait tokio::io::AsyncWrite"><code>AsyncWrite</code></a> 实现中，<a href="../../io/trait.AsyncWrite.html#tymethod.poll_shutdown" title="method tokio::io::AsyncWrite::poll_shutdown"><code>poll_shutdown</code></a> 将关闭 TCP 流的写方向。</p>'),
    ('<p>Writing to an <code>WriteHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found\non the <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>写入 <code>WriteHalf</code> 通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncWriteExt"><code>AsyncWriteExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>Data is written from each buffer in order, with the final buffer read\nfrom possible being only partially consumed. This method behaves\nequivalently to a single call to <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> with concatenated\nbuffers.</p>',
     '<p>按顺序从每个缓冲区写入数据，最后读取的缓冲区可能只被部分使用。此方法的行为等效于使用串联缓冲区对 <a href="struct.WriteHalf.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::net::tcp::WriteHalf::try_write"><code>try_write()</code></a> 进行单次调用。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 107: OwnedReadHalf (2 items) ============
    ('<p>Attempt to receive data on the socket, without removing that data from\nthe queue, registering the current task for wakeup if data is not yet\navailable.</p>',
     '<p>尝试在套接字上接收数据，但不会从队列中移除该数据，如果数据尚不可用，则注册当前任务以进行唤醒。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a>. It can be used instead\nof <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> to check the returned ready set for <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READABLE"><code>Ready::READABLE</code></a>\nand <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READ_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READ_CLOSED"><code>Ready::READ_CLOSED</code></a> events.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 配合使用。它可以用来代替 <a href="struct.OwnedReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::OwnedReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>，以检查返回的就绪集中的 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READABLE"><code>Ready::READABLE</code></a> 和 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READ_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READ_CLOSED"><code>Ready::READ_CLOSED</code></a> 事件。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 108: Timeout (3 items) ============
    ('<p>Gets a reference to the underlying value in this timeout.</p>',
     '<p>获取对此 timeout 中底层值的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Gets a mutable reference to the underlying value in this timeout.</p>',
     '<p>获取对此 timeout 中底层值的可变引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Consumes this timeout, returning the underlying value.</p>',
     '<p>消耗此 timeout，返回底层值。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 109: timeout fn (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Requires a <code>Future</code> to complete before the specified duration has elapsed.</p>',
     '<p>要求 <code>Future</code> 在指定的持续时间过去之前完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the future completes before the duration has elapsed, then the completed\nvalue is returned. Otherwise, an error is returned and the future is\ncanceled.</p>',
     '<p>如果 future 在持续时间过去之前完成，则返回已完成的 future 值。否则，返回错误并取消该 future。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that the timeout is checked before polling the future, so if the future\ndoes not yield during execution then it is possible for the future to complete\nand exceed the timeout <em>without</em> returning an error.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，timeout 是在 poll future 之前检查的，因此如果 future 在执行期间不让步，则 future 可能会完成并超过 timeout，而<em>不会</em>返回错误。</p>'),
    ('<p>If the provided future completes immediately, then the future returned from\nthis function is guaranteed to complete immediately with an <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Ok" title="variant core::result::Result::Ok"><code>Ok</code></a> variant\nno matter the provided duration.</p>',
     '<p>如果所提供的 future 立即完成，则无论提供的持续时间如何，此函数返回的 future 保证立即以 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/result/enum.Result.html#variant.Ok" title="variant core::result::Result::Ok"><code>Ok</code></a> 变体完成。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 110: interval fn (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Creates new <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> that yields with interval of <code>period</code>. The first\ntick completes immediately. The default <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> is\n<a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>, but this can be configured\nby calling <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.set_missed_tick_behavior" title="method tokio::time::Interval::set_missed_tick_behavior"><code>set_missed_tick_behavior</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个新的 <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a>，以 <code>period</code> 间隔产生值。第一个 tick 立即完成。默认的 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html" title="enum tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior"><code>MissedTickBehavior</code></a> 是 <a href="enum.MissedTickBehavior.html#variant.Burst" title="variant tokio::time::MissedTickBehavior::Burst"><code>Burst</code></a>，但可以通过调用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.set_missed_tick_behavior" title="method tokio::time::Interval::set_missed_tick_behavior"><code>set_missed_tick_behavior</code></a> 进行配置。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is equivalent to\n<a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at(Instant::now(), period)</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>此函数等效于 <a href="fn.interval_at.html" title="fn tokio::time::interval_at"><code>interval_at(Instant::now(), period)</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>A simple example using <code>interval</code> to execute a task every two seconds.</p>',
     '<p>使用 <code>interval</code> 每两秒执行一个任务的简单示例。</p>'),
    ('<p>The difference between <code>interval</code> and <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> is that an <a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a>\nmeasures the time since the last tick, which means that <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>.tick().await</code></a>\nmay wait for a shorter time than the duration specified for the interval\nif some time has passed between calls to <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>.tick().await</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><code>interval</code> 和 <a href="fn.sleep.html" title="fn tokio::time::sleep"><code>sleep</code></a> 的区别在于，<a href="struct.Interval.html" title="struct tokio::time::Interval"><code>Interval</code></a> 测量自上一个 tick 以来经过的时间，这意味着如果两次调用 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>.tick().await</code></a> 之间经过了一些时间，则 <a href="struct.Interval.html#method.tick" title="method tokio::time::Interval::tick"><code>.tick().await</code></a> 可能等待的时间比为间隔指定的时间更短。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 111: poll_proceed (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Decrements the task budget and returns <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/poll/enum.Poll.html#variant.Pending" title="variant core::task::poll::Poll::Pending"><code>Poll::Pending</code></a> if the budget is depleted.\nThis indicates that the task should yield to the scheduler. Otherwise, returns\n<a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> which can be used to commit the budget consumption.</p>',
     '<p>如果预算已用尽，则递减任务预算并返回 <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.95.0/core/task/poll/enum.Poll.html#variant.Pending" title="variant core::task::poll::Poll::Pending"><code>Poll::Pending</code></a>。这表明任务应让步给调度器。否则，返回 <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a>，可用于提交预算消耗。</p>'),
    ('<p>The returned <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> will revert the budget to its former\nvalue when dropped unless <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html#method.made_progress" title="method tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending::made_progress"><code>RestoreOnPending::made_progress</code></a>\nis called. It is the caller’s responsibility to do so when it <em>was</em> able to\nmake progress after the call to <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a>.\nRestoring the budget automatically ensures the task can try to make progress in some other\nway.</p>',
     '<p>返回的 <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> 在 drop 时会将预算恢复为之前的值，除非调用 <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html#method.made_progress" title="method tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending::made_progress"><code>RestoreOnPending::made_progress</code></a>。调用方有责任在调用 <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> 后<em>能够</em>取得进展时执行此操作。恢复预算会自动确保任务可以尝试以其他方式取得进展。</p>'),
    ('<p>Note that <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> restores the budget <strong>as it was before <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a></strong>.\nTherefore, if the budget is <em>further</em> adjusted between when <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> returns and\n<a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> is dropped, those adjustments are erased unless the caller indicates\nthat progress was made.</p>',
     '<p>请注意，<a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> 将预算恢复为<strong>调用 <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> 之前的状态</strong>。因此，如果在 <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> 返回到 <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html" title="struct tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending"><code>RestoreOnPending</code></a> 被 drop 之间预算被<em>进一步</em>调整，则这些调整将被擦除，除非调用方表明已取得进展。</p>'),
    ('<p>This example wraps the <code>futures::channel::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver</code> to\ncooperate with the Tokio scheduler. Each time a value is received, task budget\nis consumed. If no budget is available, the task yields to the scheduler.</p>',
     '<p>此示例包装了 <code>futures::channel::mpsc::UnboundedReceiver</code>，以与 Tokio 调度器协作。每次接收到一个值时，都会消耗任务预算。如果预算不可用，则任务将让步给调度器。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 112: cooperative (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Creates a wrapper future that makes the inner future cooperate with the Tokio scheduler.</p>',
     '<p>创建一个 wrapper future，使内部 future 与 Tokio 调度器协作。</p>'),
    ('<p>When polled, the wrapper will first call <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> to consume task budget, and\nimmediately yield if the budget has been depleted. If budget was available, the inner future\nis polled. The budget consumption will be made final using <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html#method.made_progress" title="method tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending::made_progress"><code>RestoreOnPending::made_progress</code></a>\nif the inner future resolves to its final value.</p>',
     '<p>被 poll 时，wrapper 将首先调用 <a href="fn.poll_proceed.html" title="fn tokio::task::coop::poll_proceed"><code>poll_proceed</code></a> 来消耗任务预算，如果预算已用尽，则立即让步。如果预算可用，则 poll 内部 future。如果内部 future 解析为其最终值，则将使用 <a href="struct.RestoreOnPending.html#method.made_progress" title="method tokio::task::coop::RestoreOnPending::made_progress"><code>RestoreOnPending::made_progress</code></a> 确定预算消耗。</p>'),
    ('<p>When you call <code>recv</code> on the <code>Receiver</code> of a <a href="../../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>tokio::sync::mpsc</code></a>\nchannel, task budget will automatically be consumed when the next value is returned.\nThis makes tasks that use Tokio mpsc channels automatically cooperative.</p>',
     '<p>当在 <a href="../../sync/mpsc/index.html" title="mod tokio::sync::mpsc"><code>tokio::sync::mpsc</code></a> channel 的 <code>Receiver</code> 上调用 <code>recv</code> 时，返回下一个值时会自动消耗任务预算。这使得使用 Tokio mpsc channel 的任务自动成为协作式的。</p>'),
    ('<p>If you’re using <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/latest/futures/channel/mpsc/index.html"><code>futures::channel::mpsc</code></a>\ninstead, automatic task budget consumption will not happen. This example shows how can use\n<code>cooperative</code> to make <code>futures::channel::mpsc</code> channels cooperate with the scheduler in the\nsame way Tokio channels do.</p>',
     '<p>如果改用 <a href="https://docs.rs/futures/latest/futures/channel/mpsc/index.html"><code>futures::channel::mpsc</code></a>，则不会自动消耗任务预算。此示例演示了如何使用 <code>cooperative</code> 使 <code>futures::channel::mpsc</code> channel 以与 Tokio channel 相同的方式与调度器协作。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 113: watch Ref (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Returns a reference to the inner value.</p>',
     '<p>返回对内部值的引用。</p>'),
    ('<p>Indicates if the borrowed value is considered as <em>changed</em> since the last\ntime it has been marked as seen.</p>',
     '<p>指示自上次将借用值标记为已读取以来，该借用值是否被视为<em>已更改</em>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Unlike <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>Receiver::has_changed()</code></a>, this method does not fail if the channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>与 <a href="struct.Receiver.html#method.has_changed" title="method tokio::sync::watch::Receiver::has_changed"><code>Receiver::has_changed()</code></a> 不同，此方法在 channel 关闭时不会失败。</p>'),
    ('<p>When borrowed from the <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> this function will always return <code>false</code>.</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::watch::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 借用时，此函数将始终返回 <code>false</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 114: TryLockError (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Error returned from the <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>Mutex::try_lock</code></a>, <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_read"><code>RwLock::try_read</code></a> and\n<a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_write"><code>RwLock::try_write</code></a> functions.</p>',
     '<p>从 <a href="struct.Mutex.html#method.try_lock" title="method tokio::sync::Mutex::try_lock"><code>Mutex::try_lock</code></a>、<a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_read"><code>RwLock::try_read</code></a> 和 <a href="struct.RwLock.html#method.try_write" title="method tokio::sync::RwLock::try_write"><code>RwLock::try_write</code></a> 函数返回的错误。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>Mutex::try_lock</code> operation will only fail if the mutex is already locked.</p>',
     '<p>仅当 mutex 已被锁定时，<code>Mutex::try_lock</code> 操作才会失败。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>RwLock::try_read</code> operation will only fail if the lock is currently held\nby an exclusive writer.</p>',
     '<p>仅当锁当前由独占写入者持有时，<code>RwLock::try_read</code> 操作才会失败。</p>'),
    ('<p><code>RwLock::try_write</code> operation will only fail if the lock is currently held\nby any reader or by an exclusive writer.</p>',
     '<p>仅当锁当前由任何读取者或独占写入者持有时，<code>RwLock::try_write</code> 操作才会失败。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 115: SemaphorePermit (1 item) ============
    ('<p>Splits <code>n</code> permits from <code>self</code> and returns a new <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> instance that holds <code>n</code> permits.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>self</code> 拆分 <code>n</code> 个 permit，并返回持有 <code>n</code> 个 permit 的新 <a href="struct.SemaphorePermit.html" title="struct tokio::sync::SemaphorePermit"><code>SemaphorePermit</code></a> 实例。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 116: RwLockMappedWriteGuard (4 items) ============
    ('<p>This structure is created by <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::map">mapping</a> an <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard"><code>RwLockWriteGuard</code></a>. It is a\nseparate type from <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> to disallow downgrading a mapped\nguard, since doing so can cause undefined behavior.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体通过对 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard"><code>RwLockWriteGuard</code></a> 进行 <a href="struct.RwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::RwLockWriteGuard::map">映射</a> 创建。它是与 <code>RwLockWriteGuard</code> 分开的类型，因为降级映射后的 guard 可能导致未定义行为，因此不允许这样做。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> for a component of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be used as\n<code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(..)</code>. A method would interfere with methods\nof the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::map(..)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere\nwith methods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>RwLockMappedWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 117: OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard (4 items) ============
    ('<p>This structure is created by <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map">mapping</a> an <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code></a>. It is a\nseparate type from <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> to disallow downgrading a mapped\nguard, since doing so can cause undefined behavior.</p>',
     '<p>此结构体通过对 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html" title="struct tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard"><code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code></a> 进行 <a href="struct.OwnedRwLockWriteGuard.html#method.map" title="associated function tokio::sync::OwnedRwLockWriteGuard::map">映射</a> 创建。它是与 <code>OwnedRwLockWriteGuard</code> 分开的类型，因为降级映射后的 guard 可能导致未定义行为，因此不允许这样做。</p>'),
    ('<p>Makes a new <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> for a component of the locked\ndata.</p>',
     '<p>为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Attempts to make a new <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code> for a component\nof the locked data. The original guard is returned if the closure\nreturns <code>None</code>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试为锁定数据的组件创建一个新的 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard</code>。如果闭包返回 <code>None</code>，则返回原始 guard。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is an associated function that needs to be\nused as <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>. A method would interfere with\nmethods of the same name on the contents of the locked data.</p>',
     '<p>这是一个关联函数，需要用作 <code>OwnedRwLockMappedWriteGuard::try_map(...)</code>。方法会与锁定数据内容上的同名方法冲突。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 118: WeakUnboundedSender (4 items) ============
    ('<p>An unbounded sender that does not prevent the channel from being closed.</p>',
     '<p>不会阻止 channel 被关闭的无界 sender。</p>'),
    ('<p>If all <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> instances of a channel were dropped and only\n<code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> instances remain, the channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的所有 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop，仅剩下 <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> 实例，则 channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>In order to send messages, the <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> needs to be upgraded using\n<a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html#method.upgrade" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender::upgrade"><code>WeakUnboundedSender::upgrade</code></a>, which returns <code>Option&lt;UnboundedSender&gt;</code>. It returns <code>None</code>\nif all <code>UnboundedSender</code>s have been dropped, and otherwise it returns an <code>UnboundedSender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>为了发送消息，<code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> 需要使用 <a href="struct.WeakUnboundedSender.html#method.upgrade" title="method tokio::sync::mpsc::WeakUnboundedSender::upgrade"><code>WeakUnboundedSender::upgrade</code></a> 进行升级，该函数返回 <code>Option&lt;UnboundedSender&gt;</code>。如果所有 <code>UnboundedSender</code> 都已被 drop，则返回 <code>None</code>，否则返回 <code>UnboundedSender</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to convert a <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> into an <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a>.\nThis will return <code>Some</code> if there are other <code>Sender</code> instances alive and\nthe channel wasn’t previously dropped, otherwise <code>None</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将 <code>WeakUnboundedSender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.UnboundedSender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::UnboundedSender"><code>UnboundedSender</code></a>。如果存在其他存活的 <code>Sender</code> 实例且 channel 之前未被 drop，则返回 <code>Some</code>，否则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 119: WeakSender (4 items) ============
    ('<p>If all <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> instances of a channel were dropped and only <code>WeakSender</code>\ninstances remain, the channel is closed.</p>',
     '<p>如果 channel 的所有 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a> 实例都已被 drop，仅剩下 <code>WeakSender</code> 实例，则 channel 关闭。</p>'),
    ('<p>In order to send messages, the <code>WeakSender</code> needs to be upgraded using\n<a href="struct.WeakSender.html#method.upgrade" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender::upgrade"><code>WeakSender::upgrade</code></a>, which returns <code>Option&lt;Sender&gt;</code>. It returns <code>None</code>\nif all <code>Sender</code>s have been dropped, and otherwise it returns a <code>Sender</code>.</p>',
     '<p>为了发送消息，<code>WeakSender</code> 需要使用 <a href="struct.WeakSender.html#method.upgrade" title="method tokio::sync::broadcast::WeakSender::upgrade"><code>WeakSender::upgrade</code></a> 进行升级，该函数返回 <code>Option&lt;Sender&gt;</code>。如果所有 <code>Sender</code> 都已被 drop，则返回 <code>None</code>，否则返回 <code>Sender</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Tries to convert a <code>WeakSender</code> into a <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>尝试将 <code>WeakSender</code> 转换为 <a href="struct.Sender.html" title="struct tokio::sync::broadcast::Sender"><code>Sender</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This will return <code>Some</code> if there are other <code>Sender</code> instances alive and\nthe channel wasn’t previously dropped, otherwise <code>None</code> is returned.</p>',
     '<p>如果存在其他存活的 <code>Sender</code> 实例且 channel 之前未被 drop，则返回 <code>Some</code>，否则返回 <code>None</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 120: stream/index (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Due to the <code>Stream</code> trait’s inclusion in <code>std</code> landing later than Tokio’s 1.0\nrelease, most of the Tokio stream utilities have been moved into the <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream"><code>tokio-stream</code></a>\ncrate.</p>',
     '<p>由于 <code>Stream</code> trait 进入 <code>std</code> 的时间晚于 Tokio 1.0 发布，因此大多数 Tokio 流实用工具已移至 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream"><code>tokio-stream</code></a> crate。</p>'),
    ('<p>Originally, we had planned to ship Tokio 1.0 with a stable <code>Stream</code> type\nbut unfortunately the <a href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/2996">RFC</a> had not been merged in time for <code>Stream</code> to\nreach <code>std</code> on a stable compiler in time for the 1.0 release of Tokio. For\nthis reason, the team has decided to move all <code>Stream</code> based utilities to\nthe <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream"><code>tokio-stream</code></a> crate. While this is not ideal, once <code>Stream</code> has made\nit into the standard library and the <code>MSRV</code> period has passed, we will implement\nstream for our different types.</p>',
     '<p>最初，我们计划在 Tokio 1.0 中发布一个稳定的 <code>Stream</code> 类型，但不幸的是，<a href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/2996">RFC</a> 未能在 Tokio 1.0 发布前及时合并，使 <code>Stream</code> 能够在稳定编译器上进入 <code>std</code>。因此，团队决定将所有基于 <code>Stream</code> 的实用工具移至 <a href="https://docs.rs/tokio-stream"><code>tokio-stream</code></a> crate。虽然这并不理想，但一旦 <code>Stream</code> 进入标准库并且 <code>MSRV</code> 期限过去，我们将为不同的类型实现 stream。</p>'),
    ('<p>While this may seem unfortunate, not all is lost as you can get much of the\n<code>Stream</code> support with <code>async/await</code> and <code>while let</code> loops. It is also possible\nto create a <code>impl Stream</code> from <code>async fn</code> using the <a href="https://docs.rs/async-stream"><code>async-stream</code></a> crate.</p>',
     '<p>虽然这似乎令人遗憾，但并非一无所有，因为你可以通过 <code>async/await</code> 和 <code>while let</code> 循环获得大部分 <code>Stream</code> 支持。也可以使用 <a href="https://docs.rs/async-stream"><code>async-stream</code></a> crate 从 <code>async fn</code> 创建 <code>impl Stream</code>。</p>'),
    ('<p>Convert a <a href="../sync/mpsc/struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>sync::mpsc::Receiver</code></a> to an <code>impl Stream</code>.</p>',
     '<p>将 <a href="../sync/mpsc/struct.Receiver.html" title="struct tokio::sync::mpsc::Receiver"><code>sync::mpsc::Receiver</code></a> 转换为 <code>impl Stream</code>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 121: RuntimeFlavor (4 items) ============
    ('<p>The flavor of a <code>Runtime</code>.</p>',
     '<p><code>Runtime</code> 的风格。</p>'),
    ('<p>This is the return type for <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.runtime_flavor" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::runtime_flavor"><code>Handle::runtime_flavor</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>这是 <a href="struct.Handle.html#method.runtime_flavor" title="method tokio::runtime::Handle::runtime_flavor"><code>Handle::runtime_flavor</code></a> 的返回类型。</p>'),
    ('<p>The flavor that executes all tasks on the current thread.</p>',
     '<p>在当前线程上执行所有任务的风格。</p>'),
    ('<p>The flavor that executes tasks across multiple threads.</p>',
     '<p>跨多个线程执行任务的风格。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 122: PipeEnd (4 items) ============
    ('<p>The named pipe refers to the client end of a named pipe instance.</p>',
     '<p>命名管道指的是命名管道实例的客户端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Corresponds to <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_CLIENT_END.html"><code>PIPE_CLIENT_END</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对应 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_CLIENT_END.html"><code>PIPE_CLIENT_END</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>The named pipe refers to the server end of a named pipe instance.</p>',
     '<p>命名管道指的是命名管道实例的服务器端。</p>'),
    ('<p>Corresponds to <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_SERVER_END.html"><code>PIPE_SERVER_END</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>对应 <a href="https://docs.rs/windows-sys/latest/windows_sys/Win32/System/Pipes/constant.PIPE_SERVER_END.html"><code>PIPE_SERVER_END</code></a>。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 123: ToSocketAddrs (4 items) ============
    ('<p>Converts or resolves without blocking to one or more <code>SocketAddr</code> values.</p>',
     '<p>在不阻塞的情况下转换或解析为一个或多个 <code>SocketAddr</code> 值。</p>'),
    ('<p>Implementations of <code>ToSocketAddrs</code> for string types require a DNS lookup.</p>',
     '<p>字符串类型的 <code>ToSocketAddrs</code> 实现需要 DNS 查找。</p>'),
    ('<p>Currently, this trait is only used as an argument to Tokio functions that\nneed to reference a target socket address. To perform a <code>SocketAddr</code>\nconversion directly, use <a href="fn.lookup_host.html" title="fn tokio::net::lookup_host"><code>lookup_host()</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>目前，此 trait 仅用作需要引用目标套接字地址的 Tokio 函数的参数。要直接执行 <code>SocketAddr</code> 转换，请使用 <a href="fn.lookup_host.html" title="fn tokio::net::lookup_host"><code>lookup_host()</code></a>。</p>'),
    ('<p>This trait is sealed and is intended to be opaque. The details of the trait\nwill change. Stabilization is pending enhancements to the Rust language.</p>',
     '<p>此 trait 是封闭的，意图是不透明的。该 trait 的细节将会改变。稳定化有待 Rust 语言的增强。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 124: ReadHalf (3 items) ============
    ('<p>Borrowed read half of a <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a>, created by <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p><a href="../struct.TcpStream.html" title="struct tokio::net::TcpStream"><code>TcpStream</code></a> 的借用读半部，由 <a href="../struct.TcpStream.html#method.split" title="method tokio::net::TcpStream::split"><code>split</code></a> 创建。</p>'),
    ('<p>Reading from a <code>ReadHalf</code> is usually done using the convenience methods found on the\n<a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait.</p>',
     '<p>从 <code>ReadHalf</code> 读取通常使用 <a href="trait@crate::io::AsyncReadExt"><code>AsyncReadExt</code></a> trait 上提供的便捷方法来完成。</p>'),
    ('<p>This function is usually paired with <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a>. It can be used instead\nof <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a> to check the returned ready set for <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READABLE"><code>Ready::READABLE</code></a>\nand <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READ_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READ_CLOSED"><code>Ready::READ_CLOSED</code></a> events.</p>',
     '<p>此函数通常与 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.try_read" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::try_read"><code>try_read()</code></a> 配合使用。它可以用来代替 <a href="struct.ReadHalf.html#method.readable" title="method tokio::net::tcp::ReadHalf::readable"><code>readable()</code></a>，以检查返回的就绪集中的 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READABLE" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READABLE"><code>Ready::READABLE</code></a> 和 <a href="../../io/struct.Ready.html#associatedconstant.READ_CLOSED" title="associated constant tokio::io::Ready::READ_CLOSED"><code>Ready::READ_CLOSED</code></a> 事件。</p>'),


    # ============ Round 125: index.html (1 item) ============
    ('<p>A runtime for writing reliable network applications without compromising speed.</p>',
     '<p>用于编写可靠的网络应用程序而不影响速度的运行时。</p>'),

    # ============ Round 126: macro.task_local (3 items) ============
    ('<p>Declares a new task-local key of type <a href="task/struct.LocalKey.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalKey"><code>tokio::task::LocalKey</code></a>.</p>',
     '<p>声明一个类型为 <a href="task/struct.LocalKey.html" title="struct tokio::task::LocalKey"><code>tokio::task::LocalKey</code></a> 的新任务本地 key。</p>'),
    ('<p>The macro wraps any number of static declarations and makes them local to the current task.\nPublicity and attributes for each static is preserved. For example:</p>',
     '<p>该宏包装任意数量的 static 声明，并使它们对当前任务本地化。每个 static 的公开性和属性都会被保留。例如：</p>'),
